 plane, or theater, offering a view.","main_translations_es":["ventana","ventanilla","ventanilla de coche"],"collocations":["window seat on a plane","window seat on a train","window seat in a theater","window seat in a car"],"synonyms_en":["seat by the window","window-side seat","view seat"],"example_sentence":"I sat in the window seat of the train to enjoy the view.","example_es":"Me senté en la ventanilla del tren para disfrutar de la vista.","example_en":"I sat in the window seat of the train to enjoy the view.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a tiny vent in a plane; the window seat feels like a ventanilla you look through.","cloze_distractors_en":["Aisle floor","Cabin roof","Engine deck","Cargo wall"],"examples":[{"es":"Me senté en la ventanilla del tren para disfrutar de la vista.","en":"I sat in the window seat of the train to enjoy the view."},{"es":"Al reservar mi vuelo, pedí una ventanilla para poder ver las nubes.","en":"When booking my flight, I requested a window seat so I could see the clouds."},{"es":"El pasajero prefirió una ventanilla para descansar la cabeza contra el cristal durante el viaje en autobús.","en":"The passenger preferred a window seat to rest his head against the glass during the bus trip."}]},{"spanish_text":"Pasillo","english_text":"Aisle seat","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A seat located next to an aisle in a vehicle or theater.","main_translations_es":["pasillo","hall","corridor"],"collocations":["aisle seat","aisle seat reservation","aisle seat preference","aisle seat booking"],"synonyms_en":["aisle-side seat","seat by the aisle","aisle position"],"example_sentence":"I prefer to book an aisle seat to stretch my legs during the flight.","example_es":"Prefiero reservar un asiento en el pasillo para estirar las piernas durante el vuelo.","example_en":"I prefer to book an aisle seat to stretch my legs during the flight.","mnemonic_en":"I pass low down the aisle to my seat.","cloze_distractors_en":["Wing seat","Cargo hold","Cockpit door"],"examples":[{"es":"Prefiero reservar un asiento en el pasillo para estirar las piernas durante el vuelo.","en":"I prefer to book an aisle seat to stretch my legs during the flight."},{"es":"El asistente de vuelo me pidió que guardara mi maleta antes de llegar a mi pasillo.","en":"The flight attendant asked me to stow my bag before reaching my aisle seat."},{"es":"Si eliges un asiento en el pasillo, podrás salir del tren más rápido al llegar a la estación.","en":"If you choose an aisle seat, you will be able to exit the train faster upon arriving at the station."}]},{"spanish_text":"Embarcar","english_text":"Board","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to get on or into a vehicle, such as a plane or ship.","main_translations_es":["Subir","A bordo","Embarcarse"],"collocations":["board a plane","board a bus","board a ship","board a train"],"synonyms_en":["get on","embark","enter"],"example_sentence":"The passenger must board before departure.","example_es":"El pasajero debe embarcar antes de la salida.","example_en":"The passenger must board before departure.","mnemonic_en":"A bored sailor finally gets to embarcar onto the ship.","cloze_distractors_en":["Refund","Unpack","Ignore","Upload"],"examples":[{"es":"El pasajero debe embarcar antes de la salida.","en":"The passenger must board before departure."},{"es":"Es hora de embarcar en el avión hacia Madrid.","en":"It is time to board the plane to Madrid."},{"es":"Los viajeros comienzan a embarcar por la puerta número cinco.","en":"The travelers begin to board at gate number five."}]},{"spanish_text":"Desembarcar","english_text":"Get off","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to leave a vehicle or place, especially by disembarking","main_translations_es":["bajar","descender","salir"],"collocations":["get off the bus","get off the train","get off the phone","get off the ground"],"synonyms_en":["disembark","alight","step down"],"example_sentence":"Passengers must get off the bus before arriving at the stop.","example_es":"Los pasajeros deben desembarcar del autobús antes de llegar a la parada.","example_en":"Passengers must get off the bus before arriving at the stop.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a desert gate opening as you get off the boat, shouting ''Desembarcar!''","cloze_distractors_en":["Get over","Get past","Get near","Get with"],"examples":[{"es":"Los pasajeros deben desembarcar del autobús antes de llegar a la parada.","en":"Passengers must get off the bus before arriving at the stop."},{"es":"Es necesario desembarcar del tren cuando lleguemos a la estación central.","en":"It is necessary to get off the train when we arrive at the central station."},{"es":"Todos los turistas tienen que desembarcar del crucero para el tour de la mañana.","en":"All tourists have to get off the cruise ship for the morning tour."}]},{"spanish_text":"Mostrador","english_text":"Counter","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"a flat surface used for displaying or serving items, often found in stores or restaurants.","main_translations_es":["mesa de mostrador","estantería","cajón"],"collocations":["counter top","counter offer","counter argument","counter point"],"synonyms_en":["service desk","checkout area","bar"],"example_sentence":"The counter at the café is full of cups.","example_es":"El mostrador del café está lleno de tazas.","example_en":"The counter at the café is full of cups.","mnemonic_en":"The counter displays the most rad door.","cloze_distractors_en":["Staircase","Backpack","Pavement","Envelope"],"examples":[{"es":"El mostrador del café está lleno de tazas.","en":"The counter at the café is full of cups."},{"es":"Por favor, diríjase al mostrador de facturación para registrar su equipaje.","en":"Please go to the check-in counter to register your luggage."},{"es":"El cliente espera su turno frente al mostrador de información turística.","en":"The customer is waiting for their turn at the information counter."}]},{"spanish_text":"Terminal","english_text":"Terminal","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A place where passengers board or disembark from transportation, such as a bus or train station.","main_translations_es":["Estación","Puerta de salida","Terminal de transporte"],"collocations":["terminal illness","terminal velocity","terminal station","terminal computer"],"synonyms_en":[],"example_sentence":"The train arrives at the terminal at 5 p.m.","example_es":"El tren llega a la terminal a las 5 p.m.","example_en":"The train arrives at the terminal at 5 p.m.","mnemonic_en":null,"cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El tren llega a la terminal a las 5 p.m.","en":"The train arrives at the terminal at 5 p.m."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cambio de puerta","english_text":"Gate change","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A modification or alteration of a gate.","main_translations_es":["Intercambio de puerta","Reemplazo de puerta","Cambio de puerta"],"collocations":["gate change request","gate change policy","gate change announcement","gate change fee"],"synonyms_en":["gate alteration","gate modification","gate swap"],"example_sentence":"Please check the monitors because there was a gate change for our flight to Madrid.","example_es":"Por favor, revisa las pantallas de información porque hubo un cambio de puerta para nuestro vuelo a Madrid.","example_en":"Please check the monitors because there was a gate change for our flight to Madrid.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a gate that suddenly changes like a door flipping open.","cloze_distractors_en":["Floor routine","Coast passage","Board meeting","Road painting"],"examples":[{"es":"Por favor, revisa las pantallas de información porque hubo un cambio de puerta para nuestro vuelo a Madrid.","en":"Please check the monitors because there was a gate change for our flight to Madrid."},{"es":"Escuchamos un anuncio sobre un cambio de puerta en el aeropuerto.","en":"We heard an announcement about a gate change at the airport."},{"es":"Debido al retraso, hubo un cambio de puerta inesperado.","en":"Due to the delay, there was an unexpected gate change."}]},{"spanish_text":"Andén","english_text":"Platform","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A raised area where passengers wait for trains or buses.","main_translations_es":["Plataforma","Pista","Banda"],"collocations":["social media platform","platform for discussion","platform for change","platform of the train"],"synonyms_en":["stage","dais","deck"],"example_sentence":"The train arrived at the platform and passengers began to disembark.","example_es":"El tren llegó al andén y los pasajeros comenzaron a bajar.","example_en":"The train arrived at the platform and passengers began to disembark.","mnemonic_en":"Think of a flat plate (plat) on a train''s Andén, a perfect platform.","cloze_distractors_en":["Pavement","Entrance","Corridor"],"examples":[{"es":"El tren llegó al andén y los pasajeros comenzaron a bajar.","en":"The train arrived at the platform and passengers began to disembark."},{"es":"Por favor, espere detrás de la línea amarilla en el andén hasta que el metro se detenga por completo.","en":"Please wait behind the yellow line on the platform until the subway comes to a complete stop."},{"es":"Corrí hacia el andén número cuatro porque mi tren salía en menos de dos minutos.","en":"I ran toward platform number four because my train was leaving in less than two minutes."}]},{"spanish_text":"Horario","english_text":"Schedule","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A plan that lists events or tasks and the times at which they will occur.","main_translations_es":["Programa","Calendario","Agenda"],"collocations":["schedule a meeting","schedule an appointment","schedule a flight","schedule a call"],"synonyms_en":["timetable","program","agenda"],"example_sentence":"The class schedule is posted every week.","example_es":"El horario de clases se publica cada semana.","example_en":"The class schedule is posted every week.","mnemonic_en":"Visualize a jewel-shaped clock labeled schedule hanging on a Spanish horario board.","cloze_distractors_en":["Distance","Entrance","Currency","Evidence"],"examples":[{"es":"El horario de clases se publica cada semana.","en":"The class schedule is posted every week."},{"es":"Por favor, consulte el horario de salida de los trenes en la pantalla.","en":"Please check the train departure schedule on the screen."},{"es":"El autobús se retrasó porque no cumplió con el horario establecido.","en":"The bus was delayed because it did not follow the established schedule."}]},{"spanish_text":"Tren","english_text":"Train","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A rail vehicle that carries passengers or freight along a railway track.","main_translations_es":["locomotora","vagón","ferrocarril"],"collocations":["train station","train schedule","train of thought","train of events"],"synonyms_en":["locomotive","railway","railcar"],"example_sentence":"The train will arrive at the station at eight.","example_es":"El tren llegará a la estación a las ocho.","example_en":"The train will arrive at the station at eight.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a train shouting ''Tren!'' as it whistles down the tracks.","cloze_distractors_en":["Bridge","Street","Flight","Hotel"],"examples":[{"es":"El tren llegará a la estación a las ocho.","en":"The train will arrive at the station at eight."},{"es":"Debemos comprar el boleto de tren antes de subir al vagón.","en":"We must buy the train ticket before boarding the carriage."},{"es":"El próximo tren sale de la plataforma número cuatro.","en":"The next train departs from platform number four."}]},{"spanish_text":"Autobús","english_text":"Bus","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A large motor vehicle that carries passengers by road, typically on a fixed route.","main_translations_es":["ómnibus","autocar","transporte público"],"collocations":["bus stop","bus route","bus schedule","bus driver"],"synonyms_en":["coach","shuttle","motorbus"],"example_sentence":"The bus arrives at eight.","example_es":"El autobús llega a las ocho.","example_en":"The bus arrives at eight.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a bright yellow bus labeled autobús zooming down the road.","cloze_distractors_en":["Road","Gate","Seat"],"examples":[{"es":"El autobús llega a las ocho.","en":"The bus arrives at eight."},{"es":"Debemos esperar el autobús en la parada de la esquina.","en":"We must wait for the bus at the corner stop."},{"es":"El conductor del autobús revisó mi boleto al subir.","en":"The bus driver checked my ticket when I boarded."}]},{"spanish_text":"Parada de autobús","english_text":"Bus stop","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A designated place where buses pick up and drop off passengers.","main_translations_es":["Parada de bus","Estación de autobuses","Parada de transporte público"],"collocations":["bus stop sign","bus stop light","bus stop shelter","bus stop announcement"],"synonyms_en":["bus station","transit stop","coach stop"],"example_sentence":"I''m going to the bus stop to catch the bus.","example_es":"Voy a la parada de autobús para coger el bus.","example_en":"I''m going to the bus stop to catch the bus.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a bus pulling up at a bright parada sign and stopping.","cloze_distractors_en":["Bike lane","Ship deck","Road sign","Fuel pump"],"examples":[{"es":"Voy a la parada de autobús para coger el bus.","en":"I''m going to the bus stop to catch the bus."},{"es":"El turista espera bajo la lluvia en la parada de autobús.","en":"The tourist is waiting in the rain at the bus stop."},{"es":"Debes bajar en la próxima parada de autobús para llegar al museo.","en":"You need to get off at the next bus stop to reach the museum."}]},{"spanish_text":"Taxi","english_text":"Taxi","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A vehicle for hire that transports passengers for a fare.","main_translations_es":["taxi","táxi","cabina de taxi"],"collocations":["take a taxi","call a taxi","taxi fare","taxi driver"],"synonyms_en":[],"example_sentence":"I need a taxi to get to the airport.","example_es":"Necesito un taxi para ir al aeropuerto.","example_en":"I need a taxi to get to the airport.","mnemonic_en":null,"cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito un taxi para ir al aeropuerto.","en":"I need a taxi to get to the airport."}]},{"spanish_text":"Metro","english_text":"Subway","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"An underground railway system used for urban transit.","main_translations_es":["metro","subterráneo","metro de la ciudad"],"collocations":["take the subway","subway station","subway line","subway map"],"synonyms_en":["metro","underground","tube"],"example_sentence":"I take the subway every morning to get to work.","example_es":"Voy al metro cada mañana para ir al trabajo.","example_en":"I take the subway every morning to get to work.","mnemonic_en":"Visualize a submarine (sub) navigating a metro tunnel as the city’s underground way.","cloze_distractors_en":["Sidewalk","Airplane","Backpack","Crosswalk"],"examples":[{"es":"Voy al metro cada mañana para ir al trabajo.","en":"I take the subway every morning to get to work."},{"es":"Debes bajar dos paradas más en el metro para llegar al museo.","en":"You need to ride the subway for two more stops to reach the museum."},{"es":"Compra un billete sencillo de metro en la máquina automática.","en":"Buy a single ticket for the subway at the automated machine."}]},{"spanish_text":"Ida y vuelta","english_text":"Round trip","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A journey that starts and ends at the same place.","main_translations_es":["ida y vuelta","ida y regreso","ida y retorno"],"collocations":["round-trip ticket","round-trip flight","round-trip journey","round-trip fare"],"synonyms_en":["return journey","out-and-back","return trip"],"example_sentence":"I bought a round trip ticket for my trip to Madrid.","example_es":"Compré un billete de ida y vuelta para mi viaje a Madrid.","example_en":"I bought a round trip ticket for my trip to Madrid.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a round circle (ronda) that trips you back home, like an ida y vuelta.","cloze_distractors_en":["Single-lane","Half-price","Full-board","Cross-town"],"examples":[{"es":"Compré un billete de ida y vuelta para mi viaje a Madrid.","en":"I bought a round trip ticket for my trip to Madrid."},{"es":"El precio del pasaje de ida y vuelta es más barato que comprar dos boletos sencillos.","en":"The price of a round trip ticket is cheaper than buying two one-way tickets."},{"es":"Necesito reservar un vuelo de ida y vuelta para mis vacaciones en diciembre.","en":"I need to book a round trip flight for my vacation in December."}]},{"spanish_text":"Solo ida","english_text":"One-way ticket","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A ticket that allows travel in only one direction, not a return.","main_translations_es":["Solo de ida","Solo ida","Solo ida de viaje"],"collocations":["buy a one-way ticket","one-way ticket to","one-way ticket for","one-way ticket price"],"synonyms_en":["single ticket","nonreturn ticket","one-way pass"],"example_sentence":"The price of a one-way ticket is cheaper than that of a round-trip ticket.","example_es":"El precio del solo ida es más barato que el del ida y vuelta.","example_en":"The price of a one-way ticket is cheaper than that of a round-trip ticket.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a solo rider saying ida as he hands over a one-way ticket.","cloze_distractors_en":["First-class seat","Boarding pass","Passport stamp","Travel voucher"],"examples":[{"es":"El precio del solo ida es más barato que el del ida y vuelta.","en":"The price of a one-way ticket is cheaper than that of a round-trip ticket."},{"es":"Para este viaje, solo necesito comprar un solo ida porque me quedaré a vivir allí.","en":"For this trip, I only need to buy a one-way ticket because I am going to stay and live there."},{"es":"El agente de viajes me preguntó si prefería un solo ida o si pensaba regresar pronto.","en":"The travel agent asked me if I preferred a one-way ticket or if I planned to return soon."}]},{"spanish_text":"Reserva","english_text":"Reservation","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the act of reserving something in advance, or a booking made for a future use","main_translations_es":["Reserva","Reservación"],"collocations":["make a reservation","hold a reservation","reservation fee","reservation system"],"synonyms_en":["booking","appointment","hold"],"example_sentence":"I made a reservation for two people.","example_es":"He hecho una reserva para dos personas.","example_en":"I made a reservation for two people.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a waiter noting a reservation on a wine reserva list.","cloze_distractors_en":["Destination","Permission","Suggestion","Collection"],"examples":[{"es":"He hecho una reserva para dos personas.","en":"I made a reservation for two people."},{"es":"Necesito confirmar mi reserva de hotel antes de llegar.","en":"I need to confirm my hotel reservation before I arrive."},{"es":"Sin una reserva, no podremos conseguir una mesa en el restaurante.","en":"Without a reservation, we will not be able to get a table at the restaurant."}]},{"spanish_text":"Mapa","english_text":"Map","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A diagram that represents an area, showing features such as roads, borders, or terrain.","main_translations_es":["Mapa","Plano"],"collocations":["world map","map out","map of","map the route"],"synonyms_en":["chart","atlas","plan"],"example_sentence":"The treasure map is hidden under the table.","example_es":"El mapa del tesoro está escondido bajo la mesa.","example_en":"The treasure map is hidden under the table.","mnemonic_en":"Visualize a MAP that looks like a MAPA poster of the world.","cloze_distractors_en":["Fence","Badge","Clock","Scale"],"examples":[{"es":"El mapa del tesoro está escondido bajo la mesa.","en":"The treasure map is hidden under the table."},{"es":"Necesito consultar el mapa para encontrar la estación de tren.","en":"I need to check the map to find the train station."},{"es":"No podemos perdernos porque tenemos un mapa de la ciudad.","en":"We cannot get lost because we have a map of the city."}]},{"spanish_text":"A la izquierda","english_text":"On the left","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Indicates a location to the left side.","main_translations_es":["Al lado izquierdo","En el lado izquierdo","A la izquierda de"],"collocations":["on the left side","on the left-hand side","on the left of","on the left side of the room"],"synonyms_en":["to the left","leftward","on the left side"],"example_sentence":"On the left of the store, you''ll find the park.","example_es":"A la izquierda de la tienda, encontrarás el parque.","example_en":"On the left of the store, you''ll find the park.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a sign pointing left that says A la izquierda and the arrow says On the left.","cloze_distractors_en":["In the middle","Under the roof","Across the map"],"examples":[{"es":"A la izquierda de la tienda, encontrarás el parque.","en":"On the left of the store, you''ll find the park."},{"es":"El baño está a la izquierda del pasillo principal.","en":"The restroom is on the left of the main hallway."},{"es":"Para llegar a la estación, gira a la izquierda en el semáforo.","en":"To reach the station, turn on the left at the traffic light."}]},{"spanish_text":"A la derecha","english_text":"On the right","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Located or positioned to the right side.","main_translations_es":["a la derecha de","en la derecha","a la derecha de la calle"],"collocations":["on the right side","on the right hand side","on the right side of the road","on the right side of the page"],"synonyms_en":["to the right","right-hand side","on the right-hand side"],"example_sentence":"Keep going on the right until you reach the park.","example_es":"Sigue a la derecha hasta el parque.","example_en":"Keep going on the right until you reach the park.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a hand shouting de‑reach‑a while pointing on the right.","cloze_distractors_en":["In the past","At the middle","Of the truth"],"examples":[{"es":"Sigue a la derecha hasta el parque.","en":"Keep going on the right until you reach the park."},{"es":"La entrada del museo está a la derecha.","en":"The museum entrance is on the right."},{"es":"Verás la estación de tren a la derecha.","en":"You will see the train station on the right."}]},{"spanish_text":"Todo recto","english_text":"Straight ahead","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Straight ahead means directly forward, in a straight line.","main_translations_es":["Todo recto"],"collocations":["straight ahead of the road","straight ahead of the line","straight ahead of the path"],"synonyms_en":["directly forward","right ahead","straight on"],"example_sentence":"Keep going straight ahead until the intersection.","example_es":"Sigue todo recto hasta el cruce.","example_en":"Keep going straight ahead until the intersection.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a straight road with a sign that reads recto, pointing straight ahead","cloze_distractors_en":["Backward slowly","Sideways quickly","Upward entirely","Inward silently"],"examples":[{"es":"Sigue todo recto hasta el cruce.","en":"Keep going straight ahead until the intersection."},{"es":"Para llegar a la estación, camina todo recto dos manzanas.","en":"To reach the station, walk straight ahead for two blocks."},{"es":"Si quieres encontrar el museo, ve todo recto por esta calle.","en":"If you want to find the museum, go straight ahead along this street."}]},{"spanish_text":"Esquina","english_text":"Corner","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"a point where two lines or surfaces meet, forming an angle.","main_translations_es":["Rincón","Ángulo","Borde"],"collocations":["corner store","corner office","corner of the room","corner of the eye"],"synonyms_en":["angle","nook","intersection"],"example_sentence":"The cat hid in the corner of the hallway.","example_es":"El gato se escondió en la esquina del pasillo.","example_en":"The cat hid in the corner of the hallway.","mnemonic_en":"A corn ear rests on the esquina, marking the corner.","cloze_distractors_en":["Ceiling","Pavement","Backyard","Platform"],"examples":[{"es":"El gato se escondió en la esquina del pasillo.","en":"The cat hid in the corner of the hallway."},{"es":"Gira a la derecha en la próxima esquina para encontrar la estación.","en":"Turn right at the next corner to find the station."},{"es":"El hotel está ubicado justo en la esquina de la avenida principal.","en":"The hotel is located right on the corner of the main avenue."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cerca","english_text":"Near","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"At or within a short distance.","main_translations_es":["Alrededor","Próximo","Junto a"],"collocations":["near the border","near the station","near the end","near the beginning"],"synonyms_en":["close","adjacent","nearby"],"example_sentence":"The park is near my house.","example_es":"El parque está cerca de mi casa.","example_en":"The park is near my house.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a circus near the arena and the ringmaster yells ''cerca'' to signal they''re close.","cloze_distractors_en":["Heavy","Quick","Empty","Daily"],"examples":[{"es":"El parque está cerca de mi casa.","en":"The park is near my house."},{"es":"La estación de tren está cerca del hotel.","en":"The train station is near the hotel."},{"es":"Hay una farmacia cerca de la parada de autobús.","en":"There is a pharmacy near the bus stop."}]},{"spanish_text":"Lejos","english_text":"Far","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"at a great distance from a particular point or place.","main_translations_es":["Distante","A distancia","Lejano"],"collocations":["far away","far from","far enough","far too"],"synonyms_en":["distant","remote","away"],"example_sentence":"The lighthouse is far from the coast.","example_es":"El faro está lejos de la costa.","example_en":"The lighthouse is far from the coast.","mnemonic_en":"A far horizon feels like the Spanish word lejos stretching into the distance.","cloze_distractors_en":["Fast","Soon","Hard"],"examples":[{"es":"El faro está lejos de la costa.","en":"The lighthouse is far from the coast."},{"es":"La estación de tren está lejos del centro de la ciudad.","en":"The train station is far from the city center."},{"es":"El hotel no está cerca, está lejos de aquí.","en":"The hotel is not nearby, it is far from here."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cruce","english_text":"Crossing","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A place where one can cross from one side to another.","main_translations_es":["intersección","cruce de caminos","cruce de calles"],"collocations":["crossing guard","crossing the street","crossing the bridge","crossing the border"],"synonyms_en":["intersection","junction","crosswalk"],"example_sentence":"The pedestrian waits for the traffic light to change at the crossing.","example_es":"El peatón espera a que el semáforo cambie en el cruce.","example_en":"The pedestrian waits for the traffic light to change at the crossing.","mnemonic_en":"Crossing sounds like cruise—picture a cruise ship crossing a busy street.","cloze_distractors_en":["Passenger","Departure","Platform","Direction"],"examples":[{"es":"El peatón espera a que el semáforo cambie en el cruce.","en":"The pedestrian waits for the traffic light to change at the crossing."},{"es":"Debes reducir la velocidad antes de llegar al cruce de trenes.","en":"You must slow down before arriving at the train crossing."},{"es":"El mapa indica que hay un cruce peatonal cerca de la estación.","en":"The map indicates that there is a pedestrian crossing near the station."}]},{"spanish_text":"Semáforo","english_text":"Traffic light","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A device that controls traffic by displaying red, yellow, and green lights.","main_translations_es":["señal de tráfico","señal luminosa","señal de luz"],"collocations":["traffic light signal","traffic light system","traffic light cycle","traffic light colors"],"synonyms_en":["stoplight","signal light","road signal"],"example_sentence":"The traffic light turned red and the drivers stopped.","example_es":"El semáforo se puso rojo y los conductores se detuvieron.","example_en":"The traffic light turned red and the drivers stopped.","mnemonic_en":"The traffic light flashes red, yellow, green like a bright semáforo guiding cars.","cloze_distractors_en":["Steering wheel","License plate","Boarding pass","Flight number"],"examples":[{"es":"El semáforo se puso rojo y los conductores se detuvieron.","en":"The traffic light turned red and the drivers stopped."},{"es":"Gira a la derecha cuando llegues al próximo semáforo.","en":"Turn right when you reach the next traffic light."},{"es":"Estamos esperando a que el semáforo cambie a verde para cruzar la calle.","en":"We are waiting for the traffic light to change to green to cross the street."}]},{"spanish_text":"Calle","english_text":"Street","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A public road in a city or town, typically with buildings on one or both sides.","main_translations_es":["avenida","callejón","paseo"],"collocations":["on the street","street address","street name","street corner"],"synonyms_en":["road","avenue","thoroughfare"],"example_sentence":"Look both ways for cars before you cross the street.","example_es":"Mira a ambos lados para ver si vienen coches antes de cruzar la calle.","example_en":"Look both ways for cars before you cross the street.","mnemonic_en":"Visualize a street where every house has a big ''C'' on the door, reminding you of the Spanish ''calle''.","cloze_distractors_en":["Ticket","Wallet","Passport","Suitcase"],"examples":[{"es":"Mira a ambos lados para ver si vienen coches antes de cruzar la calle.","en":"Look both ways for cars before you cross the street."},{"es":"Tienes que girar a la izquierda en la próxima calle.","en":"You need to turn left at the next street."},{"es":"Mi hotel está ubicado en una calle muy estrecha.","en":"My hotel is located on a very narrow street."}]},{"spanish_text":"Avenida","english_text":"Avenue","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A wide street, especially one that is lined with trees or buildings.","main_translations_es":["Calle","Vía","Paseo"],"collocations":["Avenue of the Arts","Avenue of the Americas","Broadway Avenue"],"synonyms_en":["boulevard","street","road"],"example_sentence":"The main avenue is full of shops.","example_es":"La Avenida principal está llena de tiendas.","example_en":"The main avenue is full of shops.","mnemonic_en":"Picture an AVENUE where every sign says A VENIDA, inviting you to come and go.","cloze_distractors_en":["Ticket","Driver","Wallet","Camera"],"examples":[{"es":"La Avenida principal está llena de tiendas.","en":"The main avenue is full of shops."},{"es":"Nuestro hotel está en una avenida muy concurrida.","en":"Our hotel is on a very busy avenue."},{"es":"Camina por la avenida hasta llegar al museo.","en":"Walk along the avenue until you reach the museum."}]},{"spanish_text":"Plaza","english_text":"Square","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A public open space surrounded by buildings, often used for gathering or commerce.","main_translations_es":["plaza","plazuela","parque"],"collocations":["public square","town square","city square","square footage"],"synonyms_en":["town square","public plaza","open space"],"example_sentence":"Let''s meet in the main square next to the big fountain.","example_es":"Quedemos en la plaza principal al lado de la gran fuente.","example_en":"Let''s meet in the main square next to the big fountain.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a town square bustling like a Spanish plaza.","cloze_distractors_en":["Ticket","Flight","Runway","Window"],"examples":[{"es":"Quedemos en la plaza principal al lado de la gran fuente.","en":"Let''s meet in the main square next to the big fountain."},{"es":"El autobús turístico para justo en medio de la plaza central.","en":"The tour bus stops right in the middle of the central square."},{"es":"La catedral y el ayuntamiento están situados alrededor de la plaza.","en":"The cathedral and the city hall are located around the square."}]},{"spanish_text":"Giro","english_text":"Turn","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"a movement or rotation around an axis","main_translations_es":["Vuelta","Rotación","Cambio"],"collocations":["turn on","turn off","turn around","turn over"],"synonyms_en":["rotate","twist","pivot"],"example_sentence":"Take the next turn on the left to reach the airport terminal.","example_es":"Toma el siguiente giro a la izquierda para llegar a la terminal del aeropuerto.","example_en":"Take the next turn on the left to reach the airport terminal.","mnemonic_en":"Turn the knob and picture a fast giro spin","cloze_distractors_en":["Seat","Tour","Desk","Zone"],"examples":[{"es":"Toma el siguiente giro a la izquierda para llegar a la terminal del aeropuerto.","en":"Take the next turn on the left to reach the airport terminal."},{"es":"El taxi realizó un giro prohibido cerca de la plaza principal de la ciudad.","en":"The taxi made an illegal turn near the main square of the city."},{"es":"Debes reducir la velocidad del coche antes de realizar un giro cerrado.","en":"You must reduce the speed of the car before making a sharp turn."}]},{"spanish_text":"Centro","english_text":"Downtown","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the central business district of a city, typically characterized by high-rise buildings and commercial activity.","main_translations_es":["centro","centro de la ciudad","centro urbano"],"collocations":["downtown area","downtown core","downtown business district","downtown shopping"],"synonyms_en":["city center","central business district","urban core"],"example_sentence":"The tourist information office is located in the heart of downtown.","example_es":"La oficina de información turística se encuentra en el corazón del centro.","example_en":"The tourist information office is located in the heart of downtown.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a bustling downtown as the city''s centro, the central town hub.","cloze_distractors_en":["Passport","Suitcase","Souvenir","Postcard"],"examples":[{"es":"La oficina de información turística se encuentra en el corazón del centro.","en":"The tourist information office is located in the heart of downtown."},{"es":"Muchos hoteles ofrecen un servicio de transporte gratuito al centro.","en":"Many hotels offer a free shuttle service to downtown."},{"es":"Los rascacielos más altos y la estación principal de autobuses se encuentran en medio del centro.","en":"The tallest skyscrapers and the main bus station are located in the middle of downtown."}]},{"spanish_text":"Dirección","english_text":"Address","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the details of a place where someone lives or works.","main_translations_es":["Ubicación","Localización","Sitio"],"collocations":["home address","email address","physical address","address a letter"],"synonyms_en":["location","residence","direction"],"example_sentence":"Please write the hotel address on this paper.","example_es":"Por favor, escriba la dirección del hotel en este papel.","example_en":"Please write the hotel address on this paper.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a dress with a house tag on it to remember an address.","cloze_distractors_en":["Baggage","Journey","Holiday","Airport"],"examples":[{"es":"Por favor, escriba la dirección del hotel en este papel.","en":"Please write the hotel address on this paper."},{"es":"Necesito darle la dirección al taxista para llegar al museo.","en":"I need to give the address to the taxi driver to get to the museum."},{"es":"¿Puede decirme la dirección exacta de la estación de tren?","en":"Can you tell me the exact address of the train station?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Hotel","english_text":"Hotel","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"a building where people pay to stay for a short time","main_translations_es":["hotel","albergue","posada"],"collocations":["hotel room","hotel staff","hotel reservation","hotel lobby"],"synonyms_en":[],"example_sentence":"The hotel is near the city center.","example_es":"El hotel está cerca del centro.","example_en":"The hotel is near the city center.","mnemonic_en":null,"cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El hotel está cerca del centro.","en":"The hotel is near the city center."}]},{"spanish_text":"Recepción","english_text":"Reception","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the act of receiving guests or visitors, especially at an entrance","main_translations_es":["Bienvenida","Entrada","Recepción"],"collocations":["reception desk","reception area","reception hall","reception party"],"synonyms_en":["welcome desk","front desk","receiving area"],"example_sentence":"The hotel''s reception is open 24 hours a day.","example_es":"La recepción del hotel está abierta las 24 horas.","example_en":"The hotel''s reception is open 24 hours a day.","mnemonic_en":"At the hotel reception I picture a receptionist saying recepción as guests arrive.","cloze_distractors_en":["Itinerary","Excursion","Guidebook","Checklist"],"examples":[{"es":"La recepción del hotel está abierta las 24 horas.","en":"The hotel''s reception is open 24 hours a day."},{"es":"Por favor, deje las llaves de su habitación en la recepción antes de salir.","en":"Please leave your room keys at the reception before you leave."},{"es":"¿Dónde está la recepción para registrar mi llegada al hostal?","en":"Where is the reception to check in to the hostel?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Habitación","english_text":"Room","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A separate area within a building used for a particular purpose.","main_translations_es":["cuarto","dormitorio","habitación"],"collocations":["living room","bedroom","room for improvement","room to spare"],"synonyms_en":["chamber","space","area"],"example_sentence":"I would like to book a double room for three nights.","example_es":"Me gustaría reservar una habitación doble por tres noches.","example_en":"I would like to book a double room for three nights.","mnemonic_en":"A room feels like a habitat—habitación, a cozy den.","cloze_distractors_en":["Seat","Trip","Road","View"],"examples":[{"es":"Me gustaría reservar una habitación doble por tres noches.","en":"I would like to book a double room for three nights."},{"es":"Olvidé la llave de mi habitación en la recepción del hotel.","en":"I forgot the key to my room at the hotel front desk."},{"es":"Por favor, envíen algunas toallas extra a mi habitación ahora.","en":"Please send some extra towels to my room now."}]},{"spanish_text":"Llave","english_text":"Key","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A small metal instrument used to open locks or secure items.","main_translations_es":["clave","código"],"collocations":["key point","key player","key issue","key to success"],"synonyms_en":["essential","crucial","principal"],"example_sentence":"Can you give me a key for my room?","example_es":"¿Me puede dar una llave para mi habitación?","example_en":"Can you give me a key for my room?","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a key turning the Spanish llave lock on a treasure chest.","cloze_distractors_en":["Bus","Car","Sea","Sun"],"examples":[{"es":"¿Me puede dar una llave para mi habitación?","en":"Can you give me a key for my room?"},{"es":"Perdí la llave de mi maleta en el aeropuerto.","en":"I lost the key to my suitcase at the airport."},{"es":"Por favor, deje la llave en el mostrador al salir.","en":"Please leave the key at the desk when you check out."}]},{"spanish_text":"Toalla","english_text":"Towel","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A piece of absorbent cloth or paper used for drying or wiping.","main_translations_es":["toalla","paño","pañuelo"],"collocations":["hand towel","bath towel","towel rack","towel dry"],"synonyms_en":["drying cloth","absorbent cloth","bath linen"],"example_sentence":"Please bring a fresh towel to my room because this one is wet.","example_es":"Por favor, traiga una toalla limpia a mi habitación porque esta está mojada.","example_en":"Please bring a fresh towel to my room because this one is wet.","mnemonic_en":"I picture a towel that looks like a giant toalla waving in the wind","cloze_distractors_en":["Radio","Phone","Clock","Train"],"examples":[{"es":"Por favor, traiga una toalla limpia a mi habitación porque esta está mojada.","en":"Please bring a fresh towel to my room because this one is wet."},{"es":"Necesito una toalla grande para acostarme en la arena de la playa.","en":"I need a large towel to lie down on the beach sand."},{"es":"No olvides empacar una toalla de microfibra en tu maleta.","en":"Don''t forget to pack a microfiber towel in your suitcase."}]},{"spanish_text":"Baño","english_text":"Bathroom","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A room in a house or apartment equipped for washing and personal hygiene.","main_translations_es":["Baño","Cuarto de baño","Sanitario"],"collocations":["washroom","bathroom facilities","bathroom break","bathroom sign"],"synonyms_en":["restroom","washroom","lavatory"],"example_sentence":"The hotel room has a private bathroom with a shower.","example_es":"La habitación del hotel tiene un baño privado con ducha.","example_en":"The hotel room has a private bathroom with a shower.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a bathroom with a giant \"baño\" bathtub overflowing with bubbles","cloze_distractors_en":["Passport","Souvenir","Vacation","Currency"],"examples":[{"es":"La habitación del hotel tiene un baño privado con ducha.","en":"The hotel room has a private bathroom with a shower."},{"es":"¿Hay un baño en esta cafetería? Necesito lavarme las manos antes de comer.","en":"Is there a bathroom in this cafe? I need to wash my hands before I eat."},{"es":"Necesito ir al baño antes del vuelo.","en":"I need to go to the bathroom before the flight."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cama doble","english_text":"Double bed","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A bed that is larger than a single bed, typically accommodating two people.","main_translations_es":["Cama matrimonial","Cama doble estándar","Cama doble grande"],"collocations":["double bed room","double bed size","double bed mattress","double bed furniture"],"synonyms_en":["full-size bed","queen-size bed"],"example_sentence":"We are traveling as a couple, so we reserved a room with a double bed.","example_es":"Viajamos en pareja, así que reservamos una habitación con una cama doble.","example_en":"We are traveling as a couple, so we reserved a room with a double bed.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine two beds side by side, a double bed, echoing the Spanish doble","cloze_distractors_en":["Front desk","Travel agent","Ticket office","Flight number"],"examples":[{"es":"Viajamos en pareja, así que reservamos una habitación con una cama doble.","en":"We are traveling as a couple, so we reserved a room with a double bed."},{"es":"¿Es posible tener una cama doble en lugar de dos camas individuales?","en":"Is it possible to have a double bed instead of two single beds?"},{"es":"La cabaña es pequeña y solo tiene una cama doble, así que ambos tenemos que dormir en el mismo colchón.","en":"The cabin is small and only has one double bed, so we both have to sleep on the same mattress."}]},{"spanish_text":"Una noche","english_text":"One night","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A single night, a period of 24 hours.","main_translations_es":["una noche"],"collocations":["one night stand","one night only","one night in","one night out"],"synonyms_en":["a single night","one evening","a night"],"example_sentence":"I only need the room for one night because I am checking out tomorrow morning.","example_es":"Solo necesito la habitación por una noche porque me marcharé mañana por la mañana.","example_en":"I only need the room for one night because I am checking out tomorrow morning.","mnemonic_en":"See a single night sky whispering ''one night'' like the Spanish ''una noche''","cloze_distractors_en":["One station","One seat","One taxi","One route"],"examples":[{"es":"Solo necesito la habitación por una noche porque me marcharé mañana por la mañana.","en":"I only need the room for one night because I am checking out tomorrow morning."},{"es":"Solo nos quedaremos en la ciudad una noche antes del vuelo.","en":"We will only stay in the city one night before the flight."},{"es":"El precio del hostal es de veinte euros por una noche.","en":"The hostel price is twenty euros for one night."}]},{"spanish_text":"Registrarse","english_text":"Check in","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to register upon arrival, typically at a hotel or event","main_translations_es":["Inscribirse","Matricularse","Registrarse en línea"],"collocations":["check in online","check in at the front desk","check in for a flight","check in with someone"],"synonyms_en":["sign up","register","enroll"],"example_sentence":"Please go to the front desk to check in at the hotel.","example_es":"Por favor, vaya a la recepción para registrarse en el hotel.","example_en":"Please go to the front desk to check in at the hotel.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a clerk handing you a check as you register at the front desk","cloze_distractors_en":["Get off","Pass by","Turn back","Walk away"],"examples":[{"es":"Por favor, vaya a la recepción para registrarse en el hotel.","en":"Please go to the front desk to check in at the hotel."},{"es":"Los pasajeros deben llegar temprano al aeropuerto para registrarse para el vuelo.","en":"Passengers must arrive early at the airport to check in for the flight."},{"es":"Puede usar el quiosco digital para registrarse sin esperar en la fila.","en":"You can use the digital kiosk to check in without waiting in line."}]},{"spanish_text":"Salida del hotel","english_text":"Check out","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to leave a hotel after paying the bill","main_translations_es":["Salida del hotel","Salida del establecimiento","Salida del alojamiento"],"collocations":["check out early","check out late","check out of a hotel","check out online"],"synonyms_en":["depart","leave","pay the bill"],"example_sentence":"You must check out at the reception desk to pay for the room service charges.","example_es":"Debe realizar la salida del hotel en la recepción para pagar los cargos del servicio de habitaciones.","example_en":"You must check out at the reception desk to pay for the room service charges.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a giant checkmark being taken out the hotel door as you exit.","cloze_distractors_en":["Sign in","Carry on","Hold up","Stay in"],"examples":[{"es":"Debe realizar la salida del hotel en la recepción para pagar los cargos del servicio de habitaciones.","en":"You must check out at the reception desk to pay for the room service charges."},{"es":"La política del hotel requiere que los huéspedes realicen la salida del hotel antes del mediodía para que el personal de limpieza pueda preparar la habitación.","en":"The hotel policy requires guests to check out by noon so the cleaning staff can prepare the room."},{"es":"Por favor, entregue su llave en la recepción al hacer la salida del hotel.","en":"Please return your key to the front desk when you check out."}]},{"spanish_text":"Desayuno incluido","english_text":"Breakfast included","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase indicating that breakfast is included in the price or package.","main_translations_es":["Desayuno incluido"],"collocations":["Breakfast included in the price","Breakfast included with your stay","Breakfast included for guests","Breakfast included at the hotel"],"synonyms_en":["Breakfast provided","Morning meal included","Meal included"],"example_sentence":"Does our hotel reservation have breakfast included or is it an extra charge?","example_es":"¿Nuestra reserva de hotel tiene desayuno incluido o es un cargo adicional?","example_en":"Does our hotel reservation have breakfast included or is it an extra charge?","mnemonic_en":"Picture a break-fast banner that says incluido, so the meal is already included.","cloze_distractors_en":["Passport control","Baggage allowance","Customs clearance","Airport security"],"examples":[{"es":"¿Nuestra reserva de hotel tiene desayuno incluido o es un cargo adicional?","en":"Does our hotel reservation have breakfast included or is it an extra charge?"},{"es":"No necesitamos buscar una cafetería a las 7:00 AM porque nuestro hotel tiene desayuno incluido.","en":"We don''t need to look for a cafe at 7:00 AM because our hotel has breakfast included."},{"es":"Podemos comer huevos y café en el buffet del hotel gratis porque nuestra habitación tiene desayuno incluido.","en":"We can eat eggs and coffee at the hotel buffet for free because our room has breakfast included."}]},{"spanish_text":"Aire acondicionado","english_text":"Air conditioning","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The process of controlling the temperature, humidity, and air quality in a building or vehicle.","main_translations_es":["climatizador","climatización","sistema de aire acondicionado"],"collocations":["air conditioning unit","air conditioning system","air conditioning repair","air conditioning service"],"synonyms_en":["climate control","cooling system","air conditioner"],"example_sentence":"Could you turn on the air conditioning? It is very hot on the bus.","example_es":"¿Podría encender el aire acondicionado? Hace mucho calor en el autobús.","example_en":"Could you turn on the air conditioning? It is very hot on the bus.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a chilly wind that airs and condi-tiones the room like a Spanish acondicionado.","cloze_distractors_en":["Interior lighting","Navigation system","Bluetooth audio"],"examples":[{"es":"¿Podría encender el aire acondicionado? Hace mucho calor en el autobús.","en":"Could you turn on the air conditioning? It is very hot on the bus."},{"es":"Por favor, baje el aire acondicionado porque tengo mucho frío en la habitación.","en":"Please turn down the air conditioning because I am very cold in the room."},{"es":"Necesito alquilar un coche que tenga aire acondicionado para mi viaje al desierto.","en":"I need to rent a car that has air conditioning for my trip to the desert."}]},{"spanish_text":"Wi-Fi","english_text":"Wi-Fi","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"a wireless networking technology that allows devices to connect to the internet or communicate with each other without cables.","main_translations_es":["Wi-Fi","wifi","red inalámbrica"],"collocations":["Wi-Fi connection","Wi-Fi network","Wi-Fi hotspot","Wi-Fi signal"],"synonyms_en":[],"example_sentence":"I connected my phone to the hotel’s Wi‑Fi.","example_es":"Conecté mi teléfono al Wi‑Fi del hotel.","example_en":"I connected my phone to the hotel’s Wi‑Fi.","mnemonic_en":null,"cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Conecté mi teléfono al Wi‑Fi del hotel.","en":"I connected my phone to the hotel’s Wi‑Fi."}]},{"spanish_text":"Ascensor","english_text":"Elevator","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A mechanical device that transports people or goods between floors of a building.","main_translations_es":["Elevador"],"collocations":["take the elevator","elevator music","elevator pitch","elevator ride"],"synonyms_en":["lift","people mover"],"example_sentence":"The elevator is not working, so we have to use the stairs.","example_es":"El ascensor no funciona, así que tenemos que usar las escaleras.","example_en":"The elevator is not working, so we have to use the stairs.","mnemonic_en":"Picture an elevator shouting Eleva señor as it lifts you up.","cloze_distractors_en":["Passport","Terminal","Schedule","Backpack"],"examples":[{"es":"El ascensor no funciona, así que tenemos que usar las escaleras.","en":"The elevator is not working, so we have to use the stairs."},{"es":"Mis maletas son muy pesadas, voy a tomar el ascensor.","en":"My suitcases are very heavy, I am going to take the elevator."},{"es":"Por favor, pulsa el botón del quinto piso en el ascensor.","en":"Please press the button for the fifth floor in the elevator."}]},{"spanish_text":"Equipaje","english_text":"Luggage","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Items of personal belongings carried in a suitcase or bag, especially when traveling.","main_translations_es":["Bolsas","Maletas","Equipamiento"],"collocations":["checked luggage","carry-on luggage","lost luggage","luggage tag"],"synonyms_en":["baggage","travel gear","suitcases"],"example_sentence":"My luggage from the flight arrived late.","example_es":"El equipaje de mi vuelo llegó tarde.","example_en":"My luggage from the flight arrived late.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a strong lug pulling a suitcase full of equipaje across the airport.","cloze_distractors_en":["Airport","Traffic","Station","Journey"],"examples":[{"es":"El equipaje de mi vuelo llegó tarde.","en":"My luggage from the flight arrived late."},{"es":"Por favor, ayúdeme a poner este equipaje pesado en el maletero del taxi.","en":"Please help me put this heavy luggage in the trunk of the taxi."},{"es":"La aerolínea perdió mi equipaje, así que no tengo ropa para el viaje.","en":"The airline lost my luggage, so I have no clothes for the trip."}]},{"spanish_text":"Mochila","english_text":"Backpack","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A bag carried on the back, typically with two straps, used for carrying books, supplies, or other items.","main_translations_es":["Bolsa","Bolso","Bolsa de viaje"],"collocations":["backpack school","backpack travel","backpack tour","backpack for hiking"],"synonyms_en":["knapsack","rucksack","daypack"],"example_sentence":"I put my passport in the small pocket of my backpack.","example_es":"Puse mi pasaporte en el bolsillo pequeño de mi mochila.","example_en":"I put my passport in the small pocket of my backpack.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a mochi bag strapped to your back, a mochila backpack.","cloze_distractors_en":["Terminal","Landmark","Stopover","Mountain"],"examples":[{"es":"Puse mi pasaporte en el bolsillo pequeño de mi mochila.","en":"I put my passport in the small pocket of my backpack."},{"es":"¿Esta mochila cabe debajo del asiento del avión?","en":"Does this backpack fit under the airplane seat?"},{"es":"Mi mochila es demasiado pesada para caminar todo el día.","en":"My backpack is too heavy to walk all day."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cargador","english_text":"Charger","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"a device that supplies electrical energy to recharge a battery","main_translations_es":["cargador","recargador","alimentador"],"collocations":["phone charger","battery charger","USB charger","portable charger"],"synonyms_en":["power adapter","charging device","battery pack"],"example_sentence":"My phone battery is at one percent, so I really need a charger.","example_es":"La batería de mi teléfono está al uno por ciento, así que realmente necesito un cargador.","example_en":"My phone battery is at one percent, so I really need a charger.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a charger feeding a car''s battery, like a CARGA‑door opening power.","cloze_distractors_en":["Ticket","Wallet","Pillow","Passport"],"examples":[{"es":"La batería de mi teléfono está al uno por ciento, así que realmente necesito un cargador.","en":"My phone battery is at one percent, so I really need a charger."},{"es":"La terminal del aeropuerto tiene puertos USB, pero olvidé mi cargador en mi maleta.","en":"The airport terminal has USB ports, but I forgot my charger in my suitcase."},{"es":"¿Hay un enchufe de pared en esta cafetería para conectar mi cargador?","en":"Is there a wall outlet in this cafe to plug in my charger?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Enchufe","english_text":"Plug","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"a device that connects an electrical appliance to a power source","main_translations_es":["toma de corriente","conector","enchufe"],"collocations":["plug in","plug out","plug and play","plug into"],"synonyms_en":["connector","stopper","adapter"],"example_sentence":"I need an adapter because the plug on my charger does not fit this outlet.","example_es":"Necesito un adaptador porque el enchufe de mi cargador no cabe en esta toma.","example_en":"I need an adapter because the plug on my charger does not fit this outlet.","mnemonic_en":"Visualize a bright plug stamped ENCHUFE, snapping into the wall like a Spanish power plug","cloze_distractors_en":["Gate","Taxi","Tour","Fare"],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito un adaptador porque el enchufe de mi cargador no cabe en esta toma.","en":"I need an adapter because the plug on my charger does not fit this outlet."},{"es":"¿Tiene este asiento del tren un enchufe para cargar mi teléfono móvil?","en":"Does this seat on the train have a plug to charge my mobile phone?"},{"es":"Por favor, saca el enchufe de la pared antes de salir de la habitación del hotel.","en":"Please pull the plug out of the wall before you leave the hotel room."}]},{"spanish_text":"Adaptador","english_text":"Adapter","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A device that allows one type of connection to be used with another.","main_translations_es":["Adaptador"],"collocations":["adapter for USB","adapter cable","power adapter","audio adapter"],"synonyms_en":["converter","connector","interface"],"example_sentence":"I need an adapter to plug my laptop into the European outlet.","example_es":"Necesito un adaptador para conectar mi portátil al enchufe europeo.","example_en":"I need an adapter to plug my laptop into the European outlet.","mnemonic_en":"Visualize an adapter plugging a Spanish adaptador into a socket, the words sound identical.","cloze_distractors_en":["Address","Account","Airport","Arrival"],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito un adaptador para conectar mi portátil al enchufe europeo.","en":"I need an adapter to plug my laptop into the European outlet."},{"es":"¿Tienen algún adaptador en recepción? Olvidé el mío y no puedo cargar el teléfono.","en":"Do you have an adapter at the front desk? I forgot mine and cannot charge my phone."},{"es":"Este adaptador universal funciona en más de cien países diferentes.","en":"This universal adapter works in more than one hundred different countries."}]},{"spanish_text":"Dinero en efectivo","english_text":"Cash","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Money in the form of coins and banknotes that can be used for transactions.","main_translations_es":["Efectivo","Dinero en mano","Dinero en efectivo"],"collocations":["cash register","cash flow","cash out","cash on hand"],"synonyms_en":["money","currency","hard cash"],"example_sentence":"The small souvenir shop only accepts cash.","example_es":"La pequeña tienda de recuerdos solo acepta dinero en efectivo.","example_en":"The small souvenir shop only accepts cash.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a cash box, a caja overflowing with dinero.","cloze_distractors_en":["Fuel","Wind","Salt","Soap"],"examples":[{"es":"La pequeña tienda de recuerdos solo acepta dinero en efectivo.","en":"The small souvenir shop only accepts cash."},{"es":"El conductor del autobús dijo que solo podemos pagar el boleto con dinero en efectivo.","en":"The bus driver said we can only pay for the ticket with cash."},{"es":"El hotel necesita un depósito en dinero en efectivo para la llave de la habitación.","en":"The hotel needs a deposit in cash for the room key."}]},{"spanish_text":"Tarjeta","english_text":"Card","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A small, flat piece of paper, cardboard, or plastic used for identification, payment, or as a playing piece.","main_translations_es":["Tarjeta","Ficha","Cartón"],"collocations":["business card","credit card","playing card","card game"],"synonyms_en":["ticket","pass","note"],"example_sentence":"You must tap your card on the reader to pay for the bus.","example_es":"Debes pasar tu tarjeta por el lector para pagar el autobús.","example_en":"You must tap your card on the reader to pay for the bus.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a playing card covered in dark tar with a tiny jet sticker echoing tarjeta","cloze_distractors_en":["Seat","Trip","Park","Gate"],"examples":[{"es":"Debes pasar tu tarjeta por el lector para pagar el autobús.","en":"You must tap your card on the reader to pay for the bus."},{"es":"Necesito una tarjeta nueva para abrir la puerta de mi habitación de hotel.","en":"I need a new key card to open my hotel room door."},{"es":"¿Este restaurante acepta tarjeta de crédito para pagar la cuenta?","en":"Does this restaurant accept a credit card to pay the bill?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Moneda","english_text":"Coin","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A small, flat piece of metal used as money.","main_translations_es":["Moneda","Dinero"],"collocations":["coin toss","coin flip","coin collection","coin-operated"],"synonyms_en":["currency","piece of money","token"],"example_sentence":"I need a coin to use the station locker.","example_es":"Necesito una moneda para usar el casillero de la estación.","example_en":"I need a coin to use the station locker.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a shiny coin stamped with the word moneda on its edge.","cloze_distractors_en":["Road","Park","Seat","Town"],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito una moneda para usar el casillero de la estación.","en":"I need a coin to use the station locker."},{"es":"Guardé una moneda de plata como recuerdo de mi viaje.","en":"I kept a silver coin as a souvenir of my trip."},{"es":"Tira una moneda a la fuente para tener buena suerte.","en":"Throw a coin into the fountain for good luck."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cambio","english_text":"Change","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the act of becoming different","main_translations_es":["Intercambio","Transformación","Modificación"],"collocations":["change of heart","change of pace","change of scenery","change of plans"],"synonyms_en":["alteration","modification","shift"],"example_sentence":"I do not have enough change to pay for the parking meter.","example_es":"No tengo suficiente cambio para pagar el parquímetro.","example_en":"I do not have enough change to pay for the parking meter.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a coin flipping and you hear cambio as it changes.","cloze_distractors_en":["Ticket","Flight","Weight","Permit"],"examples":[{"es":"No tengo suficiente cambio para pagar el parquímetro.","en":"I do not have enough change to pay for the parking meter."},{"es":"Por favor, revise la pantalla por cualquier cambio en la puerta de salida.","en":"Please check the screen for any change to the departure gate."},{"es":"Siempre empaco un cambio de ropa en mi maleta de mano.","en":"I always pack a change of clothes in my carry-on bag."}]},{"spanish_text":"Recibo","english_text":"Receipt","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A written acknowledgment of having received something, typically a payment or goods.","main_translations_es":["comprobante","boleta","ticket"],"collocations":["receipt of","receipt for","receipt slip","receipt number"],"synonyms_en":["proof of purchase","sales slip","transaction record"],"example_sentence":"I need a receipt for the taxi for my boss.","example_es":"Necesito un recibo del taxi para mi jefe.","example_en":"I need a receipt for the taxi for my boss.","mnemonic_en":"I hand the cashier a receipt, thinking of my recibo tucked in my pocket.","cloze_distractors_en":["License","Compass","Passport","Schedule"],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito un recibo del taxi para mi jefe.","en":"I need a receipt for the taxi for my boss."},{"es":"Necesitas el recibo para devolver la maleta a la tienda.","en":"You need the receipt to return the suitcase to the store."},{"es":"El camarero me dio un recibo después de que pagué la cuenta.","en":"The waiter gave me a receipt after I paid the bill."}]},{"spanish_text":"Precio","english_text":"Price","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the amount of money expected, required, or given in payment for something.","main_translations_es":["Costo","Tarifa","Valor"],"collocations":["price tag","price point","price range","price list"],"synonyms_en":["cost","charge","fee"],"example_sentence":"The price of the ticket is twenty euros.","example_es":"El precio de la entrada es de veinte euros.","example_en":"The price of the ticket is twenty euros.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a price tag shouting precio as it slides down a cash register.","cloze_distractors_en":["Route","Pilot","Staff","Guide"],"examples":[{"es":"El precio de la entrada es de veinte euros.","en":"The price of the ticket is twenty euros."},{"es":"¿Cuál es el precio por una noche en este hotel?","en":"What is the price for one night in this hotel?"},{"es":"El precio de este recuerdo no está marcado en la etiqueta.","en":"The price of this souvenir is not marked on the tag."}]},{"spanish_text":"Abierto","english_text":"Open","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Not closed; allowing passage or access.","main_translations_es":["Disponible","Libre","Apertura"],"collocations":["open door","open mind","open source","open for business"],"synonyms_en":["unlocked","unsealed","available"],"example_sentence":"The museum is open from nine to five every day.","example_es":"El museo está abierto de nueve a cinco todos los días.","example_en":"The museum is open from nine to five every day.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine an open door shouting abierto as you walk in.","cloze_distractors_en":["Lost","Last","Long","Near"],"examples":[{"es":"El museo está abierto de nueve a cinco todos los días.","en":"The museum is open from nine to five every day."},{"es":"El restaurante del hotel está abierto para la cena.","en":"The hotel restaurant is open for dinner."},{"es":"¿Está el banco abierto los sábados por la mañana?","en":"Is the bank open on Saturday mornings?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Cerrado","english_text":"Closed","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Not open; shut.","main_translations_es":["Inactivo","Bloqueado","Sin acceso"],"collocations":["closed shop","closed door","closed circuit","closed season"],"synonyms_en":["shut","sealed","locked"],"example_sentence":"The museum is closed on Mondays, so we cannot go inside.","example_es":"El museo está cerrado los lunes, así que no podemos entrar.","example_en":"The museum is closed on Mondays, so we cannot go inside.","mnemonic_en":"Closed sounds like Spanish ''cerrado'', picture a door shut with a big red ''C'' lock.","cloze_distractors_en":["Opened","Public","Nearby","Modern"],"examples":[{"es":"El museo está cerrado los lunes, así que no podemos entrar.","en":"The museum is closed on Mondays, so we cannot go inside."},{"es":"La taquilla está cerrada, así que no puedo comprar un billete.","en":"The ticket office is closed, so I cannot buy a ticket."},{"es":"Llegamos tarde y la puerta de embarque está cerrada.","en":"We arrived late and the boarding gate is closed."}]},{"spanish_text":"Ayuda","english_text":"Help","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Assistance or support given to someone in need.","main_translations_es":["Asistencia","Soporte","Auxilio"],"collocations":["help out","help with","help someone","help yourself"],"synonyms_en":["assist","aid","support"],"example_sentence":"I need help with my heavy luggage at the hotel.","example_es":"Necesito ayuda con mi equipaje pesado en el hotel.","example_en":"I need help with my heavy luggage at the hotel.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a superhero shouting ''Ayuda!'' as he lifts a heavy box, reminding you that help sounds like ayuda.","cloze_distractors_en":["Road","Sign","Gate","Stop"],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito ayuda con mi equipaje pesado en el hotel.","en":"I need help with my heavy luggage at the hotel."},{"es":"El viajero perdido le pidió ayuda al oficial de policía.","en":"The lost traveler asked the police officer for help."},{"es":"La azafata le ofreció ayuda al pasajero de la tercera edad.","en":"The flight attendant offered help to the elderly passenger."}]},{"spanish_text":"Llama a la policía","english_text":"Call the police","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to contact the police for assistance or to report a crime","main_translations_es":["Llama a la policía","Contacta a la policía","Ponte en contacto con la policía"],"collocations":["call the police right away","call the police if there''s a fire","call the police for a robbery","call the police to report a crime"],"synonyms_en":["alert the police","dial 911","report to authorities"],"example_sentence":"In case of emergency, call the police.","example_es":"En caso de emergencia, llama a la policía.","example_en":"In case of emergency, call the police.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a llama dialing the phone to call the police.","cloze_distractors_en":["Pack the luggage","Book the flight","Miss the train"],"examples":[{"es":"En caso de emergencia, llama a la policía.","en":"In case of emergency, call the police."},{"es":"¡Alguien robó mi cámara! ¡Llama a la policía ahora mismo!","en":"Someone stole my camera! Call the police right now!"},{"es":"Hubo un accidente en la carretera, así que por favor llama a la policía.","en":"There was an accident on the road, so please call the police."}]},{"spanish_text":"Necesito un médico","english_text":"I need a doctor","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement expressing the speaker''s requirement for a medical professional.","main_translations_es":["Necesito un doctor","Me hace falta un médico","Requiero un médico"],"collocations":["I need a doctor right now","I need a doctor for my child","I need a doctor urgently","I need a doctor at the hospital"],"synonyms_en":["I require a doctor","I need a physician","I need medical assistance"],"example_sentence":"I need a doctor to check my headache.","example_es":"Necesito un médico para revisar mi dolor de cabeza.","example_en":"I need a doctor to check my headache.","mnemonic_en":"When I shout ''I need a doctor'', I picture saying ''necesito doctor'' to a panicked patient.","cloze_distractors_en":["I want a ticket","I miss the train","I find a hotel","I have a map"],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito un médico para revisar mi dolor de cabeza.","en":"I need a doctor to check my headache."},{"es":"Por favor, llame a una ambulancia porque necesito un médico de inmediato.","en":"Please call an ambulance because I need a doctor immediately."},{"es":"Me duele mucho el pecho y necesito un médico con urgencia.","en":"My chest hurts a lot and I need a doctor urgently."}]},{"spanish_text":"Emergencia","english_text":"Emergency","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A sudden, urgent situation requiring immediate action.","main_translations_es":["Crisis","Situación de emergencia"],"collocations":["emergency situation","emergency services","emergency department","emergency exit"],"synonyms_en":["crisis","urgent situation","critical incident"],"example_sentence":"In case of an emergency, please use the nearest exit.","example_es":"En caso de una emergencia, por favor use la salida más cercana.","example_en":"In case of an emergency, please use the nearest exit.","mnemonic_en":"A flashing red alarm makes me think emergency, like the word emerges from the chaos","cloze_distractors_en":["Adventure","Agreement","Attraction","Invitation"],"examples":[{"es":"En caso de una emergencia, por favor use la salida más cercana.","en":"In case of an emergency, please use the nearest exit."},{"es":"Debe llamar al nueve-uno-uno solo durante una emergencia real.","en":"You should call nine-one-one only during a real emergency."},{"es":"El tren se detuvo debido a una emergencia médica a bordo.","en":"The train stopped because of a medical emergency on board."}]},{"spanish_text":"He perdido mi pasaporte","english_text":"I lost my passport","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that the speaker has lost their passport.","main_translations_es":["Perdí mi pasaporte","He extraviado mi pasaporte","He perdido mi documento de viaje"],"collocations":["I lost my passport at the airport","I lost my passport while traveling","I lost my passport and had to get a replacement","I lost my passport and can''t travel"],"synonyms_en":["misplaced my passport","my passport is missing","can''t locate my passport"],"example_sentence":"I lost my passport, so I need to apply for a new one.","example_es":"He perdido mi pasaporte, así que necesito solicitar uno nuevo.","example_en":"I lost my passport, so I need to apply for a new one.","mnemonic_en":"I lost my passport, just like I lost my ''pasaporte'' on a windy beach.","cloze_distractors_en":["I lost my suitcase","I found my ticket","I forgot my camera","I booked my room"],"examples":[{"es":"He perdido mi pasaporte, así que necesito solicitar uno nuevo.","en":"I lost my passport, so I need to apply for a new one."},{"es":"No puedo abordar el avión porque he perdido mi pasaporte en la terminal.","en":"I cannot board the plane because I lost my passport in the terminal."},{"es":"Estoy muy preocupado porque he perdido mi pasaporte y no puedo salir del país.","en":"I am very worried because I lost my passport and I cannot leave the country."}]},{"spanish_text":"He perdido mi cartera","english_text":"I lost my wallet","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A sentence expressing that the speaker has misplaced or lost their wallet.","main_translations_es":["Perdí mi cartera","He perdido mi billetera","Perdí mi bolso"],"collocations":["I lost my wallet at the restaurant","I lost my wallet in the subway","I lost my wallet and had to cancel my cards"],"synonyms_en":["misplaced my wallet","my wallet is missing","can''t locate my wallet"],"example_sentence":"I need to call the bank to cancel my cards because I lost my wallet at the train station.","example_es":"Necesito llamar al banco para cancelar mis tarjetas porque he perdido mi cartera en la estación de tren.","example_en":"I need to call the bank to cancel my cards because I lost my wallet at the train station.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a carter dropping his wallet on the road, shouting lost my wallet!","cloze_distractors_en":["I visited a museum","I climbed a mountain","I attended a wedding","I watched a parade"],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito llamar al banco para cancelar mis tarjetas porque he perdido mi cartera en la estación de tren.","en":"I need to call the bank to cancel my cards because I lost my wallet at the train station."},{"es":"No puedo pagar la cena porque he perdido mi cartera.","en":"I cannot pay for dinner because I lost my wallet."},{"es":"Creo que he perdido mi cartera en el taxi que tomé al aeropuerto.","en":"I think I lost my wallet in the taxi I took to the airport."}]},{"spanish_text":"Estoy enfermo","english_text":"I am sick","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"I am ill or unwell.","main_translations_es":["Me siento enfermo","Estoy indispuesto","Tengo fiebre"],"collocations":["I am sick with a cold","I am sick and need to rest","I am sick to my stomach","I am sick of this"],"synonyms_en":["I''m ill","I feel unwell","I''m under the weather"],"example_sentence":"I have a high fever and a stomach ache, so I am sick and need to see the hotel doctor.","example_es":"Tengo mucha fiebre y dolor de estómago, así que estoy enfermo y necesito ver al médico del hotel.","example_en":"I have a high fever and a stomach ache, so I am sick and need to see the hotel doctor.","mnemonic_en":"I am sick, picture a patient in a hospital shouting ''Estoy enfermo'' while clutching his stomach.","cloze_distractors_en":["I am happy","I am ready","I am early","I am right"],"examples":[{"es":"Tengo mucha fiebre y dolor de estómago, así que estoy enfermo y necesito ver al médico del hotel.","en":"I have a high fever and a stomach ache, so I am sick and need to see the hotel doctor."},{"es":"Necesito quedarme en la habitación del hotel hoy porque estoy enfermo.","en":"I need to stay in the hotel room today because I am sick."},{"es":"Tengo mucha tos y dolor de garganta, así que estoy enfermo y necesito encontrar una farmacia.","en":"I have a bad cough and a sore throat, so I am sick and need to find a pharmacy."}]},{"spanish_text":"Está roto","english_text":"It is broken","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"It is not functioning properly; it has been damaged.","main_translations_es":["Se ha roto","Se rompió","Está averiado"],"collocations":["It is broken beyond repair","It is broken into pieces","It is broken down","It is broken up"],"synonyms_en":["It''s damaged","It''s busted","It''s not working"],"example_sentence":"I tried to use the lock on my bag, but it is broken.","example_es":"Intenté usar el candado de mi bolso, pero está roto.","example_en":"I tried to use the lock on my bag, but it is broken.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a broken vase yelling Roto!","cloze_distractors_en":["It is ready","It is heavy","It is clean","It is lost"],"examples":[{"es":"Intenté usar el candado de mi bolso, pero está roto.","en":"I tried to use the lock on my bag, but it is broken."},{"es":"El quiosco de facturación no funciona porque está roto.","en":"The check-in kiosk is not working because it is broken."},{"es":"El calefactor de la habitación del hotel no se apaga; está roto.","en":"The heater in the hotel room won''t turn off; it is broken."}]},{"spanish_text":"No funciona","english_text":"It does not work","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase indicating that something is not functioning or operating as intended.","main_translations_es":["No funciona"],"collocations":["It does not work for me","It does not work on my machine","It does not work as expected","It does not work properly"],"synonyms_en":["doesn''t work","fails","malfunctions"],"example_sentence":"The ticket machine has a black screen. It does not work.","example_es":"La máquina de billetes tiene la pantalla negra. No funciona.","example_en":"The ticket machine has a black screen. It does not work.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a broken robot shouting No function, it does not work.","cloze_distractors_en":["It does not arrive","It does not depart","It does not stay","It does not wait"],"examples":[{"es":"La máquina de billetes tiene la pantalla negra. No funciona.","en":"The ticket machine has a black screen. It does not work."},{"es":"El aire acondicionado hace un ruido extraño. No funciona.","en":"The air conditioning makes a strange noise. It does not work."},{"es":"La tarjeta de la habitación no abre la puerta. No funciona.","en":"The room card does not open the door. It does not work."}]},{"spanish_text":"¿Puede repetir?","english_text":"Can you repeat?","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"question","definition_en":"A polite request asking someone to say something again.","main_translations_es":["¿Puedes repetir?","¿Podría repetir?","¿Me lo puede repetir?"],"collocations":["Can you repeat that?","Can you repeat the last part?","Can you repeat the instructions?","Can you repeat the question?"],"synonyms_en":["Could you say that again?","Would you repeat that?","Say that again, please."],"example_sentence":"I didn''t hear the boarding gate number. Can you repeat?","example_es":"No escuché el número de la puerta de embarque. ¿Puede repetir?","example_en":"I didn''t hear the boarding gate number. Can you repeat?","mnemonic_en":"Picture a can shouting Can you repeat? to a parrot that answers repetir.","cloze_distractors_en":["Can you sit?","Can you smoke?","Can you pack?","Can you swim?"],"examples":[{"es":"No escuché el número de la puerta de embarque. ¿Puede repetir?","en":"I didn''t hear the boarding gate number. Can you repeat?"},{"es":"La dirección del hotel es muy difícil de entender. ¿Puede repetir?","en":"The hotel address is very difficult to understand. Can you repeat?"},{"es":"Disculpe, no entendí el precio total del boleto. ¿Puede repetir?","en":"Excuse me, I didn''t understand the total ticket price. Can you repeat?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Más despacio, por favor","english_text":"More slowly, please","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A polite request to reduce the speed.","main_translations_es":["Más lento, por favor","Con más lentitud, por favor","Más pausado, por favor"],"collocations":["Could you speak more slowly, please?","Please speak more slowly, please.","Could you explain more slowly, please?"],"synonyms_en":["slow down, please","take it slower","go slower"],"example_sentence":"I''m sorry, I didn''t understand that. More slowly, please.","example_es":"Lo siento, no entendí eso. Más despacio, por favor.","example_en":"I''m sorry, I didn''t understand that. More slowly, please.","mnemonic_en":"A massive pushy robot crawls slower, politely saying please.","cloze_distractors_en":["Straight ahead, please","Round trip, please","First class, please","Window seat, please"],"examples":[{"es":"Lo siento, no entendí eso. Más despacio, por favor.","en":"I''m sorry, I didn''t understand that. More slowly, please."},{"es":"El taxi va demasiado rápido para que yo vea el hotel. Más despacio, por favor.","en":"The taxi is going too fast for me to see the hotel. More slowly, please."},{"es":"Estás hablando demasiado rápido para que yo pueda tomar notas. Más despacio, por favor.","en":"You are speaking too fast for me to take notes. More slowly, please."}]},{"spanish_text":"No entiendo","english_text":"I do not understand","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating lack of comprehension.","main_translations_es":["No comprendo","No lo entiendo","No me queda claro"],"collocations":["I do not understand what you mean","I do not understand the instructions","I do not understand why","I do not understand the concept"],"synonyms_en":["I don''t get it","I''m confused","I don''t follow"],"example_sentence":"The waiter is speaking very fast in English and I do not understand.","example_es":"El camarero está hablando muy rápido en inglés y no entiendo.","example_en":"The waiter is speaking very fast in English and I do not understand.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a person shaking head saying no while saying I do not understand.","cloze_distractors_en":["I do not have luggage","I do not like crowds","I do not want dinner","I do not feel cold"],"examples":[{"es":"El camarero está hablando muy rápido en inglés y no entiendo.","en":"The waiter is speaking very fast in English and I do not understand."},{"es":"El horario del autobús es muy confuso, así que no entiendo.","en":"The bus schedule is very confusing, so I do not understand."},{"es":"Las instrucciones de la máquina son difíciles y no entiendo.","en":"The instructions on the machine are difficult and I do not understand."}]},{"spanish_text":"¿Habla inglés?","english_text":"Do you speak English?","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"question","definition_en":"A question asking whether someone can speak English.","main_translations_es":["¿Hablas inglés?","¿Puede hablar inglés?","¿Puedes hablar inglés?"],"collocations":["speak English fluently","speak English well","speak English with confidence"],"synonyms_en":["Can you speak English?","Do you understand English?"],"example_sentence":"I need help with my luggage, but I do not know how to ask in your language. Do you speak English?","example_es":"Necesito ayuda con mi equipaje, pero no sé cómo pedirla en su idioma. ¿Habla inglés?","example_en":"I need help with my luggage, but I do not know how to ask in your language. Do you speak English?","mnemonic_en":"A talking dog (habla) asks, Do you speak English?","cloze_distractors_en":["Can we park here?","Will those shops open?","Are any rooms free?","Could they call home?"],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito ayuda con mi equipaje, pero no sé cómo pedirla en su idioma. ¿Habla inglés?","en":"I need help with my luggage, but I do not know how to ask in your language. Do you speak English?"},{"es":"Estoy tratando de leer el horario del autobús, pero no está en mi idioma. ¿Habla inglés?","en":"I am trying to read the bus schedule, but it is not in my language. Do you speak English?"},{"es":"No entiendo lo que dice el camarero en este restaurante. ¿Habla inglés?","en":"I do not understand what the waiter is saying in this restaurant. Do you speak English?"}]},{"spanish_text":"¿Dónde puedo comprar agua?","english_text":"Where can I buy water?","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"question","definition_en":"A question asking for the location where water can be purchased.","main_translations_es":["¿Dónde puedo comprar agua?","¿Dónde puedo conseguir agua?","¿Dónde puedo adquirir agua?"],"collocations":["Where can I buy water?","Where can I buy water in the city?","Where can I buy water near me?","Where can I buy water at the store?"],"synonyms_en":["Where can I purchase water?","Where can I get water?","Where can I obtain water?"],"example_sentence":"Excuse me, I am very thirsty before getting on the train, where can I buy water?","example_es":"Disculpe, tengo mucha sed antes de subir al tren, ¿dónde puedo comprar agua?","example_en":"Excuse me, I am very thirsty before getting on the train, where can I buy water?","mnemonic_en":"A mafia don hands you water, so you know where to buy water.","cloze_distractors_en":["When does that bus leave?","Who has my hotel key?","How much does travel cost?","When does this museum open?"],"examples":[{"es":"Disculpe, tengo mucha sed antes de subir al tren, ¿dónde puedo comprar agua?","en":"Excuse me, I am very thirsty before getting on the train, where can I buy water?"},{"es":"Se me acabó la botella mientras caminaba por el parque, ¿dónde puedo comprar agua?","en":"I ran out of bottles while walking through the park, where can I buy water?"},{"es":"El agua del grifo del hotel no es potable, ¿dónde puedo comprar agua?","en":"The hotel tap water is not safe to drink, where can I buy water?"}]},{"spanish_text":"¿Cuánto tarda?","english_text":"How long does it take?","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"question","definition_en":"A question asking for the duration of an event or process.","main_translations_es":["¿Cuánto tiempo tarda?","¿Cuánto tiempo lleva?","¿Cuánto demora?"],"collocations":["How long does it take to finish?","How long does it take to get there?","How long does it take to learn?"],"synonyms_en":["What''s the duration?","How much time?","Time required?"],"example_sentence":"How long does it take? I have a flight in two hours.","example_es":"¿Cuánto tarda? Tengo un vuelo en dos horas.","example_en":"How long does it take? I have a flight in two hours.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a tardy snail asking, How long does it take?","cloze_distractors_en":["Can she speak English well?","Are those children playing now?","Has he called his mother?","Do you enjoy classical music?"],"examples":[{"es":"¿Cuánto tarda? Tengo un vuelo en dos horas.","en":"How long does it take? I have a flight in two hours."},{"es":"Quiero ir caminando al hotel. ¿Cuánto tarda?","en":"I want to walk to the hotel. How long does it take?"},{"es":"El viaje en tren es muy largo. ¿Cuánto tarda?","en":"The train journey is very long. How long does it take?"}]},{"spanish_text":"¿A qué hora sale?","english_text":"What time does it leave?","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"question","definition_en":"A question asking for the time at which something departs.","main_translations_es":["¿A qué hora parte?","¿A qué hora sale el tren?","¿A qué hora sale el autobús?"],"collocations":["I need to know what time does it leave?","Do you know what time does it leave?","Can you tell me what time does it leave?"],"synonyms_en":["When does it depart?","What is the departure time?","When will it leave?"],"example_sentence":"I need to catch the last bus tonight. What time does it leave?","example_es":"Necesito tomar el último autobús de esta noche. ¿A qué hora sale?","example_en":"I need to catch the last bus tonight. What time does it leave?","mnemonic_en":"Picture a clock shouting What time does it leave while a train says a que hora sale","cloze_distractors_en":["How does room service work?","Where can we find horses?","Which room needs my name?","Can we see my balcony?"],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito tomar el último autobús de esta noche. ¿A qué hora sale?","en":"I need to catch the last bus tonight. What time does it leave?"},{"es":"Tengo un billete para el ferry. ¿A qué hora sale?","en":"I have a ticket for the ferry. What time does it leave?"},{"es":"El avión está en la puerta de embarque. ¿A qué hora sale?","en":"The plane is at the gate. What time does it leave?"}]},{"spanish_text":"¿A qué hora llega?","english_text":"What time does it arrive?","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"question","definition_en":"A question asking for the time of arrival.","main_translations_es":["¿A qué hora llega?","¿Cuándo llega?"],"collocations":["What time does it arrive?","What time does it arrive at the station?","What time does it arrive on schedule?"],"synonyms_en":["When does it arrive?","What is the arrival time?","At what time does it arrive?"],"example_sentence":"I am waiting at the station for the train from Barcelona. What time does it arrive?","example_es":"Estoy esperando en la estación el tren de Barcelona. ¿A qué hora llega?","example_en":"I am waiting at the station for the train from Barcelona. What time does it arrive?","mnemonic_en":"Picture a clock shouting What time as a bus pulls up, reminding you of a qué hora llega.","cloze_distractors_en":["Where is the bus stop?","How much is the insurance?","Is the hotel room ready?","What is the street name?"],"examples":[{"es":"Estoy esperando en la estación el tren de Barcelona. ¿A qué hora llega?","en":"I am waiting at the station for the train from Barcelona. What time does it arrive?"},{"es":"Mi vuelo viene de Londres. ¿A qué hora llega?","en":"My flight is coming from London. What time does it arrive?"},{"es":"Acabo de llamar a un taxi para llevarnos al aeropuerto. ¿A qué hora llega?","en":"I just called a taxi to take us to the airport. What time does it arrive?"}]},{"spanish_text":"¿Hay un baño?","english_text":"Is there a bathroom?","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"question","definition_en":"A question asking whether a bathroom is available.","main_translations_es":["¿Dónde está el baño?","¿Hay un baño cerca?","¿Hay un baño en este lugar?"],"collocations":["Is there a bathroom nearby?","Is there a bathroom in this building?","Is there a bathroom on the second floor?","Is there a bathroom in the restaurant?"],"synonyms_en":["Is there a restroom?","Is a bathroom available?","Do you have a washroom?"],"example_sentence":"I need to wash my hands before eating, is there a bathroom in this cafe?","example_es":"Tengo que lavarme las manos antes de comer, ¿hay un baño en este café?","example_en":"I need to wash my hands before eating, is there a bathroom in this cafe?","mnemonic_en":"Hey, a bathroom?","cloze_distractors_en":["Is there a lifeboat?","Is there a mountain?","Is there a campfire?","Is there a motorway?"],"examples":[{"es":"Tengo que lavarme las manos antes de comer, ¿hay un baño en este café?","en":"I need to wash my hands before eating, is there a bathroom in this cafe?"},{"es":"Mi hijo necesita usar el servicio con urgencia, ¿hay un baño en esta tienda?","en":"My son needs to use the toilet urgently, is there a bathroom in this store?"},{"es":"Después de este viaje tan largo en autobús, ¿hay un baño en la terminal?","en":"After this long bus ride, is there a bathroom in the terminal?"}]},{"spanish_text":"¿Puedo pagar con tarjeta?","english_text":"Can I pay by card?","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"question","definition_en":"A question asking if card payment is accepted.","main_translations_es":["¿Se puede pagar con tarjeta?","¿Puedo usar tarjeta para pagar?","¿Puedo pagar con mi tarjeta?"],"collocations":["pay by card","pay with card","pay using a card"],"synonyms_en":["May I use a card?","Is card payment allowed?","Can I pay with a card?"],"example_sentence":"I don''t have any cash for this taxi. Can I pay by card?","example_es":"No tengo efectivo para este taxi. ¿Puedo pagar con tarjeta?","example_en":"I don''t have any cash for this taxi. Can I pay by card?","mnemonic_en":"Picture a car asking, Can I pay by card? while you hand it a tarjeta.","cloze_distractors_en":["How was your trip today?","Does that bus go downtown?","When does our train leave?","What color is your suitcase?"],"examples":[{"es":"No tengo efectivo para este taxi. ¿Puedo pagar con tarjeta?","en":"I don''t have any cash for this taxi. Can I pay by card?"},{"es":"El cajero automático está roto y no tengo efectivo. ¿Puedo pagar con tarjeta?","en":"The ATM is broken and I have no cash. Can I pay by card?"},{"es":"Olvidé mi dinero en el hotel. ¿Puedo pagar con tarjeta?","en":"I forgot my money at the hotel. Can I pay by card?"}]},{"spanish_text":"¿Tiene una habitación libre?","english_text":"Do you have a room available?","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"question","definition_en":"A question asking whether a room is free for use.","main_translations_es":["¿Hay habitaciones disponibles?","¿Tiene habitaciones libres?","¿Tiene alguna habitación libre?"],"collocations":["Do you have a room available for tonight?","Do you have a room available for a short stay?","Do you have a room available for a conference?","Do you have a room available next week?"],"synonyms_en":["Is a room free?","Any rooms open?","Is there a vacancy?"],"example_sentence":"We arrived at the motel after midnight and asked the clerk, ''Do you have a room available?''","example_es":"Llegamos al motel después de medianoche y le preguntamos al recepcionista: ''¿Tiene una habitación libre?''","example_en":"We arrived at the motel after midnight and asked the clerk, ''Do you have a room available?''","mnemonic_en":"Picture a library asking for a free room: Do you have a room available?","cloze_distractors_en":["Is my flight on time today?","Where is the baggage claim area?","Is this the gate for boarding?","Does this bus go to downtown?"],"examples":[{"es":"Llegamos al motel después de medianoche y le preguntamos al recepcionista: ''¿Tiene una habitación libre?''","en":"We arrived at the motel after midnight and asked the clerk, ''Do you have a room available?''"},{"es":"No hice una reserva para esta noche, así que necesito saber: ¿Tiene una habitación libre?","en":"I didn''t make a reservation for tonight, so I need to know: Do you have a room available?"},{"es":"El cartel de afuera dice ''Habitaciones libres'', así que preguntaré: ¿Tiene una habitación libre?","en":"The sign outside says ''Vacancy'', so I''ll ask: Do you have a room available?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Necesito una reserva","english_text":"I need a reservation","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that the speaker requires a booking.","main_translations_es":["Quiero hacer una reserva","Necesito reservar","Me gustaría reservar"],"collocations":["I need a reservation for two","I need a reservation at 7pm","I need a reservation for tonight","I need a reservation for a table"],"synonyms_en":["I require a booking","I would like to book","I want a reservation"],"example_sentence":"The restaurant is fully booked for the weekend, so I need a reservation to get a table.","example_es":"El restaurante está completo para el fin de semana, así que necesito una reserva para conseguir una mesa.","example_en":"The restaurant is fully booked for the weekend, so I need a reservation to get a table.","mnemonic_en":"I need a reservation, picture me yelling ''Necesito una reserva'' to the host.","cloze_distractors_en":["I visit a museum","I write a postcard","I ride a bicycle","I take a photograph"],"examples":[{"es":"El restaurante está completo para el fin de semana, así que necesito una reserva para conseguir una mesa.","en":"The restaurant is fully booked for the weekend, so I need a reservation to get a table."},{"es":"Hola, necesito una reserva para una habitación doble por tres noches.","en":"Hello, I need a reservation for a double room for three nights."},{"es":"Disculpe, necesito una reserva para el vuelo de las ocho a Madrid.","en":"Excuse me, I need a reservation for the eight o''clock flight to Madrid."}]},{"spanish_text":"Estoy de vacaciones","english_text":"I am on vacation","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"I am currently away from work or home for leisure.","main_translations_es":["Estoy de vacaciones","Estoy de descanso"],"collocations":["on vacation","on a vacation","vacation mode","vacation days"],"synonyms_en":["I''m on holiday","I''m taking a break","I''m on leave"],"example_sentence":"I am visiting the city and staying in a hotel because I am on vacation this week.","example_es":"Estoy visitando la ciudad y quedándome en un hotel porque estoy de vacaciones esta semana.","example_en":"I am visiting the city and staying in a hotel because I am on vacation this week.","mnemonic_en":"I lounge on a beach, staying like estoy on vacation.","cloze_distractors_en":["I am at the office","I am at the bank","I am at the library","I am at the dentist"],"examples":[{"es":"Estoy visitando la ciudad y quedándome en un hotel porque estoy de vacaciones esta semana.","en":"I am visiting the city and staying in a hotel because I am on vacation this week."},{"es":"No estoy trabajando esta semana porque estoy de vacaciones.","en":"I am not working this week because I am on vacation."},{"es":"Tengo mi maleta y mi pasaporte porque estoy de vacaciones.","en":"I have my suitcase and my passport because I am on vacation."}]},{"spanish_text":"Viaje de trabajo","english_text":"Business trip","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A trip taken for work purposes.","main_translations_es":["Viaje de negocios","Viaje corporativo"],"collocations":["short business trip","long business trip","business trip expenses","business trip itinerary"],"synonyms_en":["work trip","official travel","corporate travel"],"example_sentence":"The sales manager is going to London on a business trip to sign a new contract.","example_es":"El gerente de ventas va a Londres en un viaje de trabajo para firmar un nuevo contrato.","example_en":"The sales manager is going to London on a business trip to sign a new contract.","mnemonic_en":"A busy bee (biz-ness) flies on a work trip.","cloze_distractors_en":["Travel agency","Airport lounge","Subway station","Passport photo"],"examples":[{"es":"El gerente de ventas va a Londres en un viaje de trabajo para firmar un nuevo contrato.","en":"The sales manager is going to London on a business trip to sign a new contract."},{"es":"Mi empresa pagará mi viaje de trabajo a Chicago.","en":"My company is paying for my business trip to Chicago."},{"es":"Conoceré a los nuevos clientes durante mi viaje de trabajo el próximo mes.","en":"I will meet the new clients during my business trip next month."}]},{"spanish_text":"Mal tiempo","english_text":"Bad weather","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Unfavorable atmospheric conditions.","main_translations_es":["Mal tiempo","Mal clima"],"collocations":["bad weather","bad weather forecast","bad weather conditions","bad weather days"],"synonyms_en":["inclement weather","stormy conditions","adverse weather"],"example_sentence":"The bad weather prevented us from going to the beach.","example_es":"El mal tiempo nos impidió salir a la playa.","example_en":"The bad weather prevented us from going to the beach.","mnemonic_en":"Bad weather is a mal (bad) tempo that drowns the dance floor","cloze_distractors_en":["Front desk","Room key","Train ticket","Hotel lobby"],"examples":[{"es":"El mal tiempo nos impidió salir a la playa.","en":"The bad weather prevented us from going to the beach."},{"es":"La aerolínea canceló nuestro vuelo debido al mal tiempo.","en":"The airline canceled our flight because of the bad weather."},{"es":"Nos quedamos en el hotel todo el día porque el mal tiempo hizo imposible hacer senderismo.","en":"We stayed in the hotel all day because the bad weather made it impossible to hike."}]},{"spanish_text":"Soleado","english_text":"Sunny","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Having or showing a bright, warm, and clear sky.","main_translations_es":["soleado","brillante","radiante"],"collocations":["sunny day","sunny weather","sunny outlook","sunny disposition"],"synonyms_en":["bright","clear","sunlit"],"example_sentence":"Bring your sunglasses because the forecast says it will be sunny at the beach.","example_es":"Trae tus gafas de sol porque el pronóstico dice que estará soleado en la playa.","example_en":"Bring your sunglasses because the forecast says it will be sunny at the beach.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a bright sol shining, making everything sunny.","cloze_distractors_en":["Foggy","Muddy","Rocky","Bumpy"],"examples":[{"es":"Trae tus gafas de sol porque el pronóstico dice que estará soleado en la playa.","en":"Bring your sunglasses because the forecast says it will be sunny at the beach."},{"es":"No necesitamos paraguas hoy porque el cielo está despejado y soleado.","en":"We do not need umbrellas today because the sky is clear and sunny."},{"es":"No olvides tu sombrero porque el recorrido a pie será muy soleado.","en":"Do not forget your hat because the walking tour will be very sunny."}]},{"spanish_text":"Lluvioso","english_text":"Rainy","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"characterized by frequent rain","main_translations_es":["humedecido","mojado","lluvioso"],"collocations":["rainy day","rainy season","rainy weather","rainy forecast"],"synonyms_en":["wet","showery","drizzly"],"example_sentence":"The forecast says the weather will be rainy in London, so bring an umbrella.","example_es":"El pronóstico dice que el clima estará lluvioso en Londres, así que lleva un paraguas.","example_en":"The forecast says the weather will be rainy in London, so bring an umbrella.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a rainy street where each drop whispers lluvia as it falls.","cloze_distractors_en":["Sunny","Clear","Great","Cheap"],"examples":[{"es":"El pronóstico dice que el clima estará lluvioso en Londres, así que lleva un paraguas.","en":"The forecast says the weather will be rainy in London, so bring an umbrella."},{"es":"Conducir por la costa es peligroso cuando el día está lluvioso y hay mucha niebla.","en":"Driving along the coast is dangerous when the day is rainy and very foggy."},{"es":"No pudimos visitar el parque nacional porque el clima estaba muy lluvioso.","en":"We could not visit the national park because the weather was very rainy."}]},{"spanish_text":"Ferry","english_text":"Ferry","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A boat or ship used to carry people or goods across a body of water.","main_translations_es":["ferry","transbordador","barco de ferry"],"collocations":["ferry crossing","ferry service","ferry terminal","ferry ride"],"synonyms_en":[],"example_sentence":"The ferry arrives at 10 in the morning.","example_es":"El ferry llega a las 10 de la mañana.","example_en":"The ferry arrives at 10 in the morning.","mnemonic_en":null,"cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El ferry llega a las 10 de la mañana.","en":"The ferry arrives at 10 in the morning."}]},{"spanish_text":"Barco","english_text":"Boat","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A small vessel used for traveling on water.","main_translations_es":["Nave","Embarcación","Barcaza"],"collocations":["boat trip","boat ride","boat launch"],"synonyms_en":["ship","vessel","craft"],"example_sentence":"The boat sails calmly across the sea.","example_es":"El barco navega tranquilamente por el mar.","example_en":"The boat sails calmly across the sea.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a boat with a big bar of chocolate on deck, like a barco.","cloze_distractors_en":["Train","Hotel","Ticket","Beach"],"examples":[{"es":"El barco navega tranquilamente por el mar.","en":"The boat sails calmly across the sea."},{"es":"Tomamos un barco pequeño para cruzar el río y llegar a la isla.","en":"We take a small boat to cross the river and reach the island."},{"es":"Puedes alquilar un barco para explorar el lago durante las vacaciones.","en":"You can rent a boat to explore the lake during the holidays."}]},{"spanish_text":"Playa","english_text":"Beach","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A sandy area by the sea where people can swim and sunbathe.","main_translations_es":["Costa","Litoral","Ribera"],"collocations":["beach house","beach day","beach front","beach volleyball"],"synonyms_en":["seashore","shoreline","coast"],"example_sentence":"The kids are building a big sandcastle on the beach.","example_es":"Los niños están construyendo un gran castillo de arena en la playa.","example_en":"The kids are building a big sandcastle on the beach.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a beach where every wave whispers \"play-a\" like a Spanish song","cloze_distractors_en":["Train","Plane","Metro","Route"],"examples":[{"es":"Los niños están construyendo un gran castillo de arena en la playa.","en":"The kids are building a big sandcastle on the beach."},{"es":"Encontré muchas conchas marinas hermosas mientras caminaba por la playa.","en":"I found many beautiful seashells while walking along the beach."},{"es":"Puedes alquilar una tabla de surf o un kayak en la playa.","en":"You can rent a surfboard or a kayak at the beach."}]},{"spanish_text":"Montaña","english_text":"Mountain","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A large natural elevation of the earth''s surface, typically rising abruptly and reaching a peak.","main_translations_es":["pico","cerro","montañón"],"collocations":["mountain range","mountain peak","mountain trail","mountain view"],"synonyms_en":["peak","summit","highland"],"example_sentence":"The tour guide says the view from the top of the mountain is incredible.","example_es":"El guía turístico dice que la vista desde la cima de la montaña es increíble.","example_en":"The tour guide says the view from the top of the mountain is incredible.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a massive mount of cheese topped with a Spanish montaña flag soaring like a mountain.","cloze_distractors_en":["Passport","Suitcase","Schedule","Souvenir"],"examples":[{"es":"El guía turístico dice que la vista desde la cima de la montaña es increíble.","en":"The tour guide says the view from the top of the mountain is incredible."},{"es":"Puedes tomar el teleférico para llegar a la cumbre de la montaña.","en":"You can take the cable car to reach the summit of the mountain."},{"es":"Nos alojamos en una pequeña cabaña al pie de la montaña.","en":"We are staying at a small cabin at the foot of the mountain."}]}]'::jsonb) as x(
  spanish_text text, english_text text, section_name text, part_of_speech text, definition_en text,
  main_translations_es jsonb, collocations jsonb, synonyms_en jsonb, example_sentence text, example_es text, example_en text, mnemonic_en text, cloze_distractors_en jsonb, examples jsonb
)
where c.deck_id = dk.id
  and lower(c.spanish_text) = lower(x.spanish_text)
  and lower(c.english_text) = lower(x.english_text);

-- daily-life (107 cards)
update public.decks set
  title = 'Daily Life', description = 'Useful vocabulary for routines, places, and simple actions.',
  language_from = 'es', language_to = 'en'
where slug = 'daily-life';

update public.cards c set
  section_name = x.section_name, part_of_speech = x.part_of_speech, definition_en = x.definition_en,
  main_translations_es = coalesce(x.main_translations_es, '[]'::jsonb),
  collocations = coalesce(x.collocations, '[]'::jsonb),
  synonyms_en = coalesce(x.synonyms_en, '[]'::jsonb),
  example_sentence = x.example_sentence, example_es = x.example_es, example_en = x.example_en,
  mnemonic_en = coalesce(x.mnemonic_en, c.mnemonic_en),
  cloze_distractors_en = case when jsonb_array_length(coalesce(x.cloze_distractors_en, '[]'::jsonb)) > 0
                              then x.cloze_distractors_en else c.cloze_distractors_en end,
  examples = case when jsonb_array_length(coalesce(x.examples, '[]'::jsonb)) > 0
                  then x.examples else c.examples end
from (select id from public.decks where slug = 'daily-life') dk
cross join jsonb_to_recordset('[{"spanish_text":"Trabajo","english_text":"Work","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun / verb","definition_en":"Activity you do to earn money, or the act of doing a job.","main_translations_es":["trabajo","trabajar"],"collocations":["go to work","work hard","work from home"],"synonyms_en":["labor","employment","task"],"example_sentence":"I go to work by bus.","example_es":"Voy al trabajo en autobús.","example_en":"I go to work by bus.","mnemonic_en":null,"cloze_distractors_en":["Sleep","Lunch","Birth","Death"],"examples":[{"es":"Voy al trabajo en autobús.","en":"I go to work by bus."},{"es":"Tengo mucho trabajo que terminar antes de las cinco.","en":"I have a lot of work to finish before five o''clock."},{"es":"Ellos trabajan en una oficina del centro.","en":"They work in an office downtown."}]},{"spanish_text":"Comida","english_text":"Food","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Things that people or animals eat.","main_translations_es":["comida","alimento"],"collocations":["fresh food","food market","food delivery"],"synonyms_en":["nourishment","sustenance","provisions"],"example_sentence":"The food is ready.","example_es":"La comida está lista.","example_en":"The food is ready.","mnemonic_en":null,"cloze_distractors_en":["Gravity","Patience","Distance"],"examples":[{"es":"La comida está lista.","en":"The food is ready."},{"es":"El perro robó la comida de la mesa.","en":"The dog stole the food from the table."},{"es":"Necesitamos comprar más comida para la fiesta de esta noche.","en":"We need to buy more food for tonight''s party."}]},{"spanish_text":"Casa","english_text":"House","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A building where people live, usually with a family.","main_translations_es":["casa","hogar"],"collocations":["house keys","house party","go home to the house"],"synonyms_en":["home","residence","dwelling"],"example_sentence":"My house is nearby.","example_es":"Mi casa está cerca.","example_en":"My house is nearby.","mnemonic_en":null,"cloze_distractors_en":["Bread","Smile","Month"],"examples":[{"es":"Mi casa está cerca.","en":"My house is nearby."},{"es":"Ellos pintaron la casa de color azul.","en":"They painted the house blue."},{"es":"Abrí la puerta de la casa con mis llaves para entrar a descansar.","en":"I unlocked the door of the house with my keys to go inside and rest."}]},{"spanish_text":"Caminar","english_text":"To walk","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To move forward on foot at a regular speed.","main_translations_es":["caminar","andar"],"collocations":["walk home","walk slowly","walk in the park"],"synonyms_en":["stroll","march","step"],"example_sentence":"Since there are no buses available, I have to walk to the train station.","example_es":"Como no hay autobuses disponibles, tengo que caminar hasta la estación de tren.","example_en":"Since there are no buses available, I have to walk to the train station.","mnemonic_en":null,"cloze_distractors_en":["To hungry","To silently","To beneath"],"examples":[{"es":"Como no hay autobuses disponibles, tengo que caminar hasta la estación de tren.","en":"Since there are no buses available, I have to walk to the train station."},{"es":"Es saludable caminar al trabajo todas las mañanas.","en":"It is healthy to walk to work every morning."},{"es":"Decidimos caminar hasta la playa para ver el atardecer.","en":"We decided to walk to the beach to see the sunset."}]},{"spanish_text":"Necesito ayuda","english_text":"I need help","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used when you require support or assistance.","main_translations_es":["necesito ayuda","me hace falta ayuda"],"collocations":["need help with","ask for help","get help"],"synonyms_en":["I require assistance","Help me","I need support"],"example_sentence":"I cannot open this jar, I need help.","example_es":"No puedo abrir este frasco, necesito ayuda.","example_en":"I cannot open this jar, I need help.","mnemonic_en":null,"cloze_distractors_en":["I avoid tasks","I enjoy chores","I finish fast","I prefer sleep"],"examples":[{"es":"No puedo abrir este frasco, necesito ayuda.","en":"I cannot open this jar, I need help."},{"es":"Se me cayó la maleta y necesito ayuda para levantarla.","en":"I dropped my suitcase and I need help lifting it."},{"es":"El coche no arranca y necesito ayuda para empujarlo.","en":"The car won''t start and I need help pushing it."}]},{"spanish_text":"Despertarse","english_text":"Wake up","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to stop sleeping and become awake","main_translations_es":["Levantarse","Despertar","Abrir los ojos"],"collocations":["wake up early","wake up call","wake up to the reality","wake up feeling refreshed"],"synonyms_en":["arise","get up","awaken"],"example_sentence":"I wake up at seven in the morning.","example_es":"Me despierto a las siete de la mañana.","example_en":"I wake up at seven in the morning.","mnemonic_en":"The alarm bell says wake up while a sleepy llama named Despertar yawns.","cloze_distractors_en":["Break up","Shake up","Make up","Take up"],"examples":[{"es":"Me despierto a las siete de la mañana.","en":"I wake up at seven in the morning."},{"es":"Mi perro suele despertarse cuando escucha el ruido de la puerta.","en":"My dog tends to wake up when he hears the noise at the door."},{"es":"Es difícil despertarse temprano durante los fines de semana.","en":"It is difficult to wake up early during the weekends."}]},{"spanish_text":"Ducharse","english_text":"Take a shower","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To wash oneself by standing under a spray of water.","main_translations_es":["Ducharse","Tomar una ducha","Darse una ducha"],"collocations":["take a quick shower","take a hot shower","take a shower in the morning","take a shower after work"],"synonyms_en":["have a shower","shower","wash up"],"example_sentence":"I need to take a shower after the workout.","example_es":"Necesito ducharme después del entrenamiento.","example_en":"I need to take a shower after the workout.","mnemonic_en":"Picture ducks in a bathroom, because ''ducharse'' sounds like ''ducks are'' taking a shower","cloze_distractors_en":["Make a dinner","Drive a tractor","Paint a picture","Solve a puzzle"],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito ducharme después del entrenamiento.","en":"I need to take a shower after the workout."},{"es":"Siempre prefiero ducharme antes de ir a trabajar por la mañana.","en":"I always prefer to take a shower before going to work in the morning."},{"es":"Si tienes calor, puedes ducharme en el baño de invitados.","en":"If you are hot, you can take a shower in the guest bathroom."}]},{"spanish_text":"Desayuno","english_text":"Breakfast","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The first meal of the day, typically eaten in the morning.","main_translations_es":["Desayuno","Comida de la mañana","Almuerzo temprano"],"collocations":["breakfast cereal","breakfast meeting","breakfast buffet","breakfast at the hotel"],"synonyms_en":["morning meal","first meal"],"example_sentence":"I have breakfast at eight every morning.","example_es":"Desayuno a las ocho cada mañana.","example_en":"I have breakfast at eight every morning.","mnemonic_en":"I break fast at sunrise, the day soon starts with a tasty desayuno","cloze_distractors_en":["Midnight","Homework","Sunlight"],"examples":[{"es":"Desayuno a las ocho cada mañana.","en":"I have breakfast at eight every morning."},{"es":"Preparo un desayuno saludable con fruta y yogur.","en":"I prepare a healthy breakfast with fruit and yogurt."},{"es":"El hotel sirve el desayuno en la terraza frente al mar.","en":"The hotel serves breakfast on the terrace facing the sea."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cepillarse los dientes","english_text":"Brush your teeth","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"verb (imperative)","definition_en":"To clean one''s teeth using a toothbrush.","main_translations_es":["Lavarse los dientes","Limpiar los dientes","Hacerse una higiene bucal"],"collocations":["brush your teeth twice a day","brush your teeth before bed","brush your teeth after meals"],"synonyms_en":["clean your teeth","scrub your teeth","polish your teeth"],"example_sentence":"Remember to brush your teeth before going to bed.","example_es":"Recuerda cepillarse los dientes antes de acostarte.","example_en":"Remember to brush your teeth before going to bed.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a sea (cep) of bristles brushing your teeth.","cloze_distractors_en":["Paint your fence","Drive your truck","Build your house","Plant your seeds"],"examples":[{"es":"Recuerda cepillarse los dientes antes de acostarte.","en":"Remember to brush your teeth before going to bed."},{"es":"Después de comer dulces, debes cepillarse los dientes para evitar caries.","en":"After eating candy, you should brush your teeth to avoid cavities."},{"es":"Es importante cepillarse los dientes cada mañana al despertar.","en":"It is important to brush your teeth every morning when you wake up."}]},{"spanish_text":"Vestirse","english_text":"Get dressed","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To put on clothing.","main_translations_es":["ponerse ropa","vestir","ponerse la ropa"],"collocations":["get dressed quickly","get dressed for work","get dressed up","get dressed in"],"synonyms_en":["put on clothes","dress oneself","clothe oneself"],"example_sentence":"Every morning, I hear the alarm and jump out of bed to get dressed before heading to the office.","example_es":"Cada mañana, sueno la alarma y me levanto rápidamente para vestirse antes de ir a la oficina.","example_en":"Every morning, I hear the alarm and jump out of bed to get dressed before heading to the office.","mnemonic_en":"A vest dresses the doll, so remember vestirse means get dressed","cloze_distractors_en":["Get hungry","Get tired","Get lost"],"examples":[{"es":"Cada mañana, sueno la alarma y me levanto rápidamente para vestirse antes de ir a la oficina.","en":"Every morning, I hear the alarm and jump out of bed to get dressed before heading to the office."},{"es":"Los niños aprenden a vestirse solos antes de empezar el jardín de infancia.","en":"Children learn to get dressed by themselves before starting kindergarten."},{"es":"Es necesario vestirse con un traje elegante para asistir a la boda esta tarde.","en":"It is necessary to get dressed in an elegant suit to attend the wedding this afternoon."}]},{"spanish_text":"Salir de casa","english_text":"Leave home","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To go out of one''s house.","main_translations_es":["Irse de casa","Salir del hogar","Abandonar la casa"],"collocations":["leave home early","leave home for college","leave home and never look back","leave home to start a new life"],"synonyms_en":["go out","depart home","exit the house"],"example_sentence":"I have to leave home early tomorrow.","example_es":"Tengo que salir de casa temprano mañana.","example_en":"I have to leave home early tomorrow.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a levitating house as you leave home, linking ''lev'' to ''salir'' and ''home'' to ''casa''.","cloze_distractors_en":["Finish lunch","Borrow money","Repair floor","Ignore alarm"],"examples":[{"es":"Tengo que salir de casa temprano mañana.","en":"I have to leave home early tomorrow."},{"es":"Siempre olvido mis llaves cuando voy a salir de casa.","en":"I always forget my keys when I leave home."},{"es":"Es importante cerrar todas las ventanas antes de salir de casa.","en":"It is important to close all the windows before you leave home."}]},{"spanish_text":"Llegar a tiempo","english_text":"Arrive on time","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To reach a destination at the scheduled or expected time.","main_translations_es":["Llegar puntual","Estar a tiempo","Aparecer a tiempo"],"collocations":["arrive on time for the interview","always arrive on time","make sure to arrive on time","arrive on time and be ready"],"synonyms_en":["be punctual","show up promptly","come on time"],"example_sentence":"It''s important to arrive on time for the interview.","example_es":"Es importante llegar a tiempo a la entrevista.","example_en":"It''s important to arrive on time for the interview.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a bus arriving arriba on time, perfectly punctual like a clock.","cloze_distractors_en":["Sleep during work","Forget your bags","Avoid the crowd"],"examples":[{"es":"Es importante llegar a tiempo a la entrevista.","en":"It''s important to arrive on time for the interview."},{"es":"Si quieres tomar el tren, debes llegar a tiempo a la estación.","en":"If you want to catch the train, you must arrive on time at the station."},{"es":"El profesor siempre nos pide llegar a tiempo a clase.","en":"The teacher always asks us to arrive on time for class."}]},{"spanish_text":"Tarde","english_text":"Late","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"occurring or arriving after the expected or usual time.","main_translations_es":["tarde","tardío","al atardecer"],"collocations":["late night","late arrival","late for work","late in the day"],"synonyms_en":["tardy","overdue","behind schedule"],"example_sentence":"He arrived late to the meeting.","example_es":"Llegó tarde a la reunión.","example_en":"He arrived late to the meeting.","mnemonic_en":"Being tardy feels like saying tarde as you walk in late.","cloze_distractors_en":["Vague","Dense","Stiff","Loose"],"examples":[{"es":"Llegó tarde a la reunión.","en":"He arrived late to the meeting."},{"es":"El tren salió tarde de la estación.","en":"The train departed late from the station."},{"es":"Me desperté tarde y perdí el autobús.","en":"I woke up late and missed the bus."}]},{"spanish_text":"Temprano","english_text":"Early","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"occurring or done before the usual or expected time","main_translations_es":["a primera hora","prontamente","con antelación"],"collocations":["early bird","early morning","early warning","early stage"],"synonyms_en":["ahead of schedule","premature","in advance"],"example_sentence":"He arrived early to the meeting.","example_es":"Llegó temprano a la reunión.","example_en":"He arrived early to the meeting.","mnemonic_en":"The king (el rey) rises early, just like a temprano sunrise.","cloze_distractors_en":["Rarely","Hardly","Nearly"],"examples":[{"es":"Llegó temprano a la reunión.","en":"He arrived early to the meeting."},{"es":"Me gusta despertarme temprano para ver el amanecer.","en":"I like to wake up early to watch the sunrise."},{"es":"El tren sale temprano mañana por la mañana.","en":"The train leaves early tomorrow morning."}]},{"spanish_text":"Almuerzo","english_text":"Lunch","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A meal eaten around midday.","main_translations_es":["Comida","Almuerzo"],"collocations":["have lunch","lunch break","lunch hour"],"synonyms_en":["midday meal","noon meal","afternoon meal"],"example_sentence":"I have lunch at one o''clock in the afternoon.","example_es":"Yo almuerzo a la una de la tarde.","example_en":"I have lunch at one o''clock in the afternoon.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a lunch of almonds on a big table, because almuerzo starts with “alm” like almond.","cloze_distractors_en":["Sleep","Shower","Bridge","Clouds"],"examples":[{"es":"Yo almuerzo a la una de la tarde.","en":"I have lunch at one o''clock in the afternoon."},{"es":"Preparamos un sándwich delicioso para el almuerzo.","en":"We prepared a delicious sandwich for lunch."},{"es":"Mis amigos y yo siempre vamos a la cafetería durante el almuerzo.","en":"My friends and I always go to the cafeteria during lunch."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cena","english_text":"Dinner","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the main meal of the evening","main_translations_es":["Cena","Comida nocturna","Cena familiar"],"collocations":["have dinner","dinner party","dinner reservation","dinner time"],"synonyms_en":["supper","evening meal","main meal"],"example_sentence":"Dinner is ready.","example_es":"La cena está lista.","example_en":"Dinner is ready.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a dinner scene where the family says cena before eating.","cloze_distractors_en":["Pavement","Calendar","Distance"],"examples":[{"es":"La cena está lista.","en":"Dinner is ready."},{"es":"Preparamos una cena deliciosa para celebrar su cumpleaños.","en":"We prepared a delicious dinner to celebrate his birthday."},{"es":"Después de la cena, siempre salimos a caminar por el parque.","en":"After dinner, we always go for a walk in the park."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cocinar","english_text":"Cook","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To prepare food by heating it.","main_translations_es":["Cocinar","Preparar comida","Hacer la comida"],"collocations":["cook dinner","cook up a storm","cook the books","cook something up"],"synonyms_en":["prepare food","make meals","heat"],"example_sentence":"I like to cook Italian dishes on weekends.","example_es":"Me gusta cocinar platos italianos los fines de semana.","example_en":"I like to cook Italian dishes on weekends.","mnemonic_en":"A cook shouts Coco while stirring the pot.","cloze_distractors_en":["Drive","Paint","Build","Clean"],"examples":[{"es":"Me gusta cocinar platos italianos los fines de semana.","en":"I like to cook Italian dishes on weekends."},{"es":"Debes cocinar el pollo durante treinta minutos para que esté listo.","en":"You must cook the chicken for thirty minutes so it is ready."},{"es":"Mi padre va a cocinar una cena especial para nuestro aniversario.","en":"My father is going to cook a special dinner for our anniversary."}]},{"spanish_text":"Limpiar","english_text":"Clean","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To remove dirt or impurities from something.","main_translations_es":["Limpiar","Asear","Higienizar"],"collocations":["clean up","clean house","clean the dishes","clean break"],"synonyms_en":["tidy","sanitize","purify"],"example_sentence":"I will clean the house before the party.","example_es":"Voy a limpiar la casa antes de la fiesta.","example_en":"I will clean the house before the party.","mnemonic_en":"Clean: picture a limp ear being wiped spotless.","cloze_distractors_en":["Construct","Purchase","Celebrate"],"examples":[{"es":"Voy a limpiar la casa antes de la fiesta.","en":"I will clean the house before the party."},{"es":"Debes limpiar tus zapatos después de caminar por el barro.","en":"You must clean your shoes after walking through the mud."},{"es":"Es necesario limpiar la mesa después de cenar.","en":"It is necessary to clean the table after eating dinner."}]},{"spanish_text":"Lavar los platos","english_text":"Wash the dishes","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"verb (imperative)","definition_en":"To clean the dishes by rinsing them with water and soap.","main_translations_es":["Lavar los platos","Fregar los platos","Enjuagar los platos"],"collocations":["I have to wash the dishes","She hates to wash the dishes","We wash the dishes after dinner"],"synonyms_en":["clean the dishes","do the dishes","rinse the dishes"],"example_sentence":"I am going to wash the dishes after dinner.","example_es":"Voy a lavar los platos después de la cena.","example_en":"I am going to wash the dishes after dinner.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a lava river washing the dishes clean.","cloze_distractors_en":["Paint the ceiling","Drive the tractor","Build the chimney","Fold the curtains"],"examples":[{"es":"Voy a lavar los platos después de la cena.","en":"I am going to wash the dishes after dinner."},{"es":"Por favor, ayuda a tu hermano a lavar los platos en la cocina.","en":"Please help your brother to wash the dishes in the kitchen."},{"es":"Es tu turno de lavar los platos porque ayer yo cociné.","en":"It is your turn to wash the dishes because I cooked yesterday."}]},{"spanish_text":"Hacer la cama","english_text":"Make the bed","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To arrange the sheets, blankets, and pillows on a bed after getting up.","main_translations_es":["Arreglar la cama","Poner la cama","Tender la cama"],"collocations":["make the bed every morning","make the bed neatly","make the bed before leaving","make the bed quickly"],"synonyms_en":["tidy the bed","arrange the bedding","straighten the bed"],"example_sentence":"Every morning, my brother always gets up early to make the bed before going to school.","example_es":"Cada mañana, mi hermano siempre se levanta temprano para hacer la cama antes de ir a la escuela.","example_en":"Every morning, my brother always gets up early to make the bed before going to school.","mnemonic_en":"Picture yourself hammering a Spanish cama, turning it into a perfect make‑the‑bed.","cloze_distractors_en":["Cook the floor","Wash the wall","Iron the door","Fold the roof"],"examples":[{"es":"Cada mañana, mi hermano siempre se levanta temprano para hacer la cama antes de ir a la escuela.","en":"Every morning, my brother always gets up early to make the bed before going to school."},{"es":"Después de despertarme, lo primero que hago es hacer la cama para que mi habitación se vea ordenada.","en":"After I wake up, the first thing I do is make the bed so that my room looks tidy."},{"es":"Antes de salir de casa para ir a trabajar, siempre me aseguro de hacer la cama para que la habitación se vea ordenada.","en":"Before I leave the house for work, I always make sure to make the bed so the room looks tidy."}]},{"spanish_text":"Dormitorio","english_text":"Bedroom","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A room used for sleeping.","main_translations_es":["habitación","cuarto","alcoba"],"collocations":["master bedroom","bedroom suite","bedroom furniture","guest bedroom"],"synonyms_en":["sleeping room","bedchamber","sleeping quarters"],"example_sentence":"The bedroom is decorated with soft colors.","example_es":"El dormitorio está decorado con colores suaves.","example_en":"The bedroom is decorated with soft colors.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a dormitory full of beds, just like a bedroom.","cloze_distractors_en":["Notebook","Envelope","Headrest"],"examples":[{"es":"El dormitorio está decorado con colores suaves.","en":"The bedroom is decorated with soft colors."},{"es":"Cansado tras el largo viaje, me acosté en mi dormitorio.","en":"Tired after the long trip, I lay down in my bedroom."},{"es":"Mi hermano pequeño tiene muchos juguetes tirados por todo el dormitorio.","en":"My little brother has many toys scattered all over the bedroom."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cocina","english_text":"Kitchen","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A room or area where food is prepared and cooked.","main_translations_es":["cocina","cocina (habitación)","cocina (arte culinario)"],"collocations":["kitchen sink","kitchen table","kitchen appliances","kitchen remodel"],"synonyms_en":["cooking area","culinary space","cookhouse"],"example_sentence":"The kitchen is freshly painted.","example_es":"La cocina está recién pintada.","example_en":"The kitchen is freshly painted.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a kitchen where a big coconut (coco) is cooking, reminding you of cocina.","cloze_distractors_en":["Envelope","Pavement","Cemetery","Telephone"],"examples":[{"es":"La cocina está recién pintada.","en":"The kitchen is freshly painted."},{"es":"Mi madre prepara la cena en la cocina.","en":"My mother is preparing dinner in the kitchen."},{"es":"Hay un refrigerador grande en la cocina.","en":"There is a large refrigerator in the kitchen."}]},{"spanish_text":"Sala de estar","english_text":"Living room","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A room in a house used for relaxing and entertaining guests.","main_translations_es":["Salón","Sala","Estancia"],"collocations":["living room furniture","living room décor","living room rug","living room layout"],"synonyms_en":["family room","sitting room","lounge"],"example_sentence":"The living room is decorated with a blue sofa.","example_es":"La sala de estar está decorada con un sofá azul.","example_en":"The living room is decorated with a blue sofa.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a lively salsa party in the living room.","cloze_distractors_en":["Swimming pool","Parking garage","Storage closet"],"examples":[{"es":"La sala de estar está decorada con un sofá azul.","en":"The living room is decorated with a blue sofa."},{"es":"Toda la familia se reúne en la sala de estar para ver películas los domingos.","en":"The whole family gathers in the living room to watch movies on Sundays."},{"es":"Dejé mis llaves sobre la mesa de centro de la sala de estar.","en":"I left my keys on the coffee table in the living room."}]},{"spanish_text":"Baño","english_text":"Bathroom","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A room containing a toilet and sink for personal hygiene.","main_translations_es":["baño","servicio","aseo"],"collocations":["bathroom break","bathroom remodel","bathroom scale","bathroom sink"],"synonyms_en":["restroom","washroom","lavatory"],"example_sentence":"After the long road trip, the first thing I looked for at the gas station was the bathroom.","example_es":"Después del largo viaje por carretera, lo primero que busqué en la gasolinera fue el baño.","example_en":"After the long road trip, the first thing I looked for at the gas station was the bathroom.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a bathroom sign that reads baño, reminding you the bath is the bathroom.","cloze_distractors_en":["Morning","Evening","Weekend","Sunshine"],"examples":[{"es":"Después del largo viaje por carretera, lo primero que busqué en la gasolinera fue el baño.","en":"After the long road trip, the first thing I looked for at the gas station was the bathroom."},{"es":"Necesito fregar el baño y poner toallas limpias antes de que lleguen los invitados.","en":"I need to scrub the bathroom and put out fresh towels before the guests arrive."},{"es":"El baño está ocupado, tendrás que esperar un momento.","en":"The bathroom is occupied, you''ll have to wait a moment."}]},{"spanish_text":"Puerta","english_text":"Door","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A movable barrier that provides access to or from a building, room, or vehicle.","main_translations_es":["Puerta","Portón","Entrada"],"collocations":["open the door","door to door","behind closed doors"],"synonyms_en":["entrance","gate","portal"],"example_sentence":"I closed the door before leaving.","example_es":"Cerré la puerta antes de salir.","example_en":"I closed the door before leaving.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a door with a big sign that reads PUERTA.","cloze_distractors_en":["Floor","Cloud","Bread","Sheep"],"examples":[{"es":"Cerré la puerta antes de salir.","en":"I closed the door before leaving."},{"es":"Llamaron a la puerta mientras yo cocinaba.","en":"Someone knocked on the door while I was cooking."},{"es":"Olvidé las llaves dentro y no pude abrir la puerta.","en":"I forgot my keys inside and could not open the door."}]},{"spanish_text":"Ventana","english_text":"Window","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A framed opening in a wall or building that lets in light and air, often fitted with glass.","main_translations_es":["Ventana","Abertura","Ventanal"],"collocations":["window of opportunity","window pane","window seat","window dressing"],"synonyms_en":["opening","casement","pane"],"example_sentence":"The window is open.","example_es":"La ventana está abierta.","example_en":"The window is open.","mnemonic_en":"A vent in the house opens a window, reminding me of the Spanish ventana.","cloze_distractors_en":["Pillow","Staple","Magnet","Handle"],"examples":[{"es":"La ventana está abierta.","en":"The window is open."},{"es":"Cierra la ventana porque hace mucho frío afuera.","en":"Close the window because it is very cold outside."},{"es":"Ella mira a través de la ventana para ver quién llegó.","en":"She looks through the window to see who arrived."}]},{"spanish_text":"Silla","english_text":"Chair","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A piece of furniture with a seat, back, and legs for one person to sit on.","main_translations_es":["asiento","butaca","sillón"],"collocations":["chair the meeting","rocking chair","chairperson","chair of the board"],"synonyms_en":["seat","stool","armchair"],"example_sentence":"The chair is next to the table.","example_es":"La silla está al lado de la mesa.","example_en":"The chair is next to the table.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a giant silla turned into a comfy chair that you share with friends.","cloze_distractors_en":["Cloud","Ocean","Planet"],"examples":[{"es":"La silla está al lado de la mesa.","en":"The chair is next to the table."},{"es":"Me senté en la silla para ponerme los zapatos.","en":"I sat on the chair to put on my shoes."},{"es":"El niño arrastró la silla por toda la cocina.","en":"The boy dragged the chair across the kitchen."}]},{"spanish_text":"Mesa","english_text":"Table","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A piece of furniture with a flat top and legs, used for working, eating, or placing items.","main_translations_es":["mesa","mesa de comedor","mesa de trabajo"],"collocations":["dining table","coffee table","table of contents","periodic table"],"synonyms_en":["desk","counter","workstation"],"example_sentence":"The table is covered with books.","example_es":"La mesa está cubierta de libros.","example_en":"The table is covered with books.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a Spanish mesa holding a dinner table of tacos.","cloze_distractors_en":["Window","Pillow","Carpet","Garden"],"examples":[{"es":"La mesa está cubierta de libros.","en":"The table is covered with books."},{"es":"Pon los platos sucios sobre la mesa después de cenar.","en":"Put the dirty dishes on the table after dinner."},{"es":"Limpiamos la mesa con un paño húmedo antes de comer.","en":"We clean the table with a damp cloth before eating."}]},{"spanish_text":"Llaves","english_text":"Keys","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Objects used to open locks or to operate a keyboard.","main_translations_es":["Llaves","Claves","Llaves de casa"],"collocations":["key to success","turn the key","key player","key issue"],"synonyms_en":["key","unlocking devices","access tools"],"example_sentence":"I can''t find my keys, have you seen them?","example_es":"No encuentro mis llaves, ¿las has visto?","example_en":"I can''t find my keys, have you seen them?","mnemonic_en":"She jingles the keys, tiny llaves, unlocking a bright treasure chest.","cloze_distractors_en":["Clouds","Dreams","Smiles"],"examples":[{"es":"No encuentro mis llaves, ¿las has visto?","en":"I can''t find my keys, have you seen them?"},{"es":"Deja las llaves sobre la mesa cuando entres a casa.","en":"Leave the keys on the table when you come home."},{"es":"Necesito un duplicado de las llaves para entrar al apartamento.","en":"I need a spare set of keys to enter the apartment."}]},{"spanish_text":"Teléfono","english_text":"Phone","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A device used for voice communication over distances.","main_translations_es":["celular","móvil","teléfono móvil"],"collocations":["phone call","phone number","phone charger","phone book"],"synonyms_en":["telephone","cellphone","mobile"],"example_sentence":"The phone is ringing on the table, can you answer it?","example_es":"El teléfono está sonando en la mesa, ¿puedes contestar?","example_en":"The phone is ringing on the table, can you answer it?","mnemonic_en":"Picture a phone morphing into a huge teléfono with a bright pho label.","cloze_distractors_en":["Wall","Door","Floor","Window"],"examples":[{"es":"El teléfono está sonando en la mesa, ¿puedes contestar?","en":"The phone is ringing on the table, can you answer it?"},{"es":"Mi teléfono no tiene batería, necesito cargarlo.","en":"My phone has no battery, I need to charge it."},{"es":"Necesito llamar a mi mamá, pero no encuentro mi teléfono en ningún lado de la casa.","en":"I need to call my mom, but I can''t find my phone anywhere in the house."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cargador","english_text":"Charger","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A device used to replenish the electrical power of a battery or other rechargeable device.","main_translations_es":["cargador","cargador de teléfono","cargador portátil"],"collocations":["phone charger","car charger","fast charger","USB charger"],"synonyms_en":["power adapter","battery pack","charging device"],"example_sentence":"Where is my phone''s charger?","example_es":"¿Dónde está el cargador de mi teléfono?","example_en":"Where is my phone''s charger?","mnemonic_en":"Picture a charger loading a car, because charger sounds like Spanish cargar, to load.","cloze_distractors_en":["Blanket","Wallet","Ticket","Towel"],"examples":[{"es":"¿Dónde está el cargador de mi teléfono?","en":"Where is my phone''s charger?"},{"es":"Necesito el cargador porque mi teléfono solo tiene cinco por ciento de batería.","en":"I need the charger because my phone only has five percent battery left."},{"es":"Mi batería está por agotarse, ¿puedo tomar prestado tu cargador?","en":"My battery is about to die, can I borrow your charger?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Ropa","english_text":"Clothes","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Items worn to cover the body.","main_translations_es":["vestimenta","indumentaria","prendas"],"collocations":["change of clothes","clothes line","clothes rack","clothes store"],"synonyms_en":["apparel","garments","attire"],"example_sentence":"I bought new clothes for the trip.","example_es":"Compré ropa nueva para el viaje.","example_en":"I bought new clothes for the trip.","mnemonic_en":"I close the wardrobe door and pull out my bright ropa, the clothes I love.","cloze_distractors_en":["Furniture","Hardware","Software"],"examples":[{"es":"Compré ropa nueva para el viaje.","en":"I bought new clothes for the trip."},{"es":"Tengo que lavar toda la ropa sucia este fin de semana.","en":"I have to wash all the dirty clothes this weekend."},{"es":"Ella guarda su ropa en el armario después de plancharla.","en":"She puts her clothes in the closet after ironing them."}]},{"spanish_text":"Zapatos","english_text":"Shoes","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Footwear that covers and protects the feet, typically consisting of a sole and a heel.","main_translations_es":["Zapatos","Calzado"],"collocations":["shoes off","shoes on","shoes for sale"],"synonyms_en":["footwear","kicks","trainers"],"example_sentence":"I bought new shoes for the wedding.","example_es":"Me compré unos zapatos nuevos para la boda.","example_en":"I bought new shoes for the wedding.","mnemonic_en":"I zap my toes with shiny new shoes.","cloze_distractors_en":["Clouds","Stairs","Dreams"],"examples":[{"es":"Me compré unos zapatos nuevos para la boda.","en":"I bought new shoes for the wedding."},{"es":"Antes de entrar a la casa, siempre me quito los zapatos.","en":"Before entering the house, I always take off my shoes."},{"es":"Mis pies me duelen porque estos zapatos son muy pequeños.","en":"My feet hurt because these shoes are too small."}]},{"spanish_text":"Calcetines","english_text":"Socks","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A piece of clothing worn on the feet, usually covering the ankle and sometimes extending up the leg.","main_translations_es":["calcetines","medias","calcetas"],"collocations":["pair of socks","sock drawer","warm socks","sock hop"],"synonyms_en":["stockings","hosiery"],"example_sentence":"My socks are wet after the rain.","example_es":"Mis calcetines están mojados después de la lluvia.","example_en":"My socks are wet after the rain.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a sock hugging a calf—calcetín—so you remember socks.","cloze_distractors_en":["Carpets","Pillows","Curtains","Blankets"],"examples":[{"es":"Mis calcetines están mojados después de la lluvia.","en":"My socks are wet after the rain."},{"es":"No encuentro el par de calcetines que combina con mis zapatos.","en":"I cannot find the pair of socks that matches my shoes."},{"es":"Debes ponerte calcetines antes de usar tus botas nuevas.","en":"You must put on socks before wearing your new boots."}]},{"spanish_text":"Lavadora","english_text":"Washing machine","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A household appliance used to wash laundry.","main_translations_es":["lavadora","máquina de lavar ropa","máquina de lavado"],"collocations":["run the washing machine","load the washing machine","wash clothes in the washing machine","washing machine cycle"],"synonyms_en":["laundry machine","clothes washer","washer"],"example_sentence":"I bought a new washing machine because the old one broke.","example_es":"Compré una lavadora nueva porque la anterior se rompió.","example_en":"I bought a new washing machine because the old one broke.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a lava flow spilling into a giant washing machine, turning the lava into clean clothes.","cloze_distractors_en":["Kitchen ceiling","Garage window","Frontal balcony"],"examples":[{"es":"Compré una lavadora nueva porque la anterior se rompió.","en":"I bought a new washing machine because the old one broke."},{"es":"Tengo que sacar la ropa mojada de la lavadora para tenderla.","en":"I need to take the wet clothes out of the washing machine to hang them up."},{"es":"Pon el detergente en el compartimento de la lavadora antes de iniciar el ciclo.","en":"Put the detergent in the compartment of the washing machine before starting the cycle."}]},{"spanish_text":"Toalla","english_text":"Towel","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A piece of absorbent fabric used for drying or wiping something.","main_translations_es":["toalla","pañuelo","paño"],"collocations":["hand towel","bath towel","towel rack"],"synonyms_en":["drying cloth","washcloth","hand towel"],"example_sentence":"I dried my hands with a towel.","example_es":"Me sequé las manos con una toalla.","example_en":"I dried my hands with a towel.","mnemonic_en":"Visualize a bright towel embroidered with TOALLA, soaking up water on the beach.","cloze_distractors_en":["Sponge","Faucet","Mirror","Pillow"],"examples":[{"es":"Me sequé las manos con una toalla.","en":"I dried my hands with a towel."},{"es":"Colgué la toalla mojada en el baño para que se secara.","en":"I hung the wet towel in the bathroom to dry."},{"es":"Necesito una toalla limpia para salir de la ducha.","en":"I need a clean towel to get out of the shower."}]},{"spanish_text":"Jabón","english_text":"Soap","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A cleansing substance, usually a solid or liquid, used for washing and removing dirt and oils.","main_translations_es":["jabón","sabonete","jaboncillo"],"collocations":["soap opera","hand soap","soap suds","soap bar"],"synonyms_en":["detergent","cleanser","washing bar"],"example_sentence":"I bought soap to wash my hands.","example_es":"Compré jabón para lavar mis manos.","example_en":"I bought soap to wash my hands.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a soap bar shouting ja‑bone while scrubbing away dirt.","cloze_distractors_en":["Sand","Salt","Soup","Dust"],"examples":[{"es":"Compré jabón para lavar mis manos.","en":"I bought soap to wash my hands."},{"es":"Necesito más jabón porque la barra se está haciendo muy pequeña en la ducha.","en":"I need more soap because the bar is getting very small in the shower."},{"es":"El aroma del jabón dejó un olor fresco en toda la cocina después de limpiar los platos.","en":"The scent of the soap left a fresh smell throughout the kitchen after cleaning the dishes."}]},{"spanish_text":"Champú","english_text":"Shampoo","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A liquid soap used for cleaning hair.","main_translations_es":["champú","shampoo","gel para el cabello"],"collocations":["shampoo and conditioner","anti-dandruff shampoo","wash your hair with shampoo"],"synonyms_en":["hair cleanser","hair wash","cleansing shampoo"],"example_sentence":"I bought a shampoo that makes the hair very soft.","example_es":"Compré un champú que deja el cabello muy suave.","example_en":"I bought a shampoo that makes the hair very soft.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a sham poo being scrubbed with shampoo, linking Champú to the clean hair.","cloze_distractors_en":["Toothpaste","Detergent","Mouthwash","Sunscreen"],"examples":[{"es":"Compré un champú que deja el cabello muy suave.","en":"I bought a shampoo that makes the hair very soft."},{"es":"Se me terminó el champú mientras me estaba duchando.","en":"I ran out of shampoo while I was taking a shower."},{"es":"Necesito ir al supermercado a buscar más champú para lavarme la cabeza.","en":"I need to go to the supermarket to get more shampoo to wash my hair."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cepillo","english_text":"Brush","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A tool with bristles used for cleaning, grooming, or applying substances.","main_translations_es":["cepillo","cepillado","cepilladora"],"collocations":["brush teeth","brush hair","paint brush","brush up"],"synonyms_en":["scrub","broom","paintbrush"],"example_sentence":"I need a brush to comb my hair.","example_es":"Necesito un cepillo para peinar mi cabello.","example_en":"I need a brush to comb my hair.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a soft pillow named sep that you use as a hair brush.","cloze_distractors_en":["Fridge","Pillow","Ladder","Wallet"],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito un cepillo para peinar mi cabello.","en":"I need a brush to comb my hair."},{"es":"Usa el cepillo para limpiar el barro de tus botas.","en":"Use the brush to clean the mud off your boots."},{"es":"Ella compró un cepillo nuevo para lavar los platos.","en":"She bought a new brush to wash the dishes."}]},{"spanish_text":"Mercado","english_text":"Market","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A place or system where goods and services are bought and sold.","main_translations_es":["mercado","mercadillo","tianguis"],"collocations":["stock market","farmers market","open market","market share"],"synonyms_en":["bazaar","exchange","mart"],"example_sentence":"I go to the market every Saturday to buy fresh fruit.","example_es":"Voy al mercado cada sábado para comprar frutas frescas.","example_en":"I go to the market every Saturday to buy fresh fruit.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a bustling market where vendors shout ''Mercado'' while selling goods.","cloze_distractors_en":["Library","Airport","Kitchen","Factory"],"examples":[{"es":"Voy al mercado cada sábado para comprar frutas frescas.","en":"I go to the market every Saturday to buy fresh fruit."},{"es":"Los agricultores venden sus verduras recién cosechadas en el mercado del pueblo.","en":"The farmers sell their freshly harvested vegetables at the town market."},{"es":"Hay mucha gente buscando ofertas en el mercado durante la mañana.","en":"There are many people looking for deals at the market during the morning."}]},{"spanish_text":"Tienda","english_text":"Store","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A place where goods are sold to the public.","main_translations_es":["Almacén","Boutique","Negocio"],"collocations":["store manager","store front","online store","store hours"],"synonyms_en":["shop","boutique","outlet"],"example_sentence":"I am going to the store to buy bread.","example_es":"Voy a la tienda a comprar pan.","example_en":"I am going to the store to buy bread.","mnemonic_en":"I store my snacks in a tiny tienda chest.","cloze_distractors_en":["Street","Bridge","Stair","Cloud"],"examples":[{"es":"Voy a la tienda a comprar pan.","en":"I am going to the store to buy bread."},{"es":"Ella trabaja en una tienda de ropa en el centro.","en":"She works at a clothing store downtown."},{"es":"El dueño cerró la tienda porque ya era muy tarde.","en":"The owner closed the store because it was very late."}]},{"spanish_text":"Supermercado","english_text":"Supermarket","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A large self-service store that sells a wide variety of food and household items.","main_translations_es":["tienda de comestibles","hipermercado","tienda de abarrotes"],"collocations":["supermarket aisle","supermarket chain","supermarket checkout","supermarket shopping"],"synonyms_en":["grocery store","food market","grocery"],"example_sentence":"I go to the supermarket to buy fruit.","example_es":"Voy al supermercado para comprar frutas.","example_en":"I go to the supermarket to buy fruit.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a super market with a big sign reading Supermercado.","cloze_distractors_en":["Playground","Apartment","Waterfall","Telephone"],"examples":[{"es":"Voy al supermercado para comprar frutas.","en":"I go to the supermarket to buy fruit."},{"es":"Olvidé comprar leche en el supermercado.","en":"I forgot to buy milk at the supermarket."},{"es":"El supermercado está cerrado los domingos por la noche.","en":"The supermarket is closed on Sunday nights."}]},{"spanish_text":"Lista de compras","english_text":"Shopping list","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A written or printed list of items to be bought.","main_translations_es":["Lista de la compra","Lista de compras","Lista de artículos"],"collocations":["make a shopping list","add to the shopping list","check off the shopping list","cross off items from the shopping list"],"synonyms_en":["grocery list","purchase list","buying list"],"example_sentence":"I''m going to prepare the shopping list before going to the supermarket.","example_es":"Voy a preparar la lista de compras antes de ir al supermercado.","example_en":"I''m going to prepare the shopping list before going to the supermarket.","mnemonic_en":"I see a grocery list, a ''lista'' of shopping items pinned on the fridge.","cloze_distractors_en":["Parking ticket","Cooking lesson","Building permit","Working schedule"],"examples":[{"es":"Voy a preparar la lista de compras antes de ir al supermercado.","en":"I''m going to prepare the shopping list before going to the supermarket."},{"es":"Se me olvidó la lista de compras en la mesa de la cocina.","en":"I forgot the shopping list on the kitchen table."},{"es":"Mi esposo anotó todo lo que necesitamos en la lista de compras.","en":"My husband wrote down everything we need on the shopping list."}]},{"spanish_text":"Carrito","english_text":"Cart","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A small wheeled vehicle used for carrying goods, often pulled by a person or animal.","main_translations_es":["Carro","Coche","Carrito de compras"],"collocations":["shopping cart","cartwheel","pushcart","cart load"],"synonyms_en":["trolley","shopping cart","wagon"],"example_sentence":"I bought a cart to carry my groceries to the market.","example_es":"Compré un carrito para llevar mis compras al mercado.","example_en":"I bought a cart to carry my groceries to the market.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a tiny cart rolling like a little car carrito in a grocery aisle.","cloze_distractors_en":["Shelf","Floor","Scale","Badge"],"examples":[{"es":"Compré un carrito para llevar mis compras al mercado.","en":"I bought a cart to carry my groceries to the market."},{"es":"Puse todas mis compras en el carrito antes de pasar por la caja.","en":"I put all my groceries in the cart before going through the checkout line."},{"es":"Dejé mi carrito en la entrada mientras buscaba frutas frescas.","en":"I left my cart at the entrance while I looked for fresh fruit."}]},{"spanish_text":"Caja","english_text":"Checkout counter","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A checkout counter is a place in a store where customers pay for their purchases.","main_translations_es":["caja registradora","mostrador de pago","caja de pago"],"collocations":["at the checkout counter","checkout counter staff","checkout counter line","checkout counter area"],"synonyms_en":["cash register","checkout desk","payment counter"],"example_sentence":"I''m going to the checkout counter to pay for my purchases.","example_es":"Voy a la caja para pagar mis compras.","example_en":"I''m going to the checkout counter to pay for my purchases.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a cashier at the checkout counter shouting caja while scanning groceries","cloze_distractors_en":["Parking garage","Changing room","Shopping trolley"],"examples":[{"es":"Voy a la caja para pagar mis compras.","en":"I''m going to the checkout counter to pay for my purchases."},{"es":"El cliente dejó su tarjeta de crédito olvidada en la caja.","en":"The customer left his credit card behind at the checkout counter."},{"es":"Hay una fila muy larga esperando frente a la caja.","en":"There is a very long line waiting in front of the checkout counter."}]},{"spanish_text":"Efectivo","english_text":"Cash","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Money in the form of bills and coins that is used for transactions.","main_translations_es":["Dinero en efectivo","Efectivo","Plata"],"collocations":["cash flow","cash register","cash payment","cash on hand"],"synonyms_en":["money","currency","hard cash"],"example_sentence":"I prefer to pay in cash.","example_es":"Prefiero pagar en efectivo.","example_en":"I prefer to pay in cash.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a cash register flashing the word Efectivo on its screen.","cloze_distractors_en":["Debt","Loan","Cost","Sale"],"examples":[{"es":"Prefiero pagar en efectivo.","en":"I prefer to pay in cash."},{"es":"El cajero no acepta tarjetas, solo efectivo.","en":"The cashier does not accept cards, only cash."},{"es":"Saqué algo de efectivo del cajero automático para el mercado.","en":"I withdrew some cash from the ATM for the market."}]},{"spanish_text":"Tarjeta de crédito","english_text":"Credit card","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A plastic or digital card issued by a financial institution that lets the holder borrow money to make purchases.","main_translations_es":["Tarjeta de crédito","Tarjeta bancaria","Tarjeta de pago"],"collocations":["apply for a credit card","credit card debt","credit card statement","credit card limit"],"synonyms_en":["charge card","payment card","plastic money"],"example_sentence":"I need to apply for a new credit card for my online purchases.","example_es":"Necesito solicitar una nueva tarjeta de crédito para mis compras en línea.","example_en":"I need to apply for a new credit card for my online purchases.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a credit card stamped with the word tarjeta, so credit equals tarjeta.","cloze_distractors_en":["Grocery list","Library card","Parking spot","Coffee maker"],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito solicitar una nueva tarjeta de crédito para mis compras en línea.","en":"I need to apply for a new credit card for my online purchases."},{"es":"El camarero me pidió mi tarjeta de crédito para pagar la cuenta del restaurante.","en":"The waiter asked for my credit card to pay the restaurant bill."},{"es":"Olvidé mi tarjeta de crédito en casa y no pude comprar el regalo.","en":"I left my credit card at home and could not buy the gift."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cambio","english_text":"Change","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the act or result of making something different; a transformation or alteration","main_translations_es":["Modificación","Alteración","Variación"],"collocations":["make a change","change of pace","change your mind","change the subject"],"synonyms_en":["alteration","modification","shift"],"example_sentence":"I need a career change.","example_es":"Necesito un cambio de carrera.","example_en":"I need a career change.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a cashier handing over a cambio of coins, instantly creating a fresh change.","cloze_distractors_en":["Stance","Charge","Range","Pledge"],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito un cambio de carrera.","en":"I need a career change."},{"es":"El cajero me dio el cambio incorrecto.","en":"The cashier gave me the wrong change."},{"es":"El clima tuvo un cambio repentino hoy.","en":"The weather had a sudden change today."}]},{"spanish_text":"Recibo","english_text":"Receipt","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A written acknowledgment that something has been received, often confirming a payment.","main_translations_es":["Comprobante","Factura","Ticket"],"collocations":["receipt of payment","receipt number","receipt printer","receipt confirmation"],"synonyms_en":["proof of purchase","sales slip","transaction record"],"example_sentence":"The receipt from the purchase is on the table.","example_es":"El recibo de la compra está sobre la mesa.","example_en":"The receipt from the purchase is on the table.","mnemonic_en":"I keep a receipt (recibo) in my wallet as proof.","cloze_distractors_en":["Recipe","Registry","Recipient","Receptacle"],"examples":[{"es":"El recibo de la compra está sobre la mesa.","en":"The receipt from the purchase is on the table."},{"es":"Guarda el recibo por si necesitas devolver los zapatos.","en":"Keep the receipt in case you need to return the shoes."},{"es":"El cajero me entregó el recibo después de pagar el café.","en":"The cashier handed me the receipt after I paid for the coffee."}]},{"spanish_text":"Barato","english_text":"Cheap","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Low in price; inexpensive.","main_translations_es":["Económico","Asequible","Baratillo"],"collocations":["cheap and cheerful","cheap as chips","cheap thrill","cheap shot"],"synonyms_en":["inexpensive","low-cost","budget"],"example_sentence":"This restaurant is very cheap.","example_es":"Este restaurante es muy barato.","example_en":"This restaurant is very cheap.","mnemonic_en":"A cheep bird perched on a cheap sign shouts Barato.","cloze_distractors_en":["Vertical","Polite","Frequent","Sincere"],"examples":[{"es":"Este restaurante es muy barato.","en":"This restaurant is very cheap."},{"es":"Compré unos zapatos baratos en la tienda de la esquina.","en":"I bought some cheap shoes at the corner store."},{"es":"El billete de autobús es barato si lo compras con antelación.","en":"The bus ticket is cheap if you buy it in advance."}]},{"spanish_text":"Caro","english_text":"Expensive","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Costing a lot of money; having a high price.","main_translations_es":["Costoso","Elevado","Carísimo"],"collocations":["expensive taste","expensive purchase","expensive item","expensive price"],"synonyms_en":["costly","pricey","high-priced"],"example_sentence":"That car is very expensive.","example_es":"Ese coche es muy caro.","example_en":"That car is very expensive.","mnemonic_en":"A shiny car named Caro costs an expensive price.","cloze_distractors_en":["Frequent","Vertical","Invisible"],"examples":[{"es":"Ese coche es muy caro.","en":"That car is very expensive."},{"es":"No puedo comprar este reloj porque es demasiado caro.","en":"I cannot buy this watch because it is too expensive."},{"es":"El menú de este restaurante es muy caro para nosotros.","en":"The menu at this restaurant is very expensive for us."}]},{"spanish_text":"Oferta","english_text":"Sale","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A transaction in which goods or services are sold, often at a reduced price.","main_translations_es":["Descuento","Promoción","Rebaja"],"collocations":["on sale","sale price","sale event","sale season"],"synonyms_en":["discount","bargain","clearance"],"example_sentence":"Take advantage of the 50% off sale at the store.","example_es":"Aprovecha la oferta de 50% de descuento en la tienda.","example_en":"Take advantage of the 50% off sale at the store.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a SALE banner with a loud Oferta shouted by a street vendor.","cloze_distractors_en":["Debt","Goal","Task","Gain"],"examples":[{"es":"Aprovecha la oferta de 50% de descuento en la tienda.","en":"Take advantage of the 50% off sale at the store."},{"es":"Compré este televisor porque estaba en oferta.","en":"I bought this television because it was on sale."},{"es":"Revisa el periódico para ver si hay alguna oferta en el supermercado.","en":"Check the newspaper to see if there is a sale at the supermarket."}]},{"spanish_text":"Abierto","english_text":"Open","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Not closed or blocked, allowing access or passage.","main_translations_es":["Desplegado","Libre","Sin cerrar"],"collocations":["open the door","open a book","open to suggestions"],"synonyms_en":["unlocked","unsealed","available"],"example_sentence":"The restaurant is open.","example_es":"El restaurante está abierto.","example_en":"The restaurant is open.","mnemonic_en":"Open the door and hear a crowd shout abierto as the light spills in","cloze_distractors_en":["Hungry","Furious","Broken"],"examples":[{"es":"El restaurante está abierto.","en":"The restaurant is open."},{"es":"Por favor, deja la ventana abierta para que entre aire fresco.","en":"Please leave the window open so fresh air can come in."},{"es":"La tienda de regalos siempre está abierta los fines de semana.","en":"The gift shop is always open on the weekends."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cerrado","english_text":"Closed","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Not open; shut.","main_translations_es":["Clausurado","Bloqueado","Sellado"],"collocations":["closed door","closed account","closed caption","closed meeting"],"synonyms_en":["shut","sealed","locked"],"example_sentence":"The restaurant is closed.","example_es":"El restaurante está cerrado.","example_en":"The restaurant is closed.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a closed door stamped with the word cerrado","cloze_distractors_en":["Hungry","Tired","Polite"],"examples":[{"es":"El restaurante está cerrado.","en":"The restaurant is closed."},{"es":"La tienda de ropa permanece cerrada los domingos.","en":"The clothing store remains closed on Sundays."},{"es":"Por favor, asegúrate de que la puerta principal esté cerrada al salir.","en":"Please make sure the front door is closed when you leave."}]},{"spanish_text":"Oficina","english_text":"Office","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A room or set of rooms where people work, especially in a business or organization.","main_translations_es":["Despacho","Establecimiento","Local"],"collocations":["office hours","home office","office space","office manager"],"synonyms_en":["workplace","bureau","workroom"],"example_sentence":"I work in an office downtown.","example_es":"Trabajo en una oficina en el centro de la ciudad.","example_en":"I work in an office downtown.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a busy office where every file is stamped with the word oficina.","cloze_distractors_en":["Sidewalk","Backpack","Notebook","Envelope"],"examples":[{"es":"Trabajo en una oficina en el centro de la ciudad.","en":"I work in an office downtown."},{"es":"Dejé mis llaves olvidadas sobre el escritorio de la oficina.","en":"I left my keys on the desk at the office."},{"es":"Mi jefe me llamó para una reunión urgente en su oficina.","en":"My boss called me for an urgent meeting in his office."}]},{"spanish_text":"Reunión","english_text":"Meeting","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A gathering of people for discussion or decision-making.","main_translations_es":["Junta","Encuentro","Asamblea"],"collocations":["team meeting","board meeting","meeting minutes","meeting agenda"],"synonyms_en":["gathering","assembly","session"],"example_sentence":"The meeting will start at ten o''clock in the morning.","example_es":"La reunión comenzará a las diez de la mañana.","example_en":"The meeting will start at ten o''clock in the morning.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a meat‑ing where everyone reunites around a grill.","cloze_distractors_en":["Furniture","Pavement","Envelope"],"examples":[{"es":"La reunión comenzará a las diez de la mañana.","en":"The meeting will start at ten o''clock in the morning."},{"es":"Tengo una reunión importante con mi jefe en la oficina.","en":"I have an important meeting with my boss at the office."},{"es":"Por favor, no interrumpas la reunión mientras estamos hablando.","en":"Please do not interrupt the meeting while we are talking."}]},{"spanish_text":"Compañero","english_text":"Coworker","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person who works together with someone else in the same organization or on the same project.","main_translations_es":["Colega","Compañero de trabajo","Compañero laboral"],"collocations":["my coworker","a coworker of mine","work with a coworker","coworker relationship"],"synonyms_en":["colleague","workmate","associate"],"example_sentence":"My coworker helped me finish the report.","example_es":"Mi compañero de trabajo me ayudó a terminar el informe.","example_en":"My coworker helped me finish the report.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a cow at a desk working with your compañero, the friendly coworker.","cloze_distractors_en":["Furniture","Landscape","Vegetable","Algorithm"],"examples":[{"es":"Mi compañero de trabajo me ayudó a terminar el informe.","en":"My coworker helped me finish the report."},{"es":"Voy a almorzar con mi compañero en la cafetería de la oficina.","en":"I am going to have lunch with my coworker at the office cafeteria."},{"es":"Le pedí a mi compañero que revisara los correos electrónicos antes de enviarlos.","en":"I asked my coworker to check the emails before sending them."}]},{"spanish_text":"Jefe","english_text":"Boss","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person who is in charge of others, especially at work.","main_translations_es":["Jefe","Patrón","Superior"],"collocations":["the boss is coming","call the boss","boss level","boss around"],"synonyms_en":["supervisor","manager","chief"],"example_sentence":"My boss gave me a raise last week.","example_es":"Mi jefe me dio un aumento la semana pasada.","example_en":"My boss gave me a raise last week.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine the jefe wearing a boss crown, shouting BOSS like a real boss.","cloze_distractors_en":["Guest","Shelf","Lunch","Clock"],"examples":[{"es":"Mi jefe me dio un aumento la semana pasada.","en":"My boss gave me a raise last week."},{"es":"El jefe revisó mi informe antes de la reunión importante.","en":"The boss reviewed my report before the important meeting."},{"es":"Mañana tengo una entrevista con mi nuevo jefe en la oficina.","en":"Tomorrow I have an interview with my new boss at the office."}]},{"spanish_text":"Clase","english_text":"Class","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A group of students who are taught together, or a category of objects or ideas that share common characteristics.","main_translations_es":["Categoría","Tipo","Grupo"],"collocations":["class schedule","first class","classroom","class action"],"synonyms_en":["category","lesson","group"],"example_sentence":"The class is cancelled today.","example_es":"La clase está cancelada hoy.","example_en":"The class is cancelled today.","mnemonic_en":"I picture a teacher ringing a bell for each class, shouting Clase to start the lesson.","cloze_distractors_en":["Street","Clock","Floor","Cloud"],"examples":[{"es":"La clase está cancelada hoy.","en":"The class is cancelled today."},{"es":"Llegué tarde a mi primera clase de la mañana.","en":"I arrived late to my first class of the morning."},{"es":"El profesor terminó la clase antes de tiempo.","en":"The teacher finished the class ahead of schedule."}]},{"spanish_text":"Tarea","english_text":"Homework","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"School assignments given to be completed outside of class.","main_translations_es":["deber","trabajo","encargo"],"collocations":["do homework","homework assignment","homework help","homework deadline"],"synonyms_en":["assignment","schoolwork","task"],"example_sentence":"I have to finish my homework before dinner.","example_es":"Tengo que terminar mi tarea antes de la cena.","example_en":"I have to finish my homework before dinner.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a house (home) with a big ''tarea'' sign on the door—homework.","cloze_distractors_en":["Breakfast","Furniture","Vacation"],"examples":[{"es":"Tengo que terminar mi tarea antes de la cena.","en":"I have to finish my homework before dinner."},{"es":"El profesor asignó mucha tarea para el fin de semana.","en":"The teacher assigned a lot of homework for the weekend."},{"es":"Mi hijo se sienta en la mesa de la cocina a hacer su tarea.","en":"My son sits at the kitchen table to do his homework."}]},{"spanish_text":"Estudiar","english_text":"Study","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To devote time and attention to acquiring knowledge or skill in a subject.","main_translations_es":["Aprender","Repasar","Prepararse"],"collocations":["study hard","study abroad","study for the exam","study group"],"synonyms_en":["learn","review","research"],"example_sentence":"I have to study for the exam.","example_es":"Tengo que estudiar para el examen.","example_en":"I have to study for the exam.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a stew bubbling in a pot labeled Estudiar as you study.","cloze_distractors_en":["Sleep","Dance","Laugh","Paint"],"examples":[{"es":"Tengo que estudiar para el examen.","en":"I have to study for the exam."},{"es":"Voy a la biblioteca para estudiar en silencio.","en":"I go to the library to study in silence."},{"es":"Necesito estudiar mis notas antes de la reunión.","en":"I need to study my notes before the meeting."}]},{"spanish_text":"Aprender","english_text":"Learn","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To acquire knowledge or skill through study, experience, or instruction.","main_translations_es":["Estudiar","Adquirir conocimientos","Instruirse"],"collocations":["learn by heart","learn the ropes","learn quickly","learn from experience"],"synonyms_en":["study","acquire knowledge","master"],"example_sentence":"I want to learn to play the guitar.","example_es":"Quiero aprender a tocar la guitarra.","example_en":"I want to learn to play the guitar.","mnemonic_en":"I press the switch (prender) to learn the lesson.","cloze_distractors_en":["Forget","Refuse","Ignore","Avoid"],"examples":[{"es":"Quiero aprender a tocar la guitarra.","en":"I want to learn to play the guitar."},{"es":"Los niños van a la escuela para aprender matemáticas.","en":"The children go to school to learn math."},{"es":"Es necesario practicar mucho para aprender un nuevo idioma.","en":"It is necessary to practice a lot to learn a new language."}]},{"spanish_text":"Descansar","english_text":"Rest","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A period of relaxation or inactivity intended to recover strength.","main_translations_es":["Reposar","Tomar un descanso","Relajarse"],"collocations":["rest and recover","rest assured","take a rest","rest of the day"],"synonyms_en":["relax","take a break","repose"],"example_sentence":"I need to rest after work.","example_es":"Necesito descansar después del trabajo.","example_en":"I need to rest after work.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a weary traveler sitting on a rest bench called descANSAR for a quick rest","cloze_distractors_en":["Digest","Expand","Inhale","Govern"],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito descansar después del trabajo.","en":"I need to rest after work."},{"es":"Los médicos recomiendan descansar durante el fin de semana para recuperar energías.","en":"Doctors recommend to rest during the weekend to recover energy."},{"es":"Si te sientes mareado, es mejor sentarte y descansar un momento.","en":"If you feel dizzy, it is better to sit down and rest for a moment."}]},{"spanish_text":"Horario","english_text":"Schedule","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A plan that lists the times at which events or tasks are intended to occur.","main_translations_es":["Calendario","Programa","Agenda"],"collocations":["keep a schedule","schedule a meeting","on schedule","schedule changes"],"synonyms_en":["timetable","agenda","program"],"example_sentence":"What is the meeting schedule?","example_es":"¿Cuál es el horario de la reunión?","example_en":"What is the meeting schedule?","mnemonic_en":"I picture a school board with the word horario, and the schedule (sked-ule) pinned beside it.","cloze_distractors_en":["weather","ticket","luggage","furniture"],"examples":[{"es":"¿Cuál es el horario de la reunión?","en":"What is the meeting schedule?"},{"es":"El horario del autobús cambia los fines de semana.","en":"The bus schedule changes on weekends."},{"es":"Mi horario de trabajo es de nueve a cinco.","en":"My work schedule is from nine to five."}]},{"spanish_text":"Hoy","english_text":"Today","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"The current day; the day that is happening now.","main_translations_es":["En el día de hoy","Esta jornada","En la fecha actual"],"collocations":["today is the day","as of today","today''s agenda","today and tomorrow"],"synonyms_en":["now","this day","the present"],"example_sentence":"Today I am going to the market.","example_es":"Hoy voy al mercado.","example_en":"Today I am going to the market.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a bright toy today, saying ''hoy'' as you hold it.","cloze_distractors_en":["Upward","Hardly","Inward","Awkward"],"examples":[{"es":"Hoy voy al mercado.","en":"Today I am going to the market."},{"es":"Tengo una cita médica muy importante hoy.","en":"I have a very important doctor''s appointment today."},{"es":"El informe debe estar terminado hoy antes de las cinco.","en":"The report must be finished today before five o''clock."}]},{"spanish_text":"Mañana","english_text":"Tomorrow","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"The day after today.","main_translations_es":["El día siguiente","Al día siguiente","En la mañana"],"collocations":["Tomorrow morning","See you tomorrow","Tomorrow night","Tomorrow will be better"],"synonyms_en":["the next day","the following day","day after today"],"example_sentence":"Tomorrow we will go to the park.","example_es":"Mañana iremos al parque.","example_en":"Tomorrow we will go to the park.","mnemonic_en":"Tomorrow I picture the sunrise and hear \"mañana\" whispering in my ear.","cloze_distractors_en":["Yesterday","Elsewhere","Everywhere"],"examples":[{"es":"Mañana iremos al parque.","en":"Tomorrow we will go to the park."},{"es":"Tengo una cita con el dentista mañana por la tarde.","en":"I have a dentist appointment tomorrow afternoon."},{"es":"No olvides terminar tu tarea para entregarla mañana.","en":"Do not forget to finish your homework to turn it in tomorrow."}]},{"spanish_text":"Ayer","english_text":"Yesterday","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"the day before today","main_translations_es":["el día anterior","el día de ayer","el día previo"],"collocations":["Yesterday morning","Yesterday evening","Yesterday I went","Yesterday was a good day"],"synonyms_en":["the day before","the previous day"],"example_sentence":"Yesterday we went to the cinema and watched an action movie.","example_es":"Ayer fuimos al cine y vimos una película de acción.","example_en":"Yesterday we went to the cinema and watched an action movie.","mnemonic_en":"Yesterday sounds like Spanish ''ayer'', picture the day before today fading away.","cloze_distractors_en":["Tomorrow","Sometimes","Everywhere"],"examples":[{"es":"Ayer fuimos al cine y vimos una película de acción.","en":"Yesterday we went to the cinema and watched an action movie."},{"es":"Ayer terminé de leer el libro que me prestaste.","en":"Yesterday I finished reading the book you lent me."},{"es":"Ayer compré frutas frescas en el mercado local.","en":"Yesterday I bought fresh fruit at the local market."}]},{"spanish_text":"Esta semana","english_text":"This week","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"the current week, referring to the seven-day period that includes today","main_translations_es":["Esta semana","La semana actual","La presente semana"],"collocations":["later this week","by this week","this week only","this week''s schedule"],"synonyms_en":["the current week","the present week"],"example_sentence":"This week I have many important meetings at the office.","example_es":"Esta semana tengo muchas reuniones importantes en la oficina.","example_en":"This week I have many important meetings at the office.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a calendar saying esta week on the page linking this week to Spanish esta semana","cloze_distractors_en":["Last century","Every decade","That lifetime","Some millennium"],"examples":[{"es":"Esta semana tengo muchas reuniones importantes en la oficina.","en":"This week I have many important meetings at the office."},{"es":"Voy a visitar a mis abuelos esta semana para celebrar su aniversario.","en":"I am going to visit my grandparents this week to celebrate their anniversary."},{"es":"El supermercado tiene ofertas especiales esta semana en frutas y verduras.","en":"The supermarket has special offers this week on fruits and vegetables."}]},{"spanish_text":"Fin de semana","english_text":"Weekend","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The period of Saturday and Sunday, or the days at the end of the week, when most people are not working.","main_translations_es":["fin de semana","el fin de semana"],"collocations":["weekend getaway","weekend plans","weekend vibes"],"synonyms_en":["off days","rest days","free time"],"example_sentence":"This weekend I''m going to visit my grandparents.","example_es":"Este fin de semana voy a visitar a mis abuelos.","example_en":"This weekend I''m going to visit my grandparents.","mnemonic_en":"Picture the week ending, a weekend, the fin of the week.","cloze_distractors_en":["Midnight","Calendar","Schedule","Duration"],"examples":[{"es":"Este fin de semana voy a visitar a mis abuelos.","en":"This weekend I''m going to visit my grandparents."},{"es":"Me gusta descansar mucho durante el fin de semana.","en":"I like to rest a lot during the weekend."},{"es":"Mi jefe me envió un correo electrónico de trabajo durante el fin de semana.","en":"My boss sent me a work email during the weekend."}]},{"spanish_text":"Rápido","english_text":"Fast","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Moving or capable of moving at high speed.","main_translations_es":["Veloz","Ágil","Ligero"],"collocations":["fast food","fast track","fast lane","fast pace"],"synonyms_en":["quick","rapid","swift"],"example_sentence":"The cheetah is fast when it hunts its prey on the savanna.","example_es":"El guepardo es rápido cuando caza a su presa en la sabana.","example_en":"The cheetah is fast when it hunts its prey on the savanna.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a rabbit saying rapido as it darts fast.","cloze_distractors_en":["Heavy","Loose","Sharp"],"examples":[{"es":"El guepardo es rápido cuando caza a su presa en la sabana.","en":"The cheetah is fast when it hunts its prey on the savanna."},{"es":"Necesito un internet rápido para trabajar desde casa.","en":"I need a fast internet connection to work from home."},{"es":"El atleta corre muy rápido en la pista.","en":"The athlete runs very fast on the track."}]},{"spanish_text":"Despacio","english_text":"Slowly","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"In a slow manner; at a low speed.","main_translations_es":["Lentamente","Con calma","A paso lento"],"collocations":["slowly but surely","take it slowly","move slowly"],"synonyms_en":["gradually","at a slow pace","leisurely"],"example_sentence":"Walk slowly so you don''t slip.","example_es":"Camina despacio para no resbalar.","example_en":"Walk slowly so you don''t slip.","mnemonic_en":"A snail whispers despacio as it slides, reminding you everything moves slowly.","cloze_distractors_en":["Rarely","Hourly","Merely"],"examples":[{"es":"Camina despacio para no resbalar.","en":"Walk slowly so you don''t slip."},{"es":"El anciano sube las escaleras despacio porque le duelen las rodillas.","en":"The old man climbs the stairs slowly because his knees hurt."},{"es":"Por favor, habla despacio para que pueda entenderte mejor.","en":"Please speak slowly so that I can understand you better."}]},{"spanish_text":"Espera un momento","english_text":"Wait a moment","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A polite request to pause briefly.","main_translations_es":["Un momento","Espera un segundo","Aguarda un momento"],"collocations":["Wait a moment, please","Hold on a moment","Just wait a moment","Wait a moment while I check"],"synonyms_en":["Hold on","Just a sec","One moment"],"example_sentence":"Wait a moment while I look up the information.","example_es":"Espera un momento, voy a buscar la información.","example_en":"Wait a moment while I look up the information.","mnemonic_en":"I wait hearing the Spanish espera echo in the quiet hallway","cloze_distractors_en":["Walk away fast","Sleep soundly now","Drive around town","Jump over there"],"examples":[{"es":"Espera un momento, voy a buscar la información.","en":"Wait a moment while I look up the information."},{"es":"El autobús está por llegar, espera un momento en la parada.","en":"The bus is about to arrive, so wait a moment at the stop."},{"es":"No cuelgues el teléfono, espera un momento mientras hablo con mi jefe.","en":"Do not hang up the phone, wait a moment while I speak with my boss."}]},{"spanish_text":"Perdón","english_text":"Excuse me","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"interjection","definition_en":"A polite phrase used to get someone''s attention or to apologize for a minor offense.","main_translations_es":["Disculpa","Lo siento","Con permiso"],"collocations":["Excuse me, could you repeat that?","Excuse me, I have a question","Excuse me, may I sit here?"],"synonyms_en":["Pardon","Sorry","I beg your pardon"],"example_sentence":"Excuse me, can you pass me the salt?","example_es":"Perdón, ¿puedes pasarme la sal?","example_en":"Excuse me, can you pass me the salt?","mnemonic_en":"Excuse me, I''m a robot that says ''per‑done'' when I apologize.","cloze_distractors_en":["Forget me","Believe me","Follow me","Notice me"],"examples":[{"es":"Perdón, ¿puedes pasarme la sal?","en":"Excuse me, can you pass me the salt?"},{"es":"Perdón, ¿me dejas pasar para llegar a mi asiento?","en":"Excuse me, can I get past you to reach my seat?"},{"es":"Perdón, ¿sabe usted a qué hora abre la biblioteca?","en":"Excuse me, do you know what time the library opens?"}]},{"spanish_text":"De nada","english_text":"You are welcome","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A polite response indicating that the speaker is happy to have helped.","main_translations_es":["No hay de qué","Con gusto","A la orden"],"collocations":["You’re welcome!","No problem","Anytime","My pleasure"],"synonyms_en":["No problem","My pleasure","Don''t mention it"],"example_sentence":"Thank you for holding the door open for me, you are welcome.","example_es":"Muchas gracias por abrirme la puerta, de nada.","example_en":"Thank you for holding the door open for me, you are welcome.","mnemonic_en":"Hear ''De nada'' and picture a door opening, saying ''You are welcome'' to the visitor.","cloze_distractors_en":["It is forbidden","I am confused","That is unlikely","You are mistaken"],"examples":[{"es":"Muchas gracias por abrirme la puerta, de nada.","en":"Thank you for holding the door open for me, you are welcome."},{"es":"Muchas gracias por enseñarme el camino a la estación, de nada, ha sido un placer ayudarte.","en":"Thank you so much for showing me the way to the station, you are welcome, it was a pleasure to help you."},{"es":"Gracias por ayudarme con las bolsas del supermercado, de nada, no hay problema.","en":"Thanks for helping me with the grocery bags, you are welcome, no problem at all."}]},{"spanish_text":"Nos vemos luego","english_text":"See you later","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A casual way to say goodbye, indicating that you will meet again later.","main_translations_es":["Hasta luego","Nos vemos después","Hasta pronto"],"collocations":["See you later, alligator","See you later, gator","See you later, buddy"],"synonyms_en":["Catch you later","Talk to you later","Until next time"],"example_sentence":"I have to head home now, see you later.","example_es":"Ya me tengo que ir a casa, nos vemos luego.","example_en":"I have to head home now, see you later.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a friend waving and shouting nos vemos, then you both smile and think see you later","cloze_distractors_en":["Always be quiet","Never look back","Keep moving fast","Please stay home"],"examples":[{"es":"Ya me tengo que ir a casa, nos vemos luego.","en":"I have to head home now, see you later."},{"es":"Tengo que irme a trabajar, nos vemos luego.","en":"I have to go to work, see you later."},{"es":"Ya terminó la clase, nos vemos luego en la biblioteca.","en":"Class is over, see you later at the library."}]},{"spanish_text":"Buenas noches","english_text":"Good night","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A polite phrase used to wish someone a pleasant night, typically said when parting in the evening.","main_translations_es":["Buenas noches","Que tengas una buena noche","Que descanses"],"collocations":["Good night, sweet dreams","Good night, see you tomorrow","Good night, everyone","Good night, sleep tight"],"synonyms_en":["sleep well","sweet dreams","nighttime"],"example_sentence":"Good night, see you tomorrow.","example_es":"Buenas noches, nos vemos mañana.","example_en":"Good night, see you tomorrow.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a good night where ''buenas'' sounds like good and ''noches'' sounds like nights under a bright moon.","cloze_distractors_en":["Good morning","Good afternoon","Good lunch","Good holiday"],"examples":[{"es":"Buenas noches, nos vemos mañana.","en":"Good night, see you tomorrow."},{"es":"Apaga la luz, buenas noches.","en":"Turn off the light, Good night."},{"es":"Le di un beso a mi hija y le dije buenas noches antes de dormir.","en":"I kissed my daughter and said Good night before she went to sleep."}]},{"spanish_text":"Tengo hambre","english_text":"I am hungry","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that the speaker feels the need to eat.","main_translations_es":["Tengo hambre","Siento hambre","Me da hambre"],"collocations":["I am hungry for success","I am hungry for knowledge","I am hungry and tired"],"synonyms_en":["famished","starving","ravenous"],"example_sentence":"I am hungry, so I am going to make a sandwich.","example_es":"Tengo hambre, así que voy a preparar un sándwich.","example_en":"I am hungry, so I am going to make a sandwich.","mnemonic_en":"I am hungry, I picture a giant hamburger satisfying my hambre.","cloze_distractors_en":["I am asleep","I am bored","I am busy"],"examples":[{"es":"Tengo hambre, así que voy a preparar un sándwich.","en":"I am hungry, so I am going to make a sandwich."},{"es":"Después de correr en el parque, tengo hambre y quiero cenar pronto.","en":"After running in the park, I am hungry and want to eat dinner soon."},{"es":"No he almorzado nada hoy y tengo hambre, ¿podemos ir a un restaurante?","en":"I have not had lunch today and I am hungry, can we go to a restaurant?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Tengo sueño","english_text":"I am sleepy","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that the speaker feels drowsy.","main_translations_es":["Estoy cansado","Me da sueño","Me siento somnoliento"],"collocations":["feeling sleepy","getting sleepy","too sleepy to work"],"synonyms_en":["feeling drowsy","half-asleep","tired"],"example_sentence":"I am sleepy after working all day.","example_es":"Tengo sueño después de trabajar todo el día.","example_en":"I am sleepy after working all day.","mnemonic_en":"I am sleepy like a tired llama whispering ''tengo sueño''.","cloze_distractors_en":["I am colorful","I am triangular","I am metallic","I am historical"],"examples":[{"es":"Tengo sueño después de trabajar todo el día.","en":"I am sleepy after working all day."},{"es":"Apaga la luz, por favor, porque tengo sueño.","en":"Turn off the light, please, because I am sleepy."},{"es":"Bostecé tres veces durante la película porque tengo sueño.","en":"I yawned three times during the movie because I am sleepy."}]},{"spanish_text":"Tengo frío","english_text":"I am cold","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that the speaker feels cold.","main_translations_es":["Siento frío","Hace frío","Me está dando frío"],"collocations":["I am cold today","I am cold, can you close the window?","I am cold and need a sweater"],"synonyms_en":["feeling chilly","I''m freezing","I''m chilly"],"example_sentence":"I am cold, so I will put on a jacket.","example_es":"Tengo frío, así que me pondré una chaqueta.","example_en":"I am cold, so I will put on a jacket.","mnemonic_en":"I shiver, thinking ''tengo frío'' like a frozen ego wearing a coat.","cloze_distractors_en":["I am hungry","I am thirsty","I am tired","I am bored"],"examples":[{"es":"Tengo frío, así que me pondré una chaqueta.","en":"I am cold, so I will put on a jacket."},{"es":"Cierra la ventana porque tengo frío.","en":"Close the window because I am cold."},{"es":"Apaga el aire acondicionado, tengo frío.","en":"Turn off the air conditioning, I am cold."}]},{"spanish_text":"Tengo calor","english_text":"I am hot","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Used to say that you feel warm or have a high body temperature.","main_translations_es":["Hace calor","Siento calor","Estoy acalorado"],"collocations":["I am hot today","I am hot after the workout","I am hot and bothered"],"synonyms_en":["I''m warm","feeling warm","I''m heated"],"example_sentence":"I am hot, so I am going to open the window.","example_es":"Tengo calor, así que voy a abrir la ventana.","example_en":"I am hot, so I am going to open the window.","mnemonic_en":"I am hot, like a blazing ''calor'' flame scorching the desert.","cloze_distractors_en":["I am lost","I am late","I am tired","I am bored"],"examples":[{"es":"Tengo calor, así que voy a abrir la ventana.","en":"I am hot, so I am going to open the window."},{"es":"Apaga la calefacción porque tengo calor en esta habitación.","en":"Turn off the heater because I am hot in this room."},{"es":"Por favor, enciende el ventilador porque tengo calor.","en":"Please turn on the fan because I am hot."}]},{"spanish_text":"Estoy cansado","english_text":"I am tired","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that the speaker feels fatigue.","main_translations_es":["Me siento cansado","Estoy agotado","Tengo sueño"],"collocations":["I''m tired of","I''m so tired","I''m tired, let''s go home","I''m tired and need rest"],"synonyms_en":["I''m exhausted","I''m fatigued","I''m weary"],"example_sentence":"I am tired after running five kilometers.","example_es":"Estoy cansado después de correr cinco kilómetros.","example_en":"I am tired after running five kilometers.","mnemonic_en":"I am tired and open a sad empty can, feeling cansado","cloze_distractors_en":["I am invisible","I am Tuesday","I am circular","I am stationary"],"examples":[{"es":"Estoy cansado después de correr cinco kilómetros.","en":"I am tired after running five kilometers."},{"es":"No puedo seguir trabajando porque estoy cansado.","en":"I cannot keep working because I am tired."},{"es":"Aunque dormí ocho horas, todavía estoy cansado.","en":"Even though I slept for eight hours, I am tired."}]},{"spanish_text":"Estoy ocupado","english_text":"I am busy","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that someone is occupied or has no free time.","main_translations_es":["Tengo mucho trabajo","No tengo tiempo","Estoy atareado"],"collocations":["I''m busy right now","I''m busy with work","I''m busy all day"],"synonyms_en":["I''m occupied","I''m tied up","I''m swamped"],"example_sentence":"I am busy right now, but I will call you later.","example_es":"Estoy ocupado ahora, pero te llamaré más tarde.","example_en":"I am busy right now, but I will call you later.","mnemonic_en":"I picture a crowded desk, shouting Estoy ocupado as I juggle papers.","cloze_distractors_en":["I am Tuesday","I am quickly","I am between"],"examples":[{"es":"Estoy ocupado ahora, pero te llamaré más tarde.","en":"I am busy right now, but I will call you later."},{"es":"No puedo ir al cine porque estoy ocupado con mi tarea.","en":"I cannot go to the movies because I am busy with my homework."},{"es":"Por favor, no me molestes mientras estoy ocupado trabajando.","en":"Please do not disturb me while I am busy working."}]},{"spanish_text":"Estoy libre","english_text":"I am free","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that one is not occupied or constrained.","main_translations_es":["No tengo nada","Tengo tiempo libre","Estoy disponible"],"collocations":["I am free tomorrow","I am free to help","I am free now"],"synonyms_en":["I''m available","I have no plans","I''m unoccupied"],"example_sentence":"I am free this weekend to go out.","example_es":"Estoy libre este fin de semana para salir.","example_en":"I am free this weekend to go out.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a free bird shouting Libre as it flies.","cloze_distractors_en":["I am yellow","I am quickly","I am between"],"examples":[{"es":"Estoy libre este fin de semana para salir.","en":"I am free this weekend to go out."},{"es":"Si termino mi trabajo temprano, estoy libre para ayudarte con la mudanza.","en":"If I finish my work early, I am free to help you with the move."},{"es":"Dime a qué hora estás disponible porque hoy estoy libre toda la tarde.","en":"Tell me what time you are available because I am free all afternoon today."}]},{"spanish_text":"Quédate aquí","english_text":"Stay here","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"imperative verb","definition_en":"A command telling someone to remain in this place.","main_translations_es":["Quédate aquí","Quédate en este lugar","Quédate aquí mismo"],"collocations":["stay safe","stay tuned","stay put","stay in touch"],"synonyms_en":["remain here","stay put","hang around"],"example_sentence":"Stay here while I prepare dinner.","example_es":"Quédate aquí mientras preparo la cena.","example_en":"Stay here while I prepare dinner.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a sign that says Stay here while hearing quédate aquí sounding like stay‑date.","cloze_distractors_en":["Leave fast","Walk away","Move along","Start work"],"examples":[{"es":"Quédate aquí mientras preparo la cena.","en":"Stay here while I prepare dinner."},{"es":"El guía turístico nos dijo: Quédate aquí hasta que regrese con las entradas.","en":"The tour guide told us: Stay here until I return with the tickets."},{"es":"Si te sientes mareado, por favor, quédate aquí sentado en la silla.","en":"If you feel dizzy, please, Stay here sitting in the chair."}]},{"spanish_text":"Ven aquí","english_text":"Come here","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"imperative verb phrase","definition_en":"A command telling someone to approach the speaker.","main_translations_es":["Acércate","Vente aquí","Vengan aquí"],"collocations":["Come here and sit down","Come here quickly","Come here, please"],"synonyms_en":["approach","step over","move closer"],"example_sentence":"When the dog ran away, the owner shouted, \"Come here!\"","example_es":"Cuando el perro se escapó, el dueño gritó: \"¡Ven aquí!\"","example_en":"When the dog ran away, the owner shouted, \"Come here!\"","mnemonic_en":"A dove says come here when you hear Ven aquí","cloze_distractors_en":["Go away","Look down","Sit back"],"examples":[{"es":"Cuando el perro se escapó, el dueño gritó: \"¡Ven aquí!\"","en":"When the dog ran away, the owner shouted, \"Come here!\""},{"es":"La profesora señaló el pupitre vacío y le dijo al alumno: \"Ven aquí, por favor\".","en":"The teacher pointed to the empty desk and told the student, \"Come here, please.\""},{"es":"Mi madre me vio desde la cocina y me hizo señas diciendo: \"Ven aquí para ayudarme con la cena\".","en":"My mother saw me from the kitchen and signaled, \"Come here to help me with dinner.\""}]},{"spanish_text":"Siéntate","english_text":"Sit down","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To take a seat.","main_translations_es":["Toma asiento","Acomódate","Siéntese"],"collocations":["Sit down and relax","Sit down for a meeting","Sit down, please"],"synonyms_en":["take a seat","have a seat"],"example_sentence":"Sit down on the chair and wait.","example_es":"Siéntate en la silla y espera.","example_en":"Sit down on the chair and wait.","mnemonic_en":"Sit down as the chair whispers siéntate, inviting you to rest.","cloze_distractors_en":["Look away","Turn over","Fall down","Walk past"],"examples":[{"es":"Siéntate en la silla y espera.","en":"Sit down on the chair and wait."},{"es":"Siéntate aquí para que podamos hablar del proyecto.","en":"Sit down here so we can talk about the project."},{"es":"Siéntate frente al escritorio para empezar a escribir la carta.","en":"Sit down in front of the desk to start writing the letter."}]},{"spanish_text":"Levántate","english_text":"Stand up","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To rise to a standing position.","main_translations_es":["Ponte de pie","Alzarse","Ponte en pie"],"collocations":["stand up for","stand up to","stand up straight","stand up and shout"],"synonyms_en":["rise","get up","arise"],"example_sentence":"Please stand up from the chair to greet our guest.","example_es":"Por favor, levántate de la silla para saludar a nuestra visita.","example_en":"Please stand up from the chair to greet our guest.","mnemonic_en":"Stand up as if pulling a lever that says levanta to lift yourself","cloze_distractors_en":["Look down","Turn over","Fall back"],"examples":[{"es":"Por favor, levántate de la silla para saludar a nuestra visita.","en":"Please stand up from the chair to greet our guest."},{"es":"Si quieres ver mejor el desfile, levántate de tu asiento.","en":"If you want to see the parade better, stand up from your seat."},{"es":"Cuando el himno nacional comience a sonar, levántate por respeto.","en":"When the national anthem starts playing, stand up out of respect."}]},{"spanish_text":"Abre la puerta","english_text":"Open the door","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"imperative verb phrase","definition_en":"A command telling someone to open the door.","main_translations_es":["Abre la puerta","Abre la puerta, por favor","Desbloquea la puerta"],"collocations":["open the door for someone","open the door to","open the door wide"],"synonyms_en":["unlock the door","let in","unseal the door"],"example_sentence":"Open the door before the guests arrive.","example_es":"Abre la puerta antes de que lleguen los invitados.","example_en":"Open the door before the guests arrive.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a hand shouting abre as it opens the bright red door","cloze_distractors_en":["Water the carpet","Sweep the clouds","Feed the furniture"],"examples":[{"es":"Abre la puerta antes de que lleguen los invitados.","en":"Open the door before the guests arrive."},{"es":"Si tienes las manos ocupadas con las bolsas, abre la puerta con el codo.","en":"If your hands are full with the bags, open the door with your elbow."},{"es":"Por favor, abre la puerta para que el perro pueda salir al jardín.","en":"Please open the door so the dog can go out to the garden."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cierra la ventana","english_text":"Close the window","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"A command telling someone to shut the window.","main_translations_es":["Cierra la ventana","Cierra la ventana, por favor","Cierra la ventana ahora"],"collocations":["Please close the window","Make sure to close the window","Don''t forget to close the window"],"synonyms_en":["shut the window","shut the pane"],"example_sentence":"Close the window, please.","example_es":"Cierra la ventana, por favor.","example_en":"Close the window, please.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a saw (cierra) chopping the window closed.","cloze_distractors_en":["Eat the carpet","Fold the weather","Wash the silence","Plant the furniture"],"examples":[{"es":"Cierra la ventana, por favor.","en":"Close the window, please."},{"es":"Hace mucho frío afuera, así que cierra la ventana.","en":"It is very cold outside, so close the window."},{"es":"Para evitar que entre el ruido de la calle, cierra la ventana.","en":"To keep out the street noise, close the window."}]},{"spanish_text":"Enciende la luz","english_text":"Turn on the light","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To activate the light by switching it on.","main_translations_es":["Prende la luz","Enciende la lámpara","Ilumina la habitación"],"collocations":["turn on the light","turn the lights on","switch on the light","flip the switch"],"synonyms_en":["switch on the light","activate the light","illuminate"],"example_sentence":"I cannot see anything in this hallway, turn on the light so we can walk.","example_es":"No veo nada en este pasillo, enciende la luz para que podamos caminar.","example_en":"I cannot see anything in this hallway, turn on the light so we can walk.","mnemonic_en":"Flip the switch and shout ''luz'' as the room brightens.","cloze_distractors_en":["Freeze the time","Empty the ocean","Breathe the clouds","Melt the shadow"],"examples":[{"es":"No veo nada en este pasillo, enciende la luz para que podamos caminar.","en":"I cannot see anything in this hallway, turn on the light so we can walk."},{"es":"Está muy oscuro aquí, enciende la luz para ver mejor.","en":"It is very dark in here, turn on the light to see better."},{"es":"Cuando entres en la habitación, enciende la luz.","en":"When you enter the room, turn on the light."}]},{"spanish_text":"Apaga la luz","english_text":"Turn off the light","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"imperative verb phrase","definition_en":"A command telling someone to switch the light off.","main_translations_es":["Apaga la luz","Apaga la lámpara","Apaga la luz, por favor"],"collocations":["turn off the light","turn off the lights","turn off the light switch","turn off the light before bed"],"synonyms_en":["switch off the light","shut off the light","kill the lights"],"example_sentence":"Please turn off the light when you leave the room.","example_es":"Por favor, apaga la luz cuando salgas de la habitación.","example_en":"Please turn off the light when you leave the room.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a torn-off lamp whispering apaga la luz as you turn off the light.","cloze_distractors_en":["Open the window","Clean the carpet","Paint the ceiling"],"examples":[{"es":"Por favor, apaga la luz cuando salgas de la habitación.","en":"Please turn off the light when you leave the room."},{"es":"Antes de irte a dormir, apaga la luz de la mesita de noche.","en":"Before you go to sleep, turn off the light on the nightstand."},{"es":"Si eres la última persona en salir de la oficina, apaga la luz del pasillo.","en":"If you are the last person to leave the office, turn off the light in the hallway."}]},{"spanish_text":"Lava la ropa","english_text":"Wash the clothes","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To clean the clothing by using water and detergent.","main_translations_es":["Lava la ropa","Lava la ropa sucia","Haz la colada"],"collocations":["wash the clothes thoroughly","wash the clothes in cold water","wash the clothes before drying","wash the clothes regularly"],"synonyms_en":["launder the garments","clean the laundry","do the washing"],"example_sentence":"Wash the clothes before it starts to rain.","example_es":"Lava la ropa antes de que empiece a llover.","example_en":"Wash the clothes before it starts to rain.","mnemonic_en":"Picture lava bubbling as it washes the clothes.","cloze_distractors_en":["Freeze the carpets","Melt the pillows","Bury the curtains"],"examples":[{"es":"Lava la ropa antes de que empiece a llover.","en":"Wash the clothes before it starts to rain."},{"es":"Si la camisa está sucia, lava la ropa hoy mismo.","en":"If the shirt is dirty, wash the clothes today."},{"es":"Usa detergente cuando lava la ropa en la lavadora.","en":"Use detergent when you wash the clothes in the machine."}]},{"spanish_text":"Saca la basura","english_text":"Take out the trash","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To remove the garbage from a location and place it in a waste container or outside for collection.","main_translations_es":["Saca la basura","Lleva la basura al contenedor"],"collocations":["take out the trash","take out the trash before dinner","take out the trash daily"],"synonyms_en":["remove the garbage","dispose of the waste","empty the bin"],"example_sentence":"Take out the trash before the guests arrive.","example_es":"Saca la basura antes de que lleguen los invitados.","example_en":"Take out the trash before the guests arrive.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a taco taking out trash from the bin","cloze_distractors_en":["Paint the ceiling","Drive the tractor","Build the balcony","Water the carpet"],"examples":[{"es":"Saca la basura antes de que lleguen los invitados.","en":"Take out the trash before the guests arrive."},{"es":"Por favor, saca la basura al contenedor de la calle esta noche.","en":"Please take out the trash to the street bin tonight."},{"es":"Si la cocina huele mal, saca la basura inmediatamente.","en":"If the kitchen smells bad, take out the trash immediately."}]},{"spanish_text":"Haz la compra","english_text":"Do the shopping","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To purchase groceries or other needed items.","main_translations_es":["Haz la compra","Ir de compras","Hacer la compra"],"collocations":["do the shopping","do the grocery shopping","do the weekly shopping","do some shopping"],"synonyms_en":["Go shopping","Shop for groceries","Buy groceries"],"example_sentence":"Tomorrow, do the shopping for the food we need.","example_es":"Mañana haz la compra de los alimentos que necesitamos.","example_en":"Tomorrow, do the shopping for the food we need.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a hazy llama pushing a cart, doing the shopping.","cloze_distractors_en":["Make the laundry","Cook the furniture","Wash the sunshine","Paint the kitchen"],"examples":[{"es":"Mañana haz la compra de los alimentos que necesitamos.","en":"Tomorrow, do the shopping for the food we need."},{"es":"Por favor, haz la compra antes de que cierren el supermercado.","en":"Please, do the shopping before the supermarket closes."},{"es":"Si no tienes nada en la nevera, haz la compra hoy mismo.","en":"If you have nothing in the fridge, do the shopping today."}]},{"spanish_text":"Voy al banco","english_text":"I am going to the bank","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that the speaker is traveling to the bank.","main_translations_es":["Voy al banco","Me dirijo al banco","Voy a ir al banco"],"collocations":["I''m going to the bank tomorrow","I''m going to the bank later today","I''m going to the bank to deposit some money","I''m going to the bank for a loan"],"synonyms_en":["heading to the bank","off to the bank","on my way to the bank"],"example_sentence":"I have to withdraw money for the trip, so I am going to the bank right now.","example_es":"Tengo que retirar dinero para el viaje, así que voy al banco ahora mismo.","example_en":"I have to withdraw money for the trip, so I am going to the bank right now.","mnemonic_en":"I walk to the bank, picturing a wooden banco bench waiting for me.","cloze_distractors_en":["I am eating the wall","I am buying the moon","I am driving the ocean","I am washing the clouds"],"examples":[{"es":"Tengo que retirar dinero para el viaje, así que voy al banco ahora mismo.","en":"I have to withdraw money for the trip, so I am going to the bank right now."},{"es":"Como necesito dinero en efectivo, voy al banco.","en":"Since I need some cash, I am going to the bank."},{"es":"Voy al banco a abrir una cuenta de ahorros nueva.","en":"I am going to the bank to open a new savings account."}]},{"spanish_text":"Voy a la farmacia","english_text":"I am going to the pharmacy","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that the speaker is heading to the pharmacy.","main_translations_es":["Me dirijo a la farmacia","Voy a la farmacia","Voy a la botica"],"collocations":["going to the pharmacy","head to the pharmacy","stop by the pharmacy","run to the pharmacy"],"synonyms_en":["I''m heading to the drugstore","I''m off to the pharmacy","I''m on my way to the pharmacy"],"example_sentence":"I have a headache, so I am going to the pharmacy.","example_es":"Tengo dolor de cabeza, así que voy a la farmacia.","example_en":"I have a headache, so I am going to the pharmacy.","mnemonic_en":"I’m going to the pharmacy, a voy (voyage) to the farm of medicines.","cloze_distractors_en":["I am eating the furniture","I am painting the clouds","I am fixing the sunshine","I am reading the alphabet"],"examples":[{"es":"Tengo dolor de cabeza, así que voy a la farmacia.","en":"I have a headache, so I am going to the pharmacy."},{"es":"Necesito comprar medicina para mi resfriado, así que voy a la farmacia.","en":"I need to buy medicine for my cold, so I am going to the pharmacy."},{"es":"Como se me acabó el champú, voy a la farmacia ahora mismo.","en":"Since I ran out of shampoo, I am going to the pharmacy right now."}]},{"spanish_text":"Voy al gimnasio","english_text":"I am going to the gym","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that the speaker is heading to the gym.","main_translations_es":["Voy al gimnasio","Me dirijo al gimnasio","Me voy al gimnasio"],"collocations":["go to the gym","hit the gym","work out at the gym","exercise at the gym"],"synonyms_en":["I''m heading to the gym","I''m off to the gym","I''m going to work out"],"example_sentence":"I am going to the gym every day to stay fit.","example_es":"Voy al gimnasio todos los días para mantenerme en forma.","example_en":"I am going to the gym every day to stay fit.","mnemonic_en":"I picture myself walking into the gym, hearing the Spanish word ''gimnasio'' echoing in the hallway.","cloze_distractors_en":["I am eating the wall","I am sleeping the floor","I am buying the clouds","I am painting the wind"],"examples":[{"es":"Voy al gimnasio todos los días para mantenerme en forma.","en":"I am going to the gym every day to stay fit."},{"es":"Como tengo mucha energía esta tarde, voy al gimnasio a levantar pesas.","en":"Since I have a lot of energy this afternoon, I am going to the gym to lift weights."},{"es":"Después de terminar mi jornada laboral, voy al gimnasio para correr en la cinta.","en":"After finishing my workday, I am going to the gym to run on the treadmill."}]},{"spanish_text":"Toma el autobús","english_text":"Take the bus","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To travel by riding a bus.","main_translations_es":["Coge el autobús","Sube al autobús","Toma el bus"],"collocations":["take the bus to work","take the bus downtown","take the bus every day","take the bus instead of driving"],"synonyms_en":["ride the bus","catch the bus","board the bus"],"example_sentence":"Every morning, he decides to take the bus to go to his office.","example_es":"Cada mañana, él decide tomar el autobús para ir a su oficina.","example_en":"Every morning, he decides to take the bus to go to his office.","mnemonic_en":"Picture Tom a bus driver waving, saying Take the bus.","cloze_distractors_en":["Fly the rocket","Swim the ocean","Paint the fence"],"examples":[{"es":"Cada mañana, él decide tomar el autobús para ir a su oficina.","en":"Every morning, he decides to take the bus to go to his office."},{"es":"Si no tienes coche, lo más rápido es tomar el autobús para llegar a tiempo.","en":"If you do not have a car, the fastest way is to take the bus to arrive on time."},{"es":"Para ahorrar dinero en gasolina, prefiero tomar el autobús todos los días.","en":"To save money on gas, I prefer to take the bus every day."}]},{"spanish_text":"Espera el tren","english_text":"Wait for the train","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A directive telling someone to stay until the train arrives.","main_translations_es":["Espera al tren","Aguarda el tren","Quédate esperando el tren"],"collocations":["wait for the train to arrive","wait for the train at the platform","wait for the train on time"],"synonyms_en":["await the train","stay for the train","hold for the train"],"example_sentence":"Wait for the train on platform number four.","example_es":"Espera el tren en el andén número cuatro.","example_en":"Wait for the train on platform number four.","mnemonic_en":"Picture an esper wizard waiting for the train.","cloze_distractors_en":["Drive the airplane","Build the kitchen","Read the weather"],"examples":[{"es":"Espera el tren en el andén número cuatro.","en":"Wait for the train on platform number four."},{"es":"Si llegas temprano, espera el tren sentado en el banco.","en":"If you arrive early, wait for the train sitting on the bench."},{"es":"No te vayas todavía, espera el tren que llega a las diez.","en":"Do not leave yet, wait for the train that arrives at ten."}]},{"spanish_text":"Llama a tu madre","english_text":"Call your mother","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"imperative verb","definition_en":"A command telling someone to telephone their mother.","main_translations_es":["Marca a tu madre","Comunícate con tu madre","Haz una llamada a tu madre"],"collocations":["Don''t forget to call your mother","Make sure you call your mother","I need to call my mother","She told me to call your mother"],"synonyms_en":["Phone your mother","Give your mother a call","Ring your mother"],"example_sentence":"Call your mother when you get home.","example_es":"Llama a tu madre cuando llegues a casa.","example_en":"Call your mother when you get home.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine calling a llama and telling it call your mother","cloze_distractors_en":["Feed your house","Paint your clock","Lock your weather"],"examples":[{"es":"Llama a tu madre cuando llegues a casa.","en":"Call your mother when you get home."},{"es":"Llama a tu madre para avisarle que el vuelo se retrasó.","en":"Call your mother to let her know the flight was delayed."},{"es":"Llama a tu madre antes de que empiece la cena de cumpleaños.","en":"Call your mother before the birthday dinner starts."}]},{"spanish_text":"Envía un mensaje","english_text":"Send a message","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"verb (imperative)","definition_en":"To transmit a written or electronic communication to someone.","main_translations_es":["Manda un mensaje","Envía un mensaje","Remite un mensaje"],"collocations":["send a message to","send a message via email","send a message instantly","send a message quickly"],"synonyms_en":["message someone","dispatch a message","transmit a message"],"example_sentence":"Send a message to your friend when you arrive.","example_es":"Envía un mensaje a tu amigo cuando llegues.","example_en":"Send a message to your friend when you arrive.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a courier handing over a note that says SEND like a Spanish envía sign","cloze_distractors_en":["Build a bridge","Paint a fence","Catch a flight","Watch a movie"],"examples":[{"es":"Envía un mensaje a tu amigo cuando llegues.","en":"Send a message to your friend when you arrive."},{"es":"Si necesitas ayuda urgente, envía un mensaje al grupo de trabajo.","en":"If you need urgent help, send a message to the work group."},{"es":"Por favor, envía un mensaje para confirmar tu asistencia a la fiesta.","en":"Please send a message to confirm your attendance at the party."}]},{"spanish_text":"Revisa el correo","english_text":"Check the mail","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To look at or retrieve the email messages.","main_translations_es":["Revisa el correo","Chequea el correo","Mira el correo"],"collocations":["check the mail regularly","check the mail before leaving","check the mail daily"],"synonyms_en":["look at the mail","review the mail","inspect the mail"],"example_sentence":"Check the mail before you leave.","example_es":"Revisa el correo antes de salir.","example_en":"Check the mail before you leave.","mnemonic_en":"Check the mail, just like you ''chequeas'' the inbox in Spanish.","cloze_distractors_en":["Feed the clouds","Wash the street","Cook the garden"],"examples":[{"es":"Revisa el correo antes de salir.","en":"Check the mail before you leave."},{"es":"Por favor, revisa el correo cuando llegues a casa del trabajo.","en":"Please check the mail when you get home from work."},{"es":"Si esperas una carta importante, deberías revisar el correo en cuanto llegues a casa.","en":"If you are expecting an important letter, you should check the mail as soon as you get home."}]},{"spanish_text":"Necesito descansar","english_text":"I need to rest","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that the speaker requires rest.","main_translations_es":["Tengo que descansar","Me hace falta descansar","Preciso descansar"],"collocations":["I need to rest and recover","I need to rest for a while","I need to rest after work"],"synonyms_en":["I need a break","I need to relax","I need to unwind"],"example_sentence":"I need to rest after so much work.","example_es":"Necesito descansar después de tanto trabajo.","example_en":"I need to rest after so much work.","mnemonic_en":"I picture a tired llama needing a rest, whispering ''descansar'' as it naps.","cloze_distractors_en":["I must run fast","I will eat cake","I have to jump","I can sing loud"],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito descansar después de tanto trabajo.","en":"I need to rest after so much work."},{"es":"Estoy muy cansado y necesito descansar antes de seguir conduciendo.","en":"I am very tired and I need to rest before I continue driving."},{"es":"El médico me dijo que necesito descansar durante todo el fin de semana.","en":"The doctor told me that I need to rest throughout the entire weekend."}]},{"spanish_text":"Tengo prisa","english_text":"I am in a hurry","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that someone needs to act quickly because they have limited time.","main_translations_es":["Voy deprisa","Estoy apurado","Tengo urgencia"],"collocations":["I''m in a hurry","in a hurry","hurry up","rush hour"],"synonyms_en":["I''m rushing","I''m in a rush","I''m pressed for time"],"example_sentence":"I am in a hurry, so I can''t stay long.","example_es":"Tengo prisa, así que no puedo quedarme mucho tiempo.","example_en":"I am in a hurry, so I can''t stay long.","mnemonic_en":"I am in a hurry, chasing a prize‑a rabbit.","cloze_distractors_en":["I am very lazy","I am quite bored","I am fully awake","I am really calm"],"examples":[{"es":"Tengo prisa, así que no puedo quedarme mucho tiempo.","en":"I am in a hurry, so I can''t stay long."},{"es":"Por favor, conduce más rápido porque tengo prisa para llegar a la reunión.","en":"Please drive faster because I am in a hurry to get to the meeting."},{"es":"No puedo hablar ahora porque tengo prisa por tomar el autobús.","en":"I cannot talk now because I am in a hurry to catch the bus."}]},{"spanish_text":"No pasa nada","english_text":"No problem","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A casual way of saying that something is not an issue or that you are happy to help.","main_translations_es":["No hay problema","Todo bien","No ocurre nada"],"collocations":["No problem at all","No problem, thanks","No problem, you''re welcome"],"synonyms_en":["It''s fine","All good","No worries"],"example_sentence":"No problem, we can try again.","example_es":"No pasa nada, podemos intentarlo de nuevo.","example_en":"No problem, we can try again.","mnemonic_en":"No problem—no pasa nada, nothing passes by.","cloze_distractors_en":["Quite hungry","Mostly cloudy","Highly unlikely","Deeply sorry"],"examples":[{"es":"No pasa nada, podemos intentarlo de nuevo.","en":"No problem, we can try again."},{"es":"Se me olvidó comprar la leche, pero no pasa nada, iré a la tienda más tarde.","en":"I forgot to buy the milk, but no problem, I will go to the store later."},{"es":"Perdón por llegar tarde a la reunión, no pasa nada, acabamos de empezar.","en":"Sorry for being late to the meeting, no problem, we just started."}]},{"spanish_text":"Vecino","english_text":"Neighbor","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person who lives near or next to another person.","main_translations_es":["Vecino","Vecina","colindante"],"collocations":["next‑door neighbor","good neighbor","friendly neighbor","neighboring house"],"synonyms_en":["adjacent resident","nearby dweller","next-door resident"],"example_sentence":"My neighbor helped me carry the boxes.","example_es":"Mi vecino me ayudó a cargar las cajas.","example_en":"My neighbor helped me carry the boxes.","mnemonic_en":"I see my neighbor waving a big ve sign, echoing the Spanish vecino.","cloze_distractors_en":["Furniture","Vegetable","Direction","Breakfast"],"examples":[{"es":"Mi vecino me ayudó a cargar las cajas.","en":"My neighbor helped me carry the boxes."},{"es":"El vecino siempre saca a pasear a su perro por la mañana.","en":"The neighbor always takes his dog for a walk in the morning."},{"es":"Le pedí una taza de azúcar a mi vecino porque se me había terminado.","en":"I asked my neighbor for a cup of sugar because I had run out."}]},{"spanish_text":"Parque","english_text":"Park","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A public area of land with grass, trees, and facilities for recreation and leisure.","main_translations_es":["Parque","Jardín público","Zona verde"],"collocations":["national park","theme park","park the car"],"synonyms_en":["playground","garden","green space"],"example_sentence":"We go to the park to play soccer.","example_es":"Vamos al parque a jugar al fútbol.","example_en":"We go to the park to play soccer.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a park with a long queue of ducks waiting for bread.","cloze_distractors_en":["Office","Fridge","Garage","Castle"],"examples":[{"es":"Vamos al parque a jugar al fútbol.","en":"We go to the park to play soccer."},{"es":"Los niños corren y se divierten mucho en el parque.","en":"The children run and have a lot of fun at the park."},{"es":"Saqué a pasear a mi perro por el parque esta mañana.","en":"I took my dog for a walk through the park this morning."}]}]'::jsonb) as x(
  spanish_text text, english_text text, section_name text, part_of_speech text, definition_en text,
  main_translations_es jsonb, collocations jsonb, synonyms_en jsonb, example_sentence text, example_es text, example_en text, mnemonic_en text, cloze_distractors_en jsonb, examples jsonb
)
where c.deck_id = dk.id
  and lower(c.spanish_text) = lower(x.spanish_text)
  and lower(c.english_text) = lower(x.english_text);

-- basics (105 cards)
update public.decks set
  title = 'English Basics', description = 'Everyday words and short expressions for beginners.',
  language_from = 'es', language_to = 'en'
where slug = 'basics';

update public.cards c set
  section_name = x.section_name, part_of_speech = x.part_of_speech, definition_en = x.definition_en,
  main_translations_es = coalesce(x.main_translations_es, '[]'::jsonb),
  collocations = coalesce(x.collocations, '[]'::jsonb),
  synonyms_en = coalesce(x.synonyms_en, '[]'::jsonb),
  example_sentence = x.example_sentence, example_es = x.example_es, example_en = x.example_en,
  mnemonic_en = coalesce(x.mnemonic_en, c.mnemonic_en),
  cloze_distractors_en = case when jsonb_array_length(coalesce(x.cloze_distractors_en, '[]'::jsonb)) > 0
                              then x.cloze_distractors_en else c.cloze_distractors_en end,
  examples = case when jsonb_array_length(coalesce(x.examples, '[]'::jsonb)) > 0
                  then x.examples else c.examples end
from (select id from public.decks where slug = 'basics') dk
cross join jsonb_to_recordset('[{"spanish_text":"Hola","english_text":"Hello","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"interjection","definition_en":"A word used when meeting someone or starting a conversation.","main_translations_es":["hola","buenas"],"collocations":["say hello","hello everyone","hello there"],"synonyms_en":["Hi","Greetings","Hey"],"example_sentence":"Hello, how are you?","example_es":"Hola, ¿cómo estás?","example_en":"Hello, how are you?","mnemonic_en":null,"cloze_distractors_en":["Maybe","Until","Below","Often"],"examples":[{"es":"Hola, ¿cómo estás?","en":"Hello, how are you?"},{"es":"¡Hola! Buenos días, ¿cómo ha amanecido usted?","en":"Hello! Good morning, how are you doing today?"},{"es":"Hola, mucho gusto en conocerte.","en":"Hello, nice to meet you."}]},{"spanish_text":"Gracias","english_text":"Thank you","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A polite expression used to show gratitude.","main_translations_es":["gracias","muchas gracias"],"collocations":["thank you very much","thank you for","say thank you"],"synonyms_en":["Thanks","Much appreciated","Many thanks"],"example_sentence":"Thank you for your help.","example_es":"Gracias por tu ayuda.","example_en":"Thank you for your help.","mnemonic_en":null,"cloze_distractors_en":["Excuse me","Pardon me","Believe me","Follow me"],"examples":[{"es":"Gracias por tu ayuda.","en":"Thank you for your help."},{"es":"Gracias por el regalo de cumpleaños.","en":"Thank you for the birthday present."},{"es":"Gracias por invitarme a cenar esta noche.","en":"Thank you for inviting me to dinner tonight."}]},{"spanish_text":"Por favor","english_text":"Please","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"A polite word used when asking for something or making a request.","main_translations_es":["por favor"],"collocations":["please help","please sit down","yes, please"],"synonyms_en":["kindly","if you would be so kind","pray"],"example_sentence":"Please open the door.","example_es":"Por favor, abre la puerta.","example_en":"Please open the door.","mnemonic_en":null,"cloze_distractors_en":["Unless","Despite","Instead"],"examples":[{"es":"Por favor, abre la puerta.","en":"Please open the door."},{"es":"Pásame la sal, por favor.","en":"Pass me the salt, please."},{"es":"Por favor, siéntate en esa silla.","en":"Please sit in that chair."}]},{"spanish_text":"Buenos días","english_text":"Good morning","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A greeting used in the early part of the day.","main_translations_es":["buenos días"],"collocations":["say good morning","good morning everyone","good morning sir"],"synonyms_en":["Morning","Top of the morning"],"example_sentence":"Good morning, teacher.","example_es":"Buenos días, profesora.","example_en":"Good morning, teacher.","mnemonic_en":null,"cloze_distractors_en":["Very hungry","Quite slowly","Almost ready","Highly likely"],"examples":[{"es":"Buenos días, profesora.","en":"Good morning, teacher."},{"es":"Buenos días, ¿cómo has dormido?","en":"Good morning, how did you sleep?"},{"es":"Al entrar en la cafetería, el camarero nos dijo: Buenos días.","en":"When we entered the cafe, the waiter said to us: Good morning."}]},{"spanish_text":"¿Cuánto cuesta?","english_text":"How much does it cost?","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"question","definition_en":"A question used to ask for the price of something.","main_translations_es":["¿cuánto cuesta?","¿qué precio tiene?"],"collocations":["how much does it cost","cost too much","cost a lot"],"synonyms_en":["What is the price?","What does it cost?","What is the cost?"],"example_sentence":"I like this shirt, how much does it cost?","example_es":"Me gusta esta camisa, ¿cuánto cuesta?","example_en":"I like this shirt, how much does it cost?","mnemonic_en":null,"cloze_distractors_en":["How many is that?","Where are they sold?","When is the time?","Which is the size?"],"examples":[{"es":"Me gusta esta camisa, ¿cuánto cuesta?","en":"I like this shirt, how much does it cost?"},{"es":"Voy a comprar manzanas, ¿cuánto cuesta el kilo?","en":"I am going to buy apples, how much does it cost per kilo?"},{"es":"El boleto para el cine es caro, ¿cuánto cuesta?","en":"The movie ticket is expensive, how much does it cost?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Adiós","english_text":"Goodbye","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"interjection","definition_en":"A word used to express farewell.","main_translations_es":["Hasta luego","Chao","Nos vemos"],"collocations":["Goodbye for now","Say goodbye to","Goodbye and good luck"],"synonyms_en":["Farewell","See you later","Take care"],"example_sentence":"Goodbye, see you tomorrow.","example_es":"Adiós, nos vemos mañana.","example_en":"Goodbye, see you tomorrow.","mnemonic_en":"I wave goodbye and shout adiós as the ship sails away.","cloze_distractors_en":["Welcome","Yesterday","Perhaps"],"examples":[{"es":"Adiós, nos vemos mañana.","en":"Goodbye, see you tomorrow."},{"es":"Le dije adiós a mi madre antes de subir al autobús.","en":"I said Goodbye to my mother before getting on the bus."},{"es":"Es hora de irse, así que adiós a todos.","en":"It is time to leave, so Goodbye to everyone."}]},{"spanish_text":"Buenas tardes","english_text":"Good afternoon","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A polite greeting used in the early afternoon.","main_translations_es":["Buenas tardes","Que tengas una buena tarde","Feliz tarde"],"collocations":["Good afternoon, everyone","Good afternoon, how are you?","Good afternoon, sir","Good afternoon, ladies and gentlemen"],"synonyms_en":["Hello","Good day","Hi"],"example_sentence":"Good afternoon, how are you?","example_es":"Buenas tardes, ¿cómo está usted?","example_en":"Good afternoon, how are you?","mnemonic_en":"Think of a good (buenas) tardy (tardes) afternoon sipping coffee.","cloze_distractors_en":["Very midnight","Quite breakfast","Mostly yesterday","Hardly tomorrow"],"examples":[{"es":"Buenas tardes, ¿cómo está usted?","en":"Good afternoon, how are you?"},{"es":"El profesor entró al salón y dijo: Buenas tardes a todos los alumnos.","en":"The teacher walked into the classroom and said: Good afternoon to all the students."},{"es":"Al llegar a la oficina después de comer, siempre saludo diciendo: Buenas tardes.","en":"When I arrive at the office after lunch, I always greet people by saying: Good afternoon."}]},{"spanish_text":"Buenas noches","english_text":"Good evening","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A polite greeting used in the early part of the night.","main_translations_es":["Buenas noches","Que tengas una buena noche","Que descanses"],"collocations":["Good evening, everyone","Good evening and welcome","Good evening, sir"],"synonyms_en":["Evening greetings","Pleasant evening","Hello"],"example_sentence":"Good evening, how was your day?","example_es":"Buenas noches, ¿cómo estuvo tu día?","example_en":"Good evening, how was your day?","mnemonic_en":"Think of a good night, because Good evening sounds like ''Buenas noches'' under a bright moon.","cloze_distractors_en":["Good breakfast","Good midnight","Good daylight","Good sunshine"],"examples":[{"es":"Buenas noches, ¿cómo estuvo tu día?","en":"Good evening, how was your day?"},{"es":"Al entrar al restaurante, el mesero nos dijo: Buenas noches.","en":"When we entered the restaurant, the waiter said to us: Good evening."},{"es":"Al ver a mis vecinos en el pasillo a las siete de la tarde, les dije: Buenas noches.","en":"When I saw my neighbors in the hallway at seven in the evening, I said to them: Good evening."}]},{"spanish_text":"¿Cómo estás?","english_text":"How are you?","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"question","definition_en":"A polite way to ask someone about their well-being.","main_translations_es":["¿Qué tal?","¿Cómo te va?","¿Cómo estás tú?"],"collocations":["How are you doing?","How are you feeling?","How are you today?"],"synonyms_en":["How''s it going?","What''s up?","How do you do?"],"example_sentence":"Hello, I haven''t seen you in a long time, how are you?","example_es":"Hola, hace mucho que no nos vemos, ¿cómo estás?","example_en":"Hello, I haven''t seen you in a long time, how are you?","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a coma patient asking How are you?","cloze_distractors_en":["Who are they?","Where is mine?","When was that?","Why is there?"],"examples":[{"es":"Hola, hace mucho que no nos vemos, ¿cómo estás?","en":"Hello, I haven''t seen you in a long time, how are you?"},{"es":"Te noto un poco triste hoy, ¿cómo estás?","en":"You seem a bit sad today, how are you?"},{"es":"Entro a la oficina y saludo a mi jefe: ¿cómo estás?","en":"I walk into the office and greet my boss: how are you?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Estoy bien","english_text":"I am fine","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A polite response indicating that one is doing well.","main_translations_es":["Estoy bien","Me encuentro bien","Todo bien"],"collocations":["I''m fine, thank you","I''m fine, how about you?","I''m fine, and you?"],"synonyms_en":["I''m okay","I''m well","I''m all right"],"example_sentence":"I am fine, thanks for asking.","example_es":"Estoy bien, gracias por preguntar.","example_en":"I am fine, thanks for asking.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a fine wine labeled bien, reminding you I am fine","cloze_distractors_en":["I eat bread","I run fast","I like blue","I jump high"],"examples":[{"es":"Estoy bien, gracias por preguntar.","en":"I am fine, thanks for asking."},{"es":"No te preocupes por mí, estoy bien.","en":"Don''t worry about me, I am fine."},{"es":"Aunque tuve un día largo, estoy bien.","en":"Even though I had a long day, I am fine."}]},{"spanish_text":"Sí","english_text":"Yes","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"interjection","definition_en":"An affirmative response used to indicate agreement or confirmation.","main_translations_es":["Sí","Claro","Por supuesto"],"collocations":["yes, please","yes indeed","yes and no","yes, that''s right"],"synonyms_en":["Sure","Certainly","Affirmative"],"example_sentence":"Do you want to go to the movies with me? Yes, I would love to go.","example_es":"¿Quieres ir al cine conmigo? Sí, me encantaría ir.","example_en":"Do you want to go to the movies with me? Yes, I would love to go.","mnemonic_en":"I nod and smile, shouting Yes like a bright sun saying sí.","cloze_distractors_en":["Never","Maybe","Hardly","Seldom"],"examples":[{"es":"¿Quieres ir al cine conmigo? Sí, me encantaría ir.","en":"Do you want to go to the movies with me? Yes, I would love to go."},{"es":"¿Es esta tu mochila? Sí, es mía.","en":"Is this your backpack? Yes, it is mine."},{"es":"¿Vas a terminar tu tarea hoy? Sí, la terminaré antes de cenar.","en":"Are you going to finish your homework today? Yes, I will finish it before dinner."}]},{"spanish_text":"No","english_text":"No","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"interjection","definition_en":"A word used to give a negative answer or to refuse something.","main_translations_es":["No","Negativo","De ninguna manera"],"collocations":["no way","no problem","no doubt","no thanks"],"synonyms_en":[],"example_sentence":"No, I don''t have time.","example_es":"No, no tengo tiempo.","example_en":"No, I don''t have time.","mnemonic_en":null,"cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"No, no tengo tiempo.","en":"No, I don''t have time."}]},{"spanish_text":"Tal vez","english_text":"Maybe","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"Perhaps; possibly.","main_translations_es":["Quizá","Quizás","Puede ser"],"collocations":["maybe later","maybe not","maybe tomorrow","maybe you"],"synonyms_en":["perhaps","possibly","could be"],"example_sentence":"Maybe it will rain tomorrow.","example_es":"Tal vez llueva mañana.","example_en":"Maybe it will rain tomorrow.","mnemonic_en":"A tall (tal) friend shrugs, unsure, and says maybe.","cloze_distractors_en":["Slowly","Briefly","Highly","Widely"],"examples":[{"es":"Tal vez llueva mañana.","en":"Maybe it will rain tomorrow."},{"es":"Tal vez lleguemos tarde a la reunión.","en":"Maybe we will arrive late to the meeting."},{"es":"Tal vez ella quiera ir al cine con nosotros.","en":"Maybe she wants to go to the movies with us."}]},{"spanish_text":"Hoy","english_text":"Today","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"the present day; the current date","main_translations_es":["En el día de hoy","Esta jornada","Actualmente"],"collocations":["today''s news","as of today","today''s date","today and tomorrow"],"synonyms_en":["this day","the present day"],"example_sentence":"Today I''m going to the market.","example_es":"Hoy voy al mercado.","example_en":"Today I''m going to the market.","mnemonic_en":"A bright toy flashes the date, reminding you it''s today.","cloze_distractors_en":["Somewhere","Whatever","Anywhere","However"],"examples":[{"es":"Hoy voy al mercado.","en":"Today I''m going to the market."},{"es":"Tenemos una reunión importante hoy.","en":"We have an important meeting today."},{"es":"El clima está muy soleado hoy.","en":"The weather is very sunny today."}]},{"spanish_text":"Mañana","english_text":"Tomorrow","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"The day after today.","main_translations_es":["El día siguiente","El día de mañana","Al día siguiente"],"collocations":["See you tomorrow","Tomorrow morning","Tomorrow night","Tomorrow''s agenda"],"synonyms_en":["the next day","the following day"],"example_sentence":"Tomorrow we will go to the park.","example_es":"Mañana iremos al parque.","example_en":"Tomorrow we will go to the park.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a tomato rowing a boat at sunrise, reminding you that mañana means tomorrow.","cloze_distractors_en":["Upward","Hardly","Awkward"],"examples":[{"es":"Mañana iremos al parque.","en":"Tomorrow we will go to the park."},{"es":"Tengo una cita médica mañana por la tarde.","en":"I have a doctor''s appointment tomorrow afternoon."},{"es":"La tienda estará cerrada mañana por ser festivo.","en":"The store will be closed tomorrow because it is a holiday."}]},{"spanish_text":"Ayer","english_text":"Yesterday","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"The day before today.","main_translations_es":["El día anterior","Ayer mismo"],"collocations":["I saw him yesterday","Yesterday was a good day","Yesterday''s news","Yesterday, I went to the park"],"synonyms_en":["the day before","the previous day"],"example_sentence":"Yesterday I went to the market and bought fruit.","example_es":"Ayer fui al mercado y compré frutas.","example_en":"Yesterday I went to the market and bought fruit.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a yawn (ayer) at sunrise, the day before today, that was yesterday.","cloze_distractors_en":["Elsewhere","Otherwise","Forward"],"examples":[{"es":"Ayer fui al mercado y compré frutas.","en":"Yesterday I went to the market and bought fruit."},{"es":"Terminé de leer este libro ayer por la noche.","en":"I finished reading this book yesterday at night."},{"es":"El examen de matemáticas fue ayer en la escuela.","en":"The math exam was yesterday at school."}]},{"spanish_text":"Lunes","english_text":"Monday","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Monday is the day of the week after Sunday and before Tuesday.","main_translations_es":["Lunes","el lunes","día lunes"],"collocations":["on Monday","Monday morning","Monday night","Monday blues"],"synonyms_en":["start of the week","first weekday","beginning of the week"],"example_sentence":"On Monday I go to the market.","example_es":"El lunes voy al mercado.","example_en":"On Monday I go to the market.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a bright moon on Monday lighting the word lunes on a calendar.","cloze_distractors_en":["Winter","Always","Nearby"],"examples":[{"es":"El lunes voy al mercado.","en":"On Monday I go to the market."},{"es":"Tengo una reunión importante el próximo lunes.","en":"I have an important meeting next Monday."},{"es":"El lunes es el primer día de la semana laboral.","en":"Monday is the first day of the work week."}]},{"spanish_text":"Martes","english_text":"Tuesday","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Tuesday is the second day of the week, following Monday and preceding Wednesday.","main_translations_es":["Martes","el martes","día martes"],"collocations":["on Tuesday","next Tuesday","Tuesday morning","Tuesday night"],"synonyms_en":["Tues.","the second day of the week"],"example_sentence":"Next Tuesday we will go to the movies.","example_es":"El próximo martes iremos al cine.","example_en":"Next Tuesday we will go to the movies.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a tiger dancing on Tuesday, yelling Martes.","cloze_distractors_en":["Yesterday","Midnight","Sometimes","Breakfast"],"examples":[{"es":"El próximo martes iremos al cine.","en":"Next Tuesday we will go to the movies."},{"es":"Tengo una cita con el dentista el martes por la mañana.","en":"I have a dentist appointment on Tuesday morning."},{"es":"La reunión semanal de la oficina es siempre el martes.","en":"The weekly office meeting is always on Tuesday."}]},{"spanish_text":"Miércoles","english_text":"Wednesday","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Wednesday is the third day of the week, following Tuesday and preceding Thursday.","main_translations_es":["Miércoles","el miércoles","el día miércoles"],"collocations":["on Wednesday","Wednesday morning","Wednesday afternoon","Wednesday night"],"synonyms_en":["midweek","hump day","the middle of the week"],"example_sentence":"Next Wednesday we will go to the movies.","example_es":"El próximo miércoles iremos al cine.","example_en":"Next Wednesday we will go to the movies.","mnemonic_en":"Wednesday sounds like when''s day, imagine a mid‑week market called miércoles.","cloze_distractors_en":["Yesterday","Sometimes","Everything","Elsewhere"],"examples":[{"es":"El próximo miércoles iremos al cine.","en":"Next Wednesday we will go to the movies."},{"es":"Tengo una reunión importante el miércoles por la mañana.","en":"I have an important meeting on Wednesday morning."},{"es":"La tienda cierra temprano todos los miércoles.","en":"The store closes early every Wednesday."}]},{"spanish_text":"Jueves","english_text":"Thursday","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Thursday is the fourth day of the week, following Wednesday and preceding Friday.","main_translations_es":["Jueves","el jueves"],"collocations":["on Thursday","Thursday night","Thursday morning"],"synonyms_en":["Thu","Thurs","Thor''s day"],"example_sentence":"Next Thursday we will go to the movies.","example_es":"El próximo jueves iremos al cine.","example_en":"Next Thursday we will go to the movies.","mnemonic_en":"Throw a juicy orange on Thursday to remember Jueves.","cloze_distractors_en":["Yesterday","Sometimes","Breakfast","Everything"],"examples":[{"es":"El próximo jueves iremos al cine.","en":"Next Thursday we will go to the movies."},{"es":"Tengo una reunión importante el jueves por la mañana.","en":"I have an important meeting on Thursday morning."},{"es":"La tienda cierra temprano todos los jueves.","en":"The store closes early every Thursday."}]},{"spanish_text":"Viernes","english_text":"Friday","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Friday is the fifth day of the week, following Thursday and preceding Saturday.","main_translations_es":["Viernes","el viernes","día viernes"],"collocations":["Thank God it''s Friday","Friday night","Friday the 13th","Friday afternoon"],"synonyms_en":["pre‑weekend day","end of the work week"],"example_sentence":"On Friday we will go to the movies.","example_es":"El viernes iremos al cine.","example_en":"On Friday we will go to the movies.","mnemonic_en":"I celebrate Friday by raising a ''vier'' (beer) toast, linking to Viernes.","cloze_distractors_en":["Always","Quickly","Inside","Nobody"],"examples":[{"es":"El viernes iremos al cine.","en":"On Friday we will go to the movies."},{"es":"Termino de trabajar el viernes por la tarde.","en":"I finish working on Friday afternoon."},{"es":"La fiesta de cumpleaños es este viernes.","en":"The birthday party is this Friday."}]},{"spanish_text":"Sábado","english_text":"Saturday","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Saturday is the seventh day of the week, following Friday and preceding Sunday.","main_translations_es":["sábado","día sábado"],"collocations":["on Saturday","Saturday night","Saturday morning"],"synonyms_en":["Sat.","weekend day","the Sabbath"],"example_sentence":"Next Saturday we will go to the park.","example_es":"El próximo sábado iremos al parque.","example_en":"Next Saturday we will go to the park.","mnemonic_en":"On Saturday I hear friends cheer Sábado as we start the weekend.","cloze_distractors_en":["Yesterday","Sometimes","Breakfast","Geography"],"examples":[{"es":"El próximo sábado iremos al parque.","en":"Next Saturday we will go to the park."},{"es":"La fiesta de cumpleaños será este sábado por la noche.","en":"The birthday party will be this Saturday night."},{"es":"El sábado es mi día favorito de la semana porque no tengo clases.","en":"Saturday is my favorite day of the week because I do not have classes."}]},{"spanish_text":"Domingo","english_text":"Sunday","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Sunday is the day of the week that follows Saturday and precedes Monday.","main_translations_es":["Domingo","día de descanso","día del Señor"],"collocations":["Sunday morning","Sunday brunch","Sunday best","Sunday school"],"synonyms_en":["the Sabbath","weekend day","day of rest"],"example_sentence":"Next Sunday we will go to the park.","example_es":"El próximo domingo iremos al parque.","example_en":"Next Sunday we will go to the park.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a bright Sunday with a golden dome rising over the town.","cloze_distractors_en":["Always","Quickly","Outside","Between"],"examples":[{"es":"El próximo domingo iremos al parque.","en":"Next Sunday we will go to the park."},{"es":"La tienda cierra temprano cada domingo.","en":"The store closes early every Sunday."},{"es":"Tenemos una reunión familiar este domingo.","en":"We have a family gathering this Sunday."}]},{"spanish_text":"Enero","english_text":"January","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"January is the first month of the year in the Gregorian calendar.","main_translations_es":["Enero","mes de enero","primer mes del año"],"collocations":["in January","January sales","January 1st","January weather"],"synonyms_en":["first month","New Year''s month","winter month"],"example_sentence":"My birthday is in January.","example_es":"Mi cumpleaños es en enero.","example_en":"My birthday is in January.","mnemonic_en":"Visualize a January snowflake shaped like the letter E for Enero.","cloze_distractors_en":["Tuesday","Yesterday","Midnight"],"examples":[{"es":"Mi cumpleaños es en enero.","en":"My birthday is in January."},{"es":"El año comienza en enero.","en":"The year begins in January."},{"es":"Hace mucho frío en enero.","en":"It is very cold in January."}]},{"spanish_text":"Febrero","english_text":"February","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The second month of the year in the Gregorian calendar.","main_translations_es":["Febrero","el mes de febrero","mes de febrero"],"collocations":["in February","February 14th","February weather","February sales"],"synonyms_en":["the second month","month after January","month before March"],"example_sentence":"My birthday is in February.","example_es":"Mi cumpleaños es en febrero.","example_en":"My birthday is in February.","mnemonic_en":"A feverish bear (Febrero) shivers during February.","cloze_distractors_en":["Wednesday","Yesterday","Afternoon","Tomorrow"],"examples":[{"es":"Mi cumpleaños es en febrero.","en":"My birthday is in February."},{"es":"El mes más corto del año es febrero.","en":"The shortest month of the year is February."},{"es":"Nos vamos de vacaciones a la nieve en febrero.","en":"We are going on a ski vacation in February."}]},{"spanish_text":"Marzo","english_text":"March","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The third month of the year in the Gregorian calendar.","main_translations_es":["Marzo","el mes de marzo","el tercer mes del año"],"collocations":["in March","March Madness","March onward","the month of March"],"synonyms_en":["stride","parade","trudge"],"example_sentence":"My birthday is in March.","example_es":"Mi cumpleaños es en marzo.","example_en":"My birthday is in March.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a marching band in March holding a banner that reads ''Marzo''.","cloze_distractors_en":["Clock","Bread","Floor"],"examples":[{"es":"Mi cumpleaños es en marzo.","en":"My birthday is in March."},{"es":"Las clases terminan a finales de marzo.","en":"Classes end at the end of March."},{"es":"El clima empieza a mejorar en marzo.","en":"The weather starts to get better in March."}]},{"spanish_text":"Abril","english_text":"April","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the fourth month of the year in the Gregorian calendar","main_translations_es":["mes de abril","el mes de abril"],"collocations":["April Fool''s Day","April showers","in April"],"synonyms_en":["the fourth month","spring month"],"example_sentence":"The fourth month of the year is April.","example_es":"El cuarto mes del año es abril.","example_en":"The fourth month of the year is April.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a bright spring flower blooming in April, echoing the Spanish word Abril","cloze_distractors_en":["Tuesday","Kitchen","Yellow"],"examples":[{"es":"El cuarto mes del año es abril.","en":"The fourth month of the year is April."},{"es":"Las flores empiezan a brotar en abril.","en":"Flowers start to bloom in April."},{"es":"Tenemos vacaciones escolares durante el mes de abril.","en":"We have school holidays during the month of April."}]},{"spanish_text":"Mayo","english_text":"May","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the fifth month of the year in the Gregorian calendar","main_translations_es":["Mayo","mes de mayo","el mes de mayo"],"collocations":["May I","May I help","May the force be with you","May the best man win"],"synonyms_en":["might","could","is allowed to"],"example_sentence":"My birthday is in May.","example_es":"Mi cumpleaños es en mayo.","example_en":"My birthday is in May.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a mayo jar dancing in May","cloze_distractors_en":["Blue","Fast","Near","Each"],"examples":[{"es":"Mi cumpleaños es en mayo.","en":"My birthday is in May."},{"es":"Las flores florecen durante el mes de mayo.","en":"Flowers bloom during the month of May."},{"es":"El festival de las flores se celebra cada año en mayo.","en":"The flower festival is held every year in May."}]},{"spanish_text":"Junio","english_text":"June","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"June is the sixth month of the year in the Gregorian calendar.","main_translations_es":["Junio","mes de junio","sexto mes del año"],"collocations":["in June","June 2023","June wedding","June holidays"],"synonyms_en":["the sixth month","early summer","mid-year month"],"example_sentence":"My birthday is in June.","example_es":"Mi cumpleaños es en junio.","example_en":"My birthday is in June.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a sunny June garden where a rooster says junio to welcome the month","cloze_distractors_en":["Table","Quick","Often","Bread"],"examples":[{"es":"Mi cumpleaños es en junio.","en":"My birthday is in June."},{"es":"Las clases terminan en junio.","en":"Classes finish in June."},{"es":"Nos casamos el próximo junio.","en":"We are getting married next June."}]},{"spanish_text":"Julio","english_text":"July","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"July is the seventh month of the year in the Gregorian calendar.","main_translations_es":["Julio","mes de julio","el séptimo mes"],"collocations":["in July","July heat","July vacation","July 4th"],"synonyms_en":["the seventh month","mid-summer","summer month"],"example_sentence":"My birthday is in July.","example_es":"Mi cumpleaños es en julio.","example_en":"My birthday is in July.","mnemonic_en":"Picture Julio lighting fireworks for the Fourth of July celebration.","cloze_distractors_en":["Lunch","Table","Clock","House"],"examples":[{"es":"Mi cumpleaños es en julio.","en":"My birthday is in July."},{"es":"Las vacaciones de verano empiezan en julio.","en":"Summer vacation starts in July."},{"es":"Hace mucho calor durante el mes de julio.","en":"It is very hot during the month of July."}]},{"spanish_text":"Agosto","english_text":"August","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The eighth month of the year in the Gregorian calendar.","main_translations_es":["Agosto","mes de agosto","el mes de agosto"],"collocations":["in August","August deadline","August heat","the month of August"],"synonyms_en":["the eighth month","summer month","eighth month of the year"],"example_sentence":"My birthday is in August.","example_es":"Mi cumpleaños es en agosto.","example_en":"My birthday is in August.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a gust of wind blowing over the Spanish calendar on Agosto, the month of August.","cloze_distractors_en":["Yesterday","Breakfast","Together","Midnight"],"examples":[{"es":"Mi cumpleaños es en agosto.","en":"My birthday is in August."},{"es":"Las vacaciones de verano terminan en agosto.","en":"Summer vacation ends in August."},{"es":"Hace mucho calor durante el mes de agosto.","en":"It is very hot during the month of August."}]},{"spanish_text":"Septiembre","english_text":"September","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"September is the ninth month of the year in the Gregorian calendar.","main_translations_es":["Septiembre","mes de septiembre","el noveno mes"],"collocations":["in September","September weather","September deadline","September sales"],"synonyms_en":["the ninth month","early fall"],"example_sentence":"My birthday is in September.","example_es":"Mi cumpleaños es en septiembre.","example_en":"My birthday is in September.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a septum (sept) on a calendar, showing the month September.","cloze_distractors_en":["Yesterday","Breakfast","Sometimes","Everything"],"examples":[{"es":"Mi cumpleaños es en septiembre.","en":"My birthday is in September."},{"es":"Las clases en la universidad comienzan en septiembre.","en":"Classes at the university start in September."},{"es":"El verano termina y el otoño empieza en septiembre.","en":"Summer ends and autumn begins in September."}]},{"spanish_text":"Octubre","english_text":"October","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"October is the tenth month of the year in the Gregorian calendar.","main_translations_es":["Octubre","mes de octubre","el mes de octubre"],"collocations":["in October","October rain","October surprise","October sky"],"synonyms_en":["tenth month","Fall month","autumn month"],"example_sentence":"My birthday is in October.","example_es":"Mi cumpleaños es en octubre.","example_en":"My birthday is in October.","mnemonic_en":"Picture an octopus (oct) with a blue leaf in October, chanting Octubre.","cloze_distractors_en":["Tuesday","Midnight","Yesterday"],"examples":[{"es":"Mi cumpleaños es en octubre.","en":"My birthday is in October."},{"es":"Las hojas de los árboles cambian de color en octubre.","en":"The leaves on the trees change color in October."},{"es":"Celebramos Halloween el treinta y uno de octubre.","en":"We celebrate Halloween on the thirty-first of October."}]},{"spanish_text":"Noviembre","english_text":"November","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The eleventh month of the year in the Gregorian calendar.","main_translations_es":["Noviembre","mes de noviembre","Nov."],"collocations":["in November","the month of November","late November","November 2023"],"synonyms_en":["Nov.","eleventh month"],"example_sentence":"My birthday is in November.","example_es":"Mi cumpleaños es en noviembre.","example_en":"My birthday is in November.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a new (nuevo) calendar page turning to November hearing Noviembre echo like a fresh start","cloze_distractors_en":["Saturday","Yesterday","Breakfast","Midnight"],"examples":[{"es":"Mi cumpleaños es en noviembre.","en":"My birthday is in November."},{"es":"Las hojas de los árboles caen durante noviembre.","en":"The leaves fall from the trees during November."},{"es":"El Día de Acción de Gracias se celebra en noviembre.","en":"Thanksgiving Day is celebrated in November."}]},{"spanish_text":"Diciembre","english_text":"December","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"December is the twelfth month of the year in the Gregorian calendar.","main_translations_es":["diciembre","mes de diciembre","el último mes del año"],"collocations":["in December","December holidays","December 25","December weather"],"synonyms_en":["the twelfth month","month twelve","the final month of the year"],"example_sentence":"My birthday is in December.","example_es":"Mi cumpleaños es en diciembre.","example_en":"My birthday is in December.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a dice falling into December because Diciembre sounds like dice.","cloze_distractors_en":["Tuesday","Midnight","Tomorrow","Yesterday"],"examples":[{"es":"Mi cumpleaños es en diciembre.","en":"My birthday is in December."},{"es":"La Navidad se celebra cada año en diciembre.","en":"Christmas is celebrated every year in December."},{"es":"El invierno comienza oficialmente en diciembre.","en":"Winter officially begins in December."}]},{"spanish_text":"Uno","english_text":"One","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"numeral (cardinal)","definition_en":"The number that follows zero and precedes two.","main_translations_es":["Un","Primer","Primero"],"collocations":["one by one","one of a kind","one and only","one more time"],"synonyms_en":["single","sole","a single"],"example_sentence":"I have only one brother at school.","example_es":"Tengo solo uno hermano en la escuela.","example_en":"I have only one brother at school.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a single UNO card labeled ONE on the table.","cloze_distractors_en":["None","Many","Each"],"examples":[{"es":"Tengo solo uno hermano en la escuela.","en":"I have only one brother at school."},{"es":"El equipo anotó uno gol al final del partido.","en":"The team scored one goal at the end of the game."},{"es":"Solo queda un pastel en la bandeja.","en":"There is only one cake left on the tray."}]},{"spanish_text":"Dos","english_text":"Two","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"numeral","definition_en":"The cardinal number that follows one and precedes three.","main_translations_es":["Dos","el número dos","un par"],"collocations":["two weeks","two people","two times","two-thirds"],"synonyms_en":["a pair","both","couple"],"example_sentence":"I have two dogs.","example_es":"Tengo dos perros.","example_en":"I have two dogs.","mnemonic_en":"Picture two dice forming the letters D‑O‑S on the table.","cloze_distractors_en":["Blue","Hard","Late"],"examples":[{"es":"Tengo dos perros.","en":"I have two dogs."},{"es":"El reloj marca las dos en punto.","en":"The clock shows two o''clock."},{"es":"Compré dos manzanas en el mercado.","en":"I bought two apples at the market."}]},{"spanish_text":"Tres","english_text":"Three","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"numeral","definition_en":"The cardinal number that follows two and precedes four.","main_translations_es":["tres","el número tres","tres unidades"],"collocations":["three times","three days","three people","three hundred"],"synonyms_en":["trio","triad","triple"],"example_sentence":"I have three apples in my backpack.","example_es":"Tengo tres manzanas en mi mochila.","example_en":"I have three apples in my backpack.","mnemonic_en":"Three tall trees sway, reminding me of tres.","cloze_distractors_en":["Every","Which","Their"],"examples":[{"es":"Tengo tres manzanas en mi mochila.","en":"I have three apples in my backpack."},{"es":"El semáforo tiene tres colores: rojo, amarillo y verde.","en":"The traffic light has three colors: red, yellow, and green."},{"es":"Mi hermano pequeño tiene tres años de edad.","en":"My little brother is three years old."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cuatro","english_text":"Four","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The number that comes after three and before five.","main_translations_es":["cuatro","el número cuatro","el cuatro"],"collocations":["four of a kind","four wheels","four seasons","four corners"],"synonyms_en":["quartet","quad","IV"],"example_sentence":"I have four books on the table.","example_es":"Tengo cuatro libros en la mesa.","example_en":"I have four books on the table.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a four‑leaf clover shaped like a tiny Cuatro guitar.","cloze_distractors_en":["Heavy","Empty","Often","Every"],"examples":[{"es":"Tengo cuatro libros en la mesa.","en":"I have four books on the table."},{"es":"El coche tiene cuatro ruedas nuevas.","en":"The car has four new wheels."},{"es":"Mi hermano pequeño tiene cuatro años.","en":"My little brother is four years old."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cinco","english_text":"Five","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"numeral","definition_en":"The cardinal number that comes after four and before six.","main_translations_es":["cinco","el número cinco","el 5"],"collocations":["five o''clock","five-star","five minutes","five percent"],"synonyms_en":["pentad","quintet"],"example_sentence":"I have five apples.","example_es":"Tengo cinco manzanas.","example_en":"I have five apples.","mnemonic_en":"Visualize five fingers sinking into a jar labeled CINCO.","cloze_distractors_en":["Heavy","Quick","Early"],"examples":[{"es":"Tengo cinco manzanas.","en":"I have five apples."},{"es":"El reloj marca las cinco en punto.","en":"The clock shows five o''clock."},{"es":"Mi hermano menor tiene cinco años.","en":"My little brother is five years old."}]},{"spanish_text":"Seis","english_text":"Six","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"numeral","definition_en":"The integer that comes after five and before seven.","main_translations_es":["seis","el número seis","el 6"],"collocations":["six-pack","six feet under","six of one, half a dozen","sixth sense"],"synonyms_en":["half a dozen","sextet"],"example_sentence":"There were six empty chairs, so six people sat down at the table.","example_es":"Había seis sillas vacías, así que seis personas se sentaron a la mesa.","example_en":"There were six empty chairs, so six people sat down at the table.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine six dice shouting seis as they tumble across the table.","cloze_distractors_en":["None","Minus","Twice","Every"],"examples":[{"es":"Había seis sillas vacías, así que seis personas se sentaron a la mesa.","en":"There were six empty chairs, so six people sat down at the table."},{"es":"El reloj marca las seis de la tarde.","en":"The clock shows six in the afternoon."},{"es":"Compré seis manzanas rojas en el mercado.","en":"I bought six red apples at the market."}]},{"spanish_text":"Siete","english_text":"Seven","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The cardinal number that comes after six and before eight.","main_translations_es":["siete","el número siete"],"collocations":["seven wonders","seven days","seven seas","seven years"],"synonyms_en":["VII","septet","heptad"],"example_sentence":"I have seven books on my shelf.","example_es":"Tengo siete libros en mi estantería.","example_en":"I have seven books on my shelf.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a lucky seven dice shouting siete as it rolls.","cloze_distractors_en":["Always","Quickly","Behind"],"examples":[{"es":"Tengo siete libros en mi estantería.","en":"I have seven books on my shelf."},{"es":"La semana tiene siete días.","en":"The week has seven days."},{"es":"Mi hermano menor tiene siete años.","en":"My younger brother is seven years old."}]},{"spanish_text":"Ocho","english_text":"Eight","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The number that comes after seven and before nine.","main_translations_es":["el ocho","el número ocho","el dígito ocho"],"collocations":["eight ball","eight years old","eightfold","eight miles"],"synonyms_en":["octet","eightfold"],"example_sentence":"I have eight apples.","example_es":"Tengo ocho manzanas.","example_en":"I have eight apples.","mnemonic_en":"Picture an octopus juggling eight shells while saying ocho.","cloze_distractors_en":["Heavy","Empty","Early","Angry"],"examples":[{"es":"Tengo ocho manzanas.","en":"I have eight apples."},{"es":"El reloj marca las ocho en punto.","en":"The clock shows eight o''clock."},{"es":"Mi hermano menor tiene ocho años.","en":"My little brother is eight years old."}]},{"spanish_text":"Nueve","english_text":"Nine","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The number that comes after eight and before ten.","main_translations_es":["nueve","el número nueve","IX"],"collocations":["nine times","nine out of ten","cloud nine","nine-to-five"],"synonyms_en":["IX","nonet"],"example_sentence":"I have nine books on my shelf.","example_es":"Tengo nueve libros en mi estantería.","example_en":"I have nine books on my shelf.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine nine neon signs spelling N-I-N-E above a Spanish fiesta where everyone shouts Nueve.","cloze_distractors_en":["Often","Quick","Below","Maybe"],"examples":[{"es":"Tengo nueve libros en mi estantería.","en":"I have nine books on my shelf."},{"es":"La clase termina a las nueve de la mañana.","en":"The class ends at nine in the morning."},{"es":"Mi hermano pequeño tiene nueve años.","en":"My little brother is nine years old."}]},{"spanish_text":"Diez","english_text":"Ten","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The number that follows nine and precedes eleven.","main_translations_es":["diez","el número diez","diez unidades"],"collocations":["ten percent","ten years","ten out of ten","tenfold"],"synonyms_en":["X","deca","a perfect score"],"example_sentence":"The test has ten questions that you must answer before the time is up.","example_es":"El examen tiene diez preguntas que debes responder antes de que termine el tiempo.","example_en":"The test has ten questions that you must answer before the time is up.","mnemonic_en":"Picture ten dice tumbling, because diez sounds like dice.","cloze_distractors_en":["Blue","Fast","Late"],"examples":[{"es":"El examen tiene diez preguntas que debes responder antes de que termine el tiempo.","en":"The test has ten questions that you must answer before the time is up."},{"es":"El reloj marca las diez de la mañana.","en":"The clock shows ten in the morning."},{"es":"Una persona tiene diez dedos en sus dos manos.","en":"A person has ten fingers on their two hands."}]},{"spanish_text":"Rojo","english_text":"Red","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"The color at the end of the visible spectrum next to orange and opposite violet.","main_translations_es":["rojo","color rojo","carmesí"],"collocations":["red light","red wine","red carpet","red alert"],"synonyms_en":["crimson","scarlet","ruby"],"example_sentence":"The red car is parked in front of the house.","example_es":"El coche rojo está estacionado frente a la casa.","example_en":"The red car is parked in front of the house.","mnemonic_en":"Red like a ripe rojo tomato.","cloze_distractors_en":["Quickly","Always","Slowly","Hardly"],"examples":[{"es":"El coche rojo está estacionado frente a la casa.","en":"The red car is parked in front of the house."},{"es":"Ella se puso un vestido rojo para la fiesta de graduación.","en":"She wore a red dress to the graduation party."},{"es":"Las manzanas de este árbol son de color rojo cuando están maduras.","en":"The apples on this tree are red when they are ripe."}]},{"spanish_text":"Azul","english_text":"Blue","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"A color that resembles the clear sky on a sunny day.","main_translations_es":["azul","celeste","azul marino"],"collocations":["feeling blue","out of the blue","blue sky","blue blood"],"synonyms_en":["azure","cerulean","navy"],"example_sentence":"The sky is blue today.","example_es":"El cielo está azul hoy.","example_en":"The sky is blue today.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a blue zoo—azul—where every animal is painted sky‑blue.","cloze_distractors_en":["Tasty","Loudly","Quick"],"examples":[{"es":"El cielo está azul hoy.","en":"The sky is blue today."},{"es":"Ella lleva un vestido azul a la fiesta.","en":"She is wearing a blue dress to the party."},{"es":"El mar se ve muy azul desde la playa.","en":"The ocean looks very blue from the beach."}]},{"spanish_text":"Verde","english_text":"Green","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"A color between blue and yellow in the visible spectrum.","main_translations_es":["verde","color verde","verde intenso"],"collocations":["green light","green thumb","greenhouse","green tea"],"synonyms_en":["emerald","verdant","leafy"],"example_sentence":"The traffic light turned green and the cars started to move.","example_es":"El semáforo cambió a verde y los coches empezaron a avanzar.","example_en":"The traffic light turned green and the cars started to move.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a green frog shouting Verde!","cloze_distractors_en":["Square","Heavy","Silent","Narrow"],"examples":[{"es":"El semáforo cambió a verde y los coches empezaron a avanzar.","en":"The traffic light turned green and the cars started to move."},{"es":"Las hojas de los árboles son verde en verano.","en":"The leaves on the trees are green in the summer."},{"es":"La manzana que estoy comiendo es verde.","en":"The apple I am eating is green."}]},{"spanish_text":"Amarillo","english_text":"Yellow","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"A bright color between green and orange in the visible spectrum.","main_translations_es":["amarillo","color amarillo","amarillento"],"collocations":["yellow fever","yellow light","yellow pages","mellow yellow"],"synonyms_en":["golden","amber","lemon"],"example_sentence":"The car I bought is yellow.","example_es":"El coche que compré es de color amarillo.","example_en":"The car I bought is yellow.","mnemonic_en":"A bright yellow sun shouts amarillo across the sky","cloze_distractors_en":["Fluent","Hourly","Absent"],"examples":[{"es":"El coche que compré es de color amarillo.","en":"The car I bought is yellow."},{"es":"El limón está maduro y tiene un color amarillo brillante.","en":"The lemon is ripe and has a bright yellow color."},{"es":"Ella pintó las paredes de su habitación de color amarillo.","en":"She painted the walls of her room yellow."}]},{"spanish_text":"Negro","english_text":"Black","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"The darkest color, resulting from the absence or complete absorption of visible light.","main_translations_es":["Oscuro","Azabache"],"collocations":["black coffee","black cat","black market","black and white"],"synonyms_en":["dark","ebony","jet"],"example_sentence":"The black cat sleeps on the sofa.","example_es":"El gato negro duerme en el sofá.","example_en":"The black cat sleeps on the sofa.","mnemonic_en":"The black coat matches the dark negro night sky","cloze_distractors_en":["Musical","Vertical","Frequent"],"examples":[{"es":"El gato negro duerme en el sofá.","en":"The black cat sleeps on the sofa."},{"es":"Ella lleva un vestido negro para la fiesta.","en":"She wears a black dress for the party."},{"es":"El cielo se puso negro antes de la tormenta.","en":"The sky turned black before the storm."}]},{"spanish_text":"Blanco","english_text":"White","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"The color of milk or snow, a light, achromatic hue.","main_translations_es":["blanco","albo","pálido"],"collocations":["white paper","white house","white noise","white wine"],"synonyms_en":["pale","snowy","ivory"],"example_sentence":"The paper is white and ready to write.","example_es":"El papel es blanco y listo para escribir.","example_en":"The paper is white and ready to write.","mnemonic_en":"White like the blanco snow sparkling under the sun","cloze_distractors_en":["Heavy","Early","Daily"],"examples":[{"es":"El papel es blanco y listo para escribir.","en":"The paper is white and ready to write."},{"es":"La nieve cubre el jardín y todo se ve blanco.","en":"The snow covers the garden and everything looks white."},{"es":"Ella pintó la pared de su habitación de color blanco.","en":"She painted her bedroom wall white."}]},{"spanish_text":"Naranja","english_text":"Orange","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A round citrus fruit with a thick orange skin and sweet, juicy flesh.","main_translations_es":["fruta cítrica","citrico","color naranja"],"collocations":["orange juice","orange peel","orange tree","orange slice"],"synonyms_en":["amber","tangerine","citrus hue"],"example_sentence":"I bought an orange for breakfast.","example_es":"Compré una naranja para el desayuno.","example_en":"I bought an orange for breakfast.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a bright orange fruit shouting Naranja at the market.","cloze_distractors_en":["Engine","Office","Island","Anchor"],"examples":[{"es":"Compré una naranja para el desayuno.","en":"I bought an orange for breakfast."},{"es":"Ella exprimió una naranja para obtener jugo fresco.","en":"She squeezed an orange to get fresh juice."},{"es":"El niño peló la naranja con mucho cuidado.","en":"The boy peeled the orange very carefully."}]},{"spanish_text":"Rosa","english_text":"Pink","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"A pale red color.","main_translations_es":["flor","color rosado","rosa (nombre propio)"],"collocations":["in the pink","pink slip","pink noise","pink flamingo"],"synonyms_en":["rosy","blush","magenta"],"example_sentence":"Cotton candy has a very bright pink color.","example_es":"El algodón de azúcar tiene un color rosa muy brillante.","example_en":"Cotton candy has a very bright pink color.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a pink rose, a bright rosa, blooming to remind you pink.","cloze_distractors_en":["Hard","Fast","Deep","Cold"],"examples":[{"es":"El algodón de azúcar tiene un color rosa muy brillante.","en":"Cotton candy has a very bright pink color."},{"es":"Ella pintó las paredes de su cuarto de color rosa.","en":"She painted her bedroom walls pink."},{"es":"El flamenco es un ave de plumaje rosa.","en":"The flamingo is a bird with pink feathers."}]},{"spanish_text":"Marrón","english_text":"Brown","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"A dark orange‑red color resembling chocolate or earth.","main_translations_es":["café","pardo","castaño"],"collocations":["brown sugar","brown eyes","brown bear","brown paper"],"synonyms_en":["tan","chocolate","umber"],"example_sentence":"I bought a brown jacket for the fall.","example_es":"Compré una chaqueta marrón para el otoño.","example_en":"I bought a brown jacket for the fall.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a brown bear wearing a maroon (marrón) scarf.","cloze_distractors_en":["Musical","Vertical","Polite","Liquid"],"examples":[{"es":"Compré una chaqueta marrón para el otoño.","en":"I bought a brown jacket for the fall."},{"es":"El oso que vimos en el bosque era de color marrón.","en":"The bear we saw in the forest was brown."},{"es":"Ella tiene los ojos de color marrón oscuro.","en":"She has dark brown eyes."}]},{"spanish_text":"Gris","english_text":"Gray","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"A neutral color that lies between black and white.","main_translations_es":["gris","grisáceo","gris claro"],"collocations":["gray area","gray matter","gray hair","gray sky"],"synonyms_en":["ashen","slate","charcoal"],"example_sentence":"The sky is gray today.","example_es":"El cielo está gris hoy.","example_en":"The sky is gray today.","mnemonic_en":"A gray stone rolls and mutters ''gris'' to the wind.","cloze_distractors_en":["Loud","Sour","Fast","Busy"],"examples":[{"es":"El cielo está gris hoy.","en":"The sky is gray today."},{"es":"Mi gato tiene el pelo gris.","en":"My cat has gray fur."},{"es":"El humo de la chimenea es gris.","en":"The smoke from the chimney is gray."}]},{"spanish_text":"Madre","english_text":"Mother","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A female parent.","main_translations_es":["mamá","madre"],"collocations":["mother''s day","mother tongue","mother nature","mother figure"],"synonyms_en":["mom","mum","parent"],"example_sentence":"My mother cooks dinner every night.","example_es":"Mi madre cocina la cena todas las noches.","example_en":"My mother cooks dinner every night.","mnemonic_en":"A mother cradles a mad rabbit named Madre, linking mother and madre.","cloze_distractors_en":["Fridge","Street","Window","Planet"],"examples":[{"es":"Mi madre cocina la cena todas las noches.","en":"My mother cooks dinner every night."},{"es":"Llamé a mi madre para felicitarla por su cumpleaños.","en":"I called my mother to wish her a happy birthday."},{"es":"La madre cuida a su bebé en el parque.","en":"The mother takes care of her baby in the park."}]},{"spanish_text":"Padre","english_text":"Father","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A male parent.","main_translations_es":["Papá","Papi","Progenitor"],"collocations":["father figure","father of the bride","father and son","father time"],"synonyms_en":["dad","pop","pa"],"example_sentence":"My father taught me how to ride a bike.","example_es":"Mi padre me enseñó a montar en bicicleta.","example_en":"My father taught me how to ride a bike.","mnemonic_en":"Visualize a dad holding a pad, shouting ''pa!''—that''s a Father.","cloze_distractors_en":["Bicycle","Kitchen","Morning","Window"],"examples":[{"es":"Mi padre me enseñó a montar en bicicleta.","en":"My father taught me how to ride a bike."},{"es":"El padre de Juan trabaja en un hospital como médico.","en":"Juan''s father works at a hospital as a doctor."},{"es":"Cada domingo, mi padre prepara el desayuno para toda la familia.","en":"Every Sunday, my father makes breakfast for the whole family."}]},{"spanish_text":"Hermano","english_text":"Brother","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A male sibling.","main_translations_es":["hermano","pariente masculino"],"collocations":["big brother","brotherly love","brother in arms","brotherhood"],"synonyms_en":["male sibling","bro","sib"],"example_sentence":"My little brother is playing with his toys on the floor.","example_es":"Mi hermano pequeño juega con sus juguetes en el suelo.","example_en":"My little brother is playing with his toys on the floor.","mnemonic_en":"Picture your brother shaking your hand, because brother sounds like her mano.","cloze_distractors_en":["Kitchen","Pencil","Window","Butter"],"examples":[{"es":"Mi hermano pequeño juega con sus juguetes en el suelo.","en":"My little brother is playing with his toys on the floor."},{"es":"El hermano de María juega al fútbol en el parque.","en":"Maria''s brother plays soccer in the park."},{"es":"Mi hermano mayor trabaja como ingeniero en una oficina.","en":"My older brother works as an engineer in an office."}]},{"spanish_text":"Hermana","english_text":"Sister","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A female sibling.","main_translations_es":["hermana","hermana mayor","hermana menor"],"collocations":["big sister","little sister","sister city","sister company"],"synonyms_en":["sis","female sibling","sibling"],"example_sentence":"My sister lives in Madrid.","example_es":"Mi hermana vive en Madrid.","example_en":"My sister lives in Madrid.","mnemonic_en":"Picture your sister giving a man a bottle of her mana.","cloze_distractors_en":["Kitchen","Pencil","Window","Butter"],"examples":[{"es":"Mi hermana vive en Madrid.","en":"My sister lives in Madrid."},{"es":"Le compré un regalo de cumpleaños a mi hermana.","en":"I bought a birthday present for my sister."},{"es":"Mi hermana mayor trabaja como doctora en el hospital.","en":"My sister works as a doctor at the hospital."}]},{"spanish_text":"Hijo","english_text":"Son","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A male child or offspring.","main_translations_es":["hijo","varón","crío"],"collocations":["son of a gun","son of the president","son of the soil"],"synonyms_en":["male child","offspring","heir"],"example_sentence":"My son is studying medicine at university.","example_es":"Mi hijo está estudiando medicina en la universidad.","example_en":"My son is studying medicine at university.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a son yelling ''hee-yo!'' in a sunny field, linking Son to Spanish hijo.","cloze_distractors_en":["Sun","Sin","Fan","Pan"],"examples":[{"es":"Mi hijo está estudiando medicina en la universidad.","en":"My son is studying medicine at university."},{"es":"El hijo de mi vecina juega al fútbol en el parque todos los sábados.","en":"My neighbor''s son plays soccer in the park every Saturday."},{"es":"Cada vez que veo a mi hijo, me sorprende lo rápido que ha crecido.","en":"Every time I see my son, I am surprised by how fast he has grown."}]},{"spanish_text":"Hija","english_text":"Daughter","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A female child in relation to her parents.","main_translations_es":["hija","descendiente femenina"],"collocations":["my daughter","elder daughter","only daughter","stepdaughter"],"synonyms_en":["female offspring","girl child","offspring"],"example_sentence":"My daughter is studying medicine at the university.","example_es":"Mi hija está estudiando medicina en la universidad.","example_en":"My daughter is studying medicine at the university.","mnemonic_en":"A daughter cheers hee ya while climbing the tree.","cloze_distractors_en":["Bachelor","Calendar","Semester"],"examples":[{"es":"Mi hija está estudiando medicina en la universidad.","en":"My daughter is studying medicine at the university."},{"es":"La hija de María acaba de cumplir cinco años hoy.","en":"Maria''s daughter just turned five years old today."},{"es":"El señor Pérez llevó a su hija al parque para jugar.","en":"Mr. Perez took his daughter to the park to play."}]},{"spanish_text":"Amigo","english_text":"Friend","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person with whom one shares a bond of mutual affection and trust.","main_translations_es":["Camarada","Compañero","Colega"],"collocations":["close friend","best friend","friendship","friend in need"],"synonyms_en":["buddy","pal","companion"],"example_sentence":"My friend helped me move on Saturday.","example_es":"Mi amigo me ayudó a mudarme el sábado.","example_en":"My friend helped me move on Saturday.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine an AMIGO smiling as he greets his FRIEND with a warm hug","cloze_distractors_en":["Stranger","Furniture","Vegetable"],"examples":[{"es":"Mi amigo me ayudó a mudarme el sábado.","en":"My friend helped me move on Saturday."},{"es":"Invité a mi mejor amigo a cenar a mi casa esta noche.","en":"I invited my best friend to have dinner at my house tonight."},{"es":"Ese chico es un buen amigo de la escuela primaria.","en":"That boy is a good friend from elementary school."}]},{"spanish_text":"Familia","english_text":"Family","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A group of related individuals, such as parents and their children, or people connected by blood, marriage, or adoption.","main_translations_es":["Familia","Parentesco","Hogar"],"collocations":["family tree","family reunion","family member","family ties"],"synonyms_en":["relatives","kin","household"],"example_sentence":"My family gets together every Sunday for dinner.","example_es":"Mi familia se reúne cada domingo para cenar juntos.","example_en":"My family gets together every Sunday for dinner.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a happy family gathered around a table with a big banner reading familia","cloze_distractors_en":["Furniture","Hardware","Software","Beverage"],"examples":[{"es":"Mi familia se reúne cada domingo para cenar juntos.","en":"My family gets together every Sunday for dinner."},{"es":"Llevo una foto de mi familia en mi cartera para verla cuando estoy lejos.","en":"I carry a photo of my family in my wallet to look at when I am away."},{"es":"Pasar tiempo con mi familia es lo más importante durante las vacaciones.","en":"Spending time with my family is the most important thing during the holidays."}]},{"spanish_text":"Bebé","english_text":"Baby","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A very young child or infant.","main_translations_es":["bebé","infante","niño pequeño"],"collocations":["baby shower","baby steps","baby boom","cry like a baby"],"synonyms_en":["infant","newborn","little one"],"example_sentence":"The baby is sleeping in its crib.","example_es":"El bebé está durmiendo en su cuna.","example_en":"The baby is sleeping in its crib.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a tiny baby cooing \"bebe\" like a soft lullaby.","cloze_distractors_en":["Table","Clock","Brick","Shelf"],"examples":[{"es":"El bebé está durmiendo en su cuna.","en":"The baby is sleeping in its crib."},{"es":"La madre sostiene al bebé en sus brazos con mucho cuidado.","en":"The mother holds the baby in her arms very carefully."},{"es":"El bebé empezó a llorar porque tenía hambre.","en":"The baby started to cry because it was hungry."}]},{"spanish_text":"Niño","english_text":"Child","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A young human being.","main_translations_es":["chico","infante","menor"],"collocations":["child care","child development","child support","child prodigy"],"synonyms_en":["kid","youngster","minor"],"example_sentence":"The child plays in the park.","example_es":"El niño juega en el parque.","example_en":"The child plays in the park.","mnemonic_en":"A child kneels and says \"knee, no!\"","cloze_distractors_en":["Table","Cloud","Brick","Clock"],"examples":[{"es":"El niño juega en el parque.","en":"The child plays in the park."},{"es":"La madre sostiene a su niño en brazos.","en":"The mother holds her child in her arms."},{"es":"El niño pequeño llora porque tiene hambre.","en":"The small child is crying because he is hungry."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cabeza","english_text":"Head","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the upper part of the human body that contains the brain, eyes, ears, nose, and mouth","main_translations_es":["cabeza","coco","cráneo"],"collocations":["head over heels","head start","head of the class","head and shoulders"],"synonyms_en":["cranium","noggin","skull"],"example_sentence":"My head hurts.","example_es":"Me duele la cabeza.","example_en":"My head hurts.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a hedgehog balancing a tiny hat on its cabeza.","cloze_distractors_en":["Floor","Cloud","Bread","Shelf"],"examples":[{"es":"Me duele la cabeza.","en":"My head hurts."},{"es":"Él asintió con la cabeza para decir que sí.","en":"He nodded his head to say yes."},{"es":"Lleva un sombrero sobre la cabeza.","en":"She wears a hat on her head."}]},{"spanish_text":"Ojo","english_text":"Eye","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The organ of sight in humans and many animals.","main_translations_es":["mirada","vista","óculo"],"collocations":["keep an eye on","in the blink of an eye","the apple of my eye","eye contact"],"synonyms_en":["ocular organ","peeper","orb"],"example_sentence":"My eye hurts.","example_es":"Me duele el ojo.","example_en":"My eye hurts.","mnemonic_en":"Picture an eye shaped like an O that says ''jo'' when you look.","cloze_distractors_en":["Idea","Area","Date","Goal"],"examples":[{"es":"Me duele el ojo.","en":"My eye hurts."},{"es":"Cierra el ojo derecho para apuntar mejor.","en":"Close your right eye to aim better."},{"es":"Le entró una basurita en el ojo.","en":"A little bit of dust got into his eye."}]},{"spanish_text":"Nariz","english_text":"Nose","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The protruding organ on the face used for smelling and breathing.","main_translations_es":["Nariz","Hocico","Pico"],"collocations":["runny nose","nose job","keep your nose out","nose to the grindstone"],"synonyms_en":["snout","schnoz","nasal organ"],"example_sentence":"My nose hurts when I breathe cold air.","example_es":"Me duele la nariz cuando respiro aire frío.","example_en":"My nose hurts when I breathe cold air.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a nose shouting no while a giant naríz watches it.","cloze_distractors_en":["Foot","Neck","Back"],"examples":[{"es":"Me duele la nariz cuando respiro aire frío.","en":"My nose hurts when I breathe cold air."},{"es":"El payaso tiene una nariz roja y muy grande.","en":"The clown has a red and very big nose."},{"es":"Ella se limpia la nariz con un pañuelo de papel.","en":"She wipes her nose with a tissue."}]},{"spanish_text":"Boca","english_text":"Mouth","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The opening in the face through which a person eats, speaks, and breathes.","main_translations_es":["boca","hocico"],"collocations":["mouth water","mouth of the river","mouth guard","mouthful"],"synonyms_en":["oral cavity","maw","opening"],"example_sentence":"My mouth hurts after eating ice cream.","example_es":"Me duele la boca después de comer helado.","example_en":"My mouth hurts after eating ice cream.","mnemonic_en":"My mouth says boca when I chew tacos","cloze_distractors_en":["Elbow","Finger","Shoulder","Knuckle"],"examples":[{"es":"Me duele la boca después de comer helado.","en":"My mouth hurts after eating ice cream."},{"es":"Cierra la boca mientras masticas la comida.","en":"Close your mouth while you chew your food."},{"es":"El dentista me pidió que abriera la boca para revisarme.","en":"The dentist asked me to open my mouth for a checkup."}]},{"spanish_text":"Mano","english_text":"Hand","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The five‑fingered, prehensile extremity at the end of a human arm used for grasping and manipulating objects.","main_translations_es":["mano","palma","manita"],"collocations":["hand in hand","hand over","hand out"],"synonyms_en":["palm","mitt","grip"],"example_sentence":"My hand hurts after hitting the table.","example_es":"Me duele la mano después de golpear la mesa.","example_en":"My hand hurts after hitting the table.","mnemonic_en":"I hand you a mano of cards.","cloze_distractors_en":["Floor","Cloud","Bread","Month"],"examples":[{"es":"Me duele la mano después de golpear la mesa.","en":"My hand hurts after hitting the table."},{"es":"Levanta la mano si sabes la respuesta.","en":"Raise your hand if you know the answer."},{"es":"Ella sostiene una manzana en la mano.","en":"She is holding an apple in her hand."}]},{"spanish_text":"Brazo","english_text":"Arm","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The upper limb of the human body extending from the shoulder to the hand.","main_translations_es":["brazo","miembro superior"],"collocations":["arm of a chair","arm around","arm wrestling","arm strength"],"synonyms_en":["limb","upper limb","appendage"],"example_sentence":"My arm hurts after lifting weights.","example_es":"Me duele el brazo después de levantar pesas.","example_en":"My arm hurts after lifting weights.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a muscular arm holding a bra, turning it into a brazo.","cloze_distractors_en":["Idea","Goal","Date"],"examples":[{"es":"Me duele el brazo después de levantar pesas.","en":"My arm hurts after lifting weights."},{"es":"Ella tiene un tatuaje pequeño en su brazo derecho.","en":"She has a small tattoo on her right arm."},{"es":"El médico me tomó la presión en el brazo.","en":"The doctor checked my blood pressure on my arm."}]},{"spanish_text":"Pierna","english_text":"Leg","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A limb of the human body used for standing and walking, extending from the hip to the foot.","main_translations_es":["Pierna","Extremidad inferior","Miembro inferior"],"collocations":["leg of a table","leg day","leg injury","leg room"],"synonyms_en":["limb","lower limb","appendage"],"example_sentence":"My leg hurts after running.","example_es":"Me duele la pierna después de correr.","example_en":"My leg hurts after running.","mnemonic_en":"Visualize a leg leaning on a pier, the pier says na to keep it steady.","cloze_distractors_en":["Roof","Desk","Leaf","Lamp"],"examples":[{"es":"Me duele la pierna después de correr.","en":"My leg hurts after running."},{"es":"El jugador se rompió la pierna durante el partido de fútbol.","en":"The player broke his leg during the soccer match."},{"es":"Ella tiene un tatuaje pequeño en la pierna.","en":"She has a small tattoo on her leg."}]},{"spanish_text":"Pie","english_text":"Foot","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The lower extremity of the leg on which a person stands and walks.","main_translations_es":["pie","extremidad inferior","parte inferior del cuerpo"],"collocations":["foot of the mountain","foot the bill","foot traffic","foot in the door"],"synonyms_en":["tarsus","pedal","lower extremity"],"example_sentence":"My foot hurts after running.","example_es":"Me duele el pie después de correr.","example_en":"My foot hurts after running.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a foot stepping on a tasty pie, because foot sounds just like the Spanish word pie.","cloze_distractors_en":["Roof","Leaf","Beef","Chef"],"examples":[{"es":"Me duele el pie después de correr.","en":"My foot hurts after running."},{"es":"Él se puso el zapato en el pie derecho.","en":"He put the shoe on his right foot."},{"es":"Ella se rompió el pie al caerse de la bicicleta.","en":"She broke her foot when she fell off the bike."}]},{"spanish_text":"Espalda","english_text":"Back","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The rear surface of a person or object, opposite the front.","main_translations_es":["dorso","parte posterior","espalda"],"collocations":["back up","back down","back and forth","back to basics"],"synonyms_en":["rear","posterior","hind"],"example_sentence":"My back hurts after running.","example_es":"Me duele la espalda después de correr.","example_en":"My back hurts after running.","mnemonic_en":"I turned my back and felt my espalda ache.","cloze_distractors_en":["Palm","Chin","Lung","Vein"],"examples":[{"es":"Me duele la espalda después de correr.","en":"My back hurts after running."},{"es":"Llevo una mochila pesada sobre la espalda.","en":"I am carrying a heavy backpack on my back."},{"es":"Él se recostó contra la pared para descansar la espalda.","en":"He leaned against the wall to rest his back."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cara","english_text":"Face","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The front part of a person''s head that includes the eyes, nose, and mouth.","main_translations_es":["rostro","faz","semblante"],"collocations":["face value","face the music","in your face","face-to-face"],"synonyms_en":["countenance","visage","front"],"example_sentence":"She has a very friendly face.","example_es":"Ella tiene una cara muy amable.","example_en":"She has a very friendly face.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a bright cara painted on every face you meet.","cloze_distractors_en":["Floor","Shelf","Clock","Cloud"],"examples":[{"es":"Ella tiene una cara muy amable.","en":"She has a very friendly face."},{"es":"Lávate la cara antes de ir a dormir.","en":"Wash your face before going to sleep."},{"es":"El viento frío le golpeaba la cara mientras caminaba.","en":"The cold wind hit his face while he was walking."}]},{"spanish_text":"Pelo","english_text":"Hair","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Hair is the thin strands that grow from the skin of humans and animals, especially on the head.","main_translations_es":["Cabello","Cabellera"],"collocations":["hair cut","hair color","hair style","hair loss"],"synonyms_en":["locks","tresses","mane"],"example_sentence":"I cut my hair yesterday.","example_es":"Me corté el pelo ayer.","example_en":"I cut my hair yesterday.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a single hair as a tiny ''pelo'' dancing on a breeze.","cloze_distractors_en":["Table","Cloud","Plate","Brick"],"examples":[{"es":"Me corté el pelo ayer.","en":"I cut my hair yesterday."},{"es":"Ella tiene el pelo muy largo y rubio.","en":"She has very long, blonde hair."},{"es":"El peluquero me lavó el pelo con champú.","en":"The hairdresser washed my hair with shampoo."}]},{"spanish_text":"Oreja","english_text":"Ear","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The organ of hearing located on each side of the head.","main_translations_es":["oreja","oído","lóbulo"],"collocations":["lend an ear","in one ear and out the other","ear to the ground"],"synonyms_en":["auricle","hearing organ","auditory organ"],"example_sentence":"My right ear hurts.","example_es":"Me duele la oreja derecha.","example_en":"My right ear hurts.","mnemonic_en":"Picture an ear shaped like an OREJA, the Spanish word, catching sound waves.","cloze_distractors_en":["Desk","Road","Milk","Lamp"],"examples":[{"es":"Me duele la oreja derecha.","en":"My right ear hurts."},{"es":"El médico me revisó la oreja con una linterna.","en":"The doctor checked my ear with a flashlight."},{"es":"Ella se puso un pendiente brillante en la oreja.","en":"She put a shiny earring on her ear."}]},{"spanish_text":"Agua","english_text":"Water","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A clear, colorless, odorless, and tasteless liquid that makes up seas, lakes, rivers, and rain, and is essential for most life.","main_translations_es":["agua","el agua","el líquido"],"collocations":["bottled water","running water","water supply","water bottle"],"synonyms_en":["H2O","liquid","aqua"],"example_sentence":"I need to drink water.","example_es":"Necesito beber agua.","example_en":"I need to drink water.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a blue aqua (agua) faucet gushing water.","cloze_distractors_en":["Cement","Pencil","Button","Window"],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito beber agua.","en":"I need to drink water."},{"es":"Las plantas del jardín necesitan agua todos los días.","en":"The garden plants need water every day."},{"es":"Por favor, pon un poco de agua en el cuenco del perro.","en":"Please put some water in the dog''s bowl."}]},{"spanish_text":"Pan","english_text":"Bread","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A staple food made from flour and water, typically baked.","main_translations_es":["pan","pan de trigo","pan integral"],"collocations":["bread and butter","break bread","earn your bread","breadwinner"],"synonyms_en":["loaf","baked good","grain product"],"example_sentence":"I like to eat fresh bread every morning.","example_es":"Me gusta comer pan recién horneado cada mañana.","example_en":"I like to eat fresh bread every morning.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a pan of dough turning into fresh bread.","cloze_distractors_en":["Stone","Metal","Cloud","Paint"],"examples":[{"es":"Me gusta comer pan recién horneado cada mañana.","en":"I like to eat fresh bread every morning."},{"es":"Unté un poco de mantequilla sobre la rebanada de pan.","en":"I spread some butter on the slice of bread."},{"es":"Fuimos a la panadería para comprar pan para el almuerzo.","en":"We went to the bakery to buy bread for lunch."}]},{"spanish_text":"Leche","english_text":"Milk","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Milk is the white liquid produced by the mammary glands of mammals, commonly consumed as a beverage and used in cooking.","main_translations_es":["leche","producto lácteo","leche fresca"],"collocations":["a glass of milk","milk the cow","milk chocolate","milkshake"],"synonyms_en":["dairy","cow''s milk","lacteal fluid"],"example_sentence":"I like to drink milk before going to bed.","example_es":"Me gusta tomar leche antes de dormir.","example_en":"I like to drink milk before going to bed.","mnemonic_en":"Milk sounds like mil—imagine a cow saying leche as it gives you fresh milk.","cloze_distractors_en":["Sand","Soap","Glue","Dirt"],"examples":[{"es":"Me gusta tomar leche antes de dormir.","en":"I like to drink milk before going to bed."},{"es":"El gato tiene mucha hambre y quiere un poco de leche.","en":"The cat is very hungry and wants some milk."},{"es":"Por favor, añade un chorrito de leche a mi café.","en":"Please add a splash of milk to my coffee."}]},{"spanish_text":"Manzana","english_text":"Apple","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A round fruit with red, green, or yellow skin and a sweet, crisp flesh, typically grown on apple trees.","main_translations_es":["manzana","poma","fruta"],"collocations":["apple pie","apple of my eye","big apple","apple orchard"],"synonyms_en":["fruit","pome","Malus domestica"],"example_sentence":"I bought an apple at the market.","example_es":"Compré una manzana en el mercado.","example_en":"I bought an apple at the market.","mnemonic_en":"A man bites a crisp apple and shouts zana!","cloze_distractors_en":["Avenue","Island","Office","Action"],"examples":[{"es":"Compré una manzana en el mercado.","en":"I bought an apple at the market."},{"es":"Ella cortó la manzana con un cuchillo para merendar.","en":"She sliced the apple with a knife for a snack."},{"es":"El gusano salió de la manzana roja.","en":"The worm crawled out of the red apple."}]},{"spanish_text":"Perro","english_text":"Dog","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A domesticated carnivorous mammal commonly kept as a pet or used for work, known for its loyalty and barking.","main_translations_es":["can","chucho","cachorro"],"collocations":["dog house","dog days","dog bark","dog tag"],"synonyms_en":["canine","pooch","hound"],"example_sentence":"The dog runs in the park.","example_es":"El perro corre en el parque.","example_en":"The dog runs in the park.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a dog wearing a pair of O-shaped medals around its neck.","cloze_distractors_en":["Desk","Lamp","Book","Road"],"examples":[{"es":"El perro corre en el parque.","en":"The dog runs in the park."},{"es":"Mi perro duerme sobre la alfombra de la sala.","en":"My dog sleeps on the living room rug."},{"es":"El perro ladra cuando escucha al cartero.","en":"The dog barks when it hears the mailman."}]},{"spanish_text":"Gato","english_text":"Cat","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A small domesticated carnivorous mammal with soft fur, often kept as a pet.","main_translations_es":["gato","felino doméstico","minino"],"collocations":["cat nap","scaredy cat","fat cat","cat''s meow"],"synonyms_en":["feline","kitty","tom"],"example_sentence":"The cat sleeps on the sofa.","example_es":"El gato duerme en el sofá.","example_en":"The cat sleeps on the sofa.","mnemonic_en":"A cat named Gato purrs while chasing a bright laser dot","cloze_distractors_en":["Tree","Book","Lamp","Road"],"examples":[{"es":"El gato duerme en el sofá.","en":"The cat sleeps on the sofa."},{"es":"Mi gato persigue a un ratón por la cocina.","en":"My cat chases a mouse through the kitchen."},{"es":"El gato maúlla porque tiene mucha hambre.","en":"The cat meows because it is very hungry."}]},{"spanish_text":"Libro","english_text":"Book","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A bound collection of written or printed pages that can be read.","main_translations_es":["libro","tomo","volumen"],"collocations":["read a book","book a ticket","book club","book of poems"],"synonyms_en":["volume","tome","publication"],"example_sentence":"I am reading an interesting book.","example_es":"Estoy leyendo un libro interesante.","example_en":"I am reading an interesting book.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a librarian shouting ''Libro!'' as he hands you a huge book.","cloze_distractors_en":["Soup","Road","Wind"],"examples":[{"es":"Estoy leyendo un libro interesante.","en":"I am reading an interesting book."},{"es":"Ella cerró el libro después de terminar el último capítulo.","en":"She closed the book after finishing the last chapter."},{"es":"Por favor, coloca el libro en el estante superior.","en":"Please place the book on the top shelf."}]},{"spanish_text":"Escuela","english_text":"School","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"An institution where children and young adults receive education.","main_translations_es":["Colegio","Instituto","Academia"],"collocations":["go to school","school bus","school year","school of thought"],"synonyms_en":["educational institution","academy","learning center"],"example_sentence":"The school is closed today.","example_es":"La escuela está cerrada hoy.","example_en":"The school is closed today.","mnemonic_en":"School sounds like es-cool-a, so picture a super cool school building.","cloze_distractors_en":["Balloon","Puddle","Cactus","Slipper"],"examples":[{"es":"La escuela está cerrada hoy.","en":"The school is closed today."},{"es":"Los niños caminan hacia la escuela todas las mañanas.","en":"The children walk to school every morning."},{"es":"Ella estudia mucho en la escuela para sacar buenas notas.","en":"She studies hard at school to get good grades."}]},{"spanish_text":"Profesor","english_text":"Teacher","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person who teaches, especially in a school.","main_translations_es":["Maestro","Docente","Catedrático"],"collocations":["high school teacher","teacher training","teacher''s lounge","teacher''s pet"],"synonyms_en":["instructor","educator","tutor"],"example_sentence":"The teacher explained the lesson clearly.","example_es":"El profesor explicó la lección con claridad.","example_en":"The teacher explained the lesson clearly.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a teacher in a professor''s cap shouting teach er like a Spanish profesor.","cloze_distractors_en":["Kitchen","Pencil","Window","Garden"],"examples":[{"es":"El profesor explicó la lección con claridad.","en":"The teacher explained the lesson clearly."},{"es":"Los estudiantes escuchan atentamente cuando habla el profesor.","en":"The students listen carefully when the teacher speaks."},{"es":"Después de la clase, fui a la oficina del profesor para hacer una pregunta.","en":"After class, I went to the teacher office to ask a question."}]},{"spanish_text":"Estudiante","english_text":"Student","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person who is enrolled in an educational institution or is studying.","main_translations_es":["Estudiante","Alumno","Alumna"],"collocations":["full-time student","graduate student","student loan","student visa"],"synonyms_en":["learner","pupil","scholar"],"example_sentence":"The student studies for the exam.","example_es":"El estudiante estudia para el examen.","example_en":"The student studies for the exam.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a stud wearing an est badge, reminding you that student means estudiante.","cloze_distractors_en":["Window","Pencil","Lesson","School"],"examples":[{"es":"El estudiante estudia para el examen.","en":"The student studies for the exam."},{"es":"Cada estudiante tiene un libro en su pupitre.","en":"Each student has a book on their desk."},{"es":"El profesor saluda al estudiante en la puerta del aula.","en":"The teacher greets the student at the classroom door."}]},{"spanish_text":"Abrir","english_text":"Open","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To cause something to become not closed or to allow access.","main_translations_es":["Abrir","Desplegar","Destapar"],"collocations":["open the door","open a file","open a window","open up"],"synonyms_en":["unseal","unlock","uncover"],"example_sentence":"I am going to open the window.","example_es":"Voy a abrir la ventana.","example_en":"I am going to open the window.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a breezy wind abrir the door and the door swings open","cloze_distractors_en":["Swallow","Believe","Explain"],"examples":[{"es":"Voy a abrir la ventana.","en":"I am going to open the window."},{"es":"Por favor, abre el regalo ahora.","en":"Please open the gift now."},{"es":"Tienes que abrir la puerta con esta llave.","en":"You have to open the door with this key."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cerrar","english_text":"Close","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To shut something so that it is no longer open.","main_translations_es":["Clausurar","Cerrar","Sellar"],"collocations":["close the door","close the deal","close a window","close the book"],"synonyms_en":["shut","shut down","seal"],"example_sentence":"Please close the door when you leave.","example_es":"Por favor, cierra la puerta cuando salgas.","example_en":"Please close the door when you leave.","mnemonic_en":"I close the lid and hear the Spanish word cerrar humming.","cloze_distractors_en":["Build","Taste","Dance"],"examples":[{"es":"Por favor, cierra la puerta cuando salgas.","en":"Please close the door when you leave."},{"es":"Debes cerrar todas las ventanas antes de que empiece a llover.","en":"You must close all the windows before it starts to rain."},{"es":"El banco va a cerrar en diez minutos.","en":"The bank is going to close in ten minutes."}]},{"spanish_text":"Leer","english_text":"Read","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To look at and understand the meaning of written or printed material.","main_translations_es":["descifrar","revisar","examinar"],"collocations":["read a book","read aloud","read between the lines","read the news"],"synonyms_en":["peruse","study","scan"],"example_sentence":"I like to read before going to bed.","example_es":"Me gusta leer antes de dormir.","example_en":"I like to read before going to bed.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a red book titled Leer on the shelf as you read.","cloze_distractors_en":["Blink","Float","Twist"],"examples":[{"es":"Me gusta leer antes de dormir.","en":"I like to read before going to bed."},{"es":"Los niños aprenden a leer en la escuela.","en":"Children learn to read at school."},{"es":"Necesito leer este documento para la reunión.","en":"I need to read this document for the meeting."}]},{"spanish_text":"Escribir","english_text":"Write","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To produce text or symbols on a surface using a pen, pencil, keyboard, or other instrument.","main_translations_es":["Redactar","Anotar","Apuntar"],"collocations":["write a letter","write down","write a report","write an essay"],"synonyms_en":["compose","pen","scribe"],"example_sentence":"Please take a pencil and start to Write your name on the sheet.","example_es":"Por favor, toma un lápiz y empieza a escribir tu nombre en la hoja.","example_en":"Please take a pencil and start to Write your name on the sheet.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a pen writing ''es'' on a crib, reminding you that escribir means write.","cloze_distractors_en":["Drink","Sleep","Laugh","Jump"],"examples":[{"es":"Por favor, toma un lápiz y empieza a escribir tu nombre en la hoja.","en":"Please take a pencil and start to Write your name on the sheet."},{"es":"Ella necesita escribir una carta formal para solicitar el nuevo empleo.","en":"She needs to Write a formal letter to apply for the new job."},{"es":"Los niños aprenden a escribir frases cortas en su cuaderno de clase.","en":"The children learn to Write short sentences in their class notebook."}]},{"spanish_text":"Escuchar","english_text":"Listen","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To give attention to sounds by hearing them.","main_translations_es":["Oír","Atender","Prestar atención"],"collocations":["listen carefully","listen up","listen to music","listen attentively"],"synonyms_en":["hear","pay attention","attend"],"example_sentence":"I like to listen to music while I study.","example_es":"Me gusta escuchar música mientras estudio.","example_en":"I like to listen to music while I study.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a pirate whispering \"escucha\" as he leans in, urging you to listen.","cloze_distractors_en":["Taste","Touch","Smell","Watch"],"examples":[{"es":"Me gusta escuchar música mientras estudio.","en":"I like to listen to music while I study."},{"es":"Por favor, escucha con atención lo que dice el profesor.","en":"Please listen carefully to what the teacher says."},{"es":"Debes escuchar el consejo de tus padres.","en":"You should listen to the advice of your parents."}]},{"spanish_text":"Hablar","english_text":"Speak","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To utter words or communicate verbally.","main_translations_es":["Conversar","Charlar","Platicar"],"collocations":["speak up","speak out","speak one''s mind","speak fluently"],"synonyms_en":["talk","utter","communicate"],"example_sentence":"I like to speak with my friends.","example_es":"Me gusta hablar con mis amigos.","example_en":"I like to speak with my friends.","mnemonic_en":"A tiny speck whispers ''habla'' into your ear, reminding you that speak means hablar.","cloze_distractors_en":["Freeze","Borrow","Ignore"],"examples":[{"es":"Me gusta hablar con mis amigos.","en":"I like to speak with my friends."},{"es":"Debes hablar más despacio para que te entienda.","en":"You must speak more slowly so I can understand you."},{"es":"Es importante hablar inglés en la oficina.","en":"It is important to speak English in the office."}]},{"spanish_text":"Comer","english_text":"Eat","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To consume food or drink.","main_translations_es":["Alimentarse","Ingerir","Deglutir"],"collocations":["eat out","eat up","eat healthy","eat like a horse"],"synonyms_en":["consume","devour","ingest"],"example_sentence":"I like to eat pizza on Fridays.","example_es":"Me gusta comer pizza los viernes.","example_en":"I like to eat pizza on Fridays.","mnemonic_en":"When I eat, a loud COMER echo rings from my stomach.","cloze_distractors_en":["Fold","Melt","Spin","Hide"],"examples":[{"es":"Me gusta comer pizza los viernes.","en":"I like to eat pizza on Fridays."},{"es":"Debemos comer antes de ir al cine.","en":"We must eat before going to the movies."},{"es":"Los niños quieren comer un helado de chocolate.","en":"The children want to eat a chocolate ice cream."}]},{"spanish_text":"Beber","english_text":"Drink","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To consume a liquid.","main_translations_es":["Tomar","Beber","Ingerir"],"collocations":["drink water","drink coffee","drink responsibly","drink up"],"synonyms_en":["beverage","imbibe","consume"],"example_sentence":"I like to drink water after running.","example_es":"Me gusta beber agua después de correr.","example_en":"I like to drink water after running.","mnemonic_en":"I sip a cold ''beber'' brew every time I drink.","cloze_distractors_en":["Breathe","Freeze","Crush","Paint"],"examples":[{"es":"Me gusta beber agua después de correr.","en":"I like to drink water after running."},{"es":"Debes beber mucha leche para crecer fuerte.","en":"You must drink a lot of milk to grow strong."},{"es":"Es importante beber café caliente en la mañana.","en":"It is important to drink hot coffee in the morning."}]},{"spanish_text":"Ir","english_text":"Go","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to move or travel from one place to another","main_translations_es":["Desplazarse","Acudir","Irse"],"collocations":["go ahead","go home","go for it","go on"],"synonyms_en":["depart","leave","proceed"],"example_sentence":"I go to the market every morning.","example_es":"Voy al mercado cada mañana.","example_en":"I go to the market every morning.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a goat shouting go as it runs, hearing the Spanish Ir echo across the hills.","cloze_distractors_en":["Eat","Buy","See"],"examples":[{"es":"Voy al mercado cada mañana.","en":"I go to the market every morning."},{"es":"Debes ir a la cama temprano esta noche.","en":"You must go to bed early tonight."},{"es":"Vamos a ir al cine para ver la nueva película.","en":"We are going to go to the cinema to watch the new movie."}]},{"spanish_text":"Venir","english_text":"Come","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to move or travel toward a place or person","main_translations_es":["Llegar","Acudir","Arribar"],"collocations":["come in","come back","come across","come up"],"synonyms_en":["arrive","show up","appear"],"example_sentence":"Can you come to my house tomorrow?","example_es":"¿Puedes venir a mi casa mañana?","example_en":"Can you come to my house tomorrow?","mnemonic_en":"Picture a dog barking Come while you venir from the garden","cloze_distractors_en":["Grow","Melt","Weigh","Fade"],"examples":[{"es":"¿Puedes venir a mi casa mañana?","en":"Can you come to my house tomorrow?"},{"es":"Por favor, ven aquí ahora mismo.","en":"Please come here right now."},{"es":"Ellos van a venir a la fiesta esta noche.","en":"They are going to come to the party tonight."}]},{"spanish_text":"Ver","english_text":"See","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To perceive something with the eyes.","main_translations_es":["Observar","Mirar","Contemplar"],"collocations":["see the light","see a doctor","see what I mean","see the point"],"synonyms_en":["look at","observe","view"],"example_sentence":"Can you see the mountain from here?","example_es":"¿Puedes ver la montaña desde aquí?","example_en":"Can you see the mountain from here?","mnemonic_en":"I see a ver-y clear sky.","cloze_distractors_en":["Eat","Run","Sing","Read"],"examples":[{"es":"¿Puedes ver la montaña desde aquí?","en":"Can you see the mountain from here?"},{"es":"Quiero ver al médico hoy.","en":"I want to see the doctor today."},{"es":"Veremos una película esta noche.","en":"We will see a movie tonight."}]},{"spanish_text":"Querer","english_text":"Want","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To desire or wish for something.","main_translations_es":["desear","tener ganas de","anhelar"],"collocations":["want to","I want","want something","want for"],"synonyms_en":["desire","wish for","crave"],"example_sentence":"I want to travel to Spain this summer.","example_es":"Quiero viajar a España este verano.","example_en":"I want to travel to Spain this summer.","mnemonic_en":"I want a wan (pale) taco because I ''querer'' it.","cloze_distractors_en":["Hate","Lose","Keep","Hold"],"examples":[{"es":"Quiero viajar a España este verano.","en":"I want to travel to Spain this summer."},{"es":"Los niños quieren comer helado de chocolate.","en":"The children want to eat chocolate ice cream."},{"es":"¿Quieres comprar este libro en la librería?","en":"Do you want to buy this book at the bookstore?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Necesitar","english_text":"Need","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To require something because it is necessary or desirable.","main_translations_es":["precisar","requerir","tener que"],"collocations":["need to","in need of","need help","need a break"],"synonyms_en":["require","necessitate","must have"],"example_sentence":"I need to buy milk.","example_es":"Necesito comprar leche.","example_en":"I need to buy milk.","mnemonic_en":"My knee needs a seat on the bench.","cloze_distractors_en":["Cook","Read","Feed","Seed"],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito comprar leche.","en":"I need to buy milk."},{"es":"Ellos necesitan estudiar para el examen de mañana.","en":"They need to study for the exam tomorrow."},{"es":"Necesitamos llamar a un taxi para ir al aeropuerto.","en":"We need to call a taxi to go to the airport."}]},{"spanish_text":"Grande","english_text":"Big","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Having a large size, extent, or magnitude.","main_translations_es":["Enorme","Gigante","Amplio"],"collocations":["big deal","big picture","big time","big brother"],"synonyms_en":["large","huge","massive"],"example_sentence":"The dog is very big.","example_es":"El perro es muy grande.","example_en":"The dog is very big.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a BIG elephant wearing a GRANDE sombrero","cloze_distractors_en":["Late","Sour","Vague"],"examples":[{"es":"El perro es muy grande.","en":"The dog is very big."},{"es":"Necesito una maleta grande para mi viaje.","en":"I need a big suitcase for my trip."},{"es":"La casa tiene una ventana grande en la sala.","en":"The house has a big window in the living room."}]},{"spanish_text":"Pequeño","english_text":"Small","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Having a limited size, amount, or extent.","main_translations_es":["chico","pequeñito","menudo"],"collocations":["small business","small town","small amount","small problem"],"synonyms_en":["tiny","little","compact"],"example_sentence":"The dog is small but very brave.","example_es":"El perro es pequeño pero muy valiente.","example_en":"The dog is small but very brave.","mnemonic_en":"A tiny (pequeño) mouse sniffs a small crumb.","cloze_distractors_en":["Silent","Absent","Formal"],"examples":[{"es":"El perro es pequeño pero muy valiente.","en":"The dog is small but very brave."},{"es":"Necesito una caja pequeño para guardar mis llaves.","en":"I need a small box to keep my keys."},{"es":"Ellos viven en un apartamento pequeño en el centro de la ciudad.","en":"They live in a small apartment in the city center."}]},{"spanish_text":"Nuevo","english_text":"New","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Recently created, discovered, or introduced; not existing before.","main_translations_es":["Reciente","Fresco","Novedoso"],"collocations":["brand new","new and improved","new generation","new era"],"synonyms_en":["fresh","brand‑new","recent"],"example_sentence":"I bought a new car.","example_es":"Compré un coche nuevo.","example_en":"I bought a new car.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a newborn baby holding a fresh, new blanket, echoing the nu sound of nuevo","cloze_distractors_en":["Hungry","Cloudy","Sleepy","Thirsty"],"examples":[{"es":"Compré un coche nuevo.","en":"I bought a new car."},{"es":"Ella tiene un trabajo nuevo en la ciudad.","en":"She has a new job in the city."},{"es":"Necesito comprar un teléfono nuevo porque el mío no funciona.","en":"I need to buy a new phone because mine does not work."}]},{"spanish_text":"Viejo","english_text":"Old","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Having existed or been in use for a long time; not new.","main_translations_es":["antiguo","anciano","vetusto"],"collocations":["old friend","old habits","old age","old-fashioned"],"synonyms_en":["ancient","aged","elderly"],"example_sentence":"The old book is on the shelf.","example_es":"El libro viejo está en la estantería.","example_en":"The old book is on the shelf.","mnemonic_en":"Picture an old wizard saying VIEJO while opening a dusty ancient book.","cloze_distractors_en":["Liquid","Boiling","Crunchy","Chewy"],"examples":[{"es":"El libro viejo está en la estantería.","en":"The old book is on the shelf."},{"es":"Mi abuelo es un hombre viejo pero muy amable.","en":"My grandfather is an old man but very kind."},{"es":"Ellos viven en una casa vieja de madera.","en":"They live in an old wooden house."}]},{"spanish_text":"Feliz","english_text":"Happy","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Feeling or showing pleasure, contentment, or joy.","main_translations_es":["Contento","Alegre","Jubiloso"],"collocations":["happy birthday","happy hour","happy ending","happy couple"],"synonyms_en":["joyful","cheerful","content"],"example_sentence":"I am happy with the results.","example_es":"Estoy feliz con los resultados.","example_en":"I am happy with the results.","mnemonic_en":"A happy clown shouts Feliz as he receives a big birthday cake.","cloze_distractors_en":["Bitter","Stiff","Dull","Vague"],"examples":[{"es":"Estoy feliz con los resultados.","en":"I am happy with the results."},{"es":"Ella se siente muy feliz por su nuevo trabajo.","en":"She feels very happy about her new job."},{"es":"Los niños están tan feliz al abrir sus regalos.","en":"The children are so happy when opening their gifts."}]}]'::jsonb) as x(
  spanish_text text, english_text text, section_name text, part_of_speech text, definition_en text,
  main_translations_es jsonb, collocations jsonb, synonyms_en jsonb, example_sentence text, example_es text, example_en text, mnemonic_en text, cloze_distractors_en jsonb, examples jsonb
)
where c.deck_id = dk.id
  and lower(c.spanish_text) = lower(x.spanish_text)
  and lower(c.english_text) = lower(x.english_text);

-- ai-batch-cafe-basics (100 cards)
update public.decks set
  title = 'Cafe Counter Basics', description = 'Short English needed for simple cafe orders.',
  language_from = 'es', language_to = 'en'
where slug = 'ai-batch-cafe-basics';

update public.cards c set
  section_name = x.section_name, part_of_speech = x.part_of_speech, definition_en = x.definition_en,
  main_translations_es = coalesce(x.main_translations_es, '[]'::jsonb),
  collocations = coalesce(x.collocations, '[]'::jsonb),
  synonyms_en = coalesce(x.synonyms_en, '[]'::jsonb),
  example_sentence = x.example_sentence, example_es = x.example_es, example_en = x.example_en,
  mnemonic_en = coalesce(x.mnemonic_en, c.mnemonic_en),
  cloze_distractors_en = case when jsonb_array_length(coalesce(x.cloze_distractors_en, '[]'::jsonb)) > 0
                              then x.cloze_distractors_en else c.cloze_distractors_en end,
  examples = case when jsonb_array_length(coalesce(x.examples, '[]'::jsonb)) > 0
                  then x.examples else c.examples end
from (select id from public.decks where slug = 'ai-batch-cafe-basics') dk
cross join jsonb_to_recordset('[{"spanish_text":"Agua","english_text":"Water","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A clear, colorless, odorless, and tasteless liquid that makes up seas, lakes, rivers, and rain, and is essential for most life.","main_translations_es":["agua","el agua","agua potable"],"collocations":["drinking water","water bottle","water supply","water level"],"synonyms_en":["H2O","liquid","aqua"],"example_sentence":"Please, can I have a glass of water?","example_es":"Por favor, ¿me puede dar un vaso de agua?","example_en":"Please, can I have a glass of water?","mnemonic_en":"Picture a clear water splash shouting agua as it hits the shore","cloze_distractors_en":["Bread","Napkin","Spoon","Sugar"],"examples":[{"es":"Por favor, ¿me puede dar un vaso de agua?","en":"Please, can I have a glass of water?"},{"es":"Tengo mucha sed, ¿tienen agua embotellada?","en":"I am very thirsty, do you have bottled water?"},{"es":"Para acompañar mi sándwich, quiero pedir agua.","en":"To go with my sandwich, I want to order water."}]},{"spanish_text":"Agua con gas","english_text":"Sparkling water","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A carbonated water beverage, often served as a non‑alcoholic drink.","main_translations_es":["agua mineral","agua con burbujas","agua carbonatada"],"collocations":["sparkling water bottle","sparkling water with lemon","drink sparkling water","sparkling water on the rocks"],"synonyms_en":["carbonated water","soda water","fizzy water"],"example_sentence":"I would like to order sparkling water, please.","example_es":"Me gustaría pedir agua con gas, por favor.","example_en":"I would like to order sparkling water, please.","mnemonic_en":"Picture sparkling water bubbling like gas in a glass of agua.","cloze_distractors_en":["Plastic cutlery","Napkin holder","Table service","Counter space"],"examples":[{"es":"Me gustaría pedir agua con gas, por favor.","en":"I would like to order sparkling water, please."},{"es":"Para acompañar la comida, prefiero beber agua con gas.","en":"To go with my meal, I prefer to drink sparkling water."},{"es":"¿Tiene agua con gas o solo tiene agua natural?","en":"Do you have sparkling water or do you only have still water?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Zumo","english_text":"Juice","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A liquid extracted from fruits or vegetables, typically consumed as a drink.","main_translations_es":["jugo","jugo de fruta"],"collocations":["fruit juice","orange juice","juice bar","juice cleanse"],"synonyms_en":["fruit drink","extract","nectar"],"example_sentence":"I like to drink orange juice at breakfast.","example_es":"Me gusta tomar zumo de naranja en el desayuno.","example_en":"I like to drink orange juice at breakfast.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a zoo cow sipping bright orange juice, the word zumo echoing in your mind.","cloze_distractors_en":["Toast","Sauce","Cream","Sugar"],"examples":[{"es":"Me gusta tomar zumo de naranja en el desayuno.","en":"I like to drink orange juice at breakfast."},{"es":"Por favor, ¿me puede traer un zumo de manzana bien frío?","en":"Please, can you bring me a cold apple juice?"},{"es":"El niño pidió un zumo de piña para acompañar su sándwich.","en":"The boy ordered a pineapple juice to go with his sandwich."}]},{"spanish_text":"Zumo de naranja","english_text":"Orange juice","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A beverage made by extracting the liquid from oranges.","main_translations_es":["Jugo de naranja","Zumo de naranja"],"collocations":["fresh orange juice","bottled orange juice","orange juice concentrate"],"synonyms_en":["citrus juice","fresh orange drink","OJ"],"example_sentence":"For breakfast, the boy ordered a glass of orange juice.","example_es":"Para desayunar, el niño pidió un vaso de zumo de naranja.","example_en":"For breakfast, the boy ordered a glass of orange juice.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a bright orange spilling its zumo into a glass of juice.","cloze_distractors_en":["Olive oil","Apple sauce","Table salt","Maple syrup"],"examples":[{"es":"Para desayunar, el niño pidió un vaso de zumo de naranja.","en":"For breakfast, the boy ordered a glass of orange juice."},{"es":"El camarero trajo el zumo de naranja recién exprimido a la mesa.","en":"The waiter brought the freshly squeezed orange juice to the table."},{"es":"Por favor, ¿podría traerme un zumo de naranja en lugar de café?","en":"Could you please bring me an orange juice instead of coffee?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Chocolate caliente","english_text":"Hot chocolate","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A warm beverage made from melted chocolate or cocoa powder, milk, and sugar.","main_translations_es":["cacao caliente","bebida de chocolate","chocolate tibio"],"collocations":["a cup of hot chocolate","hot chocolate mix","hot chocolate bar","hot chocolate flavor"],"synonyms_en":["cocoa","hot cocoa","warm cocoa"],"example_sentence":"Please, can you serve me a hot chocolate with lots of whipped cream?","example_es":"Por favor, ¿me puede servir un chocolate caliente con mucha crema batida?","example_en":"Please, can you serve me a hot chocolate with lots of whipped cream?","mnemonic_en":"Picture a steaming mug of hot chocolate and hear caliente sizzling as the heat rises.","cloze_distractors_en":["Table napkin","Empty saucer","Broken kettle","Plastic straw"],"examples":[{"es":"Por favor, ¿me puede servir un chocolate caliente con mucha crema batida?","en":"Please, can you serve me a hot chocolate with lots of whipped cream?"},{"es":"Mi hijo siempre pide un chocolate caliente cuando vamos a la cafetería.","en":"My son always orders a hot chocolate when we go to the cafe."},{"es":"El camarero trajo un chocolate caliente humeante a nuestra mesa.","en":"The waiter brought a steaming hot chocolate to our table."}]},{"spanish_text":"Leche","english_t