bebida de avena en el desayuno.","en":"I like to have oat milk for breakfast."},{"es":"Por favor, prepara mi café con bebida de avena en lugar de leche entera.","en":"Please make my coffee with oat milk instead of whole milk."},{"es":"El cliente pidió un batido de frutas hecho con bebida de avena.","en":"The customer ordered a fruit smoothie made with oat milk."}]},{"spanish_text":"Bebida de soja","english_text":"Soy milk","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A plant-based beverage made from soybeans.","main_translations_es":["leche de soja","bebida vegetal de soja","leche vegetal de soja"],"collocations":["soy milk latte","add soy milk","drink soy milk","soy milk alternative"],"synonyms_en":["soy beverage","soy drink"],"example_sentence":"Since I am lactose intolerant, I always order my coffee with soy milk.","example_es":"Como soy intolerante a la lactosa, siempre pido mi café con bebida de soja.","example_en":"Since I am lactose intolerant, I always order my coffee with soy milk.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a soy bean shouting soy as it turns into a white milk splash.","cloze_distractors_en":["Table salt","Black pepper","Olive oil","Dish soap"],"examples":[{"es":"Como soy intolerante a la lactosa, siempre pido mi café con bebida de soja.","en":"Since I am lactose intolerant, I always order my coffee with soy milk."},{"es":"Por favor, prepara mi café con bebida de soja.","en":"Please make my coffee with soy milk."},{"es":"El camarero me preguntó si prefiero leche entera o bebida de soja.","en":"The waiter asked me if I prefer whole milk or soy milk."}]},{"spanish_text":"Refresco","english_text":"Soft drink","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A non-alcoholic, carbonated beverage.","main_translations_es":["bebida gaseosa","bebida refrescante","cola"],"collocations":["soft drink can","soft drink machine","soft drink industry","soft drink brand"],"synonyms_en":["soda","pop","carbonated beverage"],"example_sentence":"I bought a cold soft drink to go with the pizza.","example_es":"Me compré un refresco frío para acompañar la pizza.","example_en":"I bought a cold soft drink to go with the pizza.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a cold soft drink that refreshes you like a gust called Refresco on a hot day.","cloze_distractors_en":["Hard bread","Fast lunch","Cold plate","Main table"],"examples":[{"es":"Me compré un refresco frío para acompañar la pizza.","en":"I bought a cold soft drink to go with the pizza."},{"es":"El menú dice que el combo incluye una hamburguesa y un refresco.","en":"The menu says the combo includes a burger and a soft drink."},{"es":"Por favor, ¿me puede traer un refresco con mucho hielo?","en":"Please, can you bring me a soft drink with lots of ice?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Limonada","english_text":"Lemonade","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A sweetened drink made from lemon juice, water, and sugar.","main_translations_es":["bebida de limón","refresco de limón","agua de limón"],"collocations":["lemonade stand","make lemonade","fresh lemonade","lemonade pitcher"],"synonyms_en":["citrus drink","lemon drink","refreshing beverage"],"example_sentence":"I like drinking fresh lemonade on hot days.","example_es":"Me gusta tomar limonada fresca en los días calurosos.","example_en":"I like drinking fresh lemonade on hot days.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a bright lemon drink, because lemonade sounds like limon in limonada.","cloze_distractors_en":["Furniture","Notebook","Backpack","Envelope"],"examples":[{"es":"Me gusta tomar limonada fresca en los días calurosos.","en":"I like drinking fresh lemonade on hot days."},{"es":"Por favor, ¿me puede traer una limonada con mucho hielo?","en":"Please, can you bring me a lemonade with lots of ice?"},{"es":"El niño pidió una limonada para acompañar su sándwich.","en":"The boy ordered a lemonade to go with his sandwich."}]},{"spanish_text":"Batido","english_text":"Milkshake","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A cold, sweet beverage made by blending milk with ice cream or flavorings.","main_translations_es":["Malteada","Batido de leche"],"collocations":["chocolate milkshake","strawberry milkshake","order a milkshake"],"synonyms_en":["shake","frappe","blended drink"],"example_sentence":"I want a strawberry milkshake.","example_es":"Quiero un batido de fresa.","example_en":"I want a strawberry milkshake.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a bat shaking a milk bottle, turning it into a milkshake","cloze_distractors_en":["Sandwich","Hamburger","Spaghetti"],"examples":[{"es":"Quiero un batido de fresa.","en":"I want a strawberry milkshake."},{"es":"El niño pidió un batido de chocolate con crema batida.","en":"The boy ordered a chocolate milkshake with whipped cream."},{"es":"Para el postre, voy a tomar un batido de vainilla.","en":"For dessert, I am going to have a vanilla milkshake."}]},{"spanish_text":"Café descafeinado","english_text":"Decaf coffee","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Coffee that has had most of its caffeine removed.","main_translations_es":["café sin cafeína","café descafeinado"],"collocations":["order decaf coffee","drink decaf coffee","decaf coffee beans","decaf coffee shop"],"synonyms_en":["caffeine‑free coffee","decaffeinated coffee","coffee without caffeine"],"example_sentence":"I like to drink decaf coffee at night.","example_es":"Me gusta tomar café descafeinado por la noche.","example_en":"I like to drink decaf coffee at night.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a coffee saying de‑caf to the café, showing it’s caffeine‑free.","cloze_distractors_en":["Used napkin","Broken saucer","Empty pitcher","Sticky counter"],"examples":[{"es":"Me gusta tomar café descafeinado por la noche.","en":"I like to drink decaf coffee at night."},{"es":"Como no puedo dormir, prefiero pedir un café descafeinado.","en":"Since I cannot sleep, I prefer to order a decaf coffee."},{"es":"El camarero me trajo un café descafeinado en lugar de uno normal.","en":"The waiter brought me a decaf coffee instead of a regular one."}]},{"spanish_text":"Espresso","english_text":"Espresso","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A strong, concentrated coffee made by forcing hot water through finely ground coffee beans.","main_translations_es":["café expreso","café solo"],"collocations":["espresso shot","espresso machine","espresso bar"],"synonyms_en":[],"example_sentence":"I like to have an espresso in the morning.","example_es":"Me gusta tomar un espresso por la mañana.","example_en":"I like to have an espresso in the morning.","mnemonic_en":null,"cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Me gusta tomar un espresso por la mañana.","en":"I like to have an espresso in the morning."}]},{"spanish_text":"Capuchino","english_text":"Cappuccino","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A coffee beverage made with espresso and steamed milk, topped with a layer of foamed milk.","main_translations_es":["cappuccino","café con leche y espuma","café con leche espumoso"],"collocations":["order a cappuccino","cappuccino foam","cappuccino machine","hot cappuccino"],"synonyms_en":["frothy coffee","espresso latte","milk coffee"],"example_sentence":"I would like to order a cappuccino.","example_es":"Me gustaría pedir un capuchino.","example_en":"I would like to order a cappuccino.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a capuchin monkey sipping a frothy cappuccino.","cloze_distractors_en":["Tablecloth","Napkin","Dishwasher"],"examples":[{"es":"Me gustaría pedir un capuchino.","en":"I would like to order a cappuccino."},{"es":"El camarero preparó un capuchino con mucha espuma.","en":"The barista prepared a cappuccino with extra foam."},{"es":"Para desayunar, siempre tomo un capuchino caliente.","en":"I always have a hot cappuccino for breakfast."}]},{"spanish_text":"Café con leche","english_text":"Latte","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A coffee beverage made with espresso and steamed milk.","main_translations_es":["café con leche","café con leche caliente","café con leche tibio"],"collocations":["order a latte","latte art","vanilla latte","cold latte"],"synonyms_en":["coffee with milk","milk coffee","café au lait"],"example_sentence":"I would like a latte, please.","example_es":"Quiero un café con leche, por favor.","example_en":"I would like a latte, please.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a latte, a coffee with milk, as the Spanish café con leche in a creamy cup.","cloze_distractors_en":["Blueprint","Headlight","Sandpaper","Thermometer"],"examples":[{"es":"Quiero un café con leche, por favor.","en":"I would like a latte, please."},{"es":"Para desayunar, siempre pido un café con leche.","en":"For breakfast, I always order a latte."},{"es":"El camarero me trajo un café con leche muy caliente.","en":"The waiter brought me a very hot latte."}]},{"spanish_text":"Té helado","english_text":"Iced tea","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A cold beverage made by chilling tea, often served with ice.","main_translations_es":["té frío","té con hielo","té refrescante"],"collocations":["a glass of iced tea","iced tea with lemon","iced tea on a hot day"],"synonyms_en":["cold tea","chilled tea"],"example_sentence":"To cool down after walking in the sun, I will order an iced tea.","example_es":"Para refrescarme después de caminar bajo el sol, pediré un té helado.","example_en":"To cool down after walking in the sun, I will order an iced tea.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a frosty cup of iced tea spilling over a snow‑capped ''té'' hill.","cloze_distractors_en":["Hard toast","Slow milk","Dark salt"],"examples":[{"es":"Para refrescarme después de caminar bajo el sol, pediré un té helado.","en":"To cool down after walking in the sun, I will order an iced tea."},{"es":"Por favor, ¿me puede traer un té helado con limón?","en":"Please, can you bring me an iced tea with lemon?"},{"es":"Para acompañar mi sándwich, prefiero pedir un té helado.","en":"To go with my sandwich, I prefer to order an iced tea."}]},{"spanish_text":"Croissant","english_text":"Croissant","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A buttery, flaky, crescent-shaped pastry commonly eaten for breakfast.","main_translations_es":["croissant","cruasán","cruasan"],"collocations":["have a croissant for breakfast","freshly baked croissant","buttery croissant","croissant sandwich"],"synonyms_en":[],"example_sentence":"I love eating a freshly baked croissant in the morning.","example_es":"Me encanta comer un croissant recién horneado en la mañana.","example_en":"I love eating a freshly baked croissant in the morning.","mnemonic_en":null,"cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Me encanta comer un croissant recién horneado en la mañana.","en":"I love eating a freshly baked croissant in the morning."}]},{"spanish_text":"Magdalena","english_text":"Muffin","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A small, sweet, individual cake or quick bread, typically round and baked in a cup-shaped mold.","main_translations_es":["magdalena","bizcocho","pastelito"],"collocations":["blueberry muffin","chocolate muffin","English muffin","muffin top"],"synonyms_en":["quickbread","biscuit","cupcake"],"example_sentence":"I ate a muffin for breakfast.","example_es":"Me comí una magdalena en el desayuno.","example_en":"I ate a muffin for breakfast.","mnemonic_en":"Picture Magdalena the saint handing you a warm golden muffin.","cloze_distractors_en":["Counter","Receipt","Grinder"],"examples":[{"es":"Me comí una magdalena en el desayuno.","en":"I ate a muffin for breakfast."},{"es":"Por favor, ¿me das una magdalena con mi café?","en":"Please, can I have a muffin with my coffee?"},{"es":"El cliente pidió una magdalena recién horneada.","en":"The customer ordered a freshly baked muffin."}]},{"spanish_text":"Galleta","english_text":"Cookie","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A sweet baked snack, typically small, flat, and either crisp or soft.","main_translations_es":["galleta","biscocho","galleta dulce"],"collocations":["cookie jar","chocolate chip cookie","fortune cookie","cookie cutter"],"synonyms_en":["biscuit","treat","sweet"],"example_sentence":"I ate a chocolate cookie after dinner.","example_es":"Me comí una galleta de chocolate después de la cena.","example_en":"I ate a chocolate cookie after dinner.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a cook placing a golden galleta on a plate, calling it a cookie.","cloze_distractors_en":["Coffee","Sugar","Water"],"examples":[{"es":"Me comí una galleta de chocolate después de la cena.","en":"I ate a chocolate cookie after dinner."},{"es":"El niño pidió una galleta con chispas para acompañar su vaso de leche.","en":"The boy asked for a chocolate chip cookie to go with his glass of milk."},{"es":"La barista puso la galleta en una servilleta antes de entregármela.","en":"The barista placed the cookie on a napkin before handing it to me."}]},{"spanish_text":"Tarta","english_text":"Cake","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A sweet baked dessert typically made from flour, sugar, and other ingredients.","main_translations_es":["Pastel","Bizcocho","Torta"],"collocations":["piece of cake","have your cake and eat it too","icing on the cake","cakewalk"],"synonyms_en":["pastry","gateau","torte"],"example_sentence":"I bought a chocolate cake for my sister''s birthday.","example_es":"Compré una tarta de chocolate para el cumpleaños de mi hermana.","example_en":"I bought a chocolate cake for my sister''s birthday.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a cake wearing a tarta flag, because cake sounds like ''c-a-ke'' and tarta means tart.","cloze_distractors_en":["Table","Plate","Knife","Floor"],"examples":[{"es":"Compré una tarta de chocolate para el cumpleaños de mi hermana.","en":"I bought a chocolate cake for my sister''s birthday."},{"es":"El camarero trajo una porción de tarta con un poco de nata encima.","en":"The waiter brought a slice of cake with some whipped cream on top."},{"es":"Por favor, ¿me puede poner una tarta de fresa para llevar?","en":"Could you please give me a strawberry cake to go?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Bocadillo","english_text":"Sandwich","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A food item consisting of two slices of bread with a filling such as meat, cheese, or vegetables placed between them.","main_translations_es":["sándwich","emparedado","bocata"],"collocations":["sandwich shop","sandwich maker","sandwich filling","sandwich bread"],"synonyms_en":["sub","hero","panini"],"example_sentence":"I ate a ham and cheese sandwich in the park.","example_es":"Me comí un bocadillo de jamón y queso en el parque.","example_en":"I ate a ham and cheese sandwich in the park.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a sandwich on a beach of sand, like a bocadillo floating in the sea.","cloze_distractors_en":["Furniture","Envelope","Notebook"],"examples":[{"es":"Me comí un bocadillo de jamón y queso en el parque.","en":"I ate a ham and cheese sandwich in the park."},{"es":"El cliente pidió un bocadillo caliente para llevar.","en":"The customer ordered a hot sandwich to go."},{"es":"Preparamos un bocadillo fresco con pollo y lechuga para el almuerzo.","en":"We prepared a fresh chicken and lettuce sandwich for lunch."}]},{"spanish_text":"Tostada","english_text":"Toast","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A slice of bread that has been browned by heat.","main_translations_es":["Pan tostado","Tostada de pan","Tostada integral"],"collocations":["make toast","buttered toast","toast and jam","toast the bread"],"synonyms_en":["fried bread","toasted bread","bread slice"],"example_sentence":"Please serve me a toast with a black coffee.","example_es":"Por favor, sírveme una tostada con un café solo.","example_en":"Please serve me a toast with a black coffee.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a crunchy toast popping out of a huge Tostada sandwich.","cloze_distractors_en":["Faucet","Pencil","Wallet","Bucket"],"examples":[{"es":"Por favor, sírveme una tostada con un café solo.","en":"Please serve me a toast with a black coffee."},{"es":"El camarero trajo la tostada recién hecha a la mesa.","en":"The waiter brought the freshly made toast to the table."},{"es":"Para desayunar, siempre pido un zumo de naranja y una tostada.","en":"For breakfast, I always order an orange juice and a toast."}]},{"spanish_text":"Ensalada","english_text":"Salad","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A dish made of mixed raw or cooked vegetables, often served with a dressing.","main_translations_es":["ensalada mixta","ensalada verde","ensalada fresca"],"collocations":["Caesar salad","garden salad","fruit salad","salad dressing"],"synonyms_en":["mixed greens","greens","vegetable dish"],"example_sentence":"I like to eat salad with chicken.","example_es":"Me gusta comer ensalada con pollo.","example_en":"I like to eat salad with chicken.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a bowl of lettuce chanting ''ensalada'' while you mix the fresh salad.","cloze_distractors_en":["Napkin","Receipt","Kitchen","Coffee"],"examples":[{"es":"Me gusta comer ensalada con pollo.","en":"I like to eat salad with chicken."},{"es":"Para el almuerzo, prefiero pedir una ensalada fresca.","en":"For lunch, I prefer to order a fresh salad."},{"es":"El camarero trajo la ensalada antes del plato principal.","en":"The waiter brought the salad before the main course."}]},{"spanish_text":"Sopa","english_text":"Soup","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A liquid dish made by boiling ingredients such as meat, vegetables, or legumes in water or stock.","main_translations_es":["caldo","consomé","sopa"],"collocations":["chicken noodle soup","soup of the day","soup kitchen"],"synonyms_en":["broth","stew","bisque"],"example_sentence":"I ordered a bowl of soup to start my lunch.","example_es":"Pedí un tazón de sopa para empezar mi almuerzo.","example_en":"I ordered a bowl of soup to start my lunch.","mnemonic_en":"Soap bubbles pop on a steaming bowl of soup.","cloze_distractors_en":["Desk","Lamp","Belt","Road"],"examples":[{"es":"Pedí un tazón de sopa para empezar mi almuerzo.","en":"I ordered a bowl of soup to start my lunch."},{"es":"El camarero trajo una cuchara para comer la sopa.","en":"The waiter brought a spoon to eat the soup."},{"es":"Hoy el menú del día incluye una sopa de verduras.","en":"Today the daily menu includes a vegetable soup."}]},{"spanish_text":"Yogur","english_text":"Yogurt","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A creamy, fermented dairy product made from milk, commonly eaten as a snack or used in cooking.","main_translations_es":["yogur","yogur natural","yogur griego"],"collocations":["Greek yogurt","yogurt parfait","low-fat yogurt","yogurt drink"],"synonyms_en":["yoghurt","curd","cultured milk"],"example_sentence":"I like to eat yogurt with fruit for breakfast.","example_es":"Me gusta comer yogur con frutas en el desayuno.","example_en":"I like to eat yogurt with fruit for breakfast.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a yogurt cup wearing a tiny yogur label like a flag.","cloze_distractors_en":["Butter","Pepper","Napkin","Salami"],"examples":[{"es":"Me gusta comer yogur con frutas en el desayuno.","en":"I like to eat yogurt with fruit for breakfast."},{"es":"Por favor, ¿me puede dar un yogur natural con granola?","en":"Please, can I have a yogurt with granola?"},{"es":"El niño pidió un yogur de fresa para merendar en la cafetería.","en":"The boy ordered a strawberry yogurt for his snack at the cafe."}]},{"spanish_text":"Queso","english_text":"Cheese","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A dairy product made from curdled milk, commonly eaten as food.","main_translations_es":["queso","queso curado","queso fresco"],"collocations":["cheese plate","cheese sandwich","cheese sauce","cheese cake"],"synonyms_en":["dairy product","curd"],"example_sentence":"Please add a slice of Cheese to my sandwich.","example_es":"Por favor, añada una rebanada de queso a mi sándwich.","example_en":"Please add a slice of Cheese to my sandwich.","mnemonic_en":"Say cheese and picture a mouse shouting queso as it nibbles the cheesy slice.","cloze_distractors_en":["Napkin","Coffee","Spoon","Table"],"examples":[{"es":"Por favor, añada una rebanada de queso a mi sándwich.","en":"Please add a slice of Cheese to my sandwich."},{"es":"Me gustaría pedir una hamburguesa con queso, por favor.","en":"I would like to order a burger with Cheese, please."},{"es":"El plato de degustación incluye uvas, galletas y queso.","en":"The tasting platter includes grapes, crackers, and Cheese."}]},{"spanish_text":"Mantequilla","english_text":"Butter","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A pale yellow dairy product made by churning cream, used as a spread or in cooking.","main_translations_es":["Mantequilla","Manteca de leche"],"collocations":["spread butter","butter up","melt butter","butter the toast"],"synonyms_en":["dairy spread","spread","butterfat"],"example_sentence":"I like to spread butter on the bread.","example_es":"Me gusta untar mantequilla en el pan.","example_en":"I like to spread butter on the bread.","mnemonic_en":"A buttered bat spreads mantequilla on toast, melting like gold.","cloze_distractors_en":["Cement","Pencil","Sponge","Napkin"],"examples":[{"es":"Me gusta untar mantequilla en el pan.","en":"I like to spread butter on the bread."},{"es":"Por favor, ¿me puede dar un poco de mantequilla para mis tostadas?","en":"Please, can you give me some butter for my toast?"},{"es":"El camarero trajo un pequeño plato con mantequilla para el desayuno.","en":"The waiter brought a small dish with butter for breakfast."}]},{"spanish_text":"Mermelada","english_text":"Jam","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A sweet spread made from fruit and sugar, typically used on bread or toast.","main_translations_es":["Conserva de frutas","Dulce de fruta"],"collocations":["traffic jam","jam session","jam‑packed"],"synonyms_en":["preserve","fruit spread","conserve"],"example_sentence":"I like spreading jam on toast every morning.","example_es":"Me gusta untar mermelada en el pan tostado cada mañana.","example_en":"I like spreading jam on toast every morning.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a traffic jam of strawberries spreading mermelada on toast.","cloze_distractors_en":["Salt","Soap","Glue","Sand"],"examples":[{"es":"Me gusta untar mermelada en el pan tostado cada mañana.","en":"I like spreading jam on toast every morning."},{"es":"El camarero trajo una pequeña porción de mermelada para acompañar mis bollos.","en":"The waiter brought a small portion of jam to go with my scones."},{"es":"Por favor, ¿podría traerme un poco más de mermelada para mis tostadas?","en":"Could you please bring me some more jam for my toast?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Azúcar","english_text":"Sugar","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A sweet, crystalline substance used to sweeten foods and drinks, derived from sugarcane, sugar beet, or other plants.","main_translations_es":["azúcar","endulzante","dulce"],"collocations":["sugar rush","add sugar","sugar coating","sugar free"],"synonyms_en":["sweetener","sucrose","cane sugar"],"example_sentence":"My coffee is too bitter, could you pass me the sugar?","example_es":"Mi café está muy amargo, ¿me pasas el azúcar?","example_en":"My coffee is too bitter, could you pass me the sugar?","mnemonic_en":"Imagine sweet sugar sprinkling like ''azúcar'' dust on a cake.","cloze_distractors_en":["Napkin","Butter","Ticket"],"examples":[{"es":"Mi café está muy amargo, ¿me pasas el azúcar?","en":"My coffee is too bitter, could you pass me the sugar?"},{"es":"Por favor, ¿me puede traer un poco de azúcar para mi café?","en":"Could you please bring me some sugar for my coffee?"},{"es":"El camarero puso dos sobres de azúcar en la bandeja.","en":"The waiter put two packets of sugar on the tray."}]},{"spanish_text":"Sal","english_text":"Salt","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A white crystalline mineral used as a seasoning and preservative.","main_translations_es":["sal","sal de mesa","cloruro de sodio"],"collocations":["salt and pepper","a pinch of salt","take it with a grain of salt","salt the water"],"synonyms_en":["sodium chloride","seasoning","NaCl"],"example_sentence":"Add a pinch of salt to the soup.","example_es":"Añade una pizca de sal a la sopa.","example_en":"Add a pinch of salt to the soup.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a sea of salt where the word sal splashes onto the plate.","cloze_distractors_en":["Sand","Soap","Dirt","Glue"],"examples":[{"es":"Añade una pizca de sal a la sopa.","en":"Add a pinch of salt to the soup."},{"es":"El camarero trajo el salero con más sal para mis patatas fritas.","en":"The waiter brought the shaker with more salt for my french fries."},{"es":"Por favor, ¿podrías pasarme la sal para mi huevo?","en":"Could you please pass me the salt for my egg?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Pimienta","english_text":"Pepper","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A pungent spice made from the dried fruit of the pepper plant, commonly used to season food.","main_translations_es":["pimienta negra","pimienta picante","pimienta de la india"],"collocations":["black pepper","pepper shaker","pepper spray","pepper flakes"],"synonyms_en":["seasoning","spice","condiment"],"example_sentence":"The customer wants a little more pepper on his sandwich.","example_es":"El cliente quiere un poco más de pimienta en su sándwich.","example_en":"The customer wants a little more pepper on his sandwich.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a pepper shaker spilling bright red pimienta onto a sizzling steak.","cloze_distractors_en":["Napkin","Coffee","Silver","Window"],"examples":[{"es":"El cliente quiere un poco más de pimienta en su sándwich.","en":"The customer wants a little more pepper on his sandwich."},{"es":"El cliente pidió sal y pimienta para su sopa.","en":"The customer asked for salt and pepper for his soup."},{"es":"Por favor, pon un poco más de pimienta en mi ensalada.","en":"Please put a little more pepper on my salad."}]},{"spanish_text":"Hielo","english_text":"Ice","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A solid form of water that is frozen, often used to chill drinks or preserve food.","main_translations_es":["hielo","hielo picado","hielo en cubos"],"collocations":["on ice","break the ice","ice cream","ice water"],"synonyms_en":["frozen water","solid water","ice cube"],"example_sentence":"Put the ice in the drink.","example_es":"Pon el hielo en la bebida.","example_en":"Put the ice in the drink.","mnemonic_en":"Picture icy eyes staring at a cold ''hielo'' cube melting in a glass.","cloze_distractors_en":["Sand","Soap","Dirt"],"examples":[{"es":"Pon el hielo en la bebida.","en":"Put the ice in the drink."},{"es":"Mi café helado necesita más hielo.","en":"My iced coffee needs more ice."},{"es":"Por favor, sirve el refresco con mucho hielo.","en":"Please serve the soda with a lot of ice."}]},{"spanish_text":"Servilleta","english_text":"Napkin","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A small piece of cloth or paper used for wiping the mouth or hands while eating.","main_translations_es":["servilleta de papel","pañuelo","toalla de mesa"],"collocations":["paper napkin","napkin ring","wet napkin","napkin holder"],"synonyms_en":["serviette","paper napkin"],"example_sentence":"Please pass me the napkin to clean the table.","example_es":"Por favor, pásame la servilleta para limpiar la mesa.","example_en":"Please pass me the napkin to clean the table.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a napkin as a tiny nap for a kin, like a servilleta covering spilled soup","cloze_distractors_en":["Spatula","Blanket","Curtain","Stapler"],"examples":[{"es":"Por favor, pásame la servilleta para limpiar la mesa.","en":"Please pass me the napkin to clean the table."},{"es":"Se me cayó el café, ¿me das una servilleta?","en":"I spilled my coffee, could you give me a napkin?"},{"es":"No encuentro la servilleta para limpiarme los dedos después de comer el pastel.","en":"I cannot find the napkin to wipe my fingers after eating the cake."}]},{"spanish_text":"Taza","english_text":"Cup","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A small, open container, typically with a handle, used for drinking liquids.","main_translations_es":["taza","copa","tazón"],"collocations":["cup of tea","cup of coffee","cup of water","cup of sugar"],"synonyms_en":["mug","drinking vessel","beaker"],"example_sentence":"I''m going to buy a new cup for my coffee.","example_es":"Voy a comprar una taza nueva para mi café.","example_en":"I''m going to buy a new cup for my coffee.","mnemonic_en":"I picture a cup with the Spanish word taza painted on its rim.","cloze_distractors_en":["Fork","Tray","Menu","Bill"],"examples":[{"es":"Voy a comprar una taza nueva para mi café.","en":"I''m going to buy a new cup for my coffee."},{"es":"Por favor, lléname la taza con café recién hecho.","en":"Please fill my cup with freshly brewed coffee."},{"es":"Se me cayó la taza al suelo y se rompió en pedazos.","en":"I dropped the cup on the floor and it shattered into pieces."}]},{"spanish_text":"Vaso","english_text":"Glass","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A hard, transparent material used for windows, bottles, and other objects.","main_translations_es":["vaso","copa","copa de vino"],"collocations":["glass of water","glass ceiling","glass jar","glass bottle"],"synonyms_en":["cup","tumbler","drinking vessel"],"example_sentence":"Put the glass on the table.","example_es":"Pon el vaso sobre la mesa.","example_en":"Put the glass on the table.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a clear glass that looks just like a Spanish vaso on the table","cloze_distractors_en":["Staple","Puddle","Gravel"],"examples":[{"es":"Pon el vaso sobre la mesa.","en":"Put the glass on the table."},{"es":"Limpia el vaso sucio con agua caliente.","en":"Clean the dirty glass with hot water."},{"es":"Llena el vaso con jugo de naranja fresco.","en":"Fill the glass with fresh orange juice."}]},{"spanish_text":"Plato","english_text":"Plate","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A flat dish used for serving or eating food.","main_translations_es":["plato","cazuela","plato hondo"],"collocations":["plate of food","clean your plate","plate tectonics"],"synonyms_en":["dish","platter","serving dish"],"example_sentence":"I placed the plate on the table.","example_es":"Puse el plato sobre la mesa.","example_en":"I placed the plate on the table.","mnemonic_en":"Picture Plato serving ideas on a shining plate","cloze_distractors_en":["Faucet","Budget","Ticket"],"examples":[{"es":"Puse el plato sobre la mesa.","en":"I placed the plate on the table."},{"es":"El cliente pidió otro plato para compartir el postre.","en":"The customer asked for another plate to share the dessert."},{"es":"Por favor, lava el plato sucio después de terminar el postre.","en":"Please wash the plate after you finish the dessert."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cuchara","english_text":"Spoon","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A utensil with a shallow bowl and a handle used for scooping, stirring, or serving food.","main_translations_es":["cucharita","cucharilla","cuchara de té"],"collocations":["spoonful of sugar","spoon feeding","spoon and fork","spoon in the drawer"],"synonyms_en":["ladle","dipper","spoonful"],"example_sentence":"I need a spoon to stir the soup.","example_es":"Necesito una cuchara para mezclar la sopa.","example_en":"I need a spoon to stir the soup.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a shiny spoon acting as a tiny Cuchara scooping soup.","cloze_distractors_en":["Knife","Straw","Napkin"],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito una cuchara para mezclar la sopa.","en":"I need a spoon to stir the soup."},{"es":"El café está muy caliente, usa la cuchara para enfriarlo.","en":"The coffee is very hot, use the spoon to cool it down."},{"es":"Por favor, ¿me traes una cuchara para el postre?","en":"Please, could you bring me a spoon for the dessert?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Tenedor","english_text":"Fork","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A utensil with two or more prongs used for eating or serving food.","main_translations_es":["tenedor","tenedor de mesa","tenedor de cocina"],"collocations":["fork in the road","fork out","fork over","forklift"],"synonyms_en":["prong","tine"],"example_sentence":"Can I get a fork for this pasta, please?","example_es":"¿Me das un tenedor para esta pasta, por favor?","example_en":"Can I get a fork for this pasta, please?","mnemonic_en":"Picture a fork as a ten-eh-door opening to scoop up food.","cloze_distractors_en":["Menu","Sugar","Coffee","Cup"],"examples":[{"es":"¿Me das un tenedor para esta pasta, por favor?","en":"Can I get a fork for this pasta, please?"},{"es":"Necesito un tenedor para comer el pastel.","en":"I need a fork to eat the cake."},{"es":"¿Tienes un tenedor para la ensalada?","en":"Do you have a fork for the salad?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Cuchillo","english_text":"Knife","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A cutting instrument with a blade and handle used for slicing, cutting, or stabbing.","main_translations_es":["cuchilla","navaja","cuchillo de cocina"],"collocations":["knife and fork","knife edge","knife block","knife skills"],"synonyms_en":["blade","cutting tool","dagger"],"example_sentence":"I need a knife to cut the bread.","example_es":"Necesito un cuchillo para cortar el pan.","example_en":"I need a knife to cut the bread.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a knife slicing a cuckoo, because cuchillo sounds like cuckoo","cloze_distractors_en":["Wallet","Pillow","Camera","Ticket"],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito un cuchillo para cortar el pan.","en":"I need a knife to cut the bread."},{"es":"Por favor, ¿me puede traer un cuchillo para mi sándwich?","en":"Please, can you bring me a knife for my sandwich?"},{"es":"El cuchillo está al lado del plato de postre.","en":"The knife is next to the dessert plate."}]},{"spanish_text":"Bandeja","english_text":"Tray","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A flat, shallow container used for holding or carrying items.","main_translations_es":["charola","plato","cesta"],"collocations":["serving tray","tray of cookies","tray table","tray line"],"synonyms_en":["platter","serving dish","dish"],"example_sentence":"I placed the food on the tray.","example_es":"Puse la comida en la bandeja.","example_en":"I placed the food on the tray.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a tray wrapped in a bandage, a real bandeja.","cloze_distractors_en":["Bridge","Stair","Fence"],"examples":[{"es":"Puse la comida en la bandeja.","en":"I placed the food on the tray."},{"es":"Por favor, lleva tu bandeja a la mesa.","en":"Please carry your tray to the table."},{"es":"El camarero dejó la bandeja sobre el mostrador.","en":"The waiter left the tray on the counter."}]},{"spanish_text":"Mesa","english_text":"Table","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A piece of furniture with a flat top and legs, used for working, eating, or placing items.","main_translations_es":["mesa","mesa de comedor","mesa de escritorio"],"collocations":["dinner table","table of contents","round table","table tennis"],"synonyms_en":["desk","chart","list"],"example_sentence":"Please clean this table after we leave.","example_es":"Por favor, limpie esta mesa después de que nos vayamos.","example_en":"Please clean this table after we leave.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a wooden table shaped like a flat mesa in the desert, supporting plates.","cloze_distractors_en":["Staple","Marble","Bubble"],"examples":[{"es":"Por favor, limpie esta mesa después de que nos vayamos.","en":"Please clean this table after we leave."},{"es":"Hay una mesa libre cerca de la ventana.","en":"There is a table free near the window."},{"es":"El camarero trajo el café a nuestra mesa.","en":"The waiter brought the coffee to our table."}]},{"spanish_text":"Silla","english_text":"Chair","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A piece of furniture with a seat, back, and legs, used for sitting.","main_translations_es":["butaca","asiento","sillón"],"collocations":["chair the meeting","chair of the board","rocking chair","chairperson"],"synonyms_en":["seat","stool","armchair"],"example_sentence":"The chair is next to the table.","example_es":"La silla está junto a la mesa.","example_en":"The chair is next to the table.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a chair with a seal (cilla) perched, cheering you to sit.","cloze_distractors_en":["Ceiling","Kitchen","Window","Manager"],"examples":[{"es":"La silla está junto a la mesa.","en":"The chair is next to the table."},{"es":"Por favor, trae una silla extra para este cliente.","en":"Please bring an extra chair for this customer."},{"es":"El cliente se levantó de la silla para pedir otro café.","en":"The customer stood up from the chair to order another coffee."}]},{"spanish_text":"Menú","english_text":"Menu","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A list of dishes offered by a restaurant or a set of selectable options in a software program.","main_translations_es":["Carta","Lista de platos","Selección"],"collocations":["menu options","menu board","menu item","menu planning"],"synonyms_en":["list of dishes","food list","bill of fare"],"example_sentence":"Can you pass me the menu, please?","example_es":"¿Puedes pasarme el menú, por favor?","example_en":"Can you pass me the menu, please?","mnemonic_en":"Picture a menu where the word men serve you tacos.","cloze_distractors_en":["chair","door","window","floor"],"examples":[{"es":"¿Puedes pasarme el menú, por favor?","en":"Can you pass me the menu, please?"},{"es":"¿Tienen un menú de desayuno todo el día?","en":"Do you have an all-day breakfast menu?"},{"es":"No puedo leer el menú sin mis gafas.","en":"I cannot read the menu without my glasses."}]},{"spanish_text":"Mostrador","english_text":"Counter","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A flat surface in a shop, restaurant, or bank where transactions are conducted.","main_translations_es":["mostrador","barra","taquilla"],"collocations":["counter offer","counter strike","counter argument","counter top"],"synonyms_en":["bar","service desk","checkout"],"example_sentence":"I left my bag on the store counter.","example_es":"Dejé mi bolso en el mostrador de la tienda.","example_en":"I left my bag on the store counter.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a shop counter with a most rad sign flashing the price.","cloze_distractors_en":["Ceiling","Kitchen","Fridge"],"examples":[{"es":"Dejé mi bolso en el mostrador de la tienda.","en":"I left my bag on the store counter."},{"es":"El barista puso mi café caliente sobre el mostrador.","en":"The barista placed my hot coffee on the counter."},{"es":"Por favor, pague su pedido en el mostrador.","en":"Please pay for your order at the counter."}]},{"spanish_text":"Terraza","english_text":"Patio","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"An outdoor space adjoining a building, often paved and used for dining or recreation.","main_translations_es":["azotea","balcón"],"collocations":["patio furniture","patio door","patio garden"],"synonyms_en":["courtyard","deck","terrace"],"example_sentence":"We sat on the patio to have coffee.","example_es":"Nos sentamos en la terraza a tomar el café.","example_en":"We sat on the patio to have coffee.","mnemonic_en":"Visualize a patio built on a Spanish terraza, the word ''pat'' slapping the ''io'' tiles.","cloze_distractors_en":["Kitchen","Pantry","Fridge","Faucet"],"examples":[{"es":"Nos sentamos en la terraza a tomar el café.","en":"We sat on the patio to have coffee."},{"es":"Hace buen tiempo, así que prefiero una mesa en la terraza.","en":"The weather is nice, so I prefer a table on the patio."},{"es":"El camarero nos trajo el menú a la terraza.","en":"The waiter brought us the menu to the patio."}]},{"spanish_text":"Para llevar","english_text":"To go","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To order food or drink to be taken away and consumed elsewhere.","main_translations_es":["para llevar","para llevar a casa","para llevar fuera"],"collocations":["to go out","to go ahead","to go for","to go on"],"synonyms_en":["to leave","to depart","to head out"],"example_sentence":"I want the sandwich to go.","example_es":"Quiero el sándwich para llevar.","example_en":"I want the sandwich to go.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a waiter shouting Go while handing you a para llevar bag.","cloze_distractors_en":["To stay","To bake","To wait","To brew"],"examples":[{"es":"Quiero el sándwich para llevar.","en":"I want the sandwich to go."},{"es":"Un café solo, por favor, para llevar.","en":"One black coffee, please, to go."},{"es":"No tengo tiempo de sentarme, así que mi pedido es para llevar.","en":"I do not have time to sit down, so my order is to go."}]},{"spanish_text":"Para aquí","english_text":"For here","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Used to indicate that something should be placed or remain at this location.","main_translations_es":["para consumir aquí","para comer aquí","para quedarse aquí"],"collocations":["Is that for here or to go?","I''ll have it for here.","Do you want it for here?","Can I get that for here?"],"synonyms_en":["to stay","for on‑site","for dining in"],"example_sentence":"For here or to go?","example_es":"¿Para aquí o para llevar?","example_en":"For here or to go?","mnemonic_en":"Picture a floor mat that reads FOR right here","cloze_distractors_en":["By myself","In return","At least","On account"],"examples":[{"es":"¿Para aquí o para llevar?","en":"For here or to go?"},{"es":"Quiero mi café para aquí, por favor.","en":"I want my coffee for here, please."},{"es":"Si se va a sentar, es para aquí.","en":"If you are going to sit down, it is for here."}]},{"spanish_text":"Quiero pedir","english_text":"I want to order","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement expressing a desire to place an order.","main_translations_es":["Me gustaría pedir","Deseo pedir","Quisiera pedir"],"collocations":["I want to order a pizza","I want to order online","I want to order now","I want to order something"],"synonyms_en":["I''d like to place an order","I would like to order","I wish to order"],"example_sentence":"I want to order a latte to go.","example_es":"Quiero pedir un café con leche para llevar.","example_en":"I want to order a latte to go.","mnemonic_en":"I hand the chef a huge menu that reads ''quiero-pedir'', shouting I want to order.","cloze_distractors_en":["I refuse to buy","I never drinked","I am being served","I could have been"],"examples":[{"es":"Quiero pedir un café con leche para llevar.","en":"I want to order a latte to go."},{"es":"Quiero pedir un croissant de chocolate y un té.","en":"I want to order a chocolate croissant and a tea."},{"es":"Quiero pedir el menú del día para almorzar.","en":"I want to order the lunch special for my meal."}]},{"spanish_text":"Quisiera un...","english_text":"I would like a...","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A polite way to say that you want something.","main_translations_es":["Me gustaría un...","Desearía un...","Quisiera un..."],"collocations":["I would like a coffee","I would like a drink","I would like a break","I would like a moment"],"synonyms_en":["I''d like a","I want a","Give me a"],"example_sentence":"I would like a coffee, please.","example_es":"Quisiera un café, por favor.","example_en":"I would like a coffee, please.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a key (qui) opening a menu, prompting you to say I would like a...","cloze_distractors_en":["I am become a","They will be a","Which is really a","Where should be a"],"examples":[{"es":"Quisiera un café, por favor.","en":"I would like a coffee, please."},{"es":"Quisiera un croissant de chocolate para desayunar.","en":"I would like a chocolate croissant for breakfast."},{"es":"Cuando el camarero pregunte qué desea tomar, diga: Quisiera un zumo de naranja recién exprimido.","en":"When the server asks what you want to drink, say: I would like a freshly squeezed orange juice."}]},{"spanish_text":"¿Qué recomienda?","english_text":"What do you recommend?","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"question","definition_en":"A polite request asking for a suggestion or advice.","main_translations_es":["¿Qué me recomiendas?","¿Qué sugieres?","¿Qué me aconsejas?"],"collocations":["What do you recommend for dinner?","What do you recommend we do?","What do you recommend we try?"],"synonyms_en":["Any suggestions?","What would you suggest?","Do you have any recommendations?"],"example_sentence":"I am undecided about the menu, what do you recommend?","example_es":"Estoy indeciso con el menú, ¿qué recomienda?","example_en":"I am undecided about the menu, what do you recommend?","mnemonic_en":"Picture a waiter asking, \"What do you recommend?\" while holding a menu titled RECOMIENDA.","cloze_distractors_en":["How much I pay?","Where is the exit?","When you close shop?","Who is the manager?"],"examples":[{"es":"Estoy indeciso con el menú, ¿qué recomienda?","en":"I am undecided about the menu, what do you recommend?"},{"es":"Es mi primera vez aquí, ¿qué recomienda de postre?","en":"It is my first time here, what do you recommend for dessert?"},{"es":"No sé qué café elegir, ¿qué recomienda hoy?","en":"I do not know which coffee to choose, what do you recommend today?"}]},{"spanish_text":"¿Qué lleva?","english_text":"What is in it?","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"question","definition_en":"A question asking about the contents of something.","main_translations_es":["¿Qué contiene?","¿Qué hay dentro?","¿Qué incluye?"],"collocations":["Can you tell me what is in it?","I wonder what is in it.","Do you know what is in it?","Let''s find out what is in it."],"synonyms_en":["What’s inside?","What does it contain?","What’s in it?"],"example_sentence":"I am allergic to onions, so what is in it?","example_es":"¿Qué lleva el burrito del día?","example_en":"I am allergic to onions, so what is in it?","mnemonic_en":"Ask what is in it and hear a chef shout Que lleva about the ingredients.","cloze_distractors_en":["Who are they?","Where go you?","Which is them?","When be that?"],"examples":[{"es":"¿Qué lleva el burrito del día?","en":"I am allergic to onions, so what is in it?"},{"es":"Veo un sándwich extraño, ¿qué lleva?","en":"I see a strange sandwich, what is in it?"},{"es":"Este batido se ve delicioso, ¿qué lleva?","en":"This smoothie looks delicious, what is in it?"}]},{"spanish_text":"¿Tiene opciones vegetarianas?","english_text":"Do you have vegetarian options?","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"question","definition_en":"A polite inquiry asking whether vegetarian dishes are available.","main_translations_es":["¿Ofrecen opciones vegetarianas?","¿Hay opciones vegetarianas?","¿Tienen platos vegetarianos?"],"collocations":["Do you have vegetarian options on the menu?","Do you have vegetarian options available?","Do you have vegetarian options here?"],"synonyms_en":["Are vegetarian choices available?","Do you offer vegetarian dishes?","Can I get a vegetarian meal?"],"example_sentence":"I am allergic to meat, do you have vegetarian options?","example_es":"Soy alérgico a la carne, ¿tiene opciones vegetarianas?","example_en":"I am allergic to meat, do you have vegetarian options?","mnemonic_en":"Visualize a teen (tiene) asking, ''Do you have vegetarian options?'' at a restaurant.","cloze_distractors_en":["Is the meat cooked well?","Can you serve me bacon?","Will you prepare beef now?"],"examples":[{"es":"Soy alérgico a la carne, ¿tiene opciones vegetarianas?","en":"I am allergic to meat, do you have vegetarian options?"},{"es":"Mi amiga no come carne, ¿tiene opciones vegetarianas en el menú?","en":"My friend does not eat meat, do you have vegetarian options on the menu?"},{"es":"Para mi almuerzo, ¿tiene opciones vegetarianas disponibles hoy?","en":"For my lunch, do you have vegetarian options available today?"}]},{"spanish_text":"¿Tiene leche sin lactosa?","english_text":"Do you have lactose-free milk?","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"question","definition_en":"A polite inquiry asking if lactose-free milk is available.","main_translations_es":["¿Tiene leche sin lactosa?","¿Hay leche sin lactosa?","¿Dispone de leche sin lactosa?"],"collocations":["lactose-free milk options","order lactose-free milk","buy lactose-free milk","lactose-free milk is available"],"synonyms_en":["Is lactose-free milk available?","Do you carry lactose-free milk?","Can I get lactose-free milk?"],"example_sentence":"My stomach doesn''t handle regular milk well, do you have lactose-free milk?","example_es":"Mi estómago no tolera la leche normal, ¿tiene leche sin lactosa?","example_en":"My stomach doesn''t handle regular milk well, do you have lactose-free milk?","mnemonic_en":"Picture a lactose‑free milk saying Do you have to a Spanish shopper","cloze_distractors_en":["Are you allergic to sugar?","Will you pay with credit card?","Have you seen my lost wallet?"],"examples":[{"es":"Mi estómago no tolera la leche normal, ¿tiene leche sin lactosa?","en":"My stomach doesn''t handle regular milk well, do you have lactose-free milk?"},{"es":"Mi hijo es intolerante, ¿tiene leche sin lactosa?","en":"My son is intolerant, do you have lactose-free milk?"},{"es":"Mi dieta es estricta y no puedo consumir lácteos normales, ¿tiene leche sin lactosa?","en":"I have a dietary restriction and cannot drink regular milk, do you have lactose-free milk?"}]},{"spanish_text":"¿Sin azúcar?","english_text":"Without sugar?","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"question","definition_en":"A question asking whether something contains no sugar.","main_translations_es":["¿Sin azúcar añadido?","¿Libre de azúcar?","¿Sin azúcar?"],"collocations":["coffee without sugar","order it without sugar","ask for it without sugar","drink it without sugar"],"synonyms_en":["unsweetened","sugar-free","no sugar"],"example_sentence":"Without sugar? the waiter asked while taking my order.","example_es":"¿Sin azúcar? preguntó el camarero al anotar mi pedido.","example_en":"Without sugar? the waiter asked while taking my order.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a tiny person shouting wee toss sugar as they drop the sweet, reminding you of without sugar.","cloze_distractors_en":["Under table?","Before lunch?","Beyond reason?","Behind counter?"],"examples":[{"es":"¿Sin azúcar? preguntó el camarero al anotar mi pedido.","en":"Without sugar? the waiter asked while taking my order."},{"es":"Le entregué el café y me miró dudoso: ¿Sin azúcar?","en":"I handed him the coffee and he looked at me doubtfully: Without sugar?"},{"es":"El cliente devolvió la taza y cuestionó: ¿Sin azúcar?","en":"The customer returned the cup and questioned: Without sugar?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Con hielo","english_text":"With ice","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Indicates that something is served or prepared together with ice.","main_translations_es":["Con hielo","Con hielo incluido","Con hielo al servir"],"collocations":["served with ice","drink it with ice","on the rocks","mixed with ice"],"synonyms_en":["on the rocks","chilled","served over ice"],"example_sentence":"I want my drink with ice.","example_es":"Quiero mi bebida con hielo.","example_en":"I want my drink with ice.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a cone of ice, con ice, as you say with ice","cloze_distractors_en":["By the door","For the bill","In the oven","Under the rug"],"examples":[{"es":"Quiero mi bebida con hielo.","en":"I want my drink with ice."},{"es":"Por favor, sírveme el café solo con hielo.","en":"Please serve my black coffee with ice."},{"es":"Por favor, ponme un café solo con hielo para refrescarme.","en":"Please give me a black coffee with ice to cool down."}]},{"spanish_text":"Caliente","english_text":"Hot","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Having a high temperature or feeling warmth.","main_translations_es":["Caluroso","Ardiente","Candente"],"collocations":["hot weather","hot coffee","hot topic","hot deal"],"synonyms_en":["warm","heated","scorching"],"example_sentence":"The coffee is hot.","example_es":"El café está caliente.","example_en":"The coffee is hot.","mnemonic_en":"The hot stove sizzles like a cali‑ENTE chili.","cloze_distractors_en":["Fast","Loud","Late","Hard"],"examples":[{"es":"El café está caliente.","en":"The coffee is hot."},{"es":"Cuidado, la sopa está muy caliente.","en":"Careful, the soup is very hot."},{"es":"Prefiero beber el té caliente.","en":"I prefer to drink the tea hot."}]},{"spanish_text":"Frío","english_text":"Cold","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Having a low temperature; not warm.","main_translations_es":["Frío","Helado","Gélido"],"collocations":["cold weather","cold drink","cold shoulder","catch a cold"],"synonyms_en":["chilly","frigid","cool"],"example_sentence":"The coffee is cold, could you heat it up?","example_es":"El café está frío, ¿podrías calentarlo?","example_en":"The coffee is cold, could you heat it up?","mnemonic_en":"Cold feels like a fridge full of fríó ice cubes.","cloze_distractors_en":["Loud","Busy","Heavy","Slow"],"examples":[{"es":"El café está frío, ¿podrías calentarlo?","en":"The coffee is cold, could you heat it up?"},{"es":"Prefiero mi té frío con un poco de limón.","en":"I prefer my tea cold with a little bit of lemon."},{"es":"La leche de la nevera está muy fría.","en":"The milk from the fridge is very cold."}]},{"spanish_text":"Tibio","english_text":"Warm","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Having a moderately high temperature that is comfortably heated, but not hot.","main_translations_es":["cálido","templado"],"collocations":["warm welcome","warm weather","warm feeling","warm up"],"synonyms_en":["hot","heated","toasty"],"example_sentence":"The coffee is warm, it''s neither cold nor hot.","example_es":"El café está tibio, no está ni frío ni caliente.","example_en":"The coffee is warm, it''s neither cold nor hot.","mnemonic_en":"A warm sweater feels tibio, like a gentle hug on a cool day.","cloze_distractors_en":["Frozen","Bitter","Strong","Spicy"],"examples":[{"es":"El café está tibio, no está ni frío ni caliente.","en":"The coffee is warm, it''s neither cold nor hot."},{"es":"El panecillo acaba de salir del horno y todavía está tibio.","en":"The muffin just came out of the oven and is still warm."},{"es":"Prefiero beber el té cuando está tibio, no hirviendo.","en":"I prefer to drink my tea when it is warm, not boiling."}]},{"spanish_text":"Grande","english_text":"Large","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Having a size that is greater than normal or expected.","main_translations_es":["Enorme","Gigante","Amplio"],"collocations":["large amount","large scale","large number","large size"],"synonyms_en":["big","huge","massive"],"example_sentence":"I would like a large coffee, please.","example_es":"Quisiera un café grande, por favor.","example_en":"I would like a large coffee, please.","mnemonic_en":"Think of a L‑shaped arch holding a huge grand grande sign.","cloze_distractors_en":["Heavy","Bright","Loud","Quick"],"examples":[{"es":"Quisiera un café grande, por favor.","en":"I would like a large coffee, please."},{"es":"Como tengo mucha sed, prefiero el refresco en vaso grande.","en":"Since I am very thirsty, I prefer the soda in a large cup."},{"es":"El cliente pidió un batido grande de chocolate.","en":"The customer ordered a large chocolate milkshake."}]},{"spanish_text":"Mediano","english_text":"Medium","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Of intermediate size, amount, or quality.","main_translations_es":["Intermedio","De tamaño medio","Normal"],"collocations":["medium size","medium rare","medium level","medium pace"],"synonyms_en":["average","intermediate","mid-sized"],"example_sentence":"I would like a Medium coffee, please.","example_es":"Quisiera un café de tamaño mediano, por favor.","example_en":"I would like a Medium coffee, please.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a medium pizza called mediano on the menu.","cloze_distractors_en":["Median","Moderate","Centric"],"examples":[{"es":"Quisiera un café de tamaño mediano, por favor.","en":"I would like a Medium coffee, please."},{"es":"Para el batido, prefiero el vaso mediano.","en":"For the milkshake, I prefer the Medium cup."},{"es":"El cliente pidió un té helado mediano para llevar.","en":"The customer ordered a Medium iced tea to go."}]},{"spanish_text":"Pequeño","english_text":"Small","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Having a limited size, amount, or extent.","main_translations_es":["pequeño","chico","menudo"],"collocations":["small business","small town","small problem","small amount"],"synonyms_en":["tiny","little","compact"],"example_sentence":"I would like a small coffee, please.","example_es":"Quisiera un café pequeño, por favor.","example_en":"I would like a small coffee, please.","mnemonic_en":"A small snail whispers ''pequeño'' as it hides in a leaf.","cloze_distractors_en":["Heavy","Brief","Faint","Loose"],"examples":[{"es":"Quisiera un café pequeño, por favor.","en":"I would like a small coffee, please."},{"es":"El vaso pequeño es para el jugo de naranja.","en":"The small cup is for the orange juice."},{"es":"Solo queda un muffin pequeño en la vitrina.","en":"There is only one small muffin left in the display case."}]},{"spanish_text":"Extra grande","english_text":"Extra large","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Of a size that is larger than large; very big.","main_translations_es":["muy grande","enorme","gigante"],"collocations":["extra-large size","extra-large shirt","extra-large pizza","extra-large portion"],"synonyms_en":["oversized","huge","massive"],"example_sentence":"I would like an Extra large coffee to go, please.","example_es":"Quisiera un café para llevar de tamaño Extra grande, por favor.","example_en":"I would like an Extra large coffee to go, please.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a giant extra-large shirt that says extra grande on a runway.","cloze_distractors_en":["Extra hungry","Extra thirsty","Extra sleepy","Extra cloudy"],"examples":[{"es":"Quisiera un café para llevar de tamaño Extra grande, por favor.","en":"I would like an Extra large coffee to go, please."},{"es":"El batido de chocolate cuesta un poco más si lo pides Extra grande.","en":"The chocolate milkshake costs a bit more if you order it Extra large."},{"es":"Para el té helado, ¿prefiere el vaso mediano o el Extra grande?","en":"For the iced tea, do you prefer the medium or the Extra large cup?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Una ración","english_text":"One portion","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A single serving or amount of food.","main_translations_es":["Una porción","Una ración"],"collocations":["one portion of","one portion per day","one portion serving","one portion size"],"synonyms_en":["a serving","a helping","a share"],"example_sentence":"I want to order one portion of paella for dinner.","example_es":"Quiero pedir una ración de paella para cenar.","example_en":"I want to order one portion of paella for dinner.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a single ration, a tiny ración of food on a plate.","cloze_distractors_en":["One kitchen","One recipe","One utensil","One appetite"],"examples":[{"es":"Quiero pedir una ración de paella para cenar.","en":"I want to order one portion of paella for dinner."},{"es":"Para el aperitivo, nos gustaría solo una ración de calamares.","en":"For the appetizer, we would like only one portion of calamari."},{"es":"El camarero nos trajo una ración de patatas bravas para compartir.","en":"The waiter brought us one portion of spicy potatoes to share."}]},{"spanish_text":"Medio","english_text":"Half","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"One of two equal parts of a whole.","main_translations_es":["Mitad","Parcial","Semi"],"collocations":["half the time","half a dozen","half way","half past"],"synonyms_en":["semi","fifty percent","partially"],"example_sentence":"I ate half a sandwich.","example_es":"Comí medio sándwich.","example_en":"I ate half a sandwich.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine cutting a medio pizza in half.","cloze_distractors_en":["Plus","Once","Very"],"examples":[{"es":"Comí medio sándwich.","en":"I ate half a sandwich."},{"es":"Por favor, dame medio litro de leche.","en":"Please give me half a liter of milk."},{"es":"El café cuesta medio dólar más con leche de almendras.","en":"The coffee costs half a dollar more with almond milk."}]},{"spanish_text":"Entero","english_text":"Whole","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Complete; not divided or lacking any part.","main_translations_es":["completo","total","integral"],"collocations":["the whole story","the whole world","the whole truth","the whole shebang"],"synonyms_en":["entire","complete","intact"],"example_sentence":"I would like a whole croissant to go with my coffee.","example_es":"Me gustaría un croissant entero para acompañar mi café.","example_en":"I would like a whole croissant to go with my coffee.","mnemonic_en":"Think of an entire (entero) pizza, whole with no slices missing.","cloze_distractors_en":["Empty","Rough","Loose"],"examples":[{"es":"Me gustaría un croissant entero para acompañar mi café.","en":"I would like a whole croissant to go with my coffee."},{"es":"Quiero leche entera para mi café.","en":"I want whole milk for my coffee."},{"es":"Me comí el sándwich entero en el desayuno.","en":"I ate the whole sandwich for breakfast."}]},{"spanish_text":"¿Algo más?","english_text":"Anything else?","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"question","definition_en":"A polite way of asking if there is any additional request or information.","main_translations_es":["¿Algo más?","¿Hay algo más?","¿Algo más que necesites?"],"collocations":["Anything else?","Anything else you need?","Anything else I can do?","Anything else you want to add?"],"synonyms_en":["Anything more?","Anything additional?"],"example_sentence":"Here is your coffee. Anything else?","example_es":"Aquí tiene su café. ¿Algo más?","example_en":"Here is your coffee. Anything else?","mnemonic_en":"Picture a waiter asking Anything else? while handing you a bag labeled ALGO MAS.","cloze_distractors_en":["Everything finished?","Nobody coming?","Anywhere else?","Everywhere gone?"],"examples":[{"es":"Aquí tiene su café. ¿Algo más?","en":"Here is your coffee. Anything else?"},{"es":"Ya tengo el sándwich y el agua. ¿Algo más?","en":"I have the sandwich and the water. Anything else?"},{"es":"He anotado su pedido de dos muffins. ¿Algo más?","en":"I have noted your order for two muffins. Anything else?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Eso es todo","english_text":"That is all","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"It means that there is nothing more; that is everything.","main_translations_es":["Eso es todo"],"collocations":["That''s all for now","That''s all she wrote","That''s all folks","That''s all there is"],"synonyms_en":["That''s it","All done","That''s everything"],"example_sentence":"I just want a black coffee, that is all.","example_es":"Solo quiero un café solo, eso es todo.","example_en":"I just want a black coffee, that is all.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a complete set (todo) and you declare, \"That is all\".","cloze_distractors_en":["Always welcome","Please proceed","Keep the change"],"examples":[{"es":"Solo quiero un café solo, eso es todo.","en":"I just want a black coffee, that is all."},{"es":"Quiero un café y un muffin, eso es todo.","en":"I would like a coffee and a muffin, that is all."},{"es":"No necesito nada más, eso es todo.","en":"I do not need anything else, that is all."}]},{"spanish_text":"Aquí tiene","english_text":"Here you go","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used when handing something to someone.","main_translations_es":["Aquí tienes","Aquí está","Aquí lo tienes"],"collocations":["Here you go, thanks!","Here you go, enjoy!","Here you go, as requested"],"synonyms_en":["There you are","Here it is","Here you have it"],"example_sentence":"Here you go, your coffee.","example_es":"Aquí tiene su café.","example_en":"Here you go, your coffee.","mnemonic_en":"Hand a key to a teen and say, Here you go.","cloze_distractors_en":["Take it back","Watch your step","Keep the receipt","Leave the tip"],"examples":[{"es":"Aquí tiene su café.","en":"Here you go, your coffee."},{"es":"Aquí tiene el cambio de su compra.","en":"Here you go, your change from the purchase."},{"es":"Aquí tiene su café con leche recién hecho.","en":"Here you go, your freshly made latte."}]},{"spanish_text":"Enseguida","english_text":"Right away","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"Immediately; without delay.","main_translations_es":["de inmediato","inmediatamente","al instante"],"collocations":["I''ll do it right away","right away, please","right away, thank you"],"synonyms_en":["immediately","at once","straightaway"],"example_sentence":"I will prepare your cappuccino right away.","example_es":"Le preparo su capuchino enseguida.","example_en":"I will prepare your cappuccino right away.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a right arrow that instantly ''in segue'' to the next scene, meaning right away.","cloze_distractors_en":["Quite rarely","Almost never","Rather poorly"],"examples":[{"es":"Le preparo su capuchino enseguida.","en":"I will prepare your cappuccino right away."},{"es":"El camarero traerá su café en seguida.","en":"The waiter will bring your coffee right away."},{"es":"Por favor, prepare mi pedido en seguida.","en":"Please prepare my order right away."}]},{"spanish_text":"Su pedido está listo","english_text":"Your order is ready","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement informing someone that their order has been prepared and is now available.","main_translations_es":["Tu pedido está listo","El pedido está listo","Ya está listo su pedido"],"collocations":["Your order is ready for pickup","Your order is ready to go","Your order is ready now","Your order is ready, thank you"],"synonyms_en":["Your order is prepared","Your order is complete","Your order is set"],"example_sentence":"Your order is ready to be picked up.","example_es":"Su pedido está listo para ser recogido.","example_en":"Your order is ready to be picked up.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a your order wearing a ready badge while a Spanish waiter says Su pedido está listo","cloze_distractors_en":["Your drink is hungry","Your table is walking","Your sugar is sleeping","Your napkin is working"],"examples":[{"es":"Su pedido está listo para ser recogido.","en":"Your order is ready to be picked up."},{"es":"Puede pasar por la barra porque su pedido está listo.","en":"You can come to the counter because your order is ready."},{"es":"Escuche el número de ticket, su pedido está listo en la mesa de entrega.","en":"Listen for your ticket number, your order is ready at the pickup table."}]},{"spanish_text":"Número de pedido","english_text":"Order number","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A unique identifier assigned to a purchase or request.","main_translations_es":["Número de orden","Código de pedido","Referencia del pedido"],"collocations":["enter your order number","check the order number","order number is required","provide the order number"],"synonyms_en":["order ID","purchase ID","reference number"],"example_sentence":"Could you tell me your order number, please?","example_es":"¿Podrías decirme tu número de pedido, por favor?","example_en":"Could you tell me your order number, please?","mnemonic_en":"Picture a delivery person handing you an order (pedido) sheet with a big number (número) badge.","cloze_distractors_en":["Coffee machine","Customer service","Kitchen appliance","Payment terminal"],"examples":[{"es":"¿Podrías decirme tu número de pedido, por favor?","en":"Could you tell me your order number, please?"},{"es":"Por favor, escribe tu número de pedido en este recibo.","en":"Please write your order number on this receipt."},{"es":"El barista llamó al cliente por su número de pedido.","en":"The barista called the customer by their order number."}]},{"spanish_text":"Recogida","english_text":"Pickup","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A vehicle with an open cargo area at the rear used for transporting goods.","main_translations_es":["Recolección","Recogimiento"],"collocations":["pick up the phone","pick up the tab","pick up where we left off","pick up speed"],"synonyms_en":["collection","gathering","fetch"],"example_sentence":"Please go to the pickup area to get your coffee.","example_es":"Por favor, pase por la zona de recogida para llevarse su café.","example_en":"Please go to the pickup area to get your coffee.","mnemonic_en":"Picture yourself picking up a big recogida bag of groceries.","cloze_distractors_en":["Storage","Entrance","Bathroom","Parking"],"examples":[{"es":"Por favor, pase por la zona de recogida para llevarse su café.","en":"Please go to the pickup area to get your coffee."},{"es":"El número de su pedido para la recogida es el cuarenta y dos.","en":"Your order number for pickup is forty-two."},{"es":"Hay una fila larga en el mostrador de recogida de bebidas.","en":"There is a long line at the drink pickup counter."}]},{"spanish_text":"Reservado","english_text":"Reserved","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Quiet and restrained; not inclined to share thoughts or feelings openly.","main_translations_es":["Guardado","Apartado","Retraído"],"collocations":["reserved seat","reserved table","reserved for","reserved parking"],"synonyms_en":["reticent","introverted","quiet"],"example_sentence":"The seat next to the window is reserved for first-class passengers.","example_es":"El asiento junto a la ventana está reservado para los pasajeros de primera clase.","example_en":"The seat next to the window is reserved for first-class passengers.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a quiet librarian locking a book in a reserved, secret ''reservado'' shelf.","cloze_distractors_en":["Reflected","Relieved","Resumed","Rejected"],"examples":[{"es":"El asiento junto a la ventana está reservado para los pasajeros de primera clase.","en":"The seat next to the window is reserved for first-class passengers."},{"es":"Esta mesa pequeña en la esquina está reservado para una pareja que llegará pronto.","en":"This small table in the corner is reserved for a couple arriving soon."},{"es":"El mostrador de pedidos está reservado para los clientes que tienen una reserva previa.","en":"The ordering counter is reserved for customers who have a prior booking."}]},{"spanish_text":"Libre","english_text":"Free","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Not costing any money; available without payment.","main_translations_es":["Desocupado","Sin costo","Disponible"],"collocations":["free of charge","free time","free will","free speech"],"synonyms_en":["unrestricted","costless","liberated"],"example_sentence":"This table is free, may I sit here?","example_es":"Esta mesa está libre, ¿puedo sentarme aquí?","example_en":"This table is free, may I sit here?","mnemonic_en":"Free feels like libre—see a bird escaping a cage, shouting Libre!","cloze_distractors_en":["Cheap","Broad","Clear"],"examples":[{"es":"Esta mesa está libre, ¿puedo sentarme aquí?","en":"This table is free, may I sit here?"},{"es":"El baño está libre ahora mismo.","en":"The restroom is free right now."},{"es":"La silla junto a la ventana está libre.","en":"The chair by the window is free."}]},{"spanish_text":"Ocupado","english_text":"Occupied","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Being used or taken by someone; not free.","main_translations_es":["Atareado","Comprometido","En uso"],"collocations":["occupied with","occupied seat","occupied building","occupied territory"],"synonyms_en":["busy","engaged","taken"],"example_sentence":"Do not sit at that table because it is occupied.","example_es":"No te sientes en esa mesa porque está ocupado.","example_en":"Do not sit at that table because it is occupied.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a busy office where every desk is occupied, just like the Spanish word ocupado.","cloze_distractors_en":["Delicious","Expensive","Polite"],"examples":[{"es":"No te sientes en esa mesa porque está ocupado.","en":"Do not sit at that table because it is occupied."},{"es":"El baño está ocupado en este momento.","en":"The restroom is occupied at the moment."},{"es":"Disculpe, ¿este asiento está ocupado?","en":"Excuse me, is this seat occupied?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Sentarse","english_text":"Sit down","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"verb (imperative)","definition_en":"to take a seat.","main_translations_es":["Sentarse","Tomar asiento","Colocarse"],"collocations":["Sit down and relax","Sit down for a meeting","Sit down on the floor"],"synonyms_en":["take a seat","settle","perch"],"example_sentence":"Please sit down at the table by the window.","example_es":"Por favor, siéntese en la mesa junto a la ventana.","example_en":"Please sit down at the table by the window.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine sending a seat to someone, then you sit down.","cloze_distractors_en":["Stand up","Walk away","Look back"],"examples":[{"es":"Por favor, siéntese en la mesa junto a la ventana.","en":"Please sit down at the table by the window."},{"es":"Puede siéntese aquí mientras preparo su café.","en":"You can sit down here while I prepare your coffee."},{"es":"Siéntese en la barra si prefiere ver cómo hago el espresso.","en":"Sit down at the counter if you prefer to watch me make the espresso."}]},{"spanish_text":"Esperar","english_text":"Wait","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to remain in place or stay inactive until something happens","main_translations_es":["Aguardar","Esperar","Tardar"],"collocations":["wait a minute","wait for","wait and see","wait in line"],"synonyms_en":["hold on","stay","pause"],"example_sentence":"Please wait here until I return.","example_es":"Por favor, espera aquí hasta que regrese.","example_en":"Please wait here until I return.","mnemonic_en":"Picture yourself waiting as an esper mind‑reader checks the timer.","cloze_distractors_en":["Walk","Cook","Sell","Pay"],"examples":[{"es":"Por favor, espera aquí hasta que regrese.","en":"Please wait here until I return."},{"es":"Debes esperar en la fila para pedir tu café.","en":"You must wait in line to order your coffee."},{"es":"Si la mesa está ocupada, tendrás que esperar un momento.","en":"If the table is occupied, you will have to wait a moment."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cola","english_text":"Line","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A row of people or objects arranged one after another.","main_translations_es":["Fila","Rabo"],"collocations":["line up","in line with","cross the line","line of sight"],"synonyms_en":["queue","row","string"],"example_sentence":"Stand at the end of the line to order your coffee.","example_es":"Ponte al final de la cola para pedir tu café.","example_en":"Stand at the end of the line to order your coffee.","mnemonic_en":"A line looks like a long cola (tail) stretching forward.","cloze_distractors_en":["Shelf","Floor","Lunch","Plate"],"examples":[{"es":"Ponte al final de la cola para pedir tu café.","en":"Stand at the end of the line to order your coffee."},{"es":"Por favor, espere su turno al final de la cola.","en":"Please wait for your turn at the end of the line."},{"es":"La cola para pedir café es muy lenta hoy.","en":"The line to order coffee is very slow today."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cliente","english_text":"Customer","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person or organization that purchases goods or services from a business.","main_translations_es":["Cliente","Comprador","Consumidor"],"collocations":["customer service","customer base","customer satisfaction","loyal customer"],"synonyms_en":["client","buyer","patron"],"example_sentence":"The customer requested a detailed invoice.","example_es":"El cliente pidió una factura detallada.","example_en":"The customer requested a detailed invoice.","mnemonic_en":"The customer sounds like client and hands a receipt to the cliente.","cloze_distractors_en":["Furniture","Beverage","Equipment","Ingredient"],"examples":[{"es":"El cliente pidió una factura detallada.","en":"The customer requested a detailed invoice."},{"es":"El cliente espera en la fila para pedir su café.","en":"The customer is waiting in line to order their coffee."},{"es":"El cliente dejó una propina sobre la mesa.","en":"The customer left a tip on the table."}]},{"spanish_text":"Camarero","english_text":"Server","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person who serves food and drinks to customers in a restaurant or café.","main_translations_es":["Mesero","Mozo"],"collocations":["web server","file server","server farm","server room"],"synonyms_en":["waiter","waitstaff","attendant"],"example_sentence":"The server brought the check quickly.","example_es":"El camarero trajo la cuenta rápidamente.","example_en":"The server brought the check quickly.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a server handing a tray to a smiling camaro driver, the camarero.","cloze_distractors_en":["Kitchen","Receipt","Napkin"],"examples":[{"es":"El camarero trajo la cuenta rápidamente.","en":"The server brought the check quickly."},{"es":"Le pedí un café extra al camarero.","en":"I asked the server for an extra coffee."},{"es":"El camarero nos recomendó el pastel del día.","en":"The server recommended the cake of the day to us."}]},{"spanish_text":"Barista","english_text":"Barista","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person who prepares and serves coffee and other drinks, typically in a coffee shop.","main_translations_es":["camarero de café","preparador de café"],"collocations":["friendly barista","expert barista","barista training"],"synonyms_en":[],"example_sentence":"The barista made a perfect cappuccino.","example_es":"El barista preparó un cappuccino perfecto.","example_en":"The barista made a perfect cappuccino.","mnemonic_en":null,"cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El barista preparó un cappuccino perfecto.","en":"The barista made a perfect cappuccino."}]},{"spanish_text":"Caja registradora","english_text":"Cash register","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A machine used in stores to record sales transactions and hold cash.","main_translations_es":["Caja registradora","Registradora","Caja de cobro"],"collocations":["open the cash register","cash register drawer","cash register receipt","cash register tape"],"synonyms_en":["till","register","point-of-sale terminal"],"example_sentence":"The cash register ran out of paper.","example_es":"La caja registradora se quedó sin papel.","example_en":"The cash register ran out of paper.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a cash register as a giant caja that registers every cash coin.","cloze_distractors_en":["Coffee grinder","Kitchen pantry","Customer service","Display cabinet"],"examples":[{"es":"La caja registradora se quedó sin papel.","en":"The cash register ran out of paper."},{"es":"El cliente pagó en efectivo en la caja registradora.","en":"The customer paid with cash at the cash register."},{"es":"Por favor, abre la caja registradora para darme el cambio.","en":"Please open the cash register to give me my change."}]},{"spanish_text":"Pago","english_text":"Payment","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A sum of money given in exchange for goods, services, or to settle a debt.","main_translations_es":["Abono","Desembolso","Cancelación"],"collocations":["make a payment","payment method","payment terms","payment deadline"],"synonyms_en":["remittance","settlement","fee"],"example_sentence":"The payment for the coffee is made at the register.","example_es":"El pago por el café se hace en la caja.","example_en":"The payment for the coffee is made at the register.","mnemonic_en":"Think of a PAYing MENTor handing a coin for each PAGO you settle.","cloze_distractors_en":["Schedule","Patience","Distance","Presence"],"examples":[{"es":"El pago por el café se hace en la caja.","en":"The payment for the coffee is made at the register."},{"es":"Por favor, ¿cómo desea realizar el pago?","en":"Please, how would you like to make the payment?"},{"es":"El sistema no acepta este método de pago.","en":"The system does not accept this method of payment."}]},{"spanish_text":"Tarjeta","english_text":"Card","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A small piece of paper or plastic used for identification, payment, or playing games.","main_translations_es":["cédula","credencial","carné"],"collocations":["credit card","gift card","business card","card game"],"synonyms_en":["ticket","badge","credential"],"example_sentence":"I need my credit card to pay the bill.","example_es":"Necesito mi tarjeta de crédito para pagar la cuenta.","example_en":"I need my credit card to pay the bill.","mnemonic_en":"I picture a card shaped like a tiny tarjeta with a car driving on it.","cloze_distractors_en":["Menu","Desk","Book","Seed"],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito mi tarjeta de crédito para pagar la cuenta.","en":"I need my credit card to pay the bill."},{"es":"El cajero me pidió la tarjeta para procesar el pago del café.","en":"The cashier asked for my card to process the coffee payment."},{"es":"Lo siento, aquí no aceptamos efectivo, solo tarjeta.","en":"I am sorry, we do not accept cash here, only card."}]},{"spanish_text":"Efectivo","english_text":"Cash","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Money in the form of coins and banknotes that is readily available for transactions.","main_translations_es":["Dinero en efectivo","Dinero","Plata"],"collocations":["cash flow","cash register","cash on hand","cash payment"],"synonyms_en":["money","currency","hard cash"],"example_sentence":"I prefer to pay in cash.","example_es":"Prefiero pagar en efectivo.","example_en":"I prefer to pay in cash.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a cash register shouting Efectivo as it prints money.","cloze_distractors_en":["Receipt","Counter","Kitchen","Service"],"examples":[{"es":"Prefiero pagar en efectivo.","en":"I prefer to pay in cash."},{"es":"Lo siento, solo aceptamos efectivo en este café.","en":"I am sorry, we only accept cash at this cafe."},{"es":"¿Tiene cambio si pago con efectivo?","en":"Do you have change if I pay with cash?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Cambio","english_text":"Change","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the act or result of making something different, a transformation or alteration.","main_translations_es":["alteración","modificación","variación"],"collocations":["make a change","change of pace","change your mind","change the subject"],"synonyms_en":["alteration","modification","shift"],"example_sentence":"Here is your coffee, and here is your change.","example_es":"Aquí tiene su café, y aquí tiene su cambio.","example_en":"Here is your coffee, and here is your change.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a cashier handing you a fresh stack of bills, a cambio, to remember Change.","cloze_distractors_en":["Starch","Pledge","Branch"],"examples":[{"es":"Aquí tiene su café, y aquí tiene su cambio.","en":"Here is your coffee, and here is your change."},{"es":"Disculpe, creo que me ha dado poco cambio.","en":"Excuse me, I think you gave me the wrong change."},{"es":"No necesito el cambio, quédeselo de propina.","en":"I do not need the change, keep it as a tip."}]},{"spanish_text":"Propina","english_text":"Tip","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A small amount of money given to someone as a gratuity for their service.","main_translations_es":["propina","corte","gratificación"],"collocations":["leave a tip","tip the waiter","tip jar","tip amount"],"synonyms_en":["gratuity","bonus","extra"],"example_sentence":"I left a good tip for the waiter.","example_es":"Dejé una buena propina al camarero.","example_en":"I left a good tip for the waiter.","mnemonic_en":"Tip the waiter with a tiny propina, like sprinkling a pinch of salt.","cloze_distractors_en":["Debt","Loan","Sale"],"examples":[{"es":"Dejé una buena propina al camarero.","en":"I left a good tip for the waiter."},{"es":"No olvides incluir la propina en el total de la cuenta.","en":"Do not forget to include the tip in the total of the bill."},{"es":"El servicio fue excelente, así que añadí un 20% de propina.","en":"The service was excellent, so I added a 20% tip."}]},{"spanish_text":"Recibo","english_text":"Receipt","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A written acknowledgment that something, typically a payment, has been received.","main_translations_es":["Comprobante","Factura","Ticket"],"collocations":["receipt of payment","receipt number","receipt for"],"synonyms_en":["sales slip","proof of purchase","transaction record"],"example_sentence":"Here is your receipt for the order you just placed.","example_es":"Aquí tiene su recibo por el pedido que acaba de realizar.","example_en":"Here is your receipt for the order you just placed.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a receipt with the bold word Recibo printed on it.","cloze_distractors_en":["Recipe","Registry","Receptacle","Recipient"],"examples":[{"es":"Aquí tiene su recibo por el pedido que acaba de realizar.","en":"Here is your receipt for the order you just placed."},{"es":"Necesito el recibo para comprobar el precio de los pasteles.","en":"I need the receipt to check the price of the pastries."},{"es":"El cajero imprimió el recibo después de pagar el desayuno.","en":"The cashier printed the receipt after I paid for breakfast."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cuenta separada","english_text":"Separate bill","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A bill that is issued separately from other charges.","main_translations_es":["Factura separada","Cuenta individual","Dividir la cuenta"],"collocations":["ask for a separate bill","receive a separate bill","separate bill for each person"],"synonyms_en":["individual check","split check","separate check"],"example_sentence":"We are from different companies, so we want the separate bill.","example_es":"Somos de empresas distintas, así que queremos la cuenta separada.","example_en":"We are from different companies, so we want the separate bill.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a separate bill, a split cuenta left on the table.","cloze_distractors_en":["Daily special","Loyalty card","Takeaway menu","Table number"],"examples":[{"es":"Somos de empresas distintas, así que queremos la cuenta separada.","en":"We are from different companies, so we want the separate bill."},{"es":"Solo pedí un café, así que necesito una cuenta separada.","en":"I only ordered a coffee, so I need a separate bill."},{"es":"Mi amigo y yo nos sentamos en mesas diferentes, así que pedimos la cuenta separada.","en":"My friend and I sat at different tables, so we asked for the separate bill."}]},{"spanish_text":"¿Puedo pagar ahora?","english_text":"Can I pay now?","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"question","definition_en":"Asking if it is possible to make a payment now.","main_translations_es":["¿Puedo pagar ya?","¿Me dejo pagar ahora?","¿Es posible pagar ahora?"],"collocations":["Can I pay now or later?","Can I pay now with a credit card?","Can I pay now and get a receipt?"],"synonyms_en":["May I pay now?","Is it possible to pay now?","Can I settle the bill now?"],"example_sentence":"I am in a hurry to leave, can I pay now?","example_es":"Tengo prisa por irme, ¿puedo pagar ahora?","example_en":"I am in a hurry to leave, can I pay now?","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a tin can paying a bill right now, shouting ''Can I pay now?'' like a Spanish shopper.","cloze_distractors_en":["Do you sell shoes?","Where is the airport?","Are you hungry today?","How old is your dog?"],"examples":[{"es":"Tengo prisa por irme, ¿puedo pagar ahora?","en":"I am in a hurry to leave, can I pay now?"},{"es":"Ya terminé mi café, ¿puedo pagar ahora?","en":"I finished my coffee, can I pay now?"},{"es":"Tengo prisa por irme a trabajar, ¿puedo pagar ahora?","en":"I am in a rush to get to work, can I pay now?"}]},{"spanish_text":"¿Aceptan tarjeta?","english_text":"Do you take cards?","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"question","definition_en":"A polite way to ask if a business accepts credit or debit cards.","main_translations_es":["¿Aceptan tarjetas?","¿Se puede pagar con tarjeta?","¿Pagan con tarjeta?"],"collocations":["Do you take cards?","We take cards.","Do you accept credit cards?","We accept all major cards."],"synonyms_en":["Accept cards","Take credit cards","Card payment accepted"],"example_sentence":"I do not have cash, do you take cards?","example_es":"No tengo efectivo, ¿aceptan tarjeta?","example_en":"I do not have cash, do you take cards?","mnemonic_en":"Visualize a shopkeeper holding a deck, asking Accept an card? Do you take cards?","cloze_distractors_en":["Are you a card?","Do you have bill?","Is it a coffee?"],"examples":[{"es":"No tengo efectivo, ¿aceptan tarjeta?","en":"I do not have cash, do you take cards?"},{"es":"Quiero pagar mi café, ¿aceptan tarjeta?","en":"I want to pay for my coffee, do you take cards?"},{"es":"La cuenta es de diez dólares, ¿aceptan tarjeta?","en":"The bill is ten dollars, do you take cards?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Falta algo","english_text":"Something is missing","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that an item or element is absent.","main_translations_es":["Algo falta","Se echa de menos algo","Hay algo que falta"],"collocations":["something is missing from","something is missing here","something is missing altogether","something is missing in the report"],"synonyms_en":["There''s a gap","A piece is absent","It''s incomplete"],"example_sentence":"Something is missing from my order; I only received the coffee but not the sugar.","example_es":"Falta algo en mi pedido; solo recibí el café pero no el azúcar.","example_en":"Something is missing from my order; I only received the coffee but not the sugar.","mnemonic_en":"A faulty gap appears where the word ''falta'' signals something is missing","cloze_distractors_en":["Everything is perfect","Nothing is included","Everything is finished","Something is extra"],"examples":[{"es":"Falta algo en mi pedido; solo recibí el café pero no el azúcar.","en":"Something is missing from my order; I only received the coffee but not the sugar."},{"es":"Falta algo en la bandeja; pedí dos croissants y solo hay uno.","en":"Something is missing from the tray; I ordered two croissants and there is only one."},{"es":"Falta algo en esta cuenta; el precio del té no aparece aquí.","en":"Something is missing from this bill; the price of the tea does not appear here."}]},{"spanish_text":"Sin cebolla","english_text":"No onion","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that there is no onion.","main_translations_es":["Sin cebolla","Sin cebollas","Sin cebolla añadida"],"collocations":["no onion pizza","no onion, please","no onion in the salad"],"synonyms_en":["without onion","onion-free"],"example_sentence":"Please prepare my sandwich No onion.","example_es":"Por favor, prepare mi sándwich sin cebolla.","example_en":"Please prepare my sandwich No onion.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a No Onion sign with a sin wave spilling over a bowl (cebula).","cloze_distractors_en":["No hungry","No flavor","No kitchen","No napkin"],"examples":[{"es":"Por favor, prepare mi sándwich sin cebolla.","en":"Please prepare my sandwich No onion."},{"es":"Por favor, prepare mi hamburguesa sin cebolla.","en":"Please prepare my burger No onion."},{"es":"Por favor, ponme un perrito caliente sin cebolla.","en":"Please give me a hot dog No onion."}]},{"spanish_text":"Sin leche","english_text":"No milk","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"A statement indicating that there is no milk.","main_translations_es":["Sin leche","No hay leche","Sin leche disponible"],"collocations":["No milk, please","I want coffee, no milk","No milk in my tea"],"synonyms_en":["dairy‑free","milkless","without milk"],"example_sentence":"I would like a black coffee, no milk, please.","example_es":"Quiero un café solo, sin leche, por favor.","example_en":"I would like a black coffee, no milk, please.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a cow holding a sign that reads No milk, because it’s sin (without) any dairy.","cloze_distractors_en":["Very heavy","Extra salty","Quite hungry","More polite"],"examples":[{"es":"Quiero un café solo, sin leche, por favor.","en":"I would like a black coffee, no milk, please."},{"es":"Prefiero mi té solo, sin leche, para poder sentir mejor el sabor.","en":"I prefer my tea plain, no milk, so I can taste the flavor better."},{"es":"Para el cliente de la mesa tres, un americano sin leche.","en":"For the customer at table three, an americano no milk."}]},{"spanish_text":"Más agua","english_text":"More water","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"An increased amount of water.","main_translations_es":["Más agua","Más líquido","Más agua, por favor"],"collocations":["drink more water","add more water","need more water","more water, please"],"synonyms_en":["additional water","extra water","increased water"],"example_sentence":"I would like more water, please.","example_es":"Quiero más agua, por favor.","example_en":"I would like more water, please.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a thirsty dog shouting más agua for more water.","cloze_distractors_en":["Heavy rocks","Bright lights","Broken chairs","Empty wallets"],"examples":[{"es":"Quiero más agua, por favor.","en":"I would like more water, please."},{"es":"El vaso está vacío, necesito más agua.","en":"The glass is empty, I need more water."},{"es":"Después de este café, ¿podría traerme más agua?","en":"After this coffee, could you bring me more water?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Otra servilleta","english_text":"Another napkin","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"A second napkin, used as a replacement or additional one.","main_translations_es":["Otra servilleta","Una servilleta más","Otra toalla de mesa"],"collocations":["hand me another napkin","need another napkin","grab another napkin","spill the sauce, get another napkin"],"synonyms_en":["a spare napkin","extra napkin","additional napkin"],"example_sentence":"My pastry is really crumbly, could you hand me another napkin?","example_es":"Mi pastel se desmorona mucho, ¿podrías pasarme otra servilleta?","example_en":"My pastry is really crumbly, could you hand me another napkin?","mnemonic_en":"Picture a second napkin, because ''another napkin'' sounds like ''otra napkin'' in Spanish.","cloze_distractors_en":["Another receipt","Another order","Another bill","Another sign"],"examples":[{"es":"Mi pastel se desmorona mucho, ¿podrías pasarme otra servilleta?","en":"My pastry is really crumbly, could you hand me another napkin?"},{"es":"Se me cayó un poco de café, ¿me traes otra servilleta?","en":"I spilled some coffee, can you bring me another napkin?"},{"es":"Usé esta para limpiarme la boca y está llena de salsa, ¿puedo tener otra servilleta?","en":"I used this one to wipe my mouth and it''s covered in sauce, can I have another napkin?"}]},{"spanish_text":"La mesa está sucia","english_text":"The table is dirty","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that the table is not clean.","main_translations_es":["La mesa está mugrienta","La mesa está sucia","La mesa está ensuciada"],"collocations":["dirty table","clean the table","wipe the table","clear the table"],"synonyms_en":["The table is filthy","The table is soiled","The table is grimy"],"example_sentence":"Please clean this spot because the table is dirty.","example_es":"Por favor, limpia este lugar porque la mesa está sucia.","example_en":"Please clean this spot because the table is dirty.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a table covered in mud, just like a sucia mesa.","cloze_distractors_en":["The coffee is ready","The sugar is sweet","The menu is large","The water is cold"],"examples":[{"es":"Por favor, limpia este lugar porque la mesa está sucia.","en":"Please clean this spot because the table is dirty."},{"es":"No puedo sentarme aquí, la mesa está sucia.","en":"I cannot sit here, the table is dirty."},{"es":"El camarero no ha limpiado nada y la mesa está sucia.","en":"The waiter has not cleaned anything and the table is dirty."}]},{"spanish_text":"Está delicioso","english_text":"It is delicious","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that something tastes very good.","main_translations_es":["Qué rico","Está sabroso","Se ve delicioso"],"collocations":["This dish is delicious","That was delicious","It tastes delicious","The food is delicious"],"synonyms_en":["It''s tasty","It''s scrumptious","It''s flavorful"],"example_sentence":"Try this freshly baked croissant, It is delicious.","example_es":"Prueba este croissant recién horneado, está delicioso.","example_en":"Try this freshly baked croissant, It is delicious.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a chef tasting soup and saying It is delish-ous while pointing at the menu that reads ESTA.","cloze_distractors_en":["It is furniture","It is arithmetic","It is geography"],"examples":[{"es":"Prueba este croissant recién horneado, está delicioso.","en":"Try this freshly baked croissant, It is delicious."},{"es":"Prueba este café, está delicioso.","en":"Try this coffee, It is delicious."},{"es":"La tarta de manzana que pedimos está delicioso.","en":"The apple pie we ordered It is delicious."}]},{"spanish_text":"Está muy caliente","english_text":"It is very hot","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that the temperature is high.","main_translations_es":["Hace mucho calor","Está muy caluroso","Hace un calor tremendo"],"collocations":["It''s very hot today","It''s very hot outside","It''s very hot in here","It''s very hot during summer"],"synonyms_en":["It''s scorching","It''s sweltering","It''s boiling"],"example_sentence":"Be careful with the soup, It is very hot and you might burn your tongue.","example_es":"Ten cuidado con la sopa, está muy caliente y te puedes quemar la lengua.","example_en":"Be careful with the soup, It is very hot and you might burn your tongue.","mnemonic_en":"Picture the sun shouting Caliente as the air becomes very hot.","cloze_distractors_en":["It is very cold","It is quite empty","It is fully paid"],"examples":[{"es":"Ten cuidado con la sopa, está muy caliente y te puedes quemar la lengua.","en":"Be careful with the soup, It is very hot and you might burn your tongue."},{"es":"Cuidado con la taza, está muy caliente y podrías quemarte los dedos.","en":"Watch out for the mug, It is very hot and you might burn your fingers."},{"es":"No bebas el chocolate ahora mismo porque está muy caliente.","en":"Do not drink the hot chocolate right now because It is very hot."}]},{"spanish_text":"Buen provecho","english_text":"Enjoy your meal","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A polite phrase said to someone before they start eating, wishing them a pleasant meal.","main_translations_es":["Que aproveche","¡A comer!","Disfruta tu comida"],"collocations":["Enjoy your meal!","Enjoy your meal, everyone","Enjoy your meal and dessert"],"synonyms_en":["Have a nice meal","Eat well","Enjoy your food"],"example_sentence":"Here is your coffee and sandwich, enjoy your meal!","example_es":"Aquí tiene su café y su sándwich, ¡buen provecho!","example_en":"Here is your coffee and sandwich, enjoy your meal!","mnemonic_en":"When you prove a chew, you say enjoy your meal.","cloze_distractors_en":["Clean the floor","Close the shop","Check the bill","Clear the table"],"examples":[{"es":"Aquí tiene su café y su sándwich, ¡buen provecho!","en":"Here is your coffee and sandwich, enjoy your meal!"},{"es":"El camarero nos dejó los platos en la mesa y dijo: ¡buen provecho!","en":"The waiter set our plates on the table and said, enjoy your meal!"},{"es":"Le entregué la bandeja al cliente y le dije: buen provecho.","en":"I handed the tray to the customer and said, enjoy your meal."}]}]'::jsonb) as x(
  spanish_text text, english_text text, section_name text, part_of_speech text, definition_en text,
  main_translations_es jsonb, collocations jsonb, synonyms_en jsonb, example_sentence text, example_es text, example_en text, mnemonic_en text, cloze_distractors_en jsonb, examples jsonb
)
where c.deck_id = dk.id
  and lower(c.spanish_text) = lower(x.spanish_text)
  and lower(c.english_text) = lower(x.english_text);

-- english-c1-vocabulary (100 cards)
update public.decks set
  title = 'English C1 Vocabulary', description = 'Advanced English words and expressions for upper-level learners.',
  language_from = 'es', language_to = 'en'
where slug = 'english-c1-vocabulary';

update public.cards c set
  section_name = x.section_name, part_of_speech = x.part_of_speech, definition_en = x.definition_en,
  main_translations_es = coalesce(x.main_translations_es, '[]'::jsonb),
  collocations = coalesce(x.collocations, '[]'::jsonb),
  synonyms_en = coalesce(x.synonyms_en, '[]'::jsonb),
  example_sentence = x.example_sentence, example_es = x.example_es, example_en = x.example_en,
  mnemonic_en = coalesce(x.mnemonic_en, c.mnemonic_en),
  cloze_distractors_en = case when jsonb_array_length(coalesce(x.cloze_distractors_en, '[]'::jsonb)) > 0
                              then x.cloze_distractors_en else c.cloze_distractors_en end,
  examples = case when jsonb_array_length(coalesce(x.examples, '[]'::jsonb)) > 0
                  then x.examples else c.examples end
from (select id from public.decks where slug = 'english-c1-vocabulary') dk
cross join jsonb_to_recordset('[{"spanish_text":"Aclarar","english_text":"Clarify","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to make something clear or easier to understand","main_translations_es":["Explicar","Precisar","Elucidar"],"collocations":["clarify the situation","clarify your doubts","clarify the meaning","clarify the issue"],"synonyms_en":["explain","elucidate","make clear"],"example_sentence":"Could you clarify the steps we need to follow to complete the project?","example_es":"¿Podrías aclarar los pasos que debemos seguir para completar el proyecto?","example_en":"Could you clarify the steps we need to follow to complete the project?","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a clear window, ''a clear'' view, to clarify the meaning.","cloze_distractors_en":["Postpone","Conceal","Complicate","Fabricate"],"examples":[{"es":"¿Podrías aclarar los pasos que debemos seguir para completar el proyecto?","en":"Could you clarify the steps we need to follow to complete the project?"},{"es":"El abogado tuvo que aclarar una cláusula del contrato que resultaba confusa para ambas partes.","en":"The lawyer had to clarify a clause in the contract that was confusing for both parties."},{"es":"El gerente organizó una reunión para aclarar los nuevos protocolos de seguridad con todo el equipo.","en":"The manager organized a meeting to clarify the new safety protocols with the whole team."}]},{"spanish_text":"Recalcar","english_text":"Emphasize","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To give special importance or attention to something.","main_translations_es":["Destacar","Subrayar","Enfatizar"],"collocations":["emphasize the importance","emphasize the need","emphasize that","emphasize the point"],"synonyms_en":["highlight","stress","underscore"],"example_sentence":"The teacher wanted to emphasize the importance of punctuality.","example_es":"El profesor quiso recalcar la importancia de la puntualidad.","example_en":"The teacher wanted to emphasize the importance of punctuality.","mnemonic_en":"A RECALL CAR EMphasizes the road sign, so you never miss the point.","cloze_distractors_en":["Fabricate","Oscillate","Ameliorate","Infiltrate"],"examples":[{"es":"El profesor quiso recalcar la importancia de la puntualidad.","en":"The teacher wanted to emphasize the importance of punctuality."},{"es":"El informe médico debe recalcar que el paciente necesita reposo absoluto.","en":"The medical report must emphasize that the patient requires absolute rest."},{"es":"La candidata aprovechó su discurso para recalcar los fallos del gobierno actual.","en":"The candidate used her speech to emphasize the failures of the current government."}]},{"spanish_text":"Sostener","english_text":"Maintain","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To keep something in its existing state or condition.","main_translations_es":["Mantener","Conservar","Sustentar"],"collocations":["maintain a balance","maintain control","maintain the status quo","maintain relationships"],"synonyms_en":["preserve","keep up","sustain"],"example_sentence":"The building requires constant repairs to maintain its original structure.","example_es":"El edificio requiere reparaciones constantes para sostener su estructura original.","example_en":"The building requires constant repairs to maintain its original structure.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a sturdy stand (sostener) that you maintain, never letting the banner fall.","cloze_distractors_en":["Submerge","Exacerbate","Obliterate","Fabricate"],"examples":[{"es":"El edificio requiere reparaciones constantes para sostener su estructura original.","en":"The building requires constant repairs to maintain its original structure."},{"es":"Es difícil sostener una conversación fluida cuando hay tanto ruido en la habitación.","en":"It is difficult to maintain a fluid conversation when there is so much noise in the room."},{"es":"La empresa debe reducir sus gastos operativos para sostener su competitividad en el mercado.","en":"The company must reduce its operating expenses to maintain its competitiveness in the market."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cuestionar","english_text":"Challenge","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To invite someone to compete or to question the validity of something.","main_translations_es":["Desafiar","Poner en duda","Interrogar"],"collocations":["rise to the challenge","meet the challenge","challenge yourself","face a challenge"],"synonyms_en":["contest","oppose","question"],"example_sentence":"It''s important to challenge the sources before believing them.","example_es":"Es importante cuestionar las fuentes antes de creer en ellas.","example_en":"It''s important to challenge the sources before believing them.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a chalice smashing a question mark—challenge means to cuestionar.","cloze_distractors_en":["Fabricate","Illuminate","Decorate","Navigate"],"examples":[{"es":"Es importante cuestionar las fuentes antes de creer en ellas.","en":"It''s important to challenge the sources before believing them."},{"es":"El abogado decidió cuestionar la validez de las pruebas presentadas por la fiscalía.","en":"The lawyer decided to challenge the validity of the evidence presented by the prosecution."},{"es":"No deberías tener miedo de cuestionar las decisiones de tu jefe si crees que hay una mejor manera de hacerlo.","en":"You shouldn''t be afraid to challenge your boss''s decisions if you think there is a better way to do it."}]},{"spanish_text":"Respaldar","english_text":"Substantiate","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To provide evidence or proof that something is true or valid.","main_translations_es":["Apoyar","Confirmar","Sustentar"],"collocations":["substantiate a claim","substantiate the evidence","substantiate the allegations","substantiate findings"],"synonyms_en":["prove","validate","confirm"],"example_sentence":"The researcher must substantiate his conclusions with solid data.","example_es":"El investigador debe respaldar sus conclusiones con datos sólidos.","example_en":"The researcher must substantiate his conclusions with solid data.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a submarine planting a sturdy stance on a ship''s back to support it","cloze_distractors_en":["Subjugate","Sublimate","Subsidize","Subvert"],"examples":[{"es":"El investigador debe respaldar sus conclusiones con datos sólidos.","en":"The researcher must substantiate his conclusions with solid data."},{"es":"No puedes acusar a alguien de robo sin pruebas que puedan respaldar tu historia.","en":"You cannot accuse someone of theft without evidence that can substantiate your story."},{"es":"La empresa necesita documentos financieros adicionales para respaldar su solicitud de préstamo bancario.","en":"The company needs additional financial documents to substantiate its bank loan application."}]},{"spanish_text":"Desestimar","english_text":"Dismiss","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To reject, disregard, or send away someone or something.","main_translations_es":["Rechazar","Descartar","Desestimar"],"collocations":["dismiss a case","dismiss the allegations","dismiss the idea","dismiss someone from their job"],"synonyms_en":["reject","send away","turn down"],"example_sentence":"The judge decided to dismiss the case due to lack of evidence.","example_es":"El juez decidió desestimar el caso por falta de pruebas.","example_en":"The judge decided to dismiss the case due to lack of evidence.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a missed call being ignored, a dis-miss that dismisses the message.","cloze_distractors_en":["Applaud","Navigate","Cultivate","Illuminate"],"examples":[{"es":"El juez decidió desestimar el caso por falta de pruebas.","en":"The judge decided to dismiss the case due to lack of evidence."},{"es":"La junta directiva optó por desestimar la propuesta de fusión tras analizar los riesgos financieros.","en":"The board of directors chose to dismiss the merger proposal after analyzing the financial risks."},{"es":"No deberías desestimar sus preocupaciones, ya que tienen mucha experiencia en este sector.","en":"You should not dismiss their concerns, as they have a great deal of experience in this sector."}]},{"spanish_text":"Impulsar","english_text":"Foster","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To encourage or promote the development or growth of something.","main_translations_es":["Promover","Estimular","Fomentar"],"collocations":["foster growth","foster relationships","foster development","foster innovation"],"synonyms_en":["encourage","promote","nurture"],"example_sentence":"The government wants to foster technological innovation in the country.","example_es":"El gobierno quiere impulsar la innovación tecnológica en el país.","example_en":"The government wants to foster technological innovation in the country.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a foster parent giving a child a strong push, a force that impulsar forward.","cloze_distractors_en":["Hinder","Stifle","Thwart","Impede"],"examples":[{"es":"El gobierno quiere impulsar la innovación tecnológica en el país.","en":"The government wants to foster technological innovation in the country."},{"es":"Los profesores intentan impulsar un ambiente de colaboración entre los estudiantes de la clase.","en":"The teachers try to foster an environment of collaboration among the students in the class."},{"es":"La empresa implementó nuevas políticas para impulsar el crecimiento profesional de sus empleados.","en":"The company implemented new policies to foster the professional growth of its employees."}]},{"spanish_text":"Conllevar","english_text":"Entail","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To involve or require something as a necessary consequence.","main_translations_es":["implicar","suponer","acarrear"],"collocations":["entail consequences","entail risks","entail a cost","entail responsibility"],"synonyms_en":["involve","require","necessitate"],"example_sentence":"Renovating the old Victorian house will entail tearing down several interior walls before the new kitchen can be installed.","example_es":"Renovar la antigua casa victoriana conllevará derribar varios muros interiores antes de que se pueda instalar la nueva cocina.","example_en":"Renovating the old Victorian house will entail tearing down several interior walls before the new kitchen can be installed.","mnemonic_en":"A tangled tail (en-tail) carries the load, just like conllevar means to involve","cloze_distractors_en":["Substitute","Interrupt","Conclude","Terminate"],"examples":[{"es":"Renovar la antigua casa victoriana conllevará derribar varios muros interiores antes de que se pueda instalar la nueva cocina.","en":"Renovating the old Victorian house will entail tearing down several interior walls before the new kitchen can be installed."},{"es":"Aceptar la beca de investigación conllevaría viajar al Ártico durante seis meses para recolectar muestras de núcleos de hielo.","en":"Accepting the research grant would entail traveling to the Arctic for six months to collect ice core samples."},{"es":"El acuerdo de fusión puede conllevar el despido de hasta doscientos empleados en la planta de fabricación de la empresa más pequeña.","en":"The merger agreement may entail laying off up to two hundred employees at the smaller firm''s manufacturing plant."}]},{"spanish_text":"Mitigar","english_text":"Mitigate","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To make something less severe, harmful, or painful.","main_translations_es":["Aliviar","Reducir","Suavizar"],"collocations":["mitigate the risk","mitigate the damage","mitigate the effects","mitigate the impact"],"synonyms_en":["alleviate","lessen","reduce"],"example_sentence":"The government implemented new policies to mitigate the effects of climate change.","example_es":"El gobierno implementó nuevas políticas para mitigar los efectos del cambio climático.","example_en":"The government implemented new policies to mitigate the effects of climate change.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a tiny mite gently soothing a blaze, so the fire is mitigated.","cloze_distractors_en":["Aggravate","Instigate","Fabricate","Propagate"],"examples":[{"es":"El gobierno implementó nuevas políticas para mitigar los efectos del cambio climático.","en":"The government implemented new policies to mitigate the effects of climate change."},{"es":"Los ingenieros instalaron amortiguadores en el edificio para mitigar el impacto de los terremotos.","en":"The engineers installed shock absorbers in the building to mitigate the impact of earthquakes."},{"es":"La empresa ofreció una compensación económica para mitigar el malestar de los clientes tras el fallo del sistema.","en":"The company offered financial compensation to mitigate the customers'' frustration after the system failure."}]},{"spanish_text":"Agravar","english_text":"Exacerbate","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To make a problem, situation, or feeling worse or more intense.","main_translations_es":["Empeorar","Intensificar","Agravarse"],"collocations":["exacerbate the problem","exacerbate tensions","exacerbate symptoms","exacerbate the situation"],"synonyms_en":["worsen","intensify","aggravate"],"example_sentence":"Lack of sleep can exacerbate the symptoms of depression.","example_es":"La falta de sueño puede agravar los síntomas de la depresión.","example_en":"Lack of sleep can exacerbate the symptoms of depression.","mnemonic_en":"Picture an ex‑ace chef adding extra sour sauce, making the dish even worse.","cloze_distractors_en":["Ameliorate","Facilitate","Rejuvenate","Consolidate"],"examples":[{"es":"La falta de sueño puede agravar los síntomas de la depresión.","en":"Lack of sleep can exacerbate the symptoms of depression."},{"es":"El uso excesivo de fertilizantes químicos puede agravar la contaminación del agua en la región.","en":"The excessive use of chemical fertilizers can exacerbate water pollution in the region."},{"es":"No deberías rascarte la picadura, ya que eso solo servirá para agravar la irritación de la piel.","en":"You should not scratch the bite, as that will only serve to exacerbate the skin irritation."}]},{"spanish_text":"Plantear","english_text":"Put forward","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To propose or suggest something for consideration.","main_translations_es":["proponer","exponer","presentar"],"collocations":["put forward a proposal","put forward an argument","put forward a suggestion","put forward a theory"],"synonyms_en":["propose","suggest","present"],"example_sentence":"The committee decided to put forward a new strategy for the next year.","example_es":"El comité decidió plantear una nueva estrategia para el próximo año.","example_en":"The committee decided to put forward a new strategy for the next year.","mnemonic_en":"Plant a seed and put forward your idea, just like you would plantear a new garden.","cloze_distractors_en":["Put aside","Put across","Put under","Put behind"],"examples":[{"es":"El comité decidió plantear una nueva estrategia para el próximo año.","en":"The committee decided to put forward a new strategy for the next year."},{"es":"Durante la reunión, ella se atrevió a plantear una solución alternativa al problema técnico.","en":"During the meeting, she dared to put forward an alternative solution to the technical problem."},{"es":"Varios expertos han comenzado a plantear dudas sobre la viabilidad económica del proyecto.","en":"Several experts have begun to put forward doubts regarding the economic viability of the project."}]},{"spanish_text":"Abordar","english_text":"Address","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To direct attention to, discuss, or deal with something.","main_translations_es":["Tratar","Enfocar","Abordar"],"collocations":["address the issue","address a problem","address the audience","address the question"],"synonyms_en":["deal with","tackle","speak to"],"example_sentence":"The committee must address the climate change problem as soon as possible.","example_es":"El comité debe abordar el problema del cambio climático lo antes posible.","example_en":"The committee must address the climate change problem as soon as possible.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a fancy dress boarding a ship, so you address (abordar) the problem.","cloze_distractors_en":["Fabricate","Evaporate","Circulate","Decorate"],"examples":[{"es":"El comité debe abordar el problema del cambio climático lo antes posible.","en":"The committee must address the climate change problem as soon as possible."},{"es":"La empresa necesita abordar las quejas de los clientes sobre la calidad del servicio.","en":"The company needs to address customer complaints regarding the quality of the service."},{"es":"El profesor decidió abordar el tema de la desigualdad social durante su conferencia magistral.","en":"The professor decided to address the topic of social inequality during his keynote lecture."}]},{"spanish_text":"Determinar","english_text":"Determine","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To find out or establish something through investigation, calculation, or reasoning.","main_translations_es":["Establecer","Fijar","Precisar"],"collocations":["determine the cause","determine the outcome","determine the best approach","determine if"],"synonyms_en":["ascertain","establish","figure out"],"example_sentence":"Scientists must determine the cause of the outbreak.","example_es":"Los científicos deben determinar la causa del brote.","example_en":"Scientists must determine the cause of the outbreak.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a judge stamping a verdict, saying determine as if shouting the Spanish word determinar.","cloze_distractors_en":["Fabricate","Exaggerate","Circumvent","Contaminate"],"examples":[{"es":"Los científicos deben determinar la causa del brote.","en":"Scientists must determine the cause of the outbreak."},{"es":"El comité necesita determinar quién será el próximo director ejecutivo de la empresa.","en":"The committee needs to determine who will be the company''s next chief executive officer."},{"es":"Los resultados de las pruebas ayudarán a determinar si el paciente necesita una cirugía inmediata.","en":"The test results will help to determine whether the patient requires immediate surgery."}]},{"spanish_text":"Comprensivo","english_text":"Comprehensive","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Including all or nearly all elements or aspects; thorough and complete.","main_translations_es":["amplio","extenso","integral"],"collocations":["comprehensive review","comprehensive plan","comprehensive guide","comprehensive analysis"],"synonyms_en":["thorough","all‑inclusive","extensive"],"example_sentence":"The instruction manual provides a comprehensive guide on how to assemble and maintain the engine step by step.","example_es":"El manual de instrucciones proporciona una guía exhaustiva sobre cómo ensamblar y mantener el motor paso a paso.","example_en":"The instruction manual provides a comprehensive guide on how to assemble and maintain the engine step by step.","mnemonic_en":"A COMPREHENSIVE textbook feels like a comprensivo hug that covers every detail.","cloze_distractors_en":["Superficial","Fragmentary","Ambiguous","Negligible"],"examples":[{"es":"El manual de instrucciones proporciona una guía exhaustiva sobre cómo ensamblar y mantener el motor paso a paso.","en":"The instruction manual provides a comprehensive guide on how to assemble and maintain the engine step by step."},{"es":"El informe final ofrece un análisis exhaustivo de todos los factores que contribuyeron al colapso del puente.","en":"The final report provides a comprehensive analysis of every factor that contributed to the bridge''s collapse."},{"es":"La universidad ha implementado un plan de estudios exhaustivo que cubre todas las áreas fundamentales de la física cuántica.","en":"The university has implemented a comprehensive curriculum that covers all the fundamental areas of quantum physics."}]},{"spanish_text":"Matizado","english_text":"Nuanced","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Having subtle distinctions or variations in meaning, expression, or tone.","main_translations_es":["Sutil","Detallado","Con matices"],"collocations":["nuanced argument","nuanced perspective","nuanced approach","nuanced understanding"],"synonyms_en":["subtle","refined","complex"],"example_sentence":"His argument is nuanced and considers several points of view.","example_es":"Su argumento es matizado y considera varios puntos de vista.","example_en":"His argument is nuanced and considers several points of view.","mnemonic_en":"New ants add subtle shades to the painting, making it nuanced.","cloze_distractors_en":["Glacial","Frivolous","Inert","Opaque"],"examples":[{"es":"Su argumento es matizado y considera varios puntos de vista.","en":"His argument is nuanced and considers several points of view."},{"es":"La crítica ofreció una visión matizada sobre las causas políticas del conflicto.","en":"The critic offered a nuanced view regarding the political causes of the conflict."},{"es":"Necesitamos un enfoque más matizado para resolver este problema cultural tan complejo.","en":"We need a more nuanced approach to resolve this complex cultural problem."}]},{"spanish_text":"Ambiguo","english_text":"Ambiguous","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Open to more than one interpretation or having an unclear meaning.","main_translations_es":["Vago","Confuso","Equívoco"],"collocations":["ambiguous meaning","ambiguous statement","ambiguous result","ambiguous situation"],"synonyms_en":["unclear","vague","equivocal"],"example_sentence":"The message of the ad was ambiguous, so many interpreted it in different ways.","example_es":"El mensaje del anuncio era ambiguo, por lo que muchos lo interpretaron de distintas maneras.","example_en":"The message of the ad was ambiguous, so many interpreted it in different ways.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a vague sign that reads ambi‑guo, reminding you the meaning is ambiguous","cloze_distractors_en":["Punctual","Lucid","Rigid","Eloquent"],"examples":[{"es":"El mensaje del anuncio era ambiguo, por lo que muchos lo interpretaron de distintas maneras.","en":"The message of the ad was ambiguous, so many interpreted it in different ways."},{"es":"La respuesta del político fue tan ambigua que nadie pudo entender su postura real sobre el tema.","en":"The politician''s response was so ambiguous that no one could understand his real stance on the issue."},{"es":"Debido a que las instrucciones del contrato eran ambiguas, los abogados tuvieron que renegociar las cláusulas.","en":"Because the contract instructions were ambiguous, the lawyers had to renegotiate the clauses."}]},{"spanish_text":"Coherente","english_text":"Coherent","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Logical, consistent, and forming a unified whole.","main_translations_es":["Lógico","Consistente","Razonable"],"collocations":["coherent argument","coherent plan","coherent theory","coherent response"],"synonyms_en":["logical","consistent","clear"],"example_sentence":"His argument is coherent and easy to follow.","example_es":"Su argumento es coherente y fácil de seguir.","example_en":"His argument is coherent and easy to follow.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a coherent story where every line fits, just like the Spanish word coherente snapping neatly together.","cloze_distractors_en":["Volatile","Obsolete","Ambiguous","Erratic"],"examples":[{"es":"Su argumento es coherente y fácil de seguir.","en":"His argument is coherent and easy to follow."},{"es":"El arquitecto presentó un diseño coherente que integra perfectamente la estructura con el paisaje natural.","en":"The architect presented a coherent design that perfectly integrates the structure with the natural landscape."},{"es":"Necesitamos una política económica coherente para combatir la inflación de manera efectiva a largo plazo.","en":"We need a coherent economic policy to combat inflation effectively in the long term."}]},{"spanish_text":"Preciso","english_text":"Precise","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Exact and accurate, leaving no room for error or ambiguity.","main_translations_es":["Exacto","Concreto","Detallado"],"collocations":["precise measurement","precise timing","precise language","precise answer"],"synonyms_en":["exact","accurate","specific"],"example_sentence":"I need a precise watch to measure the race time.","example_es":"Necesito un reloj preciso para medir el tiempo de la carrera.","example_en":"I need a precise watch to measure the race time.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a precise surgeon shouting preciso while making exact, razor‑thin cuts.","cloze_distractors_en":["Vague","Erratic","Amorphous","Frivolous"],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito un reloj preciso para medir el tiempo de la carrera.","en":"I need a precise watch to measure the race time."},{"es":"El arquitecto realizó un cálculo preciso de los materiales necesarios para la estructura.","en":"The architect made a precise calculation of the materials needed for the structure."},{"es":"La cirujana hizo un corte preciso durante la operación para evitar dañar los nervios cercanos.","en":"The surgeon made a precise incision during the operation to avoid damaging nearby nerves."}]},{"spanish_text":"Convincente","english_text":"Compelling","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Evoking interest, attention, or admiration in a powerful and persuasive way.","main_translations_es":["Persuasivo","Irresistible","Cautivador"],"collocations":["compelling argument","compelling evidence","compelling story","compelling reason"],"synonyms_en":["persuasive","forceful","irresistible"],"example_sentence":"The lawyer''s argument was so compelling that the jury had no doubts.","example_es":"El argumento del abogado fue tan convincente que el jurado no tuvo dudas.","example_en":"The lawyer''s argument was so compelling that the jury had no doubts.","mnemonic_en":"A compelling speaker convinces the crowd like a confident convict shouting convince","cloze_distractors_en":["Repulsive","Incoherent","Negligible"],"examples":[{"es":"El argumento del abogado fue tan convincente que el jurado no tuvo dudas.","en":"The lawyer''s argument was so compelling that the jury had no doubts."},{"es":"La empresa presentó una propuesta convincente para reducir las emisiones de carbono en la ciudad.","en":"The company presented a compelling proposal to reduce carbon emissions in the city."},{"es":"El autor escribió una narrativa convincente sobre los desafíos de la vida en el espacio profundo.","en":"The author wrote a compelling narrative about the challenges of life in deep space."}]},{"spanish_text":"Discrepancia","english_text":"Discrepancy","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A difference or inconsistency between two or more things that should be the same.","main_translations_es":["Desacuerdo","Diferencia","Incongruencia"],"collocations":["discrepancy in the data","notice a discrepancy","account for the discrepancy","resolve the discrepancy"],"synonyms_en":["difference","inconsistency","variance"],"example_sentence":"The auditor found a significant discrepancy between the sales records and the money deposited in the bank.","example_es":"El auditor encontró una discrepancia significativa entre los registros de ventas y el dinero depositado en el banco.","example_en":"The auditor found a significant discrepancy between the sales records and the money deposited in the bank.","mnemonic_en":"A DISCO and a PANCake on the same plate look mismatched, a clear discrepancy.","cloze_distractors_en":["Conjecture","Affluence","Resonance","Propensity"],"examples":[{"es":"El auditor encontró una discrepancia significativa entre los registros de ventas y el dinero depositado en el banco.","en":"The auditor found a significant discrepancy between the sales records and the money deposited in the bank."},{"es":"Debido a una discrepancia en los datos del censo, el ayuntamiento tuvo que revisar el presupuesto para el próximo año.","en":"Due to a discrepancy in the census data, the city council had to revise the budget for the coming year."},{"es":"Hubo una clara discrepancia entre lo que prometió el candidato durante la campaña y sus acciones una vez en el poder.","en":"There was a clear discrepancy between what the candidate promised during the campaign and his actions once in office."}]},{"spanish_text":"Supuesto","english_text":"Assumption","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Something that is accepted as true without proof.","main_translations_es":["Hipótesis","Presunción","Suposición"],"collocations":["make an assumption","under the assumption that","assumption of risk","questionable assumption"],"synonyms_en":["presumption","supposition","premise"],"example_sentence":"The assumption that the project will be profitable is optimistic.","example_es":"El supuesto de que el proyecto será rentable es optimista.","example_en":"The assumption that the project will be profitable is optimistic.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a chef who assumes a sup of soup, and that guess becomes the assumption.","cloze_distractors_en":["Resolution","Allocation","Correction","Validation"],"examples":[{"es":"El supuesto de que el proyecto será rentable es optimista.","en":"The assumption that the project will be profitable is optimistic."},{"es":"Debemos cuestionar el supuesto básico sobre el cual se construyó toda la teoría económica.","en":"We must challenge the basic assumption upon which the entire economic theory was built."},{"es":"Su argumento se desmoronó cuando se demostró que su supuesto inicial era completamente falso.","en":"His argument fell apart when it was proven that his initial assumption was completely false."}]},{"spanish_text":"Planteamiento","english_text":"Approach","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A way of dealing with a problem or task.","main_translations_es":["Enfoque","Propuesta","Idea"],"collocations":["new approach","different approach","take an approach","approach the problem"],"synonyms_en":["method","strategy","tactic"],"example_sentence":"The project''s approach was approved by the committee.","example_es":"El planteamiento del proyecto fue aprobado por el comité.","example_en":"The project''s approach was approved by the committee.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a plant reaching out as your approach to a problem","cloze_distractors_en":["Appetite","Apostrophe","Apparatus"],"examples":[{"es":"El planteamiento del proyecto fue aprobado por el comité.","en":"The project''s approach was approved by the committee."},{"es":"Su planteamiento para resolver la crisis económica resultó ser muy innovador.","en":"Her approach to solving the economic crisis proved to be highly innovative."},{"es":"El entrenador cambió su planteamiento táctico durante el descanso para asegurar la victoria.","en":"The coach changed his tactical approach during halftime to secure the victory."}]},{"spanish_text":"Marco","english_text":"Framework","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A basic structure or system that supports the development or organization of something.","main_translations_es":["estructura","esquema","marco"],"collocations":["software framework","framework agreement","framework for","framework of"],"synonyms_en":["structure","system","architecture"],"example_sentence":"The framework of the theory allows understanding the basic concepts.","example_es":"El marco de la teoría permite entender los conceptos básicos.","example_en":"The framework of the theory allows understanding the basic concepts.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine Marco the builder erecting a sturdy wooden frame, a literal framework for his house.","cloze_distractors_en":["Fabrication","Foreshadow","Fragility","Friction"],"examples":[{"es":"El marco de la teoría permite entender los conceptos básicos.","en":"The framework of the theory allows understanding the basic concepts."},{"es":"Debemos establecer un marco legal sólido para regular el uso de la inteligencia artificial.","en":"We must establish a solid legal framework to regulate the use of artificial intelligence."},{"es":"El proyecto se desarrolló dentro del marco de una colaboración internacional entre universidades.","en":"The project was developed within the framework of an international collaboration between universities."}]},{"spanish_text":"Perspectiva","english_text":"Perspective","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A particular way of regarding something; a point of view.","main_translations_es":["Punto de vista","Enfoque","Óptica"],"collocations":["from a different perspective","gain perspective","broaden one''s perspective","new perspective"],"synonyms_en":["viewpoint","outlook","standpoint"],"example_sentence":"From my perspective, the project has a lot of potential.","example_es":"Desde mi perspectiva, el proyecto tiene mucho potencial.","example_en":"From my perspective, the project has a lot of potential.","mnemonic_en":"See a pair of spectacles shifting your view—just like the Spanish perspectiVA.","cloze_distractors_en":["Dimension","Precedent","Incentive"],"examples":[{"es":"Desde mi perspectiva, el proyecto tiene mucho potencial.","en":"From my perspective, the project has a lot of potential."},{"es":"Es necesario cambiar nuestra perspectiva para resolver este problema técnico tan complejo.","en":"It is necessary to change our perspective to solve this complex technical problem."},{"es":"Viajar por el mundo ayuda a los jóvenes a ampliar su perspectiva sobre otras culturas.","en":"Traveling the world helps young people broaden their perspective on other cultures."}]},{"spanish_text":"Hallazgo","english_text":"Finding","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A piece of information discovered as a result of investigation or research.","main_translations_es":["Descubrimiento","Resultado","Observación"],"collocations":["finding a solution","finding the truth","finding evidence","finding a cure"],"synonyms_en":["discovery","result","conclusion"],"example_sentence":"The archaeologist''s finding changed the understanding of the civilization.","example_es":"El hallazgo del arqueólogo cambió la comprensión de la civilización.","example_en":"The archaeologist''s finding changed the understanding of the civilization.","mnemonic_en":"Finding a hall a‑go, I discovered the hidden treasure.","cloze_distractors_en":["Stalling","Mending","Bending","Landing"],"examples":[{"es":"El hallazgo del arqueólogo cambió la comprensión de la civilización.","en":"The archaeologist''s finding changed the understanding of the civilization."},{"es":"El hallazgo de una nueva especie de planta en la selva sorprendió a los científicos.","en":"The finding of a new plant species in the jungle surprised the scientists."},{"es":"La policía presentó el hallazgo de pruebas clave que incriminan al sospechoso.","en":"The police presented the finding of key evidence that incriminates the suspect."}]},{"spanish_text":"Evidencia","english_text":"Evidence","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Evidence is information or objects that support a claim, belief, or conclusion.","main_translations_es":["prueba","testimonio","indicio"],"collocations":["gather evidence","present the evidence","lack of evidence","beyond a doubt"],"synonyms_en":["proof","testimony","confirmation"],"example_sentence":"The evidence suggests that the suspect was at the crime scene.","example_es":"La evidencia sugiere que el sospechoso estaba en la escena del crimen.","example_en":"The evidence suggests that the suspect was at the crime scene.","mnemonic_en":"Think of Eve''s dance on a courtroom floor as the evidence.","cloze_distractors_en":["Pretense","Sequence","Reference","Presence"],"examples":[{"es":"La evidencia sugiere que el sospechoso estaba en la escena del crimen.","en":"The evidence suggests that the suspect was at the crime scene."},{"es":"Los científicos presentaron evidencia irrefutable que respalda su nueva teoría sobre el cambio climático.","en":"The scientists presented irrefutable evidence that supports their new theory on climate change."},{"es":"El fiscal no pudo encontrar suficiente evidencia para condenar al acusado durante el juicio.","en":"The prosecutor could not find enough evidence to convict the defendant during the trial."}]},{"spanish_text":"Restricción","english_text":"Constraint","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A limitation or restriction that controls what can be done or achieved.","main_translations_es":["limitación","condición","restricción"],"collocations":["budget constraint","time constraint","constraint satisfaction","constraint programming"],"synonyms_en":["restriction","limitation","restraint"],"example_sentence":"The budget constraint forces us to cancel the expansion project.","example_es":"La restricción de presupuesto nos obliga a cancelar el proyecto de expansión.","example_en":"The budget constraint forces us to cancel the expansion project.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a restric-tion rope tightening, turning a box into a strict constraint.","cloze_distractors_en":["Conjecture","Confluence","Contingent","Concession"],"examples":[{"es":"La restricción de presupuesto nos obliga a cancelar el proyecto de expansión.","en":"The budget constraint forces us to cancel the expansion project."},{"es":"El diseño arquitectónico tiene una restricción importante debido a la inclinación del terreno.","en":"The architectural design has a major constraint due to the slope of the land."},{"es":"Debido a la restricción de tiempo, solo pudimos presentar los puntos más relevantes del informe.","en":"Due to the time constraint, we were only able to present the most relevant points of the report."}]},{"spanish_text":"Viable","english_text":"Feasible","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Possible to do or achieve; capable of being carried out successfully.","main_translations_es":["Factible","Viable","Realizable"],"collocations":["feasible solution","feasible option","feasible approach","feasible plan"],"synonyms_en":["practicable","doable","possible"],"example_sentence":"The project is feasible if we secure more funding.","example_es":"El proyecto es viable si conseguimos más financiación.","example_en":"The project is feasible if we secure more funding.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a feasible plan as a feast in a viable garden, showing it can be done.","cloze_distractors_en":["Fervent","Fissile","Fictive","Furtive"],"examples":[{"es":"El proyecto es viable si conseguimos más financiación.","en":"The project is feasible if we secure more funding."},{"es":"Los ingenieros determinaron que la construcción del puente no era viable debido a la inestabilidad del terreno.","en":"The engineers determined that building the bridge was not feasible due to the unstable terrain."},{"es":"Debemos buscar una solución viable para reducir las emisiones de carbono antes de que termine el año.","en":"We must find a feasible solution to reduce carbon emissions before the end of the year."}]},{"spanish_text":"Sostenible","english_text":"Sustainable","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Capable of being maintained over the long term without depleting resources or causing harm.","main_translations_es":["Sustentable","Duradero","Ecoamigable"],"collocations":["sustainable development","sustainable growth","sustainable energy","sustainable practices"],"synonyms_en":["viable","eco‑friendly","renewable"],"example_sentence":"This company has implemented sustainable practices to reduce its carbon footprint.","example_es":"Esta empresa ha implementado prácticas sostenibles para reducir su huella de carbono.","example_en":"This company has implemented sustainable practices to reduce its carbon footprint.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a sturdy table that can sustain, its label reads SOSTENIBLE, showing it''s sustainable.","cloze_distractors_en":["Subservient","Substandard","Subliminal"],"examples":[{"es":"Esta empresa ha implementado prácticas sostenibles para reducir su huella de carbono.","en":"This company has implemented sustainable practices to reduce its carbon footprint."},{"es":"El gobierno busca promover un modelo de desarrollo económico que sea sostenible a largo plazo.","en":"The government seeks to promote an economic development model that is sustainable in the long term."},{"es":"Los expertos advierten que la sobrepesca en esta región no es sostenible para el ecosistema marino.","en":"Experts warn that overfishing in this region is not sustainable for the marine ecosystem."}]},{"spanish_text":"Controvertido","english_text":"Controversial","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Describing something that provokes public disagreement or debate.","main_translations_es":["Polémico","Discutido","Contencioso"],"collocations":["controversial issue","controversial figure","controversial topic","controversial decision"],"synonyms_en":["disputed","contentious","debated"],"example_sentence":"The issue of euthanasia remains controversial in many countries.","example_es":"El tema de la eutanasia sigue siendo controvertido en muchos países.","example_en":"The issue of euthanasia remains controversial in many countries.","mnemonic_en":"A heated debate turns the article into a contra verse, making it controversial.","cloze_distractors_en":["Inconspicuous","Unanimous","Superfluous","Conspicuous"],"examples":[{"es":"El tema de la eutanasia sigue siendo controvertido en muchos países.","en":"The issue of euthanasia remains controversial in many countries."},{"es":"La decisión del árbitro de anular el gol fue muy controvertido entre los aficionados.","en":"The referee''s decision to disallow the goal was highly controversial among the fans."},{"es":"El autor publicó un ensayo controvertido sobre las políticas económicas del gobierno actual.","en":"The author published a controversial essay regarding the current government''s economic policies."}]},{"spanish_text":"Generalizado","english_text":"Widespread","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Existing or occurring over a large area or among many people.","main_translations_es":["Extenso","General","Difuso"],"collocations":["widespread use","widespread adoption","widespread problem","widespread belief"],"synonyms_en":["extensive","prevalent","common"],"example_sentence":"The use of mobile phones has become very widespread throughout the country.","example_es":"El uso de los teléfonos móviles se ha vuelto muy generalizado en todo el país.","example_en":"The use of mobile phones has become very widespread throughout the country.","mnemonic_en":"A wide spread of general news blankets the town, like a generalizado blanket.","cloze_distractors_en":["Unilateral","Incoherent","Negligible","Superfluous"],"examples":[{"es":"El uso de los teléfonos móviles se ha vuelto muy generalizado en todo el país.","en":"The use of mobile phones has become very widespread throughout the country."},{"es":"Existe un descontento generalizado entre los empleados debido a los recientes recortes salariales.","en":"There is widespread discontent among the employees due to the recent salary cuts."},{"es":"La especie ha sufrido un declive generalizado en su población debido a la pérdida de su hábitat natural.","en":"The species has suffered a widespread decline in its population due to the loss of its natural habitat."}]},{"spanish_text":"Predominante","english_text":"Predominant","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Being the most common, strongest, or most important element in a group or situation.","main_translations_es":["principal","dominante","preponderante"],"collocations":["predominant theme","predominant factor","predominant position","predominant in"],"synonyms_en":["dominant","prevalent","principal"],"example_sentence":"The color blue is predominant in the room''s decor.","example_es":"El color azul es predominante en la decoración de la habitación.","example_en":"The color blue is predominant in the room''s decor.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a PRE-DOMINANT lion, the king before any other, just like a predominante leader.","cloze_distractors_en":["Subservient","Incoherent","Negligible","Superfluous"],"examples":[{"es":"El color azul es predominante en la decoración de la habitación.","en":"The color blue is predominant in the room''s decor."},{"es":"El viento del norte es el factor predominante que afecta el clima de esta región costera.","en":"The north wind is the predominant factor affecting the climate of this coastal region."},{"es":"A pesar de la diversidad cultural, el inglés sigue siendo el idioma predominante en las reuniones de negocios internacionales.","en":"Despite cultural diversity, English remains the predominant language in international business meetings."}]},{"spanish_text":"Subyacente","english_text":"Underlying","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Existing beneath the surface or forming the basis of something.","main_translations_es":["subyacente","latente","de base"],"collocations":["underlying cause","underlying principle","underlying assumption","underlying issue"],"synonyms_en":["fundamental","basic","foundational"],"example_sentence":"The underlying problem is the lack of communication.","example_es":"El problema subyacente es la falta de comunicación.","example_en":"The underlying problem is the lack of communication.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a submarine (sub) hidden under the waves, the underlying secret.","cloze_distractors_en":["Overstated","Submerged","Outstretched","Underhanded"],"examples":[{"es":"El problema subyacente es la falta de comunicación.","en":"The underlying problem is the lack of communication."},{"es":"Debemos analizar las causas subyacentes de este conflicto económico.","en":"We must analyze the underlying causes of this economic conflict."},{"es":"Existe una tensión subyacente en la sala cada vez que mencionan el presupuesto.","en":"There is an underlying tension in the room whenever they mention the budget."}]},{"spanish_text":"Trascender","english_text":"Transcend","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To go beyond or rise above something, especially limits, expectations, or ordinary experience.","main_translations_es":["sobrepasar","ir más allá","superar"],"collocations":["transcend boundaries","transcend the ordinary","transcend time","transcend expectations"],"synonyms_en":["go beyond","exceed","surpass"],"example_sentence":"Van Gogh''s art manages to transcend time and continues to inspire new generations.","example_es":"El arte de Van Gogh logra trascender el tiempo y sigue inspirando a nuevas generaciones.","example_en":"Van Gogh''s art manages to transcend time and continues to inspire new generations.","mnemonic_en":"Visualize a ladder that trascends the clouds, letting you rise beyond all limits.","cloze_distractors_en":["Submerge","Concede","Inhibit","Descend"],"examples":[{"es":"El arte de Van Gogh logra trascender el tiempo y sigue inspirando a nuevas generaciones.","en":"Van Gogh''s art manages to transcend time and continues to inspire new generations."},{"es":"Los principios éticos de la organización deben trascender las fronteras nacionales para garantizar la justicia global.","en":"The organization''s ethical principles must transcend national borders to ensure global justice."},{"es":"Su dedicación al servicio comunitario logró trascender sus deberes laborales habituales.","en":"Her dedication to community service managed to transcend her regular job duties."}]},{"spanish_text":"Perjudicar","english_text":"Undermine","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To weaken or damage something gradually or subtly.","main_translations_es":["dañar","desmejorar","afectar negativamente"],"collocations":["undermine confidence","undermine authority","undermine credibility","undermine efforts"],"synonyms_en":["weaken","sabotage","subvert"],"example_sentence":"Constant criticism can undermine the team''s confidence.","example_es":"Las críticas constantes pueden perjudicar la confianza del equipo.","example_en":"Constant criticism can undermine the team''s confidence.","mnemonic_en":"A miner digs under the bridge, causing it to collapse and perjudicar the village.","cloze_distractors_en":["Elevate","Fortify","Illuminate","Cultivate"],"examples":[{"es":"Las críticas constantes pueden perjudicar la confianza del equipo.","en":"Constant criticism can undermine the team''s confidence."},{"es":"El escándalo financiero comenzó a perjudicar la reputación de la empresa ante sus inversores.","en":"The financial scandal began to undermine the company''s reputation among its investors."},{"es":"No permitas que sus comentarios negativos lleguen a perjudicar tu determinación para alcanzar tus metas.","en":"Do not let their negative comments undermine your determination to reach your goals."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cumplir","english_text":"Comply with","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to act in accordance with a rule, request, or demand","main_translations_es":["Obedecer","Acatar","Cumplir con"],"collocations":["comply with regulations","comply with the law","comply with standards","comply with requirements"],"synonyms_en":["obey","conform to","adhere to"],"example_sentence":"It is important to comply with the safety regulations.","example_es":"Es importante cumplir con las normas de seguridad.","example_en":"It is important to comply with the safety regulations.","mnemonic_en":"See a cumulative pile of rules you must comply with.","cloze_distractors_en":["Fabricate with","Exaggerate with","Contradict with","Negotiate with"],"examples":[{"es":"Es importante cumplir con las normas de seguridad.","en":"It is important to comply with the safety regulations."},{"es":"La empresa debe cumplir con los estándares ambientales establecidos por la ley.","en":"The company must comply with the environmental standards established by law."},{"es":"Si no logras cumplir con los requisitos del contrato, podrías enfrentar una demanda.","en":"If you fail to comply with the contract requirements, you could face a lawsuit."}]},{"spanish_text":"Ajustarse a","english_text":"Adhere to","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to follow or comply with a rule, guideline, or request","main_translations_es":["adaptarse a","cumplir con","acatar"],"collocations":["adhere to guidelines","adhere to the policy","adhere to standards","adhere to a schedule"],"synonyms_en":["follow","stick to","comply with"],"example_sentence":"It is important to adhere to the company''s rules.","example_es":"Es importante ajustarse a las normas de la empresa.","example_en":"It is important to adhere to the company''s rules.","mnemonic_en":"A deer adjusts to the fence, just like you adhere to rules.","cloze_distractors_en":["Abstain from","Depart from","Incline to","Concede to"],"examples":[{"es":"Es importante ajustarse a las normas de la empresa.","en":"It is important to adhere to the company''s rules."},{"es":"Todos los participantes deben ajustarse a los términos establecidos en el contrato.","en":"All participants must adhere to the terms established in the contract."},{"es":"El arquitecto tuvo que ajustarse a las estrictas regulaciones de seguridad del edificio.","en":"The architect had to adhere to the building''s strict safety regulations."}]},{"spanish_text":"Dar lugar a","english_text":"Give rise to","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to cause something to happen or exist","main_translations_es":["Provocar","Causar","Originar"],"collocations":["give rise to problems","give rise to controversy","give rise to questions","give rise to a new trend"],"synonyms_en":["cause","lead to","bring about"],"example_sentence":"The new policy can give rise to massive protests.","example_es":"La nueva política puede dar lugar a protestas masivas.","example_en":"The new policy can give rise to massive protests.","mnemonic_en":"A river gives rise to a new path, just like \"dar\" creates space for something to happen.","cloze_distractors_en":["Fall back on","Look down on","Make off with","Run out of"],"examples":[{"es":"La nueva política puede dar lugar a protestas masivas.","en":"The new policy can give rise to massive protests."},{"es":"El aumento de las temperaturas globales suele dar lugar a fenómenos meteorológicos extremos.","en":"Rising global temperatures often give rise to extreme weather events."},{"es":"La falta de comunicación clara en el equipo puede dar lugar a malentendidos costosos.","en":"A lack of clear communication within the team can give rise to costly misunderstandings."}]},{"spanish_text":"Tener en cuenta","english_text":"Take into account","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To consider or regard something when making a decision.","main_translations_es":["Considerar","Tomar en consideración","Tener presente"],"collocations":["take into account the fact that","take into account the costs","take into account the risks"],"synonyms_en":["consider","keep in mind","factor in"],"example_sentence":"You should take into account the weather before going out.","example_es":"Debes tener en cuenta el clima antes de salir.","example_en":"You should take into account the weather before going out.","mnemonic_en":"Take a taco, then count the beans—cuenta reminds you to take into account.","cloze_distractors_en":["Look after","Bring about","Make up","Turn over"],"examples":[{"es":"Debes tener en cuenta el clima antes de salir.","en":"You should take into account the weather before going out."},{"es":"Al planificar el presupuesto, hay que tener en cuenta los gastos imprevistos.","en":"When planning the budget, one must take into account the unexpected expenses."},{"es":"El comité decidió tener en cuenta todas las sugerencias de los empleados antes de votar.","en":"The committee decided to take into account all the employees'' suggestions before voting."}]},{"spanish_text":"Llegar a la conclusión","english_text":"Reach the conclusion","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"to arrive at a final decision or judgment after considering the evidence","main_translations_es":["Llegar a una conclusión","Concluir","Llegar a la conclusión"],"collocations":["reach the conclusion that","reach the conclusion after","reach the conclusion based on","reach the conclusion that it is"],"synonyms_en":["draw a conclusion","come to a conclusion","conclude"],"example_sentence":"In order to reach the conclusion that the treatment works, researchers need a larger sample.","example_es":"Para llegar a la conclusión de que el tratamiento funciona, los investigadores necesitan una muestra más grande.","example_en":"In order to reach the conclusion that the treatment works, researchers need a larger sample.","mnemonic_en":"I reach out and grab the final ''conclusión'' banner at the race finish.","cloze_distractors_en":["reach the assumption","reach the hypothesis","reach the presumption","reach the speculation"],"examples":[{"es":"Para llegar a la conclusión de que el tratamiento funciona, los investigadores necesitan una muestra más grande.","en":"In order to reach the conclusion that the treatment works, researchers need a larger sample."},{"es":"El comité debe llegar a la conclusión por unanimidad antes de que se implementen cambios en las políticas.","en":"The committee must reach the conclusion unanimously before any policy changes are implemented."},{"es":"Solo después de examinar todas las pruebas puede el jurado llegar a la conclusión de que el acusado es culpable.","en":"Only after examining all the evidence can the jury reach the conclusion that the defendant is guilty."}]},{"spanish_text":"En gran medida","english_text":"To a large extent","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"It means that something is true or applies to a great degree.","main_translations_es":["En gran medida","En gran parte","Considerablemente"],"collocations":["It is true to a large extent","The impact is felt to a large extent","Results vary to a large extent"],"synonyms_en":["greatly","significantly","substantially"],"example_sentence":"The success of the project depends, to a large extent, on the team''s collaboration.","example_es":"El éxito del proyecto depende, en gran medida, de la colaboración del equipo.","example_en":"The success of the project depends, to a large extent, on the team''s collaboration.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a huge tent covering a big measure of land","cloze_distractors_en":["In a minor mood","On a brief scale","By a narrow margin","At a slow tempo"],"examples":[{"es":"El éxito del proyecto depende, en gran medida, de la colaboración del equipo.","en":"The success of the project depends, to a large extent, on the team''s collaboration."},{"es":"La crisis económica actual se debe, en gran medida, a la falta de inversión en infraestructura.","en":"The current economic crisis is, to a large extent, due to the lack of investment in infrastructure."},{"es":"Su decisión de renunciar fue, en gran medida, motivada por el ambiente tóxico en la oficina.","en":"Her decision to resign was, to a large extent, motivated by the toxic environment in the office."}]},{"spanish_text":"A corto plazo","english_text":"In the short term","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"During a brief period of time, referring to the near future.","main_translations_es":["En el corto plazo","A corto plazo","En el futuro cercano"],"collocations":["In the short term, we expect...","In the short term, the company will...","In the short term, this will improve"],"synonyms_en":["short‑term","temporarily","in the near term"],"example_sentence":"In the short term, the company plans to increase its sales by 10%.","example_es":"A corto plazo, la empresa planea aumentar sus ventas en un 10%.","example_en":"In the short term, the company plans to increase its sales by 10%.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a short \"corto\" rope that snaps quickly, just like the short term.","cloze_distractors_en":["In perpetuity","In retrospectively","In retrospecting"],"examples":[{"es":"A corto plazo, la empresa planea aumentar sus ventas en un 10%.","en":"In the short term, the company plans to increase its sales by 10%."},{"es":"A corto plazo, necesitamos reducir los gastos operativos para evitar un déficit presupuestario.","en":"In the short term, we need to cut operating expenses to avoid a budget deficit."},{"es":"Aunque el proyecto es ambicioso, a corto plazo nos centraremos únicamente en la fase de desarrollo inicial.","en":"Although the project is ambitious, in the short term we will focus solely on the initial development phase."}]},{"spanish_text":"A largo plazo","english_text":"In the long run","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"refers to what will happen over a long period of time","main_translations_es":["A largo plazo","A futuro","En el futuro"],"collocations":["In the long run, it will pay off","In the long run, the benefits outweigh the costs","In the long run, we see improvement"],"synonyms_en":["eventually","over time","ultimately"],"example_sentence":"In the long run, investment in education will reduce inequality.","example_es":"A largo plazo, la inversión en educación reducirá la desigualdad.","example_en":"In the long run, investment in education will reduce inequality.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a long (largo) race that stretches far into the future.","cloze_distractors_en":["In the brief flash","In the wrong lane","In the cold light","In the deep sleep"],"examples":[{"es":"A largo plazo, la inversión en educación reducirá la desigualdad.","en":"In the long run, investment in education will reduce inequality."},{"es":"Aunque el coche eléctrico es más caro ahora, a largo plazo ahorrarás mucho dinero en combustible.","en":"Although the electric car is more expensive now, in the long run you will save a lot of money on fuel."},{"es":"Debemos considerar las consecuencias ambientales de este proyecto a largo plazo antes de comenzar la construcción.","en":"We must consider the environmental consequences of this project in the long run before beginning construction."}]},{"spanish_text":"Desde mi punto de vista","english_text":"From my perspective","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to indicate that something is being considered from one''s own point of view.","main_translations_es":["Según mi punto de vista","A mi parecer","En mi opinión"],"collocations":["From my perspective, ...","From my perspective it seems that ...","From my perspective we can see ..."],"synonyms_en":["In my view","As I see it","My perspective"],"example_sentence":"From my perspective, the labor reform proposal is far too risky for the current economy.","example_es":"Desde mi punto de vista, la propuesta de reforma laboral es demasiado arriesgada para la economía actual.","example_en":"From my perspective, the labor reform proposal is far too risky for the current economy.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a point (punto) on a map, and you view it from your own perspective.","cloze_distractors_en":["Without hesitation","Regardless of logic","Contrary to reality","Beyond all measure"],"examples":[{"es":"Desde mi punto de vista, la propuesta de reforma laboral es demasiado arriesgada para la economía actual.","en":"From my perspective, the labor reform proposal is far too risky for the current economy."},{"es":"Desde mi punto de vista, el diseño minimalista de este edificio mejora significativamente la eficiencia energética.","en":"From my perspective, the minimalist design of this building significantly improves energy efficiency."},{"es":"Desde mi punto de vista, los avances en inteligencia artificial transformarán radicalmente el mercado laboral en la próxima década.","en":"From my perspective, advancements in artificial intelligence will radically transform the job market over the next decade."}]},{"spanish_text":"En última instancia","english_text":"Ultimately","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"In the end, after everything else has been considered.","main_translations_es":["Al fin de cuentas","En definitiva","Al final"],"collocations":["ultimately decided","ultimately leads to","ultimately result","ultimately important"],"synonyms_en":["in the end","finally","eventually"],"example_sentence":"Ultimately, the decision to accept the new job offer rests entirely with you.","example_es":"En última instancia, la decisión de aceptar el nuevo puesto de trabajo depende únicamente de ti.","example_en":"Ultimately, the decision to accept the new job offer rests entirely with you.","mnemonic_en":"Picture the final ''última'' page flipping, revealing the ultimate outcome.","cloze_distractors_en":["Superficially","Arbitrarily","Sporadically"],"examples":[{"es":"En última instancia, la decisión de aceptar el nuevo puesto de trabajo depende únicamente de ti.","en":"Ultimately, the decision to accept the new job offer rests entirely with you."},{"es":"Aunque discutimos varios planes, en última instancia optamos por la opción más económica.","en":"Although we discussed several plans, we ultimately opted for the most budget-friendly option."},{"es":"El éxito de este proyecto depende, en última instancia, de nuestra capacidad para trabajar en equipo bajo presión.","en":"The success of this project ultimately depends on our ability to work as a team under pressure."}]},{"spanish_text":"En lo que respecta a","english_text":"As far as ... is concerned","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Used to indicate that something is being considered or discussed in relation to a particular subject.","main_translations_es":["En cuanto a","Con respecto a","En lo que se refiere a"],"collocations":["as far as I''m concerned","as far as you''re concerned","as far as the matter is concerned","as far as the law is concerned"],"synonyms_en":["regarding","with respect to","as for"],"example_sentence":"As far as ... is concerned, the airline will continue offering free checked bags on international flights, although the baggage fees for domestic routes remain unchanged.","example_es":"En lo que respecta a ..., la aerolínea seguirá ofreciendo equipaje facturado gratuito en los vuelos internacionales, aunque las tarifas de equipaje para trayectos domésticos permanecen sin cambios.","example_en":"As far as ... is concerned, the airline will continue offering free checked bags on international flights, although the baggage fees for domestic routes remain unchanged.","mnemonic_en":"See a faraway A (as) looking concerned at a sign reading en lo que respecta a.","cloze_distractors_en":["As far as ... is confirmed","As long as ... is concerned","As much as ... is concerned"],"examples":[{"es":"En lo que respecta a ..., la aerolínea seguirá ofreciendo equipaje facturado gratuito en los vuelos internacionales, aunque las tarifas de equipaje para trayectos domésticos permanecen sin cambios.","en":"As far as ... is concerned, the airline will continue offering free checked bags on international flights, although the baggage fees for domestic routes remain unchanged."},{"es":"En lo que respecta a ..., el departamento de recursos humanos aclaró que los empleados deberán presentarse en la oficina al menos dos días por semana para mantener su elegibilidad.","en":"As far as ... is concerned, the human resources department clarified that employees must come into the office at least two days per week to maintain their eligibility."},{"es":"En lo que respecta a ..., el director del proyecto anunció que cualquier retraso superior a 48 horas requerirá una justificación por escrito firmada por el supervisor del equipo.","en":"As far as ... is concerned, the project director announced that any delay exceeding 48 hours will require a written justification signed by the team supervisor."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cabe destacar","english_text":"It is worth noting","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to indicate that something should be emphasized or remembered.","main_translations_es":["Hay que destacar","Vale la pena señalar","Es importante señalar"],"collocations":["It is worth noting that...","It is worth noting the following...","It is worth noting the fact that..."],"synonyms_en":["It should be noted","Note that","It is notable"],"example_sentence":"It is worth noting that the research revealed new findings about the climate.","example_es":"Cabe destacar que la investigación reveló nuevos hallazgos sobre el clima.","example_en":"It is worth noting that the research revealed new findings about the climate.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a cape (cabe) that highlights a worth‑noting treasure.","cloze_distractors_en":["It remains ignored","It seems completely","It stands forgotten"],"examples":[{"es":"Cabe destacar que la investigación reveló nuevos hallazgos sobre el clima.","en":"It is worth noting that the research revealed new findings about the climate."},{"es":"Cabe destacar que el candidato tiene una experiencia excepcional en gestión de crisis internacionales.","en":"It is worth noting that the candidate has exceptional experience in international crisis management."},{"es":"Cabe destacar que las ventas del último trimestre superaron todas las expectativas de los analistas financieros.","en":"It is worth noting that the last quarter''s sales exceeded all the financial analysts'' expectations."}]},{"spanish_text":"Vale la pena señalar","english_text":"It is worth pointing out","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"idiomatic expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to indicate that something should be highlighted or mentioned.","main_translations_es":["Cabe destacar","Hay que señalar","Vale la pena mencionar"],"collocations":["It is worth pointing out that...","It is worth pointing out the fact that...","It is worth pointing out the importance of..."],"synonyms_en":["It''s notable","It''s worth mentioning","One should note"],"example_sentence":"It is worth pointing out that the report contains several errors.","example_es":"Vale la pena señalar que el informe contiene varios errores.","example_en":"It is worth pointing out that the report contains several errors.","mnemonic_en":"A valuable pen points out the secret.","cloze_distractors_en":["It is strictly forbidden","It is perpetually hungry","It is somewhat circular"],"examples":[{"es":"Vale la pena señalar que el informe contiene varios errores.","en":"It is worth pointing out that the report contains several errors."},{"es":"Vale la pena señalar que los precios de las viviendas han subido drásticamente este trimestre.","en":"It is worth pointing out that housing prices have risen drastically this quarter."},{"es":"Vale la pena señalar que el candidato no tiene experiencia previa en el sector tecnológico.","en":"It is worth pointing out that the candidate lacks prior experience in the tech sector."}]},{"spanish_text":"No cabe duda de que","english_text":"There is no doubt that","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to indicate that something is certain and unquestionable.","main_translations_es":["Sin duda","No hay duda de que","Indudablemente"],"collocations":["There is no doubt that…","There is no doubt about it.","No doubt that…"],"synonyms_en":["Undoubtedly","Without a doubt","No question that"],"example_sentence":"There is no doubt that the new policy will improve the country''s economy.","example_es":"No cabe duda de que la nueva política mejorará la economía del país.","example_en":"There is no doubt that the new policy will improve the country''s economy.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a cabbage (cabe) with the doubt question mark crossed out—no doubt.","cloze_distractors_en":["Under no circumstances","Regardless of whether","In spite of everything","For the sake of"],"examples":[{"es":"No cabe duda de que la nueva política mejorará la economía del país.","en":"There is no doubt that the new policy will improve the country''s economy."},{"es":"No cabe duda de que el equipo de investigación ha descubierto una cura revolucionaria para esta enfermedad.","en":"There is no doubt that the research team has discovered a revolutionary cure for this disease."},{"es":"No cabe duda de que ella es la candidata más cualificada para asumir el puesto de directora ejecutiva.","en":"There is no doubt that she is the most qualified candidate to take on the role of chief executive officer."}]},{"spanish_text":"Resulta evidente que","english_text":"It is evident that","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to state that something is clearly apparent or obvious.","main_translations_es":["Es evidente que","Resulta claro que","Se ve que"],"collocations":["It is evident that...","It is evident that the data shows...","It is evident that there is a problem","It is evident that this is the case"],"synonyms_en":["clearly","obviously","it is clear that"],"example_sentence":"It is evident that air pollution is worsening public health.","example_es":"Resulta evidente que la contaminación del aire está empeorando la salud pública.","example_en":"It is evident that air pollution is worsening public health.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a neon sign flashing EVIDENT above a Spanish street, shouting evidente for everyone to see.","cloze_distractors_en":["It is circular that","It is rectangular that","It is melodic that","It is flavorful that"],"examples":[{"es":"Resulta evidente que la contaminación del aire está empeorando la salud pública.","en":"It is evident that air pollution is worsening public health."},{"es":"Resulta evidente que el equipo no ha practicado lo suficiente para ganar el campeonato.","en":"It is evident that the team has not practiced enough to win the championship."},{"es":"Resulta evidente que las nuevas políticas económicas han provocado un aumento en el desempleo.","en":"It is evident that the new economic policies have caused an increase in unemployment."}]},{"spanish_text":"Sin perjuicio de","english_text":"Without prejudice to","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase indicating that something does not affect or limit another matter.","main_translations_es":["sin que ello implique","sin afectar","sin menoscabar"],"collocations":["without prejudice to the rights of","without prejudice to any claim","without prejudice to the above","without prejudice to further action"],"synonyms_en":["subject to","notwithstanding","without affecting"],"example_sentence":"Without prejudice to what has been agreed, the company may change the working hours.","example_es":"Sin perjuicio de lo acordado, la empresa podrá modificar los horarios.","example_en":"Without prejudice to what has been agreed, the company may change the working hours.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a sinless judge clearing the record: without prejudice.","cloze_distractors_en":["In defiance of","Under penalty of","By contrast to"],"examples":[{"es":"Sin perjuicio de lo acordado, la empresa podrá modificar los horarios.","en":"Without prejudice to what has been agreed, the company may change the working hours."},{"es":"Sin perjuicio de las nuevas normativas, los contratos vigentes seguirán siendo válidos.","en":"Without prejudice to the new regulations, the existing contracts will remain valid."},{"es":"Sin perjuicio de su derecho a apelar, el acusado debe cumplir la sentencia provisionalmente.","en":"Without prejudice to his right to appeal, the defendant must comply with the sentence provisionally."}]},{"spanish_text":"En aras de","english_text":"For the sake of","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Used to indicate that something is done in order to achieve or benefit something else.","main_translations_es":["con el fin de","a fin de","por el bien de"],"collocations":["for the sake of argument","for the sake of clarity","for the sake of completeness"],"synonyms_en":["in order to","for the benefit of","for the purpose of"],"example_sentence":"For the sake of safety, they closed the road during the storm.","example_es":"En aras de la seguridad, cerraron la carretera durante la tormenta.","example_en":"For the sake of safety, they closed the road during the storm.","mnemonic_en":"Run a race for the sake of victory.","cloze_distractors_en":["Regardless of","In spite of","Contrary to"],"examples":[{"es":"En aras de la seguridad, cerraron la carretera durante la tormenta.","en":"For the sake of safety, they closed the road during the storm."},{"es":"El gobierno redujo los impuestos en aras de estimular la economía local.","en":"The government lowered taxes for the sake of stimulating the local economy."},{"es":"Ella decidió perdonar a su hermano en aras de mantener la armonía familiar.","en":"She decided to forgive her brother for the sake of maintaining family harmony."}]},{"spanish_text":"De ahí que","english_text":"Hence","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"As a result; for that reason.","main_translations_es":["Por eso","Así que","De esa forma"],"collocations":["henceforth","hence the","hence we can","hence the result"],"synonyms_en":["Therefore","Thus","Consequently"],"example_sentence":"It was raining heavily, hence they cancelled the match.","example_es":"Estaba lloviendo mucho, de ahí que cancelaron el partido.","example_en":"It was raining heavily, hence they cancelled the match.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a hen seeing a clue, so from that (hence) you know the answer.","cloze_distractors_en":["Regardless","Nevertheless","Meanwhile","Otherwise"],"examples":[{"es":"Estaba lloviendo mucho, de ahí que cancelaron el partido.","en":"It was raining heavily, hence they cancelled the match."},{"es":"El candidato carecía de experiencia previa, de ahí que no lo contrataran para el puesto directivo.","en":"The candidate lacked previous experience, hence they did not hire him for the management position."},{"es":"La empresa ha registrado pérdidas millonarias este trimestre, de ahí que hayan decidido cerrar varias sucursales.","en":"The company has recorded million-dollar losses this quarter, hence they have decided to close several branches."}]},{"spanish_text":"Dado que","english_text":"Given that","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"conjunction","definition_en":"Considering that; used to introduce a reason or condition.","main_translations_es":["Considerando que","Puesto que","Ya que"],"collocations":["Given that you are here","Given that it''s raining","Given that we have no choice","Given that the data is correct"],"synonyms_en":["considering that","since","as"],"example_sentence":"Given that the budget has been cut, we must reduce travel expenses.","example_es":"Dado que el presupuesto ha sido recortado, debemos reducir los gastos de viaje.","example_en":"Given that the budget has been cut, we must reduce travel expenses.","mnemonic_en":"Picture giving a dice called dado to someone, so you’re given that.","cloze_distractors_en":["Regardless of","Contrary to","Provided that","In spite of"],"examples":[{"es":"Dado que el presupuesto ha sido recortado, debemos reducir los gastos de viaje.","en":"Given that the budget has been cut, we must reduce travel expenses."},{"es":"Dado que los resultados del experimento fueron concluyentes, el equipo decidió publicar el informe final.","en":"Given that the experiment results were conclusive, the team decided to publish the final report."},{"es":"Dado que no hay suficientes asientos en el auditorio, tendremos que transmitir la conferencia en línea.","en":"Given that there are not enough seats in the auditorium, we will have to stream the lecture online."}]},{"spanish_text":"Aunque","english_text":"Albeit","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"conjunction","definition_en":"It means ''although'' or ''even though''.","main_translations_es":["aunque","aun cuando","si bien"],"collocations":["albeit briefly","albeit unlikely","albeit not","albeit with reservations"],"synonyms_en":["although","even though","though"],"example_sentence":"The athlete finished the marathon, albeit visibly exhausted from the effort.","example_es":"El atleta terminó la maratón, aunque visiblemente agotado por el esfuerzo.","example_en":"The athlete finished the marathon, albeit visibly exhausted from the effort.","mnemonic_en":"Albeit sounds like Spanish aunque, picture a tiny al bridge letting a though pass.","cloze_distractors_en":["Moreover","Therefore","Likewise","Otherwise"],"examples":[{"es":"El atleta terminó la maratón, aunque visiblemente agotado por el esfuerzo.","en":"The athlete finished the marathon, albeit visibly exhausted from the effort."},{"es":"La reunión fue productiva, aunque un poco caótica.","en":"The meeting was productive, albeit a bit chaotic."},{"es":"El nuevo sistema es eficiente, aunque bastante costoso de implementar.","en":"The new system is efficient, albeit quite expensive to implement."}]},{"spanish_text":"Mientras que","english_text":"Whereas","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"conjunction","definition_en":"Used to introduce a contrast or comparison between two statements.","main_translations_es":["En cambio","A diferencia de","Mientras"],"collocations":["as opposed to","in contrast to","whereas the former","whereas the latter"],"synonyms_en":["while","although"],"example_sentence":"I prefer tea, whereas my brother prefers coffee.","example_es":"Yo prefiero el té, mientras que mi hermano prefiere el café.","example_en":"I prefer tea, whereas my brother prefers coffee.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a sign saying WHERE next to a WHILE (mientras) sign, showing contrast – that''s WHEREAS.","cloze_distractors_en":["Therefore","Moreover","Consequently","Furthermore"],"examples":[{"es":"Yo prefiero el té, mientras que mi hermano prefiere el café.","en":"I prefer tea, whereas my brother prefers coffee."},{"es":"El contrato estipula una jornada completa, mientras que el acuerdo verbal sugería un horario flexible.","en":"The contract stipulates a full-time schedule, whereas the verbal agreement suggested a flexible timetable."},{"es":"La empresa registró beneficios récord este trimestre, mientras que sus competidores directos sufrieron pérdidas significativas.","en":"The company reported record profits this quarter, whereas its direct competitors suffered significant losses."}]},{"spanish_text":"En cambio","english_text":"By contrast","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adverbial phrase","definition_en":"Used to introduce a statement that is different from or opposite to what has just been mentioned.","main_translations_es":["Por el contrario","En contraste","A diferencia"],"collocations":["by contrast, ...","by contrast with","by contrast to"],"synonyms_en":["in comparison","on the other hand","conversely"],"example_sentence":"Last summer was extremely hot; by contrast, this year the temperatures have been unusually cool.","example_es":"El verano pasado fue extremadamente caluroso; en cambio, este año las temperaturas han sido inusualmente frescas.","example_en":"Last summer was extremely hot; by contrast, this year the temperatures have been unusually cool.","mnemonic_en":"By contrast the picture flips like a cambio in a comic","cloze_distractors_en":["Furthermore","Consequently","Accordingly","Substantially"],"examples":[{"es":"El verano pasado fue extremadamente caluroso; en cambio, este año las temperaturas han sido inusualmente frescas.","en":"Last summer was extremely hot; by contrast, this year the temperatures have been unusually cool."},{"es":"La mayoría de los empleados optaron por trabajar desde casa; en cambio, ella prefirió seguir acudiendo a la oficina todos los días.","en":"Most employees opted to work from home; by contrast, she preferred to keep going into the office every day."},{"es":"El primer candidato presentó un plan de austeridad muy estricto; en cambio, su oponente propuso aumentar el gasto público para estimular la economía.","en":"The first candidate presented a very strict austerity plan; by contrast, his opponent proposed increasing public spending to stimulate the economy."}]},{"spanish_text":"Asimismo","english_text":"Likewise","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"In the same way or manner; similarly.","main_translations_es":["Igualmente","De igual manera","Del mismo modo"],"collocations":["Likewise, thank you","Likewise, I agree","Likewise, we will proceed","Likewise, the same applies"],"synonyms_en":["Similarly","In the same way","Also"],"example_sentence":"The study confirms that regular exercise reduces stress and, likewise, improves sleep quality.","example_es":"El estudio confirma que el ejercicio regular reduce el estrés y, asimismo, mejora la calidad del sueño.","example_en":"The study confirms that regular exercise reduces stress and, likewise, improves sleep quality.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a twin saying likewise, holding a banner that reads asimismo.","cloze_distractors_en":["Conversely","Regardless","Nevertheless"],"examples":[{"es":"El estudio confirma que el ejercicio regular reduce el estrés y, asimismo, mejora la calidad del sueño.","en":"The study confirms that regular exercise reduces stress and, likewise, improves sleep quality."},{"es":"El nuevo sistema mejora la seguridad de los datos y, asimismo, optimiza la velocidad de procesamiento del servidor.","en":"The new system improves data security and, likewise, optimizes the server''s processing speed."},{"es":"El candidato prometió reducir los impuestos y, asimismo, se comprometió a mejorar la infraestructura pública.","en":"The candidate promised to lower taxes and, likewise, pledged to improve public infrastructure."}]},{"spanish_text":"Por consiguiente","english_text":"Consequently","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"In a way that indicates a result or effect; therefore.","main_translations_es":["En consecuencia","Por lo tanto","Así que"],"collocations":["Consequently, the results were significant","Consequently, we decided to proceed","Consequently, the project was delayed"],"synonyms_en":["as a result","therefore","hence"],"example_sentence":"Consequently, the project was delayed by a week.","example_es":"Por consiguiente, el proyecto se retrasó una semana.","example_en":"Consequently, the project was delayed by a week.","mnemonic_en":"The word CONSEQUENTLY starts with cons-, reminding me of por consiguiente.","cloze_distractors_en":["Conversely","Simultaneously","Arbitrarily","Inadvertently"],"examples":[{"es":"Por consiguiente, el proyecto se retrasó una semana.","en":"Consequently, the project was delayed by a week."},{"es":"No hubo suficientes entradas vendidas; por consiguiente, el concierto fue cancelado.","en":"There were not enough tickets sold; consequently, the concert was cancelled."},{"es":"El atleta sufrió una lesión grave y, por consiguiente, no pudo participar en los Juegos Olímpicos.","en":"The athlete suffered a serious injury and, consequently, could not participate in the Olympic Games."}]},{"spanish_text":"No obstante","english_text":"Nevertheless","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"in spite of that; however","main_translations_es":["Sin embargo","Aun así","Con todo"],"collocations":["Nevertheless, ...","Nevertheless, we must","Nevertheless, it is","Nevertheless, she continued"],"synonyms_en":["however","still","nonetheless"],"example_sentence":"Nevertheless, he decided to continue with the project.","example_es":"No obstante, decidió continuar con el proyecto.","example_en":"Nevertheless, he decided to continue with the project.","mnemonic_en":"Picture no obst(acle) ahead, so you say nevertheless and keep moving forward.","cloze_distractors_en":["Consequently","Furthermore","Similarly","Undoubtedly"],"examples":[{"es":"No obstante, decidió continuar con el proyecto.","en":"Nevertheless, he decided to continue with the project."},{"es":"El pronóstico anunciaba tormentas fuertes; no obstante, el partido de fútbol se jugó según lo previsto.","en":"The forecast predicted heavy storms; nevertheless, the soccer match went ahead as scheduled."},{"es":"La empresa ha tenido pérdidas económicas este trimestre; no obstante, planean expandirse a nuevos mercados internacionales.","en":"The company has suffered financial losses this quarter; nevertheless, they plan to expand into new international markets."}]},{"spanish_text":"Aun así","english_text":"Even so","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Used to introduce a statement that contrasts with or qualifies what has just been said.","main_translations_es":["Sin embargo","No obstante","Aun así"],"collocations":["Even so, ...","Even so, he continued","Even so, the outcome changed","Even so, they agreed"],"synonyms_en":["Nevertheless","Nonetheless","Still"],"example_sentence":"Even so, he decided to go to the concert despite the rain.","example_es":"Aun así, decidió ir al concierto a pesar de la lluvia.","example_en":"Even so, he decided to go to the concert despite the rain.","mnemonic_en":"Visualize an even number holding a so sign, echoing aun así.","cloze_distractors_en":["Likewise","Moreover","Namely"],"examples":[{"es":"Aun así, decidió ir al concierto a pesar de la lluvia.","en":"Even so, he decided to go to the concert despite the rain."},{"es":"El proyecto tenía muchos errores técnicos; aun así, el equipo logró terminarlo a tiempo.","en":"The project had many technical flaws; even so, the team managed to finish it on time."},{"es":"Ella sabía que el examen sería extremadamente difícil, pero aun así estudió toda la noche.","en":"She knew the exam would be extremely difficult, but even so, she studied all night."}]},{"spanish_text":"Poner de relieve","english_text":"Highlight","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To emphasize or make something stand out.","main_translations_es":["Resaltar","Destacar","Subrayar"],"collocations":["highlight the main points","highlight a problem","highlight in yellow","highlight the differences"],"synonyms_en":["Emphasize","Feature","Underline"],"example_sentence":"The report serves to highlight the importance of early education.","example_es":"El informe pone de relieve la importancia de la educación temprana.","example_en":"The report serves to highlight the importance of early education.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a high lighthouse lighting a relief map, bringing the details into view.","cloze_distractors_en":["Fabricate","Exacerbate","Subjugate"],"examples":[{"es":"El informe pone de relieve la importancia de la educación temprana.","en":"The report serves to highlight the importance of early education."},{"es":"La investigación busca poner de relieve las discrepancias en los datos financieros del último trimestre.","en":"The investigation aims to highlight the discrepancies in the financial data from the last quarter."},{"es":"El uso de colores brillantes en el cartel ayuda a poner de relieve el mensaje principal de la campaña.","en":"The use of bright colors on the poster helps to highlight the main message of the campaign."}]},{"spanish_text":"Poner en tela de juicio","english_text":"Call into question","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"to express doubt about the truth or validity of something.","main_translations_es":["Cuestionar","Poner en duda","Poner en entredicho"],"collocations":["call into question the validity","call into question the results","call into question his motives","call into question the decision"],"synonyms_en":["question","doubt","challenge"],"example_sentence":"The committee decided to call into question the validity of the report.","example_es":"El comité decidió poner en tela de juicio la validez del informe.","example_en":"The committee decided to call into question the validity of the report.","mnemonic_en":"I call the judge, asking if his fabric is questionable.","cloze_distractors_en":["Bring to fruition","Carry out reform","Hold in contempt","Pass over lightly"],"examples":[{"es":"El comité decidió poner en tela de juicio la validez del informe.","en":"The committee decided to call into question the validity of the report."},{"es":"Los resultados inesperados del experimento obligaron a los científicos a poner en tela de juicio su hipótesis inicial.","en":"The unexpected results of the experiment forced the scientists to call into question their initial hypothesis."},{"es":"Su comportamiento errático durante la reunión hizo que todos empezaran a poner en tela de juicio su capacidad para liderar el proyecto.","en":"His erratic behavior during the meeting made everyone begin to call into question his ability to lead the project."}]},{"spanish_text":"Sacar provecho de","english_text":"Capitalize on","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to take advantage of something for one''s benefit","main_translations_es":["Aprovechar","Explotar","Beneficiarse de"],"collocations":["capitalize on opportunities","capitalize on trends","capitalize on the situation","capitalize on his strengths"],"synonyms_en":["take advantage of","exploit","leverage"],"example_sentence":"The company knew how to capitalize on the new regulations to cut its costs.","example_es":"La empresa supo sacar provecho de la nueva normativa para reducir sus costos.","example_en":"The company knew how to capitalize on the new regulations to cut its costs.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a cap pulling out (sacar) cash from a piggy bank, showing you capitalize on profit.","cloze_distractors_en":["Categorize by","Capitulate to","Capitalize in","Capsize under"],"examples":[{"es":"La empresa supo sacar provecho de la nueva normativa para reducir sus costos.","en":"The company knew how to capitalize on the new regulations to cut its costs."},{"es":"El tenista profesional logró sacar provecho de la lesión de su oponente para ganar el partido.","en":"The professional tennis player managed to capitalize on his opponent''s injury to win the match."},{"es":"Debemos sacar provecho de esta oportunidad única antes de que el mercado cambie por completo.","en":"We must capitalize on this unique opportunity before the market changes completely."}]},{"spanish_text":"Hacer frente a","english_text":"Cope with","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to deal effectively with something difficult or challenging","main_translations_es":["Enfrentar","Lidiar con","Hacer frente a"],"collocations":["cope with stress","cope with loss","cope with change","cope with difficulties"],"synonyms_en":["manage","deal with","handle"],"example_sentence":"It''s hard to cope with the loss of a loved one.","example_es":"Es difícil hacer frente a la pérdida de un ser querido.","example_en":"It''s hard to cope with the loss of a loved one.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a cup (copa) placed right in front (frente) of you to help you cope.","cloze_distractors_en":["Venerate with","Elucidate on","Fabricate for","Exacerbate in"],"examples":[{"es":"Es difícil hacer frente a la pérdida de un ser querido.","en":"It''s hard to cope with the loss of a loved one."},{"es":"Los empleados deben hacer frente a una carga de trabajo excesiva durante la temporada alta.","en":"Employees must cope with an excessive workload during the peak season."},{"es":"Ella aprendió a hacer frente a situaciones de estrés extremo manteniendo la calma.","en":"She learned to cope with extreme stress situations by staying calm."}]},{"spanish_text":"Asumir la responsabilidad","english_text":"Take responsibility","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To accept or assume accountability for something.","main_translations_es":["Asumir la responsabilidad","Hacerse cargo","Responsabilizarse"],"collocations":["take responsibility for","take responsibility seriously","take responsibility of","take responsibility and act"],"synonyms_en":["accept accountability","assume the blame","own up"],"example_sentence":"It is important to take responsibility for your actions.","example_es":"Es importante asumir la responsabilidad de tus actos.","example_en":"It is important to take responsibility for your actions.","mnemonic_en":"Take a taco and carry the huge RESPONSIBILITY banner, just like asumir la responsabilidad.","cloze_distractors_en":["Make contribution","Gain appreciation","Seek compensation"],"examples":[{"es":"Es importante asumir la responsabilidad de tus actos.","en":"It is important to take responsibility for your actions."},{"es":"Como gerente del proyecto, debes asumir la responsabilidad si el equipo no cumple con los plazos.","en":"As the project manager, you must take responsibility if the team misses the deadlines."},{"es":"El capitán decidió asumir la responsabilidad por el error de navegación que causó el accidente.","en":"The captain decided to take responsibility for the navigation error that caused the accident."}]},{"spanish_text":"Llegar a un acuerdo","english_text":"Reach an agreement","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To come to a mutual understanding or settlement.","main_translations_es":["Acuerdan","Llegar a un pacto","Cerrar un trato"],"collocations":["reach an agreement on","reach an agreement with","reach a final agreement","reach an agreement quickly"],"synonyms_en":["settle","come to terms","strike a deal"],"example_sentence":"After lengthy negotiations, we finally managed to reach an agreement.","example_es":"Después de largas negociaciones, finalmente logramos llegar a un acuerdo.","example_en":"After lengthy negotiations, we finally managed to reach an agreement.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a hand reaching to seal an accord, a firm handshake of agreement.","cloze_distractors_en":["Breach a monument","Preach a sentiment","Bleach a supplement","Teach a tournament"],"examples":[{"es":"Después de largas negociaciones, finalmente logramos llegar a un acuerdo.","en":"After lengthy negotiations, we finally managed to reach an agreement."},{"es":"Los sindicatos y la dirección se reunieron toda la noche para intentar llegar a un acuerdo sobre los nuevos salarios.","en":"The unions and management met all night to try to reach an agreement regarding the new wages."},{"es":"Si no conseguimos llegar a un acuerdo antes de la fecha límite, el proyecto será cancelado inmediatamente.","en":"If we fail to reach an agreement before the deadline, the project will be cancelled immediately."}]},{"spanish_text":"Tomar medidas","english_text":"Take action","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To do something in order to achieve a result.","main_translations_es":["Actuar","Emprender acciones","Hacer algo"],"collocations":["take action now","take action against","take decisive action","take action to"],"synonyms_en":["act","intervene","make a move"],"example_sentence":"It''s time to take action to reduce pollution.","example_es":"Es hora de tomar medidas para reducir la contaminación.","example_en":"It''s time to take action to reduce pollution.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a tomato measuring with a ruler, then taking action.","cloze_distractors_en":["Make mention","Give caution","Hold tension","Keep portion"],"examples":[{"es":"Es hora de tomar medidas para reducir la contaminación.","en":"It''s time to take action to reduce pollution."},{"es":"El gobierno decidió tomar medidas urgentes ante la crisis económica.","en":"The government decided to take action in response to the economic crisis."},{"es":"Debemos tomar medidas legales contra la empresa por incumplimiento de contrato.","en":"We must take action against the company for breach of contract."}]},{"spanish_text":"Dar prioridad a","english_text":"Prioritize","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To give priority to something, treating it as more important than other things.","main_translations_es":["Priorizar","Dar preferencia a","Poner en primer lugar"],"collocations":["prioritize tasks","prioritize safety","prioritize customer needs","prioritize the budget"],"synonyms_en":["give precedence to","rank","favor"],"example_sentence":"We must prioritize education in our budget.","example_es":"Debemos dar prioridad a la educación en nuestro presupuesto.","example_en":"We must prioritize education in our budget.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a PRIORITY stamp on a prize, showing you give it first place.","cloze_distractors_en":["Marginalize","Neutralize","Vandalize","Jeopardize"],"examples":[{"es":"Debemos dar prioridad a la educación en nuestro presupuesto.","en":"We must prioritize education in our budget."},{"es":"El equipo médico decidió dar prioridad a los pacientes con heridas más graves tras el accidente.","en":"The medical team decided to prioritize patients with the most severe injuries after the accident."},{"es":"Para cumplir con la fecha de entrega, el gerente nos pidió dar prioridad a las tareas más urgentes del proyecto.","en":"To meet the deadline, the manager asked us to prioritize the most urgent tasks of the project."}]},{"spanish_text":"Pasar por alto","english_text":"Overlook","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To fail to notice or consider something.","main_translations_es":["Ignorar","Desatender","Omitir"],"collocations":["overlook the details","overlook a mistake","overlook the fact"],"synonyms_en":["ignore","miss","disregard"],"example_sentence":"The editor decided to overlook the minor typo on the last page of the book.","example_es":"El editor decidió pasar por alto el pequeño error tipográfico en la última página del libro.","example_en":"The editor decided to overlook the minor typo on the last page of the book.","mnemonic_en":"I stand on a high overlook and watch a passing pasar train go by.","cloze_distractors_en":["Overhaul","Overstate","Overcome","Overrule"],"examples":[{"es":"El editor decidió pasar por alto el pequeño error tipográfico en la última página del libro.","en":"The editor decided to overlook the minor typo on the last page of the book."},{"es":"No puedes pasar por alto las señales de advertencia cuando el motor empieza a sobrecalentarse.","en":"You cannot overlook the warning signs when the engine starts to overheat."},{"es":"Es fácil pasar por alto los detalles importantes cuando estás bajo mucha presión en el trabajo.","en":"It is easy to overlook important details when you are under a lot of pressure at work."}]},{"spanish_text":"Contrarrestar","english_text":"Counteract","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To act against something in order to reduce or neutralize its effect.","main_translations_es":["neutralizar","compensar","mitigar"],"collocations":["counteract the effects","counteract the damage","counteract the influence"],"synonyms_en":["neutralize","offset","counterbalance"],"example_sentence":"The new drug helps to counteract the side effects of the treatment.","example_es":"El nuevo medicamento ayuda a contrarrestar los efectos secundarios del tratamiento.","example_en":"The new drug helps to counteract the side effects of the treatment.","mnemonic_en":"A counter acts against a spill, so it counteracts the mess.","cloze_distractors_en":["Aggravate","Fabricate","Infiltrate","Instigate"],"examples":[{"es":"El nuevo medicamento ayuda a contrarrestar los efectos secundarios del tratamiento.","en":"The new drug helps to counteract the side effects of the treatment."},{"es":"Es necesario implementar políticas fiscales para contrarrestar la inflación galopante en el país.","en":"It is necessary to implement fiscal policies to counteract the galloping inflation in the country."},{"es":"Los investigadores están buscando formas de contrarrestar el impacto negativo de la contaminación en los ecosistemas locales.","en":"Researchers are looking for ways to counteract the negative impact of pollution on local ecosystems."}]},{"spanish_text":"Reforzar","english_text":"Reinforce","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To strengthen or support something, often by adding material or effort.","main_translations_es":["Fortalecer","Consolidar","Robustecer"],"collocations":["reinforce the argument","reinforce the structure","reinforce security measures","reinforce the message"],"synonyms_en":["strengthen","bolster","support"],"example_sentence":"The coach decided to reinforce the team''s defense before the next match.","example_es":"El entrenador decidió reforzar la defensa del equipo antes del próximo partido.","example_en":"The coach decided to reinforce the team''s defense before the next match.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a REINFORCEing robot REINFORCING a wall, like a Spanish REFORZAR.","cloze_distractors_en":["Obliterate","Fabricate","Relegate","Exacerbate"],"examples":[{"es":"El entrenador decidió reforzar la defensa del equipo antes del próximo partido.","en":"The coach decided to reinforce the team''s defense before the next match."},{"es":"Es necesario reforzar los cimientos del edificio para que pueda soportar el peso de los nuevos pisos.","en":"It is necessary to reinforce the building''s foundations so it can support the weight of the new floors."},{"es":"El profesor utilizó ejemplos prácticos para reforzar los conceptos teóricos explicados en la clase de física.","en":"The teacher used practical examples to reinforce the theoretical concepts explained in the physics class."}]},{"spanish_text":"Debilitar","english_text":"Weaken","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To make something less strong, less effective, or less able to resist.","main_translations_es":["Atenuar","Mermar","Desgastar"],"collocations":["weaken the economy","weaken the argument","weaken the resolve"],"synonyms_en":["debilitate","diminish","undermine"],"example_sentence":"The intense cold began to weaken the garden''s plants.","example_es":"El frío intenso comenzó a debilitar las plantas del jardín.","example_en":"The intense cold began to weaken the garden''s plants.","mnemonic_en":"A weak rope debil snaps, making the bridge weaken","cloze_distractors_en":["Enrich","Fortify","Galvanize","Cultivate"],"examples":[{"es":"El frío intenso comenzó a debilitar las plantas del jardín.","en":"The intense cold began to weaken the garden''s plants."},{"es":"La falta de inversión constante terminará por debilitar la infraestructura del puente.","en":"The lack of constant investment will eventually weaken the bridge''s infrastructure."},{"es":"Los escándalos de corrupción suelen debilitar la confianza de los ciudadanos en sus líderes.","en":"Corruption scandals tend to weaken the citizens'' trust in their leaders."}]},{"spanish_text":"Desencadenar","english_text":"Trigger","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to cause something to happen or to start a process.","main_translations_es":["Provocar","Desatar","Iniciar"],"collocations":["trigger a reaction","trigger an alarm","trigger a response","trigger the event"],"synonyms_en":["activate","initiate","set off"],"example_sentence":"The discovery of the new particle could trigger a revolution in physics.","example_es":"El descubrimiento de la nueva partícula podría desencadenar una revolución en la física.","example_en":"The discovery of the new particle could trigger a revolution in physics.","mnemonic_en":"Pull the trigger and watch the chain snap, desencadenar the action.","cloze_distractors_en":["Submerge","Navigate","Obliterate","Consolidate"],"examples":[{"es":"El descubrimiento de la nueva partícula podría desencadenar una revolución en la física.","en":"The discovery of the new particle could trigger a revolution in physics."},{"es":"Un comentario desafortunado en la reunión fue suficiente para desencadenar una discusión acalorada entre los socios.","en":"An unfortunate comment at the meeting was enough to trigger a heated argument between the partners."},{"es":"Ciertos alérgenos en el aire pueden desencadenar un ataque de asma severo en pacientes sensibles.","en":"Certain allergens in the air can trigger a severe asthma attack in sensitive patients."}]},{"spanish_text":"Prever","english_text":"Anticipate","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To expect or look forward to something and act in advance based on that expectation.","main_translations_es":["predecir","anticipar","prever"],"collocations":["anticipate the outcome","anticipate a problem","anticipate the results","anticipate the future"],"synonyms_en":["expect","foresee","predict"],"example_sentence":"It''s important to anticipate problems before they happen.","example_es":"Es importante prever los problemas antes de que ocurran.","example_en":"It''s important to anticipate problems before they happen.","mnemonic_en":"I anticipate the test by pre-veer my study notes ahead","cloze_distractors_en":["Fabricate","Exacerbate","Resuscitate","Invalidate"],"examples":[{"es":"Es importante prever los problemas antes de que ocurran.","en":"It''s important to anticipate problems before they happen."},{"es":"El equipo debe prever un aumento en la demanda durante la temporada navideña.","en":"The team must anticipate an increase in demand during the holiday season."},{"es":"Los arquitectos lograron prever las dificultades estructurales del edificio mediante simulaciones digitales.","en":"The architects managed to anticipate the building''s structural difficulties through digital simulations."}]},{"spanish_text":"Logro","english_text":"Achievement","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A successful result or accomplishment that someone has attained.","main_translations_es":["Éxito","Triunfo","Conquista"],"collocations":["a great achievement","personal achievement","significant achievement","achievement unlocked"],"synonyms_en":["accomplishment","success","attainment"],"example_sentence":"This is my greatest achievement so far.","example_es":"Este es mi mayor logro hasta ahora.","example_en":"This is my greatest achievement so far.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a log rolling downhill, each roll marking an achievement.","cloze_distractors_en":["Abandonment","Adjustment","Endorsement","Detriment"],"examples":[{"es":"Este es mi mayor logro hasta ahora.","en":"This is my greatest achievement so far."},{"es":"Recibir el premio Nobel fue un logro impresionante para la científica.","en":"Receiving the Nobel Prize was an impressive achievement for the scientist."},{"es":"Completar el maratón después de meses de entrenamiento fue un logro personal muy satisfactorio.","en":"Completing the marathon after months of training was a very satisfying personal achievement."}]},{"spanish_text":"Retroceso","english_text":"Setback","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A reversal or hindrance that delays progress.","main_translations_es":["Retroceso","Reversión","Retrogradación"],"collocations":["a major setback","temporary setback","suffer a setback","setback in progress"],"synonyms_en":["obstacle","reversal","drawback"],"example_sentence":"The project suffered an unexpected setback after the loss of funding.","example_es":"El proyecto sufrió un retroceso inesperado después de la pérdida de financiación.","example_en":"The project suffered an unexpected setback after the loss of funding.","mnemonic_en":"When you set back a car, it rolls into a retroceso, a backward slip.","cloze_distractors_en":["Advantage","Pretext","Outburst"],"examples":[{"es":"El proyecto sufrió un retroceso inesperado después de la pérdida de financiación.","en":"The project suffered an unexpected setback after the loss of funding."},{"es":"A pesar de su recuperación inicial, el paciente tuvo un retroceso en su salud durante el fin de semana.","en":"Despite his initial recovery, the patient experienced a setback in his health over the weekend."},{"es":"La falta de comunicación entre los departamentos causó un retroceso significativo en el cronograma de entrega.","en":"The lack of communication between departments caused a significant setback in the delivery schedule."}]},{"spanish_text":"Aporte","english_text":"Contribution","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Something given or offered, especially to help achieve a common goal.","main_translations_es":["Contribución","Aportación","Colaboración"],"collocations":["make a contribution","significant contribution","financial contribution","contribute to the cause"],"synonyms_en":["donation","input","help"],"example_sentence":"His contribution to the project was essential for its success.","example_es":"Su aporte al proyecto fue fundamental para su éxito.","example_en":"His contribution to the project was essential for its success.","mnemonic_en":"A port unloads crates as an aporte, the contribution.","cloze_distractors_en":["Retraction","Distraction","Contraction","Extraction"],"examples":[{"es":"Su aporte al proyecto fue fundamental para su éxito.","en":"His contribution to the project was essential for its success."},{"es":"La organización agradeció el generoso aporte económico de los donantes durante la gala benéfica.","en":"The organization acknowledged the generous financial contribution from the donors during the charity gala."},{"es":"El científico realizó un aporte significativo al campo de la genética con su reciente investigación.","en":"The scientist made a significant contribution to the field of genetics with his recent research."}]},{"spanish_text":"Carencia","english_text":"Shortcoming","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A fault, deficiency, or lack of a desired quality.","main_translations_es":["Falta","Escasez","Déficit"],"collocations":["a shortcoming of","address the shortcoming","shortcoming in","the shortcoming is"],"synonyms_en":["deficiency","flaw","weakness"],"example_sentence":"His lack of experience was his greatest shortcoming.","example_es":"Su falta de experiencia fue su mayor carencia.","example_en":"His lack of experience was his greatest shortcoming.","mnemonic_en":"A shortcoming is a short car lacking its engine, just like a carencia, a lack.","cloze_distractors_en":["Advantage","Benchmark","Endeavor","Attribute"],"examples":[{"es":"Su falta de experiencia fue su mayor carencia.","en":"His lack of experience was his greatest shortcoming."},{"es":"El informe técnico destaca una grave carencia en los protocolos de seguridad de la empresa.","en":"The technical report highlights a serious shortcoming in the company''s security protocols."},{"es":"A pesar de su brillantez académica, su incapacidad para trabajar en equipo es una carencia importante.","en":"Despite his academic brilliance, his inability to work in a team is a major shortcoming."}]},{"spanish_text":"Aseveración","english_text":"Assertion","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A confident statement that something is true.","main_translations_es":["afirmación","declaración","aseguramiento"],"collocations":["make an assertion","assertion of fact","assertion of rights","assertion that"],"synonyms_en":["statement","claim","affirmation"],"example_sentence":"His assertion that the project would be finished on time turned out to be false.","example_es":"Su aseveración de que el proyecto terminaría a tiempo resultó ser falsa.","example_en":"His assertion that the project would be finished on time turned out to be false.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a lawyer shouting assertion while brandishing a giant Spanish aseveración banner.","cloze_distractors_en":["Refutation","Negation","Deviation","Inception"],"examples":[{"es":"Su aseveración de que el proyecto terminaría a tiempo resultó ser falsa.","en":"His assertion that the project would be finished on time turned out to be false."},{"es":"El testigo mantuvo su aseveración frente al juez a pesar de la presión de los abogados.","en":"The witness stood by his assertion in front of the judge despite the pressure from the lawyers."},{"es":"La científica presentó pruebas contundentes para respaldar su aseveración sobre el cambio climático.","en":"The scientist presented compelling evidence to support her assertion regarding climate change."}]},{"spanish_text":"Integridad","english_text":"Integrity","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the quality of being honest and having strong moral principles","main_translations_es":["Honestidad","Rectitud","Honradez"],"collocations":["maintain integrity","integrity and honesty","integrity of the data","integrity in the workplace"],"synonyms_en":["honesty","probity","uprightness"],"example_sentence":"The integrity of the data is essential for the system''s security.","example_es":"La integridad de los datos es fundamental para la seguridad del sistema.","example_en":"The integrity of the data is essential for the system''s security.","mnemonic_en":"Picture an integral ID badge glued together, never broken, embodying integridad.","cloze_distractors_en":["Intrigue","Inertia","Intimacy","Intensity"],"examples":[{"es":"La integridad de los datos es fundamental para la seguridad del sistema.","en":"The integrity of the data is essential for the system''s security."},{"es":"El juez fue elogiado por su integridad inquebrantable durante el juicio político.","en":"The judge was praised for his unwavering integrity during the impeachment trial."},{"es":"La integridad estructural del puente se vio comprometida tras el fuerte terremoto.","en":"The structural integrity of the bridge was compromised after the powerful earthquake."}]},{"spanish_text":"Fiabilidad","english_text":"Reliability","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The quality of being trustworthy and consistently performing as expected.","main_translations_es":["Confiabilidad","Seguridad","Estabilidad"],"collocations":["high reliability","reliability of the system","reliability engineering","test reliability"],"synonyms_en":["dependability","trustworthiness","consistency"],"example_sentence":"The reliability of this car is impressive.","example_es":"La fiabilidad de este coche es impresionante.","example_en":"The reliability of this car is impressive.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a reliable robot you can rely on, just as a ''fiable'' person never lets you down.","cloze_distractors_en":["Reluctancy","Repulsivity","Reactivity"],"examples":[{"es":"La fiabilidad de este coche es impresionante.","en":"The reliability of this car is impressive."},{"es":"El ingeniero cuestionó la fiabilidad de los datos obtenidos en el experimento.","en":"The engineer questioned the reliability of the data obtained in the experiment."},{"es":"La empresa busca mejorar la fiabilidad de su red eléctrica ante tormentas severas.","en":"The company seeks to improve the reliability of its power grid in the face of severe storms."}]},{"spanish_text":"Rendición de cuentas","english_text":"Accountability","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The obligation to accept responsibility for one''s actions and decisions.","main_translations_es":["Responsabilidad","Justificación","Transparencia"],"collocations":["accountability measures","accountability framework","hold someone accountable","accountability standards"],"synonyms_en":["responsibility","answerability","liability"],"example_sentence":"Accountability is essential for transparency in government.","example_es":"La rendición de cuentas es esencial para la transparencia en el gobierno.","example_en":"Accountability is essential for transparency in government.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a giant accountant with a super‑power to answer every ''cuenta''—that''s accountability.","cloze_distractors_en":["Adaptability","Availability","Reliability"],"examples":[{"es":"La rendición de cuentas es esencial para la transparencia en el gobierno.","en":"Accountability is essential for transparency in government."},{"es":"El director implementó un nuevo sistema de rendición de cuentas para medir el desempeño de los empleados.","en":"The director implemented a new system of accountability to measure employee performance."},{"es":"La organización exige una mayor rendición de cuentas sobre cómo se gastan los fondos de la caridad.","en":"The organization demands greater accountability regarding how charity funds are spent."}]},{"spanish_text":"Transparencia","english_text":"Transparency","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The quality of being clear, open, and easily understood, or the condition of allowing light to pass through so that objects behind can be seen.","main_translations_es":["Claridad","Visibilidad","Nítido"],"collocations":["transparency in government","financial transparency","transparency and accountability","transparent communication"],"synonyms_en":["openness","clarity","candor"],"example_sentence":"Transparency in government is essential for citizens'' trust.","example_es":"La transparencia en el gobierno es esencial para la confianza de los ciudadanos.","example_en":"Transparency in government is essential for citizens'' trust.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a transparent sea where you can see every fish, just like the word transparencia.","cloze_distractors_en":["Opacity","Ambiguity","Volatility","Inertia"],"examples":[{"es":"La transparencia en el gobierno es esencial para la confianza de los ciudadanos.","en":"Transparency in government is essential for citizens'' trust."},{"es":"La empresa implementó nuevas políticas de transparencia para evitar conflictos de intereses entre sus ejecutivos.","en":"The company implemented new policies of transparency to avoid conflicts of interest among its executives."},{"es":"El cristal de la ventana ofrece una transparencia perfecta que permite ver el paisaje sin ninguna distorsión.","en":"The window glass offers perfect transparency that allows you to see the landscape without any distortion."}]},{"spanish_text":"Imparcial","english_text":"Impartial","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Not favoring one side over another; unbiased.","main_translations_es":["Objetivo","Neutral","Sin sesgo"],"collocations":["impartial judge","impartial decision","impartial opinion","impartial observer"],"synonyms_en":["unbiased","neutral","objective"],"example_sentence":"The judge must be impartial when delivering his verdict.","example_es":"El juez debe ser imparcial al dictar su veredicto.","example_en":"The judge must be impartial when delivering his verdict.","mnemonic_en":"Picture an impartial judge, his scales perfectly balanced, echoing the Spanish imparcial.","cloze_distractors_en":["Impetuous","Imperious","Imprudent"],"examples":[{"es":"El juez debe ser imparcial al dictar su veredicto.","en":"The judge must be impartial when delivering his verdict."},{"es":"El comité de selección prometió mantener una postura imparcial durante las entrevistas de trabajo.","en":"The selection committee promised to maintain an impartial stance during the job interviews."},{"es":"Necesitamos un mediador imparcial para resolver este conflicto laboral sin favorecer a ninguna de las partes.","en":"We need an impartial mediator to resolve this labor dispute without favoring either side."}]},{"spanish_text":"Parcial","english_text":"Biased","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Showing an unfair preference or prejudice toward something or someone.","main_translations_es":["Sesgado","Tendencioso","Parcial"],"collocations":["biased opinion","biased view","biased towards","biased against"],"synonyms_en":["partial","prejudiced","one-sided"],"example_sentence":"The judge was biased in his decision.","example_es":"El juez fue parcial en su decisión.","example_en":"The judge was biased in his decision.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a biased judge who only counts the parcial scores, ignoring the rest.","cloze_distractors_en":["Voluminous","Innocuous","Facetious"],"examples":[{"es":"El juez fue parcial en su decisión.","en":"The judge was biased in his decision."},{"es":"Es imposible escribir un artículo periodístico que no sea parcial sobre este tema tan controvertido.","en":"It is impossible to write a journalistic article that is not biased regarding such a controversial topic."},{"es":"Los resultados del estudio fueron parciales debido a que solo entrevistaron a personas de un mismo grupo social.","en":"The study results were biased because they only interviewed people from the same social group."}]},{"spanish_text":"Rigurosidad","english_text":"Rigor","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"strictness or exactness in standards, procedures, or conduct","main_translations_es":["rigor","exigencia","precisión"],"collocations":["scientific rigor","rigor of the law","rigor in methodology"],"synonyms_en":["strictness","severity","exactness"],"example_sentence":"The scientist analyzed the data with the utmost rigor to ensure the results were irrefutable.","example_es":"El científico analizó los datos con la máxima rigurosidad para asegurar que los resultados fueran irrefutables.","example_en":"The scientist analyzed the data with the utmost rigor to ensure the results were irrefutable.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a strict foreman on a construction rig, his rigor forcing every bolt to fit perfectly.","cloze_distractors_en":["Levity","Frivolity","Laxity"],"examples":[{"es":"El científico analizó los datos con la máxima rigurosidad para asegurar que los resultados fueran irrefutables.","en":"The scientist analyzed the data with the utmost rigor to ensure the results were irrefutable."},{"es":"La rigurosidad académica exigida en este programa de doctorado es conocida por ser extremadamente desafiante.","en":"The academic rigor required in this doctoral program is known to be extremely challenging."},{"es":"El arquitecto revisó los planos estructurales con gran rigurosidad antes de comenzar la construcción del rascacielos.","en":"The architect reviewed the structural blueprints with great rigor before starting the construction of the skyscraper."}]},{"spanish_text":"Coexistir","english_text":"Coexist","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To exist together at the same time or in the same place.","main_translations_es":["convivir","cohabitar","coexistir"],"collocations":["coexist peacefully","coexist with","coexist in harmony","coexist side by side"],"synonyms_en":["live together","share space","cohabit"],"example_sentence":"The different cultural groups must learn to coexist in harmony.","example_es":"Los diferentes grupos culturales deben aprender a coexistir en armonía.","example_en":"The different cultural groups must learn to coexist in harmony.","mnemonic_en":"Think of a cow and a snail coexisting on a sunny meadow","cloze_distractors_en":["Submerge","Exacerbate","Obliterate","Fabricate"],"examples":[{"es":"Los diferentes grupos culturales deben aprender a coexistir en armonía.","en":"The different cultural groups must learn to coexist in harmony."},{"es":"Es un reto biológico que los depredadores y sus presas logren coexistir en el mismo ecosistema.","en":"It is a biological challenge for predators and their prey to coexist in the same ecosystem."},{"es":"Las nuevas tecnologías digitales y los métodos tradicionales de enseñanza pueden coexistir eficazmente en el aula moderna.","en":"New digital technologies and traditional teaching methods can coexist effectively in the modern classroom."}]},{"spanish_text":"Conciliar","english_text":"Reconcile","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To restore harmony between parties or to make different ideas consistent.","main_translations_es":["reconciliar","armonizar","comprometer"],"collocations":["reconcile differences","reconcile accounts","reconcile with","reconcile the data"],"synonyms_en":["settle","make up","harmonize"],"example_sentence":"The mediator managed to reconcile the two parties in conflict.","example_es":"El mediador logró conciliar a las dos partes en conflicto.","example_en":"The mediator managed to reconcile the two parties in conflict.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a RECONciling bridge where two sides CONCILIAte to become one.","cloze_distractors_en":["Fabricate","Exacerbate","Liquidate","Elucidate"],"examples":[{"es":"El mediador logró conciliar a las dos partes en conflicto.","en":"The mediator managed to reconcile the two parties in conflict."},{"es":"Es difícil conciliar las exigencias de su carrera profesional con las necesidades de su vida familiar.","en":"It is difficult to reconcile the demands of his professional career with the needs of his family life."},{"es":"El contable tuvo que conciliar los extractos bancarios con los registros de gastos de la empresa.","en":"The accountant had to reconcile the bank statements with the company''s expense records."}]},{"spanish_text":"Desplegar","english_text":"Deploy","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To position or arrange resources, personnel, or equipment for use, especially in a strategic or operational context.","main_translations_es":["Implementar","Instalar","Poner en marcha"],"collocations":["deploy a new version","deploy troops","deploy resources","deploy the application"],"synonyms_en":["launch","position","set up"],"example_sentence":"The team decided to deploy the new update tomorrow.","example_es":"El equipo decidió desplegar la nueva actualización mañana.","example_en":"The team decided to deploy the new update tomorrow.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a crew de-ploy a ship, like the Spanish desplegar a sail.","cloze_distractors_en":["Concoct","Distort","Extract","Abduct"],"examples":[{"es":"El equipo decidió desplegar la nueva actualización mañana.","en":"The team decided to deploy the new update tomorrow."},{"es":"El ejército tuvo que desplegar tropas adicionales para asegurar la frontera.","en":"The army had to deploy additional troops to secure the border."},{"es":"La empresa planea desplegar una red de sensores inteligentes por toda la ciudad.","en":"The company plans to deploy a network of smart sensors throughout the city."}]},{"spanish_text":"Aprovechar","english_text":"Harness","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To control and use something, especially a resource or energy, for a specific purpose.","main_translations_es":["Utilizar","Explotar","Sacar provecho"],"collocations":["harness the power","harness potential","harness energy","harness resources"],"synonyms_en":["utilize","exploit","apply"],"example_sentence":"We must harness the available resources to the fullest.","example_es":"Debemos aprovechar al máximo los recursos disponibles.","example_en":"We must harness the available resources to the fullest.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a horse in a harness, ready to aprovechar the wind like a captured power","cloze_distractors_en":["Hamper","Hasten","Harrow","Hallow"],"examples":[{"es":"Debemos aprovechar al máximo los recursos disponibles.","en":"We must harness the available resources to the fullest."},{"es":"Los ingenieros buscan formas de aprovechar la energía de las mareas para generar electricidad.","en":"Engineers are looking for ways to harness tidal energy to generate electricity."},{"es":"El equipo logró aprovechar su creatividad colectiva para resolver el problema técnico en tiempo récord.","en":"The team managed to harness their collective creativity to solve the technical problem in record time."}]},{"spanish_text":"Percepción","english_text":"Perception","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The process of recognizing, interpreting, and organizing sensory information.","main_translations_es":["Percepción","Sensación","Observación"],"collocations":["public perception","perception of reality","visual perception"],"synonyms_en":["awareness","recognition","sensation"],"example_sentence":"His perception of the problem changed after hearing the data.","example_es":"Su percepción del problema cambió después de escuchar los datos.","example_en":"His perception of the problem changed after hearing the data.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a pear (pera) in a cage, you get the perception of its shape.","cloze_distractors_en":["Protrusion","Retention","Incursion","Excursion"],"examples":[{"es":"Su percepción del problema cambió después de escuchar los datos.","en":"His perception of the problem changed after hearing the data."},{"es":"La percepción pública de la marca se vio afectada negativamente por el escándalo financiero.","en":"The public perception of the brand was negatively affected by the financial scandal."},{"es":"El artista juega con la percepción visual mediante el uso de sombras y ángulos imposibles.","en":"The artist plays with visual perception through the use of shadows and impossible angles."}]},{"spanish_text":"Tendencia","english_text":"Trend","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A general direction in which something is developing or changing.","main_translations_es":["Moda","Corriente","Dirección"],"collocations":["upward trend","trend towards","trend analysis","trend line"],"synonyms_en":["fashion","tendency","movement"],"example_sentence":"The current trend is to work from home.","example_es":"La tendencia actual es trabajar desde casa.","example_en":"The current trend is to work from home.","mnemonic_en":"A new trend makes everyone tend to the same style","cloze_distractors_en":["Stance","Clause","Brink","Scope"],"examples":[{"es":"La tendencia actual es trabajar desde casa.","en":"The current trend is to work from home."},{"es":"Los analistas observan una tendencia al alza en el precio de las acciones tecnológicas.","en":"Analysts are observing an upward trend in the price of technology stocks."},{"es":"La moda juvenil sigue una tendencia marcada por la sostenibilidad y el reciclaje.","en":"Youth fashion is following a trend marked by sustainability and recycling."}]},{"spanish_text":"Repercusiones","english_text":"Repercussions","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the unintended or indirect consequences of an action or event, especially negative ones","main_translations_es":["Consecuencias","Efectos","Secuelas"],"collocations":["face the repercussions","have serious repercussions","the repercussions were felt","repercussions of the decision"],"synonyms_en":["consequences","effects","ramifications"],"example_sentence":"The repercussions of the decision were unexpected.","example_es":"Las repercusiones de la decisión fueron inesperadas.","example_en":"The repercussions of the decision were unexpected.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a drum''s re-percussion sending waves that look like the Spanish word repercusiones.","cloze_distractors_en":["Resonances","Refractions","Reiterations","Reciprocals"],"examples":[{"es":"Las repercusiones de la decisión fueron inesperadas.","en":"The repercussions of the decision were unexpected."},{"es":"El escándalo político tuvo graves repercusiones en la popularidad del gobierno.","en":"The political scandal had serious repercussions for the government''s popularity."},{"es":"Debes considerar las posibles repercusiones legales antes de firmar ese contrato.","en":"You must consider the potential legal repercussions before signing that contract."}]},{"spanish_text":"Plausible","english_text":"Plausible","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Reasonable or probable; appearing worthy of belief.","main_translations_es":["verosímil","creíble","probable"],"collocations":["plausible explanation","plausible deniability","plausible scenario","plausible argument"],"synonyms_en":[],"example_sentence":"It is plausible that we will arrive on time.","example_es":"Es plausible que lleguemos a tiempo.","example_en":"It is plausible that we will arrive on time.","mnemonic_en":null,"cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Es plausible que lleguemos a tiempo.","en":"It is plausible that we will arrive on time."}]},{"spanish_text":"Inevitable","english_text":"Inevitable","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Impossible to avoid or prevent; certain to happen.","main_translations_es":["inevitable","inexorable","ineludible"],"collocations":["inevitable outcome","inevitable consequence","inevitable result"],"synonyms_en":[],"example_sentence":"It was inevitable that the project would fail.","example_es":"Era inevitable que el proyecto fracasara.","example_en":"It was inevitable that the project would fail.","mnemonic_en":null,"cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Era inevitable que el proyecto fracasara.","en":"It was inevitable that the project would fail."}]},{"spanish_text":"Rentable","english_text":"Cost-effective","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Providing good value or results relative to the amount spent.","main_translations_es":["económico","asequible","de bajo costo"],"collocations":["cost-effective solution","cost-effective strategy","cost-effective approach","cost-effective measure"],"synonyms_en":["economical","budget-friendly","money-saving"],"example_sentence":"Investing in solar panels is highly cost-effective in the long run for reducing electricity bills.","example_es":"Invertir en paneles solares resulta muy rentable a largo plazo para reducir la factura eléctrica.","example_en":"Investing in solar panels is highly cost-effective in the long run for reducing electricity bills.","mnemonic_en":"A cost-effective deal feels as rentable as a cheap apartment you can rent.","cloze_distractors_en":["Cost-prohibitive","Cost-intensive","Cost-exclusive"],"examples":[{"es":"Invertir en paneles solares resulta muy rentable a largo plazo para reducir la factura eléctrica.","en":"Investing in solar panels is highly cost-effective in the long run for reducing electricity bills."},{"es":"La gerencia decidió externalizar el servicio de atención al cliente porque es más rentable que mantener un equipo interno.","en":"Management decided to outsource customer support because it is more cost-effective than maintaining an in-house team."},{"es":"El uso de materiales reciclados en la producción ha demostrado ser una estrategia rentable para la fábrica.","en":"Using recycled materials in production has proven to be a cost-effective strategy for the factory."}]},{"spanish_text":"Práctica arraigada","english_text":"Entrenched practice","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"A practice that is firmly established and difficult to change.","main_translations_es":["costumbre arraigada","práctica consolidada","hábito profundo"],"collocations":["deeply entrenched practice","long‑standing entrenched practice","entrenched practice of","entrenched practice in"],"synonyms_en":["established custom","deep‑rooted habit","ingrained tradition"],"example_sentence":"The entrenched practice of using fossil fuels is the main obstacle to meeting global climate goals.","example_es":"La práctica arraigada de utilizar combustibles fósiles es el principal obstáculo para alcanzar los objetivos climáticos globales.","example_en":"The entrenched practice of using fossil fuels is the main obstacle to meeting global climate goals.","mnemonic_en":"A train (en tren) plants roots into a practice, making it entrenched.","cloze_distractors_en":["Ephemeral whim","Superficial nuance","Spontaneous impulse","Negligible oversight"],"examples":[{"es":"La práctica arraigada de utilizar combustibles fósiles es el principal obstáculo para alcanzar los objetivos climáticos globales.","en":"The entrenched practice of using fossil fuels is the main obstacle to meeting global climate goals."},{"es":"Es difícil reformar el sistema educativo debido a la práctica arraigada de priorizar la memorización sobre el pensamiento crítico.","en":"It is difficult to reform the education system due to the entrenched practice of prioritizing rote memorization over critical thinking."},{"es":"La empresa lucha por modernizarse porque los empleados veteranos se aferran a la práctica arraigada de gestionar los archivos en papel.","en":"The company struggles to modernize because veteran employees cling to the entrenched practice of managing files on paper."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cumplir con las expectativas","english_text":"Meet expectations","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To fulfill or satisfy the standards or requirements that are anticipated.","main_translations_es":["Estar a la altura de las expectativas","Satisfacer las expectativas","Cumplir las expectativas"],"collocations":["meet expectations","live up to expectations","exceed expectations","fall short of expectations"],"synonyms_en":["fulfill expectations","live up to expectations","satisfy expectations"],"example_sentence":"The new employee managed to meet expectations of the company from his first day.","example_es":"El nuevo empleado logró cumplir con las expectativas de la empresa desde su primer día.","example_en":"The new employee managed to meet expectations of the company from his first day.","mnemonic_en":"In a meeting, a perfect cake fulfills everyone''s expectations.","cloze_distractors_en":["Exceed boundaries","Avoid obligations","Dismiss allegations","Neglect reputations"],"examples":[{"es":"El nuevo empleado logró cumplir con las expectativas de la empresa desde su primer día.","en":"The new employee managed to meet expectations of the company from his first day."},{"es":"Si el proyecto no logra cumplir con las expectativas del cliente, perderemos el contrato principal.","en":"If the project fails to meet expectations of the client, we will lose the main contract."},{"es":"El nuevo restaurante de lujo no logró cumplir con las expectativas de los críticos gastronómicos tras su inauguración.","en":"The new luxury restaurant failed to meet expectations of the food critics following its grand opening."}]},{"spanish_text":"Superar las expectativas","english_text":"Exceed expectations","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To go beyond what is expected.","main_translations_es":["Ir más allá de lo esperado","Superar lo esperado","Sobrepasar las expectativas"],"collocations":["exceed expectations","exceed expectations by","exceed expectations consistently","exceed expectations in performance"],"synonyms_en":["surpass expectations","go beyond expectations","outperform expectations"],"example_sentence":"Our team managed to exceed expectations with the final project.","example_es":"Nuestro equipo logró superar las expectativas del cliente con el proyecto final.","example_en":"Our team managed to exceed expectations with the final project.","mnemonic_en":"A superhero leaps over a bar, exceeding expectations.","cloze_distractors_en":["Dismiss allegations","Incur liabilities","Evade responsibilities","Renounce affiliations"],"examples":[{"es":"Nuestro equipo logró superar las expectativas del cliente con el proyecto final.","en":"Our team managed to exceed expectations with the final project."},{"es":"El joven chef trabajó incansablemente para superar las expectativas de los críticos gastronómicos más exigentes.","en":"The young chef worked tirelessly to exceed expectations of the most demanding food critics."},{"es":"Si quieres un ascenso este año, debes esforzarte al máximo y superar las expectativas de tu jefe en cada tarea.","en":"If you want a promotion this year, you must work your hardest and exceed expectations on every task."}]}]'::jsonb) as x(
  spanish_text text, english_text text, section_name text, part_of_speech text, definition_en text,
  main_translations_es jsonb, collocations jsonb, synonyms_en jsonb, example_sentence text, example_es text, example_en text, mnemonic_en text, cloze_distractors_en jsonb, examples jsonb
)
where c.deck_id = dk.id
  and lower(c.spanish_text) = lower(x.spanish_text)
  and lower(c.english_text) = lower(x.english_text);

-- english-workplace-communication (121 cards)
update public.decks set
  title = 'Workplace Communication', description = 'Advanced vocabulary and expressions for meetings, projects, collaboration, and professional communication.',
  language_from = 'es', language_to = 'en'
where slug = 'english-workplace-communication';

update public.cards c set
  section_name = x.section_name, part_of_speech = x.part_of_speech, definition_en = x.definition_en,
  main_translations_es = coalesce(x.main_translations_es, '[]'::jsonb),
  collocations = coalesce(x.collocations, '[]'::jsonb),
  synonyms_en = coalesce(x.synonyms_en, '[]'::jsonb),
  example_sentence = x.example_sentence, example_es = x.example_es, example_en = x.example_en,
  mnemonic_en = coalesce(x.mnemonic_en, c.mnemonic_en),
  cloze_distractors_en = case when jsonb_array_length(coalesce(x.cloze_distractors_en, '[]'::jsonb)) > 0
                              then x.cloze_distractors_en else c.cloze_distractors_en end,
  examples = case when jsonb_array_length(coalesce(x.examples, '[]'::jsonb)) > 0
                  then x.examples else c.examples end
from (select id from public.decks where slug = 'english-workplace-communication') dk
cross join jsonb_to_recordset('[{"spanish_text":"Correo electrónico","english_text":"Email","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A system for sending digital messages electronically over the internet.","main_translations_es":["e‑mail","correo","mail"],"collocations":["send an email","check your email","email address","email inbox"],"synonyms_en":["electronic mail","e‑mail","mail"],"example_sentence":"I sent you an email yesterday.","example_es":"Te envié un correo electrónico ayer.","example_en":"I sent you an email yesterday.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine an email as a tiny electronic courier delivering a letter, like correo electrónico.","cloze_distractors_en":["Keyboard","Hardware","Database"],"examples":[{"es":"Te envié un correo electrónico ayer.","en":"I sent you an email yesterday."},{"es":"Por favor, confirma la recepción de este correo electrónico antes de la reunión.","en":"Please confirm receipt of this email before the meeting."},{"es":"Revisa tu correo electrónico para ver los detalles del nuevo proyecto.","en":"Check your email to see the details of the new project."}]},{"spanish_text":"Asunto","english_text":"Subject line","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"The line of text that identifies the topic of an email or message.","main_translations_es":["Tema","Motivo","Cuestión"],"collocations":["write a compelling subject line","optimize the subject line","subject line testing","subject line preview"],"synonyms_en":["email subject","message title","mail header"],"example_sentence":"Please make sure the subject line is clear before you send the email.","example_es":"Por favor, asegúrate de que el asunto sea claro antes de enviar el correo electrónico.","example_en":"Please make sure the subject line is clear before you send the email.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine the subject line as a banner that shouts the email''s asunto—the topic—like a billboard.","cloze_distractors_en":["Office supply","Carbon copy","Project status"],"examples":[{"es":"Por favor, asegúrate de que el asunto sea claro antes de enviar el correo electrónico.","en":"Please make sure the subject line is clear before you send the email."},{"es":"No pude encontrar el mensaje porque el asunto estaba vacío.","en":"I could not find the message because the subject line was empty."},{"es":"El cliente se quejó de que nuestro asunto no explicaba el propósito de la propuesta.","en":"The client complained that our subject line did not explain the purpose of the proposal."}]},{"spanish_text":"Adjunto","english_text":"Attachment","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A supplementary item, such as a file or document, that is attached to a message or object.","main_translations_es":["Adjunto","Anexo","Archivo adjunto"],"collocations":["email attachment","attachment size","attachment file","attachment icon"],"synonyms_en":["enclosure","appendix","addendum"],"example_sentence":"Please find the attachment with the report you requested.","example_es":"Adjunto el informe que solicitaste.","example_en":"Please find the attachment with the report you requested.","mnemonic_en":"Picture an adjunct clerk attaching a file, hearing Adjunto as the word for attachment.","cloze_distractors_en":["Assumption","Connection","Definition"],"examples":[{"es":"Adjunto el informe que solicitaste.","en":"Please find the attachment with the report you requested."},{"es":"Por favor, revisa el adjunto que envié en el correo electrónico anterior.","en":"Please review the attachment I sent in the previous email."},{"es":"No puedo abrir el adjunto porque el archivo parece estar dañado.","en":"I cannot open the attachment because the file appears to be corrupted."}]},{"spanish_text":"Reenviar","english_text":"Forward","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To send something on to another recipient.","main_translations_es":["Remitir","Enviar de nuevo","Reexpedir"],"collocations":["move forward","look forward to","forward slash","forward thinking"],"synonyms_en":["send ahead","advance","propel"],"example_sentence":"Can you forward the email to all team members?","example_es":"¿Puedes reenviar el correo a todos los miembros del equipo?","example_en":"Can you forward the email to all team members?","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a forward arrow re‑en‑vire (rain) sending the mail ahead.","cloze_distractors_en":["Delete","Cancel","Archive","Shred"],"examples":[{"es":"¿Puedes reenviar el correo a todos los miembros del equipo?","en":"Can you forward the email to all team members?"},{"es":"Por favor, reenvía este mensaje al cliente antes de las cinco.","en":"Please forward this message to the client before five."},{"es":"Voy a reenviar la agenda de la reunión a los nuevos empleados.","en":"I will forward the meeting agenda to the new employees."}]},{"spanish_text":"Responder a todos","english_text":"Reply all","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"Send a response to all recipients of an email.","main_translations_es":["Responder a todos","Responder a todos los destinatarios","Responder a todos los correos"],"collocations":["click Reply All","use Reply All","select Reply All","press Reply All"],"synonyms_en":["respond to all","reply to everyone","send to all"],"example_sentence":"Remember to reply all to the group''s messages.","example_es":"Recuerda responder a todos los mensajes del grupo.","example_en":"Remember to reply all to the group''s messages.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a pie being sent to all the guests as a reply","cloze_distractors_en":["Delete draft","Ignore sender","Filter inbox"],"examples":[{"es":"Recuerda responder a todos los mensajes del grupo.","en":"Remember to reply all to the group''s messages."},{"es":"Por favor, no olvides responder a todos cuando confirmes la fecha de la reunión.","en":"Please do not forget to reply all when you confirm the meeting date."},{"es":"Si la información es relevante para el equipo, asegúrate de responder a todos.","en":"If the information is relevant to the team, make sure to reply all."}]},{"spanish_text":"Seguimiento","english_text":"Follow-up","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"An action taken to continue or check the progress of something previously started.","main_translations_es":["Control","Monitoreo","Seguimiento"],"collocations":["follow-up email","follow-up meeting","follow-up call","follow-up action"],"synonyms_en":["check‑in","subsequent action","continuation"],"example_sentence":"I will do a follow-up on the project next week.","example_es":"Haré un seguimiento del proyecto la próxima semana.","example_en":"I will do a follow-up on the project next week.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a detective following a trail, a follow‑up like a seguimiento of clues.","cloze_distractors_en":["Back-pedal","Side-step","Break-even","Show-down"],"examples":[{"es":"Haré un seguimiento del proyecto la próxima semana.","en":"I will do a follow-up on the project next week."},{"es":"Por favor, envíame un seguimiento por correo electrónico después de la reunión.","en":"Please send me a follow-up by email after the meeting."},{"es":"El cliente espera un seguimiento detallado sobre los problemas técnicos reportados.","en":"The client expects a detailed follow-up regarding the reported technical issues."}]},{"spanish_text":"Programar una reunión","english_text":"Schedule a meeting","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To arrange a time for a meeting.","main_translations_es":["Organizar una reunión","Concertar una reunión","Fijar una reunión"],"collocations":["schedule a meeting with","schedule a meeting for","schedule a meeting next week","schedule a meeting at"],"synonyms_en":["arrange a meeting","set up a meeting","plan a meeting"],"example_sentence":"I have to schedule a meeting with the client tomorrow.","example_es":"Tengo que programar una reunión con el cliente mañana.","example_en":"I have to schedule a meeting with the client tomorrow.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a sked where a reunion (reunión) takes place.","cloze_distractors_en":["Fabricate a report","Terminate a colleague","Investigate a rumor"],"examples":[{"es":"Tengo que programar una reunión con el cliente mañana.","en":"I have to schedule a meeting with the client tomorrow."},{"es":"Podrías programar una reunión para discutir los detalles del nuevo proyecto?","en":"Could you schedule a meeting to discuss the details of the new project?"},{"es":"El gerente pidió programar una reunión urgente para revisar el presupuesto.","en":"The manager asked to schedule a meeting to review the budget."}]},{"spanish_text":"Aplazar","english_text":"Postpone","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To delay or put off something to a later time.","main_translations_es":["Posponer","Diferir","Atrasar"],"collocations":["postpone the meeting","postpone the deadline","postpone the launch","postpone the decision"],"synonyms_en":["delay","defer","put off"],"example_sentence":"We decided to postpone the meeting until next week.","example_es":"Decidimos aplazar la reunión para la próxima semana.","example_en":"We decided to postpone the meeting until next week.","mnemonic_en":"I post a plaque that says Aplazar to delay the meeting.","cloze_distractors_en":["Accelerate","Fabricate","Inaugurate"],"examples":[{"es":"Decidimos aplazar la reunión para la próxima semana.","en":"We decided to postpone the meeting until next week."},{"es":"Debido a la falta de presupuesto, tuvimos que aplazar el lanzamiento del proyecto.","en":"Due to the lack of budget, we had to postpone the project launch."},{"es":"El gerente prefirió aplazar la fecha de entrega para asegurar la calidad del trabajo.","en":"The manager preferred to postpone the delivery date to ensure the quality of the work."}]},{"spanish_text":"Reprogramar","english_text":"Reschedule","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To arrange for something to occur at a different time.","main_translations_es":["Posponer","Cambiar la fecha","Reagendar"],"collocations":["reschedule the meeting","reschedule an appointment","reschedule for next week","reschedule at a later date"],"synonyms_en":["postpone","defer","move to a later date"],"example_sentence":"I will reschedule the meeting for Friday.","example_es":"Voy a reprogramar la reunión para el viernes.","example_en":"I will reschedule the meeting for Friday.","mnemonic_en":"Think of reprogramming the TV schedule, so you reschedule the shows","cloze_distractors_en":["Fabricate","Disengage","Interrogate","Reciprocate"],"examples":[{"es":"Voy a reprogramar la reunión para el viernes.","en":"I will reschedule the meeting for Friday."},{"es":"Debido a un conflicto de agenda, tenemos que reprogramar la presentación del proyecto.","en":"Due to a scheduling conflict, we have to reschedule the project presentation."},{"es":"Por favor, avísame si necesitas reprogramar tu entrevista con el cliente.","en":"Please let me know if you need to reschedule your interview with the client."}]},{"spanish_text":"Agenda","english_text":"Agenda","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A list of items to be discussed or acted upon, especially at a meeting.","main_translations_es":["programa","calendario","planificador"],"collocations":["set the agenda","agenda item","agenda for the meeting","agenda of the day"],"synonyms_en":[],"example_sentence":"I checked my agenda before the meeting.","example_es":"Revisé mi agenda antes de la reunión.","example_en":"I checked my agenda before the meeting.","mnemonic_en":null,"cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Revisé mi agenda antes de la reunión.","en":"I checked my agenda before the meeting."}]},{"spanish_text":"Punto del orden del día","english_text":"Agenda item","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A specific topic scheduled for discussion on an agenda.","main_translations_es":["Punto de la agenda","Tema del orden del día","Asunto del día"],"collocations":["add an agenda item","agenda item for discussion","agenda item number","agenda item to be addressed"],"synonyms_en":["discussion point","topic","meeting item"],"example_sentence":"The next agenda item will be the approval of the budget.","example_es":"El siguiente punto del orden del día será la aprobación del presupuesto.","example_en":"The next agenda item will be the approval of the budget.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a point on a calendar agenda marking today’s item.","cloze_distractors_en":["Financial audit","Company mandate","Project deadline","Quarterly report"],"examples":[{"es":"El siguiente punto del orden del día será la aprobación del presupuesto.","en":"The next agenda item will be the approval of the budget."},{"es":"Por favor, añada este tema como un nuevo punto del orden del día para la reunión de mañana.","en":"Please add this topic as a new agenda item for tomorrow''s meeting."},{"es":"No tenemos suficiente tiempo para discutir cada punto del orden del día antes de que termine la sesión.","en":"We do not have enough time to discuss every agenda item before the session ends."}]},{"spanish_text":"Acta","english_text":"Minutes","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A written record of the discussions and decisions made during a meeting.","main_translations_es":["registro","acta de reunión","minuta"],"collocations":["take minutes","meeting minutes","minutes of the meeting","record the minutes"],"synonyms_en":["record","notes","proceedings"],"example_sentence":"The minutes of the meeting were approved.","example_es":"El acta de la reunión se aprobó.","example_en":"The minutes of the meeting were approved.","mnemonic_en":"Picture an act‑a written fast, like recording meeting minutes in just a few minutes.","cloze_distractors_en":["Seconds","Journeys","Profiles"],"examples":[{"es":"El acta de la reunión se aprobó.","en":"The minutes of the meeting were approved."},{"es":"Por favor, toma nota de los puntos clave para el acta.","en":"Please take note of the key points for the minutes."},{"es":"El secretario envió el acta por correo electrónico a todos los asistentes.","en":"The secretary sent the minutes by email to all attendees."}]},{"spanish_text":"Punto de acción","english_text":"Action item","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A specific task or piece of work that needs to be completed.","main_translations_es":["Elemento de acción","Tarea","Acción pendiente"],"collocations":["action item list","action item owner","action item follow‑up","action item deadline"],"synonyms_en":["task","to‑do","assignment"],"example_sentence":"The action item for the next meeting is to review the budget.","example_es":"El punto de acción para la próxima reunión es revisar el presupuesto.","example_en":"The action item for the next meeting is to review the budget.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a red point on a checklist marking the action item.","cloze_distractors_en":["Passive voice","Creative block","Mental fatigue","Negative impact"],"examples":[{"es":"El punto de acción para la próxima reunión es revisar el presupuesto.","en":"The action item for the next meeting is to review the budget."},{"es":"Por favor, añade cada tarea pendiente a la lista de punto de acción en el acta de la sesión.","en":"Please add every pending task to the action item list in the meeting minutes."},{"es":"El gerente asignó un punto de acción a cada miembro del equipo para asegurar que el proyecto termine a tiempo.","en":"The manager assigned an action item to each team member to ensure the project finishes on time."}]},{"spanish_text":"Fecha límite","english_text":"Deadline","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A date or time by which something must be completed or submitted.","main_translations_es":["Plazo","Fecha de entrega","Vencimiento"],"collocations":["meet the deadline","deadline approaching","miss the deadline","deadline extension"],"synonyms_en":["due date","time limit","cutoff"],"example_sentence":"The deadline to submit the report is Monday at 5 p.m.","example_es":"La fecha límite para entregar el informe es el lunes a las 5 p.m.","example_en":"The deadline to submit the report is Monday at 5 p.m.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a dead line at the final date, the fecha límite.","cloze_distractors_en":["Guideline","Baseline","Headline","Pipeline"],"examples":[{"es":"La fecha límite para entregar el informe es el lunes a las 5 p.m.","en":"The deadline to submit the report is Monday at 5 p.m."},{"es":"Si no terminamos el proyecto antes de la fecha límite, perderemos el contrato.","en":"If we do not finish the project before the deadline, we will lose the contract."},{"es":"El equipo solicitó una extensión de la fecha límite debido a problemas técnicos.","en":"The team requested an extension of the deadline due to technical issues."}]},{"spanish_text":"Hito","english_text":"Milestone","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A significant event or point in development that marks progress or a turning point.","main_translations_es":["evento importante","punto de referencia","marca"],"collocations":["milestone birthday","milestone achievement","milestone event","milestone in history"],"synonyms_en":["landmark","turning point","benchmark"],"example_sentence":"This project reached a major milestone when we completed the testing phase.","example_es":"Este proyecto alcanzó un hito importante cuando completamos la fase de pruebas.","example_en":"This project reached a major milestone when we completed the testing phase.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a giant stone you hit to mark a milestone.","cloze_distractors_en":["Footnote","Headstone","Backbone","Millstone"],"examples":[{"es":"Este proyecto alcanzó un hito importante cuando completamos la fase de pruebas.","en":"This project reached a major milestone when we completed the testing phase."},{"es":"El equipo celebró el hito de ventas al superar el objetivo trimestral antes de lo previsto.","en":"The team celebrated the sales milestone after exceeding the quarterly target ahead of schedule."},{"es":"Debemos definir cada hito del cronograma para asegurar que el cliente esté satisfecho con nuestro progreso.","en":"We must define every project milestone in the schedule to ensure the client is satisfied with our progress."}]},{"spanish_text":"Entregable","english_text":"Deliverable","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A tangible or intangible item that must be completed and handed over as part of a project or contract.","main_translations_es":["producto","resultado","entrega"],"collocations":["project deliverable","deliverable deadline","deliverable item","deliverable schedule"],"synonyms_en":["output","product","submission"],"example_sentence":"The deliverable must be submitted before Friday.","example_es":"El entregable debe enviarse antes del viernes.","example_en":"The deliverable must be submitted before Friday.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a delivery truck dropping a box labeled Entregable on a doorstep.","cloze_distractors_en":["Inhabitant","Vegetable","Beneficiary"],"examples":[{"es":"El entregable debe enviarse antes del viernes.","en":"The deliverable must be submitted before Friday."},{"es":"El equipo revisó cada entregable del proyecto para asegurar la calidad.","en":"The team reviewed every project deliverable to ensure quality."},{"es":"Por favor, adjunta el entregable final en el correo electrónico para el cliente.","en":"Please attach the final deliverable to the email for the client."}]},{"spanish_text":"Carga de trabajo","english_text":"Workload","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The amount of work assigned to or expected from a person or group.","main_translations_es":["Carga laboral","Volumen de trabajo","Trabajo acumulado"],"collocations":["heavy workload","manage the workload","reduce the workload","workload increase"],"synonyms_en":["task load","job load","burden"],"example_sentence":"My workload has increased a lot this month.","example_es":"Mi carga de trabajo ha aumentado mucho este mes.","example_en":"My workload has increased a lot this month.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a cargo of files stacked high, the heavy workload.","cloze_distractors_en":["Workplace","Workforce","Worksheet","Workframe"],"examples":[{"es":"Mi carga de trabajo ha aumentado mucho este mes.","en":"My workload has increased a lot this month."},{"es":"El gerente decidió delegar tareas para reducir la carga de trabajo del equipo.","en":"The manager decided to delegate tasks to reduce the team''s workload."},{"es":"Debido a la alta carga de trabajo, no podré terminar el informe hoy.","en":"Due to the high workload, I will not be able to finish the report today."}]},{"spanish_text":"Priorizar","english_text":"Prioritize","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To arrange or deal with tasks, items, or goals in order of importance, giving precedence to the most important ones.","main_translations_es":["Dar prioridad","Poner en primer lugar","Priorizar"],"collocations":["prioritize tasks","prioritize safety","prioritize customer needs"],"synonyms_en":["give precedence to","rank","order by importance"],"example_sentence":"It''s important to prioritize the most urgent tasks before starting the project.","example_es":"Es importante priorizar las tareas más urgentes antes de comenzar el proyecto.","example_en":"It''s important to prioritize the most urgent tasks before starting the project.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a priority list where each item shouts priorizar as you prioritize the tasks","cloze_distractors_en":["Fabricate","Neglect","Postpone","Exaggerate"],"examples":[{"es":"Es importante priorizar las tareas más urgentes antes de comenzar el proyecto.","en":"It''s important to prioritize the most urgent tasks before starting the project."},{"es":"Debemos priorizar la comunicación con el cliente para evitar malentendidos durante la fase de diseño.","en":"We must prioritize communication with the client to avoid misunderstandings during the design phase."},{"es":"Si tenemos poco tiempo, es mejor priorizar los objetivos principales de la reunión.","en":"If we are short on time, it is better to prioritize the main objectives of the meeting."}]},{"spanish_text":"Escalar un problema","english_text":"Escalate an issue","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To raise an issue to a higher level of authority or attention.","main_translations_es":["Elevar un problema","Derivar un problema","Remitir un problema"],"collocations":["escalate an issue to management","escalate an issue quickly","escalate an issue when necessary","escalate an issue promptly"],"synonyms_en":["raise an issue","bring up a problem","elevate the issue"],"example_sentence":"If it isn''t resolved quickly, we will have to escalate an issue to the support team.","example_es":"Si no se resuelve rápidamente, tendremos que escalar un problema al equipo de soporte.","example_en":"If it isn''t resolved quickly, we will have to escalate an issue to the support team.","mnemonic_en":"Climb the ladder to raise the issue.","cloze_distractors_en":["Navigate a detour","Delegate a vacancy","Circulate a mandate","Appreciate a grievance"],"examples":[{"es":"Si no se resuelve rápidamente, tendremos que escalar un problema al equipo de soporte.","en":"If it isn''t resolved quickly, we will have to escalate an issue to the support team."},{"es":"El gerente decidió escalar un problema de presupuesto ante la junta directiva para obtener una aprobación inmediata.","en":"The manager decided to escalate an issue regarding the budget to the board of directors to get immediate approval."},{"es":"Cuando el cliente se quejó por tercera vez, el supervisor tuvo que escalar un problema para evitar la cancelación del contrato.","en":"When the client complained for the third time, the supervisor had to escalate an issue to prevent the contract from being cancelled."}]},{"spanish_text":"Resolver un problema","english_text":"Resolve an issue","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To find a solution to a problem or difficulty.","main_translations_es":["Solucionar un problema","Arreglar un problema","Encontrar una solución a un problema"],"collocations":["resolve an issue quickly","resolve an issue promptly","resolve an issue with the team","resolve an issue before deadline"],"synonyms_en":["fix a problem","address a problem","settle a matter"],"example_sentence":"I need to resolve an issue before the meeting.","example_es":"Necesito resolver un problema antes de la reunión.","example_en":"I need to resolve an issue before the meeting.","mnemonic_en":"Visualize a resolver robot untangling a tangled issue like a problem knot.","cloze_distractors_en":["Navigate a cloud","Exaggerate a rumor","Fabricate a shadow"],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito resolver un problema antes de la reunión.","en":"I need to resolve an issue before the meeting."},{"es":"El equipo técnico trabaja duro para resolver un problema con el servidor.","en":"The technical team is working hard to resolve an issue with the server."},{"es":"Por favor, llámame si surge alguna dificultad y necesitas resolver un problema urgente.","en":"Please call me if any difficulty arises and you need to resolve an issue urgently."}]},{"spanish_text":"Ponerse al día","english_text":"Catch up","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To reach the same level or position as someone else after having fallen behind.","main_translations_es":["Actualizarse","Ponerse al corriente","Poner al día"],"collocations":["catch up on","catch up with","catch up later","catch up to"],"synonyms_en":["keep up","get up to speed","bring up to date"],"example_sentence":"After the holidays, I had to catch up with work.","example_es":"Después de las vacaciones, tuve que ponerme al día con el trabajo.","example_en":"After the holidays, I had to catch up with work.","mnemonic_en":"Visualize catching a fish and lifting it up to the day to stay current.","cloze_distractors_en":["Look down","Turn over","Hold back","Give away"],"examples":[{"es":"Después de las vacaciones, tuve que ponerme al día con el trabajo.","en":"After the holidays, I had to catch up with work."},{"es":"Llegué tarde a la reunión y necesito que alguien me ayude a ponerme al día con los temas tratados.","en":"I arrived late to the meeting and need someone to help me catch up on the topics discussed."},{"es":"Me reuniré con mi supervisor esta tarde para ponerme al día sobre el progreso del proyecto.","en":"I will meet with my supervisor this afternoon to catch up on the project''s progress."}]},{"spanish_text":"Informe de progreso","english_text":"Progress report","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A document that details the status and developments of a project or task.","main_translations_es":["Reporte de avance","Informe de avances","Informe de progreso"],"collocations":["submit a progress report","annual progress report","progress report template","progress report deadline"],"synonyms_en":["status update","performance review","update report"],"example_sentence":"The team submitted the progress report before the deadline.","example_es":"El equipo entregó el informe de progreso antes de la fecha límite.","example_en":"The team submitted the progress report before the deadline.","mnemonic_en":"A pro writes a report on his progress, just like an informe de progreso.","cloze_distractors_en":["Breakfast menu","Weather forecast","Grocery receipt"],"examples":[{"es":"El equipo entregó el informe de progreso antes de la fecha límite.","en":"The team submitted the progress report before the deadline."},{"es":"Por favor, revisa el informe de progreso para ver si hemos alcanzado nuestros objetivos mensuales.","en":"Please review the progress report to see if we have met our monthly goals."},{"es":"El gerente solicitó un informe de progreso detallado sobre el desarrollo del nuevo software.","en":"The manager requested a detailed progress report on the development of the new software."}]},{"spanish_text":"Estado actual","english_text":"Current status","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The present condition or situation of something.","main_translations_es":["Situación actual","Estado presente","Condición actual"],"collocations":["current status update","check the current status","current status report","as per the current status"],"synonyms_en":["present condition","existing state","ongoing situation"],"example_sentence":"The current status of the project is uncertain.","example_es":"El estado actual del proyecto es incierto.","example_en":"The current status of the project is uncertain.","mnemonic_en":"A flowing current tells the state that está now.","cloze_distractors_en":["Future legacy","Physical volume","Internal climate","Relative distance"],"examples":[{"es":"El estado actual del proyecto es incierto.","en":"The current status of the project is uncertain."},{"es":"Por favor, envíame un correo electrónico con el estado actual de tu informe.","en":"Please send me an email with the current status of your report."},{"es":"Durante la reunión, discutiremos el estado actual de las ventas trimestrales.","en":"During the meeting, we will discuss the current status of the quarterly sales."}]},{"spanish_text":"Retrasado","english_text":"Behind schedule","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"adverbial phrase","definition_en":"Later than planned or expected; not on time.","main_translations_es":["Atrasado","Demorado","Tardío"],"collocations":["fall behind schedule","get behind schedule","run behind schedule","be behind schedule"],"synonyms_en":["delayed","running late","late"],"example_sentence":"The project is behind schedule due to unexpected technical issues.","example_es":"El proyecto está retrasado debido a problemas técnicos inesperados.","example_en":"The project is behind schedule due to unexpected technical issues.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a delayed trash truck re‑trash‑ado stuck behind schedule","cloze_distractors_en":["Above average","Across borders","Among friends"],"examples":[{"es":"El proyecto está retrasado debido a problemas técnicos inesperados.","en":"The project is behind schedule due to unexpected technical issues."},{"es":"Si seguimos trabajando a este ritmo, terminaremos retrasado con respecto a la fecha de entrega.","en":"If we keep working at this pace, we will finish behind schedule regarding the delivery date."},{"es":"El equipo de marketing se siente retrasado en la campaña publicitaria de este mes.","en":"The marketing team feels behind schedule on this month''s advertising campaign."}]},{"spanish_text":"Adelantado","english_text":"Ahead of schedule","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Occurring earlier than the planned time.","main_translations_es":["Anticipado","Previo","Por delante"],"collocations":["finish ahead of schedule","be ahead of schedule","run ahead of schedule","complete ahead of schedule"],"synonyms_en":["early","ahead of time","in advance"],"example_sentence":"The project is ahead of schedule and we will finish earlier than planned.","example_es":"El proyecto está adelantado y terminaremos antes de lo previsto.","example_en":"The project is ahead of schedule and we will finish earlier than planned.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a runner ahead shouting adelante to stay ahead of schedule","cloze_distractors_en":["Behind the curtain","Under the weather","Out of the woods","Off the record"],"examples":[{"es":"El proyecto está adelantado y terminaremos antes de lo previsto.","en":"The project is ahead of schedule and we will finish earlier than planned."},{"es":"Gracias a que el equipo trabajó el fin de semana, la entrega final está adelantado respecto a la fecha límite.","en":"Thanks to the team working over the weekend, the final delivery is ahead of schedule regarding the deadline."},{"es":"Si logramos completar esta fase hoy, estaremos adelantado para el inicio de la siguiente etapa.","en":"If we manage to complete this phase today, we will be ahead of schedule for the start of the next stage."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cumplir el plazo","english_text":"Meet the deadline","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To complete something before or at the specified time limit.","main_translations_es":["Respetar el plazo","Entregar a tiempo","Cumplir la fecha límite"],"collocations":["to meet the deadline","hard to meet the deadline","meet the deadline on time","struggle to meet the deadline"],"synonyms_en":["hit the deadline","make the deadline","finish on time"],"example_sentence":"We have to meet the deadline to submit the report.","example_es":"Tenemos que cumplir el plazo para presentar el informe.","example_en":"We have to meet the deadline to submit the report.","mnemonic_en":"I meet the deadline by arriving at the plaza clock right on time.","cloze_distractors_en":["Cancel the meeting","Avoid the workload","Ignore the progress","Reject the feedback"],"examples":[{"es":"Tenemos que cumplir el plazo para presentar el informe.","en":"We have to meet the deadline to submit the report."},{"es":"Si trabajamos horas extra, lograremos cumplir el plazo del proyecto.","en":"If we work overtime, we will manage to meet the deadline for the project."},{"es":"El equipo está bajo mucha presión para cumplir el plazo antes de la conferencia.","en":"The team is under a lot of pressure to meet the deadline before the conference."}]},{"spanish_text":"Incumplir el plazo","english_text":"Miss the deadline","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To fail to meet a deadline.","main_translations_es":["No cumplir el plazo","Pasar la fecha límite","Atrasarse en la entrega"],"collocations":["miss the deadline","missed the deadline","to miss a deadline","deadline missed"],"synonyms_en":["fail to meet the deadline","be late","miss the due date"],"example_sentence":"I don''t want to miss the deadline for submission.","example_es":"No quiero incumplir el plazo de entrega.","example_en":"I don''t want to miss the deadline for submission.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a Miss ignoring the plaza sign and therefore missing the deadline.","cloze_distractors_en":["Skip the promotion","Lose the incentive","Drop the assignment","Quit the department"],"examples":[{"es":"No quiero incumplir el plazo de entrega.","en":"I don''t want to miss the deadline for submission."},{"es":"Si no terminamos el informe hoy, vamos a incumplir el plazo del proyecto.","en":"If we don''t finish the report today, we are going to miss the deadline for the project."},{"es":"El equipo trabajó horas extra para no incumplir el plazo acordado con el cliente.","en":"The team worked overtime so they would not miss the deadline agreed upon with the client."}]},{"spanish_text":"Disponibilidad","english_text":"Availability","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The state of being ready for use or obtainable.","main_translations_es":["Disponibilidad","Accesibilidad","Libre disponibilidad"],"collocations":["check availability","availability of resources","availability schedule","availability status"],"synonyms_en":["readiness","accessibility","presence"],"example_sentence":"Please update your availability on the shared calendar for next week.","example_es":"Por favor, actualice su disponibilidad en el calendario compartido para la próxima semana.","example_en":"Please update your availability on the shared calendar for next week.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a dispenser of time, showing my availability.","cloze_distractors_en":["Incompatibility","Unpredictability","Irresponsibility"],"examples":[{"es":"Por favor, actualice su disponibilidad en el calendario compartido para la próxima semana.","en":"Please update your availability on the shared calendar for next week."},{"es":"Necesito confirmar la disponibilidad del equipo antes de aceptar este nuevo proyecto.","en":"I need to confirm the availability of the team before accepting this new project."},{"es":"El gerente de recursos humanos revisará su disponibilidad para una entrevista presencial.","en":"The human resources manager will check your availability for an in-person interview."}]},{"spanish_text":"Franja horaria","english_text":"Time slot","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A specific period of time allocated for an activity or appointment.","main_translations_es":["Horario","Intervalo de tiempo","Periodo"],"collocations":["book a time slot","available time slot","reserve a time slot","time slot allocation"],"synonyms_en":["time window","time period","schedule slot"],"example_sentence":"What is your available time slot for the meeting?","example_es":"¿Cuál es tu franja horaria disponible para la reunión?","example_en":"What is your available time slot for the meeting?","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a striped clock, each franja marking a different time slot","cloze_distractors_en":["Task force","Team size","Desk space","File path"],"examples":[{"es":"¿Cuál es tu franja horaria disponible para la reunión?","en":"What is your available time slot for the meeting?"},{"es":"Necesito reservar una franja horaria para la llamada con el cliente.","en":"I need to book a time slot for the call with the client."},{"es":"¿Podemos mover nuestra franja horaria para la presentación al viernes?","en":"Can we move our time slot for the presentation to Friday?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Conflicto de horario","english_text":"Scheduling conflict","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A situation where two or more events are planned for the same time, making it impossible to attend all of them.","main_translations_es":["Conflicto de agenda","Choque de horarios","Solapamiento de horarios"],"collocations":["due to a scheduling conflict","resolve a scheduling conflict","avoid scheduling conflicts","schedule conflict"],"synonyms_en":["time clash","calendar clash","appointment overlap"],"example_sentence":"I have a scheduling conflict and won''t be able to attend the meeting.","example_es":"Tengo un conflicto de horario y no podré asistir a la reunión.","example_en":"I have a scheduling conflict and won''t be able to attend the meeting.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a calendar and a clock in a fight, a scheduling conflict.","cloze_distractors_en":["Professional negligence","Technical bankruptcy","Corporate resignation","Operational redundancy"],"examples":[{"es":"Tengo un conflicto de horario y no podré asistir a la reunión.","en":"I have a scheduling conflict and won''t be able to attend the meeting."},{"es":"Debido a un conflicto de horario, debemos reprogramar la entrevista con el candidato para el viernes.","en":"Due to a scheduling conflict, we must reschedule the candidate interview for Friday."},{"es":"El sistema automático envió una alerta por un conflicto de horario entre la capacitación y la presentación del proyecto.","en":"The automated system sent an alert because of a scheduling conflict between the training session and the project presentation."}]},{"spanish_text":"Plantilla","english_text":"Template","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A pre-designed format or pattern used as a starting point for creating something.","main_translations_es":["Modelo","Formato","Plantilla"],"collocations":["template file","template design","template engine"],"synonyms_en":["pattern","model","prototype"],"example_sentence":"The template of the report is available on the intranet.","example_es":"La plantilla del informe está disponible en la intranet.","example_en":"The template of the report is available on the intranet.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a plant sprouting from a template sheet, like a green leaf in a paper mold.","cloze_distractors_en":["Fragment","Stagnant","Sediment","Ornament"],"examples":[{"es":"La plantilla del informe está disponible en la intranet.","en":"The template of the report is available on the intranet."},{"es":"Por favor, utiliza esta plantilla para estandarizar el formato de todas las presentaciones del equipo.","en":"Please use this template to standardize the format of all team presentations."},{"es":"He creado una plantilla en Excel para que podamos registrar los gastos mensuales de manera eficiente.","en":"I have created an Excel template so that we can track monthly expenses efficiently."}]},{"spanish_text":"Borrador","english_text":"Draft","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A preliminary version of a document or plan.","main_translations_es":["Esbozo","Boceto","Proyecto"],"collocations":["draft a letter","draft legislation","draft version","draft copy"],"synonyms_en":["outline","sketch","preliminary version"],"example_sentence":"I will review the draft of the report before sending it.","example_es":"Voy a revisar el borrador del informe antes de enviarlo.","example_en":"I will review the draft of the report before sending it.","mnemonic_en":"A cold draft sneaks through the borrador door, reminding you it''s a draft.","cloze_distractors_en":["Staple","Badge","Glove","Shelf"],"examples":[{"es":"Voy a revisar el borrador del informe antes de enviarlo.","en":"I will review the draft of the report before sending it."},{"es":"Por favor, guarda el borrador del correo electrónico para terminarlo más tarde.","en":"Please save the draft of the email to finish it later."},{"es":"El equipo presentó un borrador del contrato para nuestra aprobación inicial.","en":"The team presented a draft of the contract for our initial approval."}]},{"spanish_text":"Presupuesto","english_text":"Budget","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A plan that estimates expected income and expenses over a specific period.","main_translations_es":["Presupuesto","Plan financiero","Estimación de costos"],"collocations":["budget plan","budget cuts","budget meeting","budget allocation"],"synonyms_en":["financial plan","spending plan","allocation"],"example_sentence":"The budget for the project was approved last week.","example_es":"El presupuesto para el proyecto se aprobó la semana pasada.","example_en":"The budget for the project was approved last week.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a bud getting a giant receipt labeled ''presupuesto'' – that''s your budget.","cloze_distractors_en":["Stapler","Curtain","Pebble","Balloon"],"examples":[{"es":"El presupuesto para el proyecto se aprobó la semana pasada.","en":"The budget for the project was approved last week."},{"es":"Debemos reducir el presupuesto de marketing para ahorrar costos este trimestre.","en":"We must reduce the marketing budget to save costs this quarter."},{"es":"El gerente solicitó una revisión detallada del presupuesto antes de la reunión.","en":"The manager requested a detailed review of the budget before the meeting."}]},{"spanish_text":"Previsión","english_text":"Forecast","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A prediction or estimate of future events, such as weather or economic conditions.","main_translations_es":["Pronóstico","Predicción","Proyección"],"collocations":["weather forecast","sales forecast","forecast the future"],"synonyms_en":["prediction","projection","prognosis"],"example_sentence":"The sales forecast for the next quarter is very optimistic.","example_es":"La previsión de ventas para el próximo trimestre es muy optimista.","example_en":"The sales forecast for the next quarter is very optimistic.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a forecaster casting a crystal ball, foreseeing the future like a clear prevision.","cloze_distractors_en":["Landscape","Footprint","Backdrop","Handshake"],"examples":[{"es":"La previsión de ventas para el próximo trimestre es muy optimista.","en":"The sales forecast for the next quarter is very optimistic."},{"es":"Debemos ajustar nuestra previsión presupuestaria debido al aumento de los costos.","en":"We must adjust our budget forecast due to the increase in costs."},{"es":"El equipo de análisis presentó una previsión detallada sobre el crecimiento del mercado.","en":"The analysis team presented a detailed forecast regarding market growth."}]},{"spanish_text":"Estimación","english_text":"Estimate","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"An approximate calculation or judgment of the value, size, or amount of something.","main_translations_es":["Cálculo","Valoración","Aproximación"],"collocations":["estimate the cost","rough estimate","estimate the time","make an estimate"],"synonyms_en":["approximation","guess","assessment"],"example_sentence":"According to the meteorologist''s estimate, it will rain tomorrow.","example_es":"Según la estimación del meteorólogo, lloverá mañana.","example_en":"According to the meteorologist''s estimate, it will rain tomorrow.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a scientist saying estimate while holding a chart titled Estimación, calculating the unknown","cloze_distractors_en":["Appetite","Altitude","Aptitude","Attitude"],"examples":[{"es":"Según la estimación del meteorólogo, lloverá mañana.","en":"According to the meteorologist''s estimate, it will rain tomorrow."},{"es":"El equipo presentó una estimación detallada de los costos para el nuevo proyecto.","en":"The team presented a detailed estimate of the costs for the new project."},{"es":"Necesitamos una estimación precisa del tiempo necesario para completar esta tarea.","en":"We need an accurate estimate of the time required to complete this task."}]},{"spanish_text":"Alcance","english_text":"Scope","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the extent or range of something''s coverage, influence, or operation","main_translations_es":["Ámbito","Cobertura","Extensión"],"collocations":["out of scope","scope of work","broad scope","scope creep"],"synonyms_en":["range","extent","breadth"],"example_sentence":"The scope of the project includes the implementation of new technologies.","example_es":"El alcance del proyecto incluye la implementación de nuevas tecnologías.","example_en":"The scope of the project includes the implementation of new technologies.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a telescope''s scope reaching far, just like the Spanish alcance meaning reach.","cloze_distractors_en":["Stance","Spine","Score"],"examples":[{"es":"El alcance del proyecto incluye la implementación de nuevas tecnologías.","en":"The scope of the project includes the implementation of new technologies."},{"es":"Debemos definir claramente el alcance de esta tarea para evitar confusiones.","en":"We must clearly define the scope of this task to avoid confusion."},{"es":"El presupuesto actual no es suficiente para cubrir el alcance ampliado de la investigación.","en":"The current budget is not sufficient to cover the expanded scope of the research."}]},{"spanish_text":"Requisito","english_text":"Requirement","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Something that is needed or demanded.","main_translations_es":["exigencia","condición","requerimiento"],"collocations":["meeting the requirement","as a requirement","requirement for","mandatory requirement"],"synonyms_en":["necessity","prerequisite","condition"],"example_sentence":"The requirement to enroll in the course is to be at least 18 years old.","example_es":"El requisito para inscribirse en el curso es tener al menos 18 años.","example_en":"The requirement to enroll in the course is to be at least 18 years old.","mnemonic_en":"The teacher demands a requisito, the requirement, on the board.","cloze_distractors_en":["Suggestion","Adjustment","Investment","Engagement"],"examples":[{"es":"El requisito para inscribirse en el curso es tener al menos 18 años.","en":"The requirement to enroll in the course is to be at least 18 years old."},{"es":"Antes de empezar el proyecto, debemos cumplir con cada requisito técnico del cliente.","en":"Before starting the project, we must meet every technical requirement from the client."},{"es":"La falta de experiencia previa no es un requisito indispensable para este puesto de trabajo.","en":"A lack of previous experience is not a mandatory requirement for this job position."}]},{"spanish_text":"Dependencia","english_text":"Dependency","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A condition in which a person, group, or thing relies on or is controlled by another for support or aid.","main_translations_es":["subordinación","adicción","sujeción"],"collocations":["dependency injection","dependency graph","dependency management","dependency relationship"],"synonyms_en":["reliance","dependence","subordination"],"example_sentence":"The dependency on fossil fuels is an environmental problem.","example_es":"La dependencia de los combustibles fósiles es un problema ambiental.","example_en":"The dependency on fossil fuels is an environmental problem.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a DEPENDENT dog clutching a DEPENDENCY rope, never letting go.","cloze_distractors_en":["Beneficiary","Visibility","Capability","Integrity"],"examples":[{"es":"La dependencia de los combustibles fósiles es un problema ambiental.","en":"The dependency on fossil fuels is an environmental problem."},{"es":"Nuestra empresa busca reducir la dependencia de proveedores externos para mejorar la eficiencia.","en":"Our company seeks to reduce the dependency on external suppliers to improve efficiency."},{"es":"El éxito del proyecto tiene una gran dependencia de la colaboración entre los departamentos.","en":"The success of the project has a strong dependency on the collaboration between departments."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cuello de botella","english_text":"Bottleneck","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A narrow point or stage that restricts flow or progress, causing a delay.","main_translations_es":["Obstáculo","Punto crítico","Cuello de botella"],"collocations":["bottleneck in production","traffic bottleneck","bottleneck effect","bottleneck situation"],"synonyms_en":["obstacle","constraint","impediment"],"example_sentence":"The project was delayed because there was a bottleneck in production.","example_es":"El proyecto se retrasó porque hubo un cuello de botella en la producción.","example_en":"The project was delayed because there was a bottleneck in production.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a bottle neck squeezing traffic like a bottleneck.","cloze_distractors_en":["Headlight","Footprint","Backtrack","Handshake"],"examples":[{"es":"El proyecto se retrasó porque hubo un cuello de botella en la producción.","en":"The project was delayed because there was a bottleneck in production."},{"es":"La falta de personal en el departamento de contabilidad creó un cuello de botella en el proceso de pagos.","en":"The lack of staff in the accounting department created a bottleneck in the payment process."},{"es":"Debemos identificar el cuello de botella en nuestro flujo de trabajo para mejorar la eficiencia del equipo.","en":"We must identify the bottleneck in our workflow to improve team efficiency."}]},{"spanish_text":"Riesgo","english_text":"Risk","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the possibility of loss, injury, or other adverse outcome","main_translations_es":["peligro","amenaza","contingencia"],"collocations":["take a risk","risk assessment","risk management","high risk"],"synonyms_en":["danger","hazard","peril"],"example_sentence":"Investing in that company carries a great risk.","example_es":"Invertir en esa empresa conlleva un gran riesgo.","example_en":"Investing in that company carries a great risk.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a dice rolling off a cliff, shouting Riesgo as it falls.","cloze_distractors_en":["Staple","Pencil","Folder","Window"],"examples":[{"es":"Invertir en esa empresa conlleva un gran riesgo.","en":"Investing in that company carries a great risk."},{"es":"Debemos evaluar el riesgo antes de lanzar el nuevo proyecto.","en":"We must evaluate the risk before launching the new project."},{"es":"El gerente decidió no proceder debido al alto riesgo financiero.","en":"The manager decided not to proceed due to the high financial risk."}]},{"spanish_text":"Mitigación","english_text":"Mitigation","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The act of reducing the severity, seriousness, or harmful effects of something.","main_translations_es":["Reducción","Alivio","Atenuación"],"collocations":["risk mitigation","climate change mitigation","mitigation measures","mitigation strategies"],"synonyms_en":["reduction","alleviation","lessening"],"example_sentence":"Mitigation of climate change requires urgent actions.","example_es":"La mitigación del cambio climático requiere acciones urgentes.","example_en":"Mitigation of climate change requires urgent actions.","mnemonic_en":"A mitten (miti) covers the garden, showing mitigation protects the area.","cloze_distractors_en":["Fabrication","Delegation","Orientation","Cultivation"],"examples":[{"es":"La mitigación del cambio climático requiere acciones urgentes.","en":"Mitigation of climate change requires urgent actions."},{"es":"El equipo implementó una estrategia de mitigación para reducir los riesgos del proyecto.","en":"The team implemented a mitigation strategy to reduce project risks."},{"es":"Debemos discutir un plan de mitigación para evitar retrasos en la entrega final.","en":"We must discuss a mitigation plan to avoid delays in the final delivery."}]},{"spanish_text":"Lanzamiento","english_text":"Launch","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The act of sending a product, vehicle, or spacecraft into operation or into the air.","main_translations_es":["Despegue","Salida","Emisión"],"collocations":["launch a product","launch a rocket","launch a campaign","launch into space"],"synonyms_en":["initiate","start","send off"],"example_sentence":"The launch of the new phone will be next month.","example_es":"El lanzamiento del nuevo teléfono será el próximo mes.","example_en":"The launch of the new phone will be next month.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a rocket launch where the crew yells Lanz as they throw the payload skyward.","cloze_distractors_en":["Retreat","Closure","Verdict","Preface"],"examples":[{"es":"El lanzamiento del nuevo teléfono será el próximo mes.","en":"The launch of the new phone will be next month."},{"es":"Todo el equipo de marketing está trabajando en el lanzamiento de la nueva campaña publicitaria.","en":"The entire marketing team is working on the launch of the new advertising campaign."},{"es":"La empresa ha pospuesto el lanzamiento del software debido a algunos errores técnicos.","en":"The company has postponed the launch of the software due to some technical bugs."}]},{"spanish_text":"Despliegue","english_text":"Rollout","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The act of introducing or launching a new product, service, or system to the market or users.","main_translations_es":["Implementación","Lanzamiento","Puesta en marcha"],"collocations":["rollout plan","product rollout","rollout schedule","rollout strategy"],"synonyms_en":["deployment","launch","implementation"],"example_sentence":"The rollout of the new software is scheduled for next Monday.","example_es":"El despliegue del nuevo software está programado para el próximo lunes.","example_en":"The rollout of the new software is scheduled for next Monday.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a giant carpet being rolled out, like a deployment (despliegue) across the floor.","cloze_distractors_en":["Backlash","Outreach","Breakdown","Turnover"],"examples":[{"es":"El despliegue del nuevo software está programado para el próximo lunes.","en":"The rollout of the new software is scheduled for next Monday."},{"es":"Debemos coordinar con el equipo de marketing antes de iniciar el despliegue de la campaña publicitaria.","en":"We must coordinate with the marketing team before beginning the rollout of the advertising campaign."},{"es":"El despliegue de estas nuevas políticas de seguridad se realizará de forma gradual en todas las sucursales.","en":"The rollout of these new security policies will be carried out gradually across all branches."}]},{"spanish_text":"Incorporación","english_text":"Onboarding","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The process of integrating new employees into an organization.","main_translations_es":["Integración","Admisión","Incorporación"],"collocations":["employee onboarding","customer onboarding","onboarding process","onboarding program"],"synonyms_en":["orientation","induction","training"],"example_sentence":"The onboarding of the new employees will take place next week.","example_es":"La incorporación de los nuevos empleados se realizará la próxima semana.","example_en":"The onboarding of the new employees will take place next week.","mnemonic_en":"Picture yourself stepping onto a board, incorporating yourself into the crew—that''s onboarding.","cloze_distractors_en":["Outsourcing","Offboarding","Overlooking","Outgrowing"],"examples":[{"es":"La incorporación de los nuevos empleados se realizará la próxima semana.","en":"The onboarding of the new employees will take place next week."},{"es":"El departamento de recursos humanos ha diseñado un programa de incorporación muy completo para los recién contratados.","en":"The human resources department has designed a very comprehensive onboarding program for the new hires."},{"es":"Necesitamos mejorar nuestro proceso de incorporación para que los nuevos miembros del equipo se sientan bienvenidos desde el primer día.","en":"We need to improve our onboarding process so that new team members feel welcome from day one."}]},{"spanish_text":"Capacitación","english_text":"Training","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The process of teaching or developing skills and knowledge.","main_translations_es":["Entrenamiento","Formación","Adiestramiento"],"collocations":["training program","on-the-job training","training session","training manual"],"synonyms_en":["instruction","coaching","education"],"example_sentence":"The company will offer technical training for all new employees next Monday.","example_es":"La empresa ofrecerá una capacitación técnica para todos los nuevos empleados el próximo lunes.","example_en":"The company will offer technical training for all new employees next Monday.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a trainer handing a cap and saying capacitación to start the training.","cloze_distractors_en":["Promotion","Departure","Appraisal","Admission"],"examples":[{"es":"La empresa ofrecerá una capacitación técnica para todos los nuevos empleados el próximo lunes.","en":"The company will offer technical training for all new employees next Monday."},{"es":"Debemos programar una capacitación sobre el nuevo software de gestión de proyectos.","en":"We need to schedule training on the new project management software."},{"es":"El departamento de recursos humanos organiza una capacitación obligatoria sobre seguridad en la oficina.","en":"The human resources department is organizing mandatory training regarding office safety."}]},{"spanish_text":"Retroalimentación","english_text":"Feedback","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Information or reactions given about a performance, product, or behavior, used to guide improvement.","main_translations_es":["comentarios","opinión","valoración"],"collocations":["give feedback","receive feedback","constructive feedback","feedback loop"],"synonyms_en":["response","input","reaction"],"example_sentence":"User feedback is essential for improving the product.","example_es":"La retroalimentación de los usuarios es esencial para mejorar el producto.","example_en":"User feedback is essential for improving the product.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a retro robot feeding back data to you.","cloze_distractors_en":["Backlash","Overhead","Deadline","Updraft"],"examples":[{"es":"La retroalimentación de los usuarios es esencial para mejorar el producto.","en":"User feedback is essential for improving the product."},{"es":"Después de la presentación, mi jefe me dio una retroalimentación muy constructiva sobre mi desempeño.","en":"After the presentation, my boss gave me very constructive feedback on my performance."},{"es":"El equipo se reunió para intercambiar retroalimentación sobre los resultados del proyecto trimestral.","en":"The team met to exchange feedback regarding the results of the quarterly project."}]},{"spanish_text":"Evaluación de desempeño","english_text":"Performance review","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A formal assessment of an employee''s work performance.","main_translations_es":["Revisión de desempeño","Valoración del rendimiento","Análisis de desempeño"],"collocations":["annual performance review","performance review meeting","conduct a performance review","performance review process"],"synonyms_en":["evaluation","appraisal","assessment"],"example_sentence":"The performance review will take place next Monday.","example_es":"La evaluación de desempeño se realizará el próximo lunes.","example_en":"The performance review will take place next Monday.","mnemonic_en":"In the performance review, the boss watches a stage revue of the employee''s ''desempeño'' like a show.","cloze_distractors_en":["Corporate cafeteria","Management vacation","Departmental birthday","Professional furniture"],"examples":[{"es":"La evaluación de desempeño se realizará el próximo lunes.","en":"The performance review will take place next Monday."},{"es":"Mi jefe me dio una evaluación de desempeño muy positiva este año.","en":"My boss gave me a very positive performance review this year."},{"es":"Debemos preparar los objetivos del equipo antes de nuestra evaluación de desempeño.","en":"We must prepare the team goals before our performance review."}]},{"spanish_text":"Ascenso","english_text":"Promotion","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A promotion is the advancement of an employee to a higher position, often with increased responsibilities and pay.","main_translations_es":["Promoción","Elevación","Subida"],"collocations":["career promotion","promotion offer","promotion campaign"],"synonyms_en":["advancement","upgrade","elevation"],"example_sentence":"After three years of hard work, he received a promotion.","example_es":"Después de tres años de trabajo duro, recibió un ascenso.","example_en":"After three years of hard work, he received a promotion.","mnemonic_en":"A pro climbs a ladder for a promotion","cloze_distractors_en":["Dismissal","Suspension","Demotion","Resignation"],"examples":[{"es":"Después de tres años de trabajo duro, recibió un ascenso.","en":"After three years of hard work, he received a promotion."},{"es":"Su excelente desempeño en el proyecto le permitió obtener un ascenso.","en":"Her excellent performance on the project allowed her to earn a promotion."},{"es":"El gerente anunció que habrá un ascenso para el empleado con mejores resultados este trimestre.","en":"The manager announced that there will be a promotion for the employee with the best results this quarter."}]},{"spanish_text":"Renuncia","english_text":"Resignation","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The act of voluntarily giving up a job or position.","main_translations_es":["Dimisión","Renuncia","Abandono"],"collocations":["letter of resignation","resignation letter","accept resignation","submit resignation"],"synonyms_en":["quit","stepping down","departure"],"example_sentence":"His resignation from the position surprised everyone.","example_es":"Su renuncia al cargo sorprendió a todos.","example_en":"His resignation from the position surprised everyone.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a boss handing a letter that says renuncia, signaling his resignation","cloze_distractors_en":["Resurrection","Registration","Regulation","Reiteration"],"examples":[{"es":"Su renuncia al cargo sorprendió a todos.","en":"His resignation from the position surprised everyone."},{"es":"La empresa recibió formalmente su carta de renuncia esta mañana.","en":"The company formally received his letter of resignation this morning."},{"es":"El director ejecutivo anunció su renuncia tras años de servicio.","en":"The chief executive officer announced his resignation after years of service."}]},{"spanish_text":"Contratación","english_text":"Hiring","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The act of employing someone for a job.","main_translations_es":["Reclutamiento","Selección de personal","Incorporación"],"collocations":["hiring process","hiring manager","hiring freeze","hiring spree"],"synonyms_en":["recruiting","staffing","employment"],"example_sentence":"Hiring new employees is a priority this quarter.","example_es":"La contratación de nuevos empleados es una prioridad este trimestre.","example_en":"Hiring new employees is a priority this quarter.","mnemonic_en":"When hiring, picture a contract—contratación reminds you of a signed deal.","cloze_distractors_en":["Firing","Retiring","Ignoring","Banning"],"examples":[{"es":"La contratación de nuevos empleados es una prioridad este trimestre.","en":"Hiring new employees is a priority this quarter."},{"es":"El departamento de recursos humanos gestiona todo el proceso de contratación para los puestos vacantes.","en":"The human resources department manages the entire Hiring process for the vacant positions."},{"es":"Debido al crecimiento de la empresa, hemos acelerado la contratación de personal técnico.","en":"Due to the company''s growth, we have accelerated the Hiring of technical staff."}]},{"spanish_text":"Entrevista","english_text":"Interview","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A formal meeting where one person asks questions and another provides answers, often to assess suitability for a job or to gather information.","main_translations_es":["Entrevista","Charla","Entrevista laboral"],"collocations":["job interview","interview process","interview panel","interview questions"],"synonyms_en":["conversation","questioning","meeting"],"example_sentence":"Tomorrow I have a job interview at ten o''clock.","example_es":"Mañana tengo una entrevista de trabajo a las diez.","example_en":"Tomorrow I have a job interview at ten o''clock.","mnemonic_en":"Enter the vista, the doorway to the interview.","cloze_distractors_en":["Intermission","Intersection","Intervention","Introversion"],"examples":[{"es":"Mañana tengo una entrevista de trabajo a las diez.","en":"Tomorrow I have a job interview at ten o''clock."},{"es":"El candidato llegó puntual a su entrevista con el gerente de recursos humanos.","en":"The candidate arrived on time for his interview with the human resources manager."},{"es":"Después de revisar su currículum, decidimos invitarla a una entrevista presencial.","en":"After reviewing her resume, we decided to invite her for an in-person interview."}]},{"spanish_text":"Candidato","english_text":"Candidate","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person who is seeking or being considered for a position, office, or honor.","main_translations_es":["aspirante","postulante","concursante"],"collocations":["job candidate","candidate for office","candidate selection","candidate profile"],"synonyms_en":["applicant","contender","nominee"],"example_sentence":"The selection team is evaluating the most qualified candidate for the engineering position.","example_es":"El equipo de selección está evaluando al candidato más cualificado para el puesto de ingeniero.","example_en":"The selection team is evaluating the most qualified candidate for the engineering position.","mnemonic_en":"The candidate shows a candid photo to a taco vendor at the door.","cloze_distractors_en":["Furniture","Equipment","Procedure","Portfolio"],"examples":[{"es":"El equipo de selección está evaluando al candidato más cualificado para el puesto de ingeniero.","en":"The selection team is evaluating the most qualified candidate for the engineering position."},{"es":"El gerente entrevistó a cada candidato para el puesto de ventas.","en":"The manager interviewed every candidate for the sales position."},{"es":"El departamento de recursos humanos revisó el currículum de cada candidato.","en":"The human resources department reviewed the resume of each candidate."}]},{"spanish_text":"Vacante","english_text":"Opening","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A position or opportunity that is available, especially a job vacancy.","main_translations_es":["Puesto disponible","Posición vacante","Oferta de empleo"],"collocations":["job opening","opening ceremony","opening hours","opening statement"],"synonyms_en":["vacancy","position","opportunity"],"example_sentence":"There is an opening for a software engineer at the company.","example_es":"Hay una vacante para ingeniero de software en la empresa.","example_en":"There is an opening for a software engineer at the company.","mnemonic_en":"Picture opening a vacant (vacante) door to a new job.","cloze_distractors_en":["Obstacle","Outbreak","Overhead"],"examples":[{"es":"Hay una vacante para ingeniero de software en la empresa.","en":"There is an opening for a software engineer at the company."},{"es":"El departamento de recursos humanos anunció una vacante en el equipo de ventas.","en":"The human resources department announced an opening on the sales team."},{"es":"Debido a la expansión del proyecto, tenemos una vacante para un nuevo gerente de proyectos.","en":"Due to the project expansion, we have an opening for a new project manager."}]},{"spanish_text":"Descripción del puesto","english_text":"Job description","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A written statement outlining the duties, responsibilities, and requirements of a particular job.","main_translations_es":["Perfil del puesto","Resumen del puesto","Descripción del cargo"],"collocations":["write a job description","review the job description","job description template","job description format"],"synonyms_en":["position summary","role outline","job profile"],"example_sentence":"The job description includes project management responsibilities.","example_es":"La descripción del puesto incluye responsabilidades de gestión de proyectos.","example_en":"The job description includes project management responsibilities.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a job posting wearing a big badge that reads descripción del puesto","cloze_distractors_en":["Work experience","Staff evaluation","Team motivation","Office decoration"],"examples":[{"es":"La descripción del puesto incluye responsabilidades de gestión de proyectos.","en":"The job description includes project management responsibilities."},{"es":"Por favor, revisa la descripción del puesto antes de publicar la oferta en LinkedIn.","en":"Please review the job description before posting the vacancy on LinkedIn."},{"es":"No entiendo mis tareas diarias porque la descripción del puesto es demasiado vaga.","en":"I do not understand my daily tasks because the job description is too vague."}]},{"spanish_text":"Trabajo remoto","english_text":"Remote work","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A work arrangement in which an employee performs their job duties from a location outside the employer''s premises, typically using digital communication tools.","main_translations_es":["Teletrabajo","Trabajo a distancia","Trabajo desde casa"],"collocations":["remote work policy","remote work arrangement","remote work opportunities","remote work culture"],"synonyms_en":["telecommuting","working from home","flexible work"],"example_sentence":"Remote work allows employees to manage their personal time better.","example_es":"El trabajo remoto permite a los empleados gestionar mejor su tiempo personal.","example_en":"Remote work allows employees to manage their personal time better.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a remote control typing a report while sitting on a couch like a remoto office.","cloze_distractors_en":["Office gossip","Company budget","Manual labor","Public transit"],"examples":[{"es":"El trabajo remoto permite a los empleados gestionar mejor su tiempo personal.","en":"Remote work allows employees to manage their personal time better."},{"es":"Nuestra empresa decidió implementar el trabajo remoto para reducir los costos de oficina.","en":"Our company decided to implement remote work to reduce office costs."},{"es":"Es necesario tener una buena conexión a internet para realizar un trabajo remoto eficiente.","en":"It is necessary to have a good internet connection to perform efficient remote work."}]},{"spanish_text":"Trabajo híbrido","english_text":"Hybrid work","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A work arrangement that combines remote and on‑site duties.","main_translations_es":["Modelo híbrido de trabajo","Trabajo mixto","Trabajo a distancia y presencial"],"collocations":["hybrid work model","hybrid work arrangement","flexible hybrid work","remote and on‑site hybrid work"],"synonyms_en":["flexible work","blended work","remote‑office model"],"example_sentence":"Our company has implemented a hybrid work model so that employees spend three days in the office and two at home.","example_es":"Nuestra empresa ha implementado un modelo de trabajo híbrido para que los empleados pasen tres días en la oficina y dos en casa.","example_en":"Our company has implemented a hybrid work model so that employees spend three days in the office and two at home.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a half‑robot employee at a desk, because hybrid work sounds like the Spanish híbrido for mixed.","cloze_distractors_en":["Stationary labor","Mandatory onsite","Permanent leave","Fragmented duty"],"examples":[{"es":"Nuestra empresa ha implementado un modelo de trabajo híbrido para que los empleados pasen tres días en la oficina y dos en casa.","en":"Our company has implemented a hybrid work model so that employees spend three days in the office and two at home."},{"es":"El equipo de recursos humanos está revisando las políticas de trabajo híbrido para mejorar la flexibilidad de los horarios.","en":"The human resources team is reviewing the hybrid work policies to improve scheduling flexibility."},{"es":"Muchos profesionales buscan ofertas de trabajo híbrido para equilibrar mejor sus responsabilidades personales y laborales.","en":"Many professionals are looking for hybrid work offers to better balance their personal and professional responsibilities."}]},{"spanish_text":"Presencial","english_text":"On-site","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Located or occurring at the place where the activity takes place.","main_translations_es":["en persona","cara a cara","presencial"],"collocations":["on-site support","on-site training","on-site inspection","on-site meeting"],"synonyms_en":["in person","at the location","on location"],"example_sentence":"The course will be on-site, so you''ll have to attend in person.","example_es":"El curso será presencial, así que tendrás que asistir en persona.","example_en":"The course will be on-site, so you''ll have to attend in person.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a presenter on a construction site shouting \"presencial\" as the on‑site meeting begins.","cloze_distractors_en":["Out-sourced","Over-booked","Up-graded"],"examples":[{"es":"El curso será presencial, así que tendrás que asistir en persona.","en":"The course will be on-site, so you''ll have to attend in person."},{"es":"La empresa requiere que el equipo de soporte técnico trabaje en modalidad presencial para resolver los problemas de hardware.","en":"The company requires the technical support team to work in an on-site capacity to resolve hardware issues."},{"es":"Debido a la nueva política de la oficina, todas las reuniones de planificación estratégica deben ser presencial.","en":"Due to the new office policy, all strategic planning meetings must be on-site."}]},{"spanish_text":"Compañero de trabajo","english_text":"Coworker","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person who works with you, typically in the same organization or workplace.","main_translations_es":["Colega","Compañero de oficina","Colega de trabajo"],"collocations":["my coworker","coworker relationship","coworker collaboration","coworker support"],"synonyms_en":["colleague","workmate","associate"],"example_sentence":"My coworker helped me finish the report.","example_es":"Mi compañero de trabajo me ayudó a terminar el informe.","example_en":"My coworker helped me finish the report.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a cow at the office, your coworker, because cow plus work sounds like coworker","cloze_distractors_en":["Furniture","Equipment","Stationery","Briefcase"],"examples":[{"es":"Mi compañero de trabajo me ayudó a terminar el informe.","en":"My coworker helped me finish the report."},{"es":"Le pregunté a mi compañero de trabajo si quería ir a almorzar con nosotros.","en":"I asked my coworker if he wanted to go to lunch with us."},{"es":"Es importante mantener una buena relación con cada compañero de trabajo en la oficina.","en":"It is important to maintain a good relationship with every coworker in the office."}]},{"spanish_text":"Parte interesada","english_text":"Stakeholder","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person or group that has an interest or concern in something, especially a business or project.","main_translations_es":["parte interesada","interesado","grupo de interés"],"collocations":["key stakeholder","stakeholder engagement","stakeholder analysis","primary stakeholder"],"synonyms_en":["interested party","concerned party","shareholder"],"example_sentence":"The stakeholder approved the new project plan.","example_es":"La parte interesada aprobó el nuevo plan del proyecto.","example_en":"The stakeholder approved the new project plan.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a steak holder serving the interested party, because stakeholder sounds like steak holder.","cloze_distractors_en":["Microphone","Landscape","Headphone","Streetscape"],"examples":[{"es":"La parte interesada aprobó el nuevo plan del proyecto.","en":"The stakeholder approved the new project plan."},{"es":"Debemos organizar una reunión para presentar los resultados a cada parte interesada.","en":"We must organize a meeting to present the results to each stakeholder."},{"es":"El gerente escuchó las preocupaciones de la parte interesada sobre el presupuesto.","en":"The manager listened to the concerns of the stakeholder regarding the budget."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cliente","english_text":"Client","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person or organization that receives professional services or purchases goods from a business.","main_translations_es":["Cliente","Comprador","Consumidor"],"collocations":["client base","client meeting","client relationship","client service"],"synonyms_en":["customer","patron","buyer"],"example_sentence":"The client requested a refund.","example_es":"El cliente pidió una devolución.","example_en":"The client requested a refund.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a client handing a contract labeled Cliente.","cloze_distractors_en":["Cabinet","Stapler","Bulletin","Keyboard"],"examples":[{"es":"El cliente pidió una devolución.","en":"The client requested a refund."},{"es":"Debemos enviar la propuesta final al cliente antes del viernes.","en":"We must send the final proposal to the client before Friday."},{"es":"El cliente está esperando una actualización sobre el estado del proyecto.","en":"The client is waiting for an update on the project status."}]},{"spanish_text":"Proveedor","english_text":"Vendor","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person or company that sells goods or services.","main_translations_es":["Suministrador","Distribuidor","Abastecedor"],"collocations":["vendor management","preferred vendor","vendor contract","vendor list"],"synonyms_en":["seller","supplier","merchant"],"example_sentence":"The vendor delivered the goods on time.","example_es":"El proveedor entregó la mercancía a tiempo.","example_en":"The vendor delivered the goods on time.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a vendor handing out a ''proveedor'' badge while selling his wares.","cloze_distractors_en":["Auditor","Founder","Debtor","Visitor"],"examples":[{"es":"El proveedor entregó la mercancía a tiempo.","en":"The vendor delivered the goods on time."},{"es":"Necesitamos comparar los precios de cada proveedor antes de firmar el contrato.","en":"We need to compare the prices from each vendor before signing the contract."},{"es":"El departamento de compras está negociando mejores condiciones con nuestro proveedor principal.","en":"The purchasing department is negotiating better terms with our primary vendor."}]},{"spanish_text":"Negociar","english_text":"Negotiate","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To discuss terms and reach an agreement.","main_translations_es":["tratar","concertar","llegar a un acuerdo"],"collocations":["negotiate a deal","negotiate terms","negotiate a contract","negotiate with"],"synonyms_en":["bargain","mediate","hammer out"],"example_sentence":"We will negotiate the terms of the contract tomorrow.","example_es":"Vamos a negociar los términos del contrato mañana.","example_en":"We will negotiate the terms of the contract tomorrow.","mnemonic_en":"I negotiate while the word negociar echoes like a courtroom gavel.","cloze_distractors_en":["Fabricate","Navigate","Exaggerate","Obliterate"],"examples":[{"es":"Vamos a negociar los términos del contrato mañana.","en":"We will negotiate the terms of the contract tomorrow."},{"es":"El equipo necesita negociar un presupuesto mayor para finalizar el proyecto.","en":"The team needs to negotiate a higher budget to finish the project."},{"es":"Es difícil negociar un aumento de sueldo sin tener datos sobre el desempeño.","en":"It is difficult to negotiate a salary increase without having performance data."}]},{"spanish_text":"Llegar a un consenso","english_text":"Reach a consensus","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To arrive at a shared agreement among all parties.","main_translations_es":["Alcanzar un consenso","Lograr un consenso","Conseguir un consenso"],"collocations":["reach a consensus on","reach a consensus among stakeholders","reach a consensus quickly","reach a consensus about"],"synonyms_en":["agree","come to an agreement","find common ground"],"example_sentence":"After long discussions, we finally managed to reach a consensus on the project.","example_es":"Después de largas discusiones, finalmente logramos llegar a un consenso sobre el proyecto.","example_en":"After long discussions, we finally managed to reach a consensus on the project.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine reaching out to take a census, everyone agreeing on the count.","cloze_distractors_en":["Fabricate a facade","Allocate a grievance","Navigate a turbulence","Terminate a sequence"],"examples":[{"es":"Después de largas discusiones, finalmente logramos llegar a un consenso sobre el proyecto.","en":"After long discussions, we finally managed to reach a consensus on the project."},{"es":"El equipo necesita reunirse mañana para llegar a un consenso respecto a la fecha de entrega.","en":"The team needs to meet tomorrow to reach a consensus regarding the delivery date."},{"es":"Si todos los departamentos colaboran, será más sencillo llegar a un consenso sobre el nuevo presupuesto.","en":"If all departments collaborate, it will be easier to reach a consensus on the new budget."}]},{"spanish_text":"Alinearse","english_text":"Align on","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to agree upon or adopt a common position or plan","main_translations_es":["coordinarse","ponerse de acuerdo","ajustarse"],"collocations":["align on goals","align on strategy","align on expectations","align on priorities"],"synonyms_en":["agree on","concur on","reach consensus on"],"example_sentence":"The teams must align on the company''s objectives.","example_es":"Los equipos deben alinearse con los objetivos de la empresa.","example_en":"The teams must align on the company''s objectives.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a line of ants aligning on a rope, just like ''alinearse'' means to line up.","cloze_distractors_en":["Distort on","Abandon on","Submerge on","Fabricate on"],"examples":[{"es":"Los equipos deben alinearse con los objetivos de la empresa.","en":"The teams must align on the company''s objectives."},{"es":"Antes de empezar el proyecto, necesitamos alinearse con las expectativas del cliente.","en":"Before starting the project, we need to align on the client''s expectations."},{"es":"Es fundamental que todos los departamentos logren alinearse con el nuevo cronograma de trabajo.","en":"It is essential that all departments manage to align on the new work schedule."}]},{"spanish_text":"Aclarar expectativas","english_text":"Clarify expectations","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To make the expectations clear.","main_translations_es":["Alinear expectativas","Establecer expectativas claras","Definir expectativas"],"collocations":["clarify expectations with the team","clarify expectations early","clarify expectations beforehand"],"synonyms_en":["Set clear expectations","Explain expectations","Define expectations"],"example_sentence":"It''s important to clarify expectations before starting the project.","example_es":"Es importante aclarar expectativas antes de iniciar el proyecto.","example_en":"It''s important to clarify expectations before starting the project.","mnemonic_en":"Clear glass clears the fog, just as ''aclarar'' clears expectations.","cloze_distractors_en":["Fabricate outcomes","Obfuscate intentions","Exaggerate grievances","Complicate procedures"],"examples":[{"es":"Es importante aclarar expectativas antes de iniciar el proyecto.","en":"It''s important to clarify expectations before starting the project."},{"es":"El gerente convocó una reunión para aclarar expectativas sobre los nuevos roles del equipo.","en":"The manager called a meeting to clarify expectations regarding the team''s new roles."},{"es":"Debemos tener una charla honesta para aclarar expectativas sobre los plazos de entrega.","en":"We need to have an honest chat to clarify expectations about the delivery deadlines."}]},{"spanish_text":"Asumir responsabilidad","english_text":"Take ownership","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To accept responsibility for something.","main_translations_es":["Asumir la responsabilidad","Hacerse cargo","Responsabilizarse"],"collocations":["take ownership of the project","take ownership of your actions","take ownership and lead","take ownership of the issue"],"synonyms_en":["Assume responsibility","Take charge","Own up"],"example_sentence":"It''s important to take ownership of your mistakes.","example_es":"Es importante asumir responsabilidad por tus errores.","example_en":"It''s important to take ownership of your mistakes.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine you take the own ship, assuming full responsibility.","cloze_distractors_en":["Make avoidance","Give permission","Keep distance","Lose confidence"],"examples":[{"es":"Es importante asumir responsabilidad por tus errores.","en":"It''s important to take ownership of your mistakes."},{"es":"El gerente pidió al equipo asumir responsabilidad sobre el nuevo proyecto de marketing.","en":"The manager asked the team to take ownership of the new marketing project."},{"es":"Si quieres ascender, debes demostrar que puedes asumir responsabilidad en situaciones difíciles.","en":"If you want a promotion, you must show that you can take ownership in difficult situations."}]},{"spanish_text":"Delegar","english_text":"Delegate","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To entrust a task or responsibility to another person.","main_translations_es":["Encargar","Asignar","Transferir"],"collocations":["delegate authority","delegate tasks","delegate responsibilities","delegate decision‑making"],"synonyms_en":["assign","empower","appoint"],"example_sentence":"I learned to delegate tasks to be more efficient.","example_es":"Aprendí a delegar tareas para ser más eficiente.","example_en":"I learned to delegate tasks to be more efficient.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a delegate handing a leg to a gar, passing the work to someone else.","cloze_distractors_en":["Navigate","Fabricate","Terminate","Aggravate"],"examples":[{"es":"Aprendí a delegar tareas para ser más eficiente.","en":"I learned to delegate tasks to be more efficient."},{"es":"Como gerente, es importante delegar responsabilidades a los miembros de tu equipo.","en":"As a manager, it is important to delegate responsibilities to your team members."},{"es":"No puedes hacerlo todo tú solo; debes delegar el trabajo si quieres cumplir con la fecha límite.","en":"You cannot do everything by yourself; you must delegate the work if you want to meet the deadline."}]},{"spanish_text":"Transferir una tarea","english_text":"Hand over a task","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To give responsibility for a task to someone else.","main_translations_es":["Ceder una tarea","Entregar una tarea","Pasar una tarea"],"collocations":["hand over a task to a colleague","hand over the task","hand over tasks","hand over the responsibility"],"synonyms_en":["delegate a task","assign a task","pass on a task"],"example_sentence":"I will hand over a task to my colleague so they can finish it sooner.","example_es":"Voy a transferir una tarea a mi colega para que la termine antes.","example_en":"I will hand over a task to my colleague so they can finish it sooner.","mnemonic_en":"Picture yourself handing a ''tarea'' folder across the desk to a colleague.","cloze_distractors_en":["Overlook a project","Withdraw a request","Underestimate a deadline","Disregard a schedule"],"examples":[{"es":"Voy a transferir una tarea a mi colega para que la termine antes.","en":"I will hand over a task to my colleague so they can finish it sooner."},{"es":"Antes de irme de vacaciones, necesito transferir una tarea pendiente al equipo de soporte.","en":"Before I go on vacation, I need to hand over a task that is still pending to the support team."},{"es":"El gerente me pidió transferir una tarea de diseño al nuevo pasante esta tarde.","en":"The manager asked me to hand over a task related to design to the new intern this afternoon."}]},{"spanish_text":"Aprobar","english_text":"Approve","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To officially accept or give consent to something.","main_translations_es":["Autorizar","Ratificar","Aceptar"],"collocations":["approve of","approve the budget","give approval","receive approval"],"synonyms_en":["endorse","sanction","ratify"],"example_sentence":"The committee decided to approve the new policy.","example_es":"El comité decidió aprobar la nueva política.","example_en":"The committee decided to approve the new policy.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a pro giving a nod, saying ''Apro'' as they approve the plan.","cloze_distractors_en":["Fabricate","Exaggerate","Contradict"],"examples":[{"es":"El comité decidió aprobar la nueva política.","en":"The committee decided to approve the new policy."},{"es":"El gerente tiene que aprobar el presupuesto antes de empezar el proyecto.","en":"The manager has to approve the budget before we start the project."},{"es":"La junta directiva debe aprobar los cambios en el contrato mañana.","en":"The board of directors must approve the changes to the contract tomorrow."}]},{"spanish_text":"Rechazar","english_text":"Reject","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To refuse to accept, consider, or agree with something.","main_translations_es":["Denegar","Rehusar","Rechazar"],"collocations":["reject the proposal","reject the offer","reject the hypothesis","reject the application"],"synonyms_en":["refuse","turn down","dismiss"],"example_sentence":"The committee decided to reject the proposed tariff increase.","example_es":"El comité decidió rechazar la propuesta de aumento de tarifas.","example_en":"The committee decided to reject the proposed tariff increase.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a chef shouting REJECT, sounding like reh-CHAHZAR, as he throws a burnt cake into the trash.","cloze_distractors_en":["Circulate","Illuminate","Navigate","Fabricate"],"examples":[{"es":"El comité decidió rechazar la propuesta de aumento de tarifas.","en":"The committee decided to reject the proposed tariff increase."},{"es":"Debemos rechazar cualquier solicitud que no cumpla con los requisitos de seguridad.","en":"We must reject any application that does not meet the safety requirements."},{"es":"El cliente prefirió rechazar el presupuesto inicial por ser demasiado elevado.","en":"The client preferred to reject the initial budget because it was too high."}]},{"spanish_text":"Revisar","english_text":"Review","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To examine or assess something again or in detail.","main_translations_es":["Repasar","Examinar","Corregir"],"collocations":["review the literature","performance review","review meeting","review process"],"synonyms_en":["examine","inspect","assess"],"example_sentence":"I will review the report before sending it.","example_es":"Voy a revisar el informe antes de enviarlo.","example_en":"I will review the report before sending it.","mnemonic_en":"I RE-VIEW the report, just like I revisar a document.","cloze_distractors_en":["Abandon","Fabricate","Disregard"],"examples":[{"es":"Voy a revisar el informe antes de enviarlo.","en":"I will review the report before sending it."},{"es":"El gerente necesita revisar los resultados del trimestre durante la reunión.","en":"The manager needs to review the quarterly results during the meeting."},{"es":"Podemos revisar el contrato juntos para asegurar que todo esté correcto.","en":"We can review the contract together to ensure everything is correct."}]},{"spanish_text":"Redactar","english_text":"Draft","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To prepare a preliminary version of a document or text.","main_translations_es":["Escribir","Elaborar","Redactar"],"collocations":["draft a letter","draft a proposal","draft an email","draft a contract"],"synonyms_en":["outline","sketch","preliminary version"],"example_sentence":"I will draft the report before the meeting.","example_es":"Voy a redactar el informe antes de la reunión.","example_en":"I will draft the report before the meeting.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a red act drafting a paper, linking Redactar to Draft.","cloze_distractors_en":["Delete","Ignore","Forget","Refuse"],"examples":[{"es":"Voy a redactar el informe antes de la reunión.","en":"I will draft the report before the meeting."},{"es":"Necesito redactar un correo electrónico para explicar los cambios en el proyecto.","en":"I need to draft an email to explain the changes to the project."},{"es":"El equipo debe redactar una propuesta formal para el nuevo cliente.","en":"The team must draft a formal proposal for the new client."}]},{"spanish_text":"Resumir","english_text":"Summarize","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To give a brief statement of the main points of something.","main_translations_es":["Sintetizar","Hacer un resumen","Abreviar"],"collocations":["summarize the main points","summarize the findings","summarize the report","summarize briefly"],"synonyms_en":["condense","recap","give a synopsis"],"example_sentence":"Please summarize the article in three sentences.","example_es":"Por favor, resume el artículo en tres frases.","example_en":"Please summarize the article in three sentences.","mnemonic_en":"I take the sum of facts and then summarize, just like resumir neatly wraps them up.","cloze_distractors_en":["Fabricate","Exaggerate","Negotiate","Participate"],"examples":[{"es":"Por favor, resume el artículo en tres frases.","en":"Please summarize the article in three sentences."},{"es":"El gerente pidió que alguien resume los puntos clave de la reunión al final.","en":"The manager asked for someone to summarize the key points of the meeting at the end."},{"es":"Necesito que tú resume los resultados del proyecto para la presentación de mañana.","en":"I need you to summarize the project results for tomorrow''s presentation."}]},{"spanish_text":"Destacar","english_text":"Highlight","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To emphasize or make something stand out.","main_translations_es":["Resaltar","Subrayar","Enfatizar"],"collocations":["highlight the main points","highlight a problem","highlight in yellow","highlight the differences"],"synonyms_en":["emphasize","underscore","spotlight"],"example_sentence":"The report should highlight last year''s achievements.","example_es":"El informe debe destacar los logros del año pasado.","example_en":"The report should highlight last year''s achievements.","mnemonic_en":"A bright spotlight high lights the actor, so he destacar on the stage.","cloze_distractors_en":["Obscure","Fabricate","Abandon","Submerge"],"examples":[{"es":"El informe debe destacar los logros del año pasado.","en":"The report should highlight last year''s achievements."},{"es":"Durante la presentación, el gerente quiere destacar las nuevas funciones del software.","en":"During the presentation, the manager wants to highlight the new software features."},{"es":"Es importante destacar los puntos clave de nuestra estrategia de ventas en la reunión.","en":"It is important to highlight the key points of our sales strategy in the meeting."}]},{"spanish_text":"Plantear una inquietud","english_text":"Raise a concern","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To bring up or express a worry or issue.","main_translations_es":["Expresar una inquietud","Manifestar una preocupación","Elevar una queja"],"collocations":["raise a concern about","raise a concern with","raise a concern to","raise a concern regarding"],"synonyms_en":["express worry","voice a concern","bring up an issue"],"example_sentence":"I wanted to raise a concern about the new work schedule.","example_es":"Quería plantear una inquietud sobre el nuevo horario de trabajo.","example_en":"I wanted to raise a concern about the new work schedule.","mnemonic_en":"Raise a concern like planting a root of worry in the ground","cloze_distractors_en":["Fabricate a deadline","Navigate a beverage","Circulate a blueprint","Calculate a landscape"],"examples":[{"es":"Quería plantear una inquietud sobre el nuevo horario de trabajo.","en":"I wanted to raise a concern about the new work schedule."},{"es":"Es importante plantear una inquietud si detectas un error en el presupuesto.","en":"It is important to raise a concern if you detect an error in the budget."},{"es":"Durante la reunión, ella decidió plantear una inquietud acerca de la falta de recursos del equipo.","en":"During the meeting, she decided to raise a concern about the team''s lack of resources."}]},{"spanish_text":"Abordar un asunto","english_text":"Address an issue","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To deal with or discuss a problem or topic.","main_translations_es":["Tratar un tema","Enfrentar un problema","Lidiar con un asunto"],"collocations":["address an issue promptly","address an issue head-on","address an issue in the meeting","address an issue with management"],"synonyms_en":["deal with a problem","tackle a problem","handle a matter"],"example_sentence":"We need to address an issue regarding the budget before tomorrow''s meeting.","example_es":"Necesitamos abordar un asunto urgente sobre el presupuesto antes de la reunión de mañana.","example_en":"We need to address an issue regarding the budget before tomorrow''s meeting.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a dress (address) patching a torn issue.","cloze_distractors_en":["Fabricate a report","Overlook a detail","Abandon a strategy","Exaggerate a deficit"],"examples":[{"es":"Necesitamos abordar un asunto urgente sobre el presupuesto antes de la reunión de mañana.","en":"We need to address an issue regarding the budget before tomorrow''s meeting."},{"es":"El gerente decidió abordar un asunto de comunicación interna para mejorar el trabajo en equipo.","en":"The manager decided to address an issue of internal communication to improve teamwork."},{"es":"Es fundamental abordar un asunto técnico con el software antes de lanzar el proyecto.","en":"It is essential to address an issue with the software before launching the project."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cumplir con el seguimiento","english_text":"Follow through","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To continue an action or plan until it is completed.","main_translations_es":["dar seguimiento","realizar el seguimiento","llevar a cabo el seguimiento"],"collocations":["follow through on a promise","follow through with a plan","follow through on commitments"],"synonyms_en":["carry out","see it through","execute"],"example_sentence":"If you commit to helping with the project, make sure to follow through until it is completely finished.","example_es":"Si te comprometes a ayudar con el proyecto, asegúrate de cumplir con el seguimiento hasta que esté terminado.","example_en":"If you commit to helping with the project, make sure to follow through until it is completely finished.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a fulfillment arrow that follows through a tunnel to the finish line.","cloze_distractors_en":["Fall behind","Back away","Look aside","Step around"],"examples":[{"es":"Si te comprometes a ayudar con el proyecto, asegúrate de cumplir con el seguimiento hasta que esté terminado.","en":"If you commit to helping with the project, make sure to follow through until it is completely finished."},{"es":"Si prometiste enviar el informe hoy, debes cumplir con el seguimiento para mantener la confianza del cliente.","en":"If you promised to send the report today, you must follow through to maintain the client''s trust."},{"es":"El gerente siempre sabe cómo cumplir con el seguimiento de las tareas asignadas en cada reunión de equipo.","en":"The manager always knows how to follow through on the tasks assigned in every team meeting."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cerrar el circuito","english_text":"Close the loop","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To complete a process by providing the missing information or final step.","main_translations_es":["Completar el circuito","Cerrar el lazo","Finalizar el circuito"],"collocations":["close the loop on","close the loop with","close the loop in the process","close the loop for feedback"],"synonyms_en":["complete the cycle","wrap up","finalize"],"example_sentence":"Please send me an email when you finish the task so we can close the loop with the client.","example_es":"Por favor, envíame un correo electrónico cuando termines la tarea para cerrar el circuito con el cliente.","example_en":"Please send me an email when you finish the task so we can close the loop with the client.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a closed loop of wire you shut, just like cerrar el circuito","cloze_distractors_en":["Bridge the gap","Clear the deck","Break the ice","Drop the ball"],"examples":[{"es":"Por favor, envíame un correo electrónico cuando termines la tarea para cerrar el circuito con el cliente.","en":"Please send me an email when you finish the task so we can close the loop with the client."},{"es":"Es importante que confirmes la recepción del informe para cerrar el circuito de esta comunicación.","en":"It is important that you confirm receipt of the report to close the loop on this communication."},{"es":"El gerente llamó al proveedor para cerrar el circuito sobre el retraso del envío.","en":"The manager called the supplier to close the loop regarding the shipping delay."}]},{"spanish_text":"Mantener informado","english_text":"Keep posted","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"To keep someone informed about developments.","main_translations_es":["Mantener al tanto","Mantener al corriente","Mantener informado"],"collocations":["keep me posted","keep us posted","keep them posted"],"synonyms_en":["stay updated","keep informed","let someone know"],"example_sentence":"Keep posted on the quarterly performance metrics by subscribing to the department dashboard.","example_es":"Mantente informado sobre las métricas de rendimiento trimestral suscribiéndote al panel de control del departamento.","example_en":"Keep posted on the quarterly performance metrics by subscribing to the department dashboard.","mnemonic_en":"I place the post on the mantel to keep it posted.","cloze_distractors_en":["Keep waiting","Keep holding","Keep guessing"],"examples":[{"es":"Mantente informado sobre las métricas de rendimiento trimestral suscribiéndote al panel de control del departamento.","en":"Keep posted on the quarterly performance metrics by subscribing to the department dashboard."},{"es":"Por favor, mantente informado sobre cualquier cambio en la agenda de la reunión con el cliente antes de la llamada del viernes.","en":"Please keep posted about any changes to the client meeting agenda before Friday''s call."},{"es":"Mantendré informado al equipo respecto al cronograma de entrega del proveedor para planificar la instalación en consecuencia.","en":"I will keep posted on the vendor''s delivery schedule so we can plan the installation accordingly."}]},{"spanish_text":"Hilo de correo","english_text":"Email thread","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A series of related email messages that share the same subject line, showing the progression of a conversation.","main_translations_es":["Cadena de correo","Conversación de correo","Hilo de email"],"collocations":["follow the email thread","reply to the email thread","email thread history","email thread view"],"synonyms_en":["mail chain","conversation thread","message chain"],"example_sentence":"I reviewed the email thread to find the information I needed.","example_es":"Revisé el hilo de correo para encontrar la información que necesitaba.","example_en":"I reviewed the email thread to find the information I needed.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a heel (hilo) stitching together a line of emails like a thread","cloze_distractors_en":["Coffee break","Office supply","Lunch voucher","Staff turnover"],"examples":[{"es":"Revisé el hilo de correo para encontrar la información que necesitaba.","en":"I reviewed the email thread to find the information I needed."},{"es":"Por favor, añade a mi jefe en este hilo de correo para que esté al tanto del proyecto.","en":"Please add my manager to this email thread so they are updated on the project."},{"es":"Hay demasiada información irrelevante en este hilo de correo, así que prefiero hablarlo en persona.","en":"There is too much irrelevant information in this email thread, so I would rather discuss it in person."}]},{"spanish_text":"Llamada breve","english_text":"Quick call","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"A brief telephone conversation.","main_translations_es":["Llamada corta","Llamada rápida","Llamada breve"],"collocations":["give me a quick call","quick call back","quick call to discuss","schedule a quick call"],"synonyms_en":["brief call","short call","fast call"],"example_sentence":"I''ll make a quick call to confirm the time.","example_es":"Haré una llamada breve para confirmar la hora.","example_en":"I''ll make a quick call to confirm the time.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a quick call as a brief llamada that darts like a hummingbird.","cloze_distractors_en":["Heavy silence","Grand lecture","Total absence","Vague promise"],"examples":[{"es":"Haré una llamada breve para confirmar la hora.","en":"I''ll make a quick call to confirm the time."},{"es":"Necesito una llamada breve con el cliente para aclarar los requisitos del proyecto.","en":"I need a quick call with the client to clarify the project requirements."},{"es":"Si tienes dudas sobre el informe, podemos tener una llamada breve después de la reunión.","en":"If you have questions about the report, we can have a quick call after the meeting."}]},{"spanish_text":"Reunión individual","english_text":"One-on-one meeting","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A private meeting between two individuals, often a manager and an employee, conducted face‑to‑face.","main_translations_es":["Entrevista individual","Reunión cara a cara","Reunión personal"],"collocations":["schedule a one-on-one meeting","have a one-on-one meeting","one-on-one meeting agenda","one-on-one meeting follow-up"],"synonyms_en":["private meeting","individual session","personal meeting"],"example_sentence":"I have a one-on-one meeting with my supervisor tomorrow at ten.","example_es":"Tengo una reunión individual con mi supervisor mañana a las diez.","example_en":"I have a one-on-one meeting with my supervisor tomorrow at ten.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a single person saying ''uno a uno'' at a reunion, meaning a one‑on‑one meeting.","cloze_distractors_en":["Company holiday","Departmental layoff","Collective bargaining","Organizational chart"],"examples":[{"es":"Tengo una reunión individual con mi supervisor mañana a las diez.","en":"I have a one-on-one meeting with my supervisor tomorrow at ten."},{"es":"El gerente programó una reunión individual para discutir mi desempeño trimestral.","en":"The manager scheduled a one-on-one meeting to discuss my quarterly performance."},{"es":"Aprovecharé la reunión individual para pedirle consejos sobre el nuevo proyecto al jefe.","en":"I will use the one-on-one meeting to ask the boss for advice on the new project."}]},{"spanish_text":"Sesión de lluvia de ideas","english_text":"Brainstorming session","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A meeting where participants generate ideas and solutions through spontaneous discussion.","main_translations_es":["Sesión creativa","Reunión de ideas","Jornada de lluvia de ideas"],"collocations":["kick off the brainstorming session","schedule a brainstorming session","productive brainstorming session","brainstorming session agenda"],"synonyms_en":["idea generation meeting","creative workshop","thought‑storming meeting"],"example_sentence":"Tomorrow we will have a brainstorming session to improve the product.","example_es":"Mañana tendremos una sesión de lluvia de ideas para mejorar el producto.","example_en":"Tomorrow we will have a brainstorming session to improve the product.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a brain catching rain, each drop a new idea in the brainstorming session.","cloze_distractors_en":["Retirement party","Performance review","Budget liquidation","Inventory clearance"],"examples":[{"es":"Mañana tendremos una sesión de lluvia de ideas para mejorar el producto.","en":"Tomorrow we will have a brainstorming session to improve the product."},{"es":"El equipo se reunió en la sala de juntas para una sesión de lluvia de ideas sobre la nueva campaña de marketing.","en":"The team met in the conference room for a brainstorming session about the new marketing campaign."},{"es":"Necesitamos organizar una sesión de lluvia de ideas para resolver los problemas técnicos del proyecto.","en":"We need to organize a brainstorming session to solve the technical problems of the project."}]},{"spanish_text":"Presentación","english_text":"Presentation","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A formal introduction or display of information, such as a talk, demonstration, or visual material.","main_translations_es":["Exposición","Introducción","Charla"],"collocations":["make a presentation","give a presentation","presentation slides","presentation skills"],"synonyms_en":["demonstration","display","exhibition"],"example_sentence":"The presentation of the project was very clear.","example_es":"La presentación del proyecto fue muy clara.","example_en":"The presentation of the project was very clear.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a presenter opening a gift box labeled presentación on stage","cloze_distractors_en":["Fabrication","Vegetation","Regurgitation"],"examples":[{"es":"La presentación del proyecto fue muy clara.","en":"The presentation of the project was very clear."},{"es":"Debemos preparar una presentación para los nuevos clientes mañana.","en":"We must prepare a presentation for the new clients tomorrow."},{"es":"El director quedó impresionado con tu presentación durante la reunión.","en":"The manager was impressed with your presentation during the meeting."}]},{"spanish_text":"Diapositiva","english_text":"Slide","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A single page of a presentation, typically shown on a screen.","main_translations_es":["diapositiva","lámina","transparencia"],"collocations":["slide show","slide deck","slide transition","slide into"],"synonyms_en":["presentation page","visual aid","overhead"],"example_sentence":"The slide shows the results of the experiment.","example_es":"La diapositiva muestra los resultados del experimento.","example_en":"The slide shows the results of the experiment.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a playground slide built from a huge Diapositiva picture you can glide down.","cloze_distractors_en":["Staple","Stance","Stripe","Stifle"],"examples":[{"es":"La diapositiva muestra los resultados del experimento.","en":"The slide shows the results of the experiment."},{"es":"Por favor, añade una diapositiva nueva para explicar el presupuesto del proyecto.","en":"Please add a new slide to explain the project budget."},{"es":"El orador cambió a la siguiente diapositiva durante la presentación de ventas.","en":"The speaker moved to the next slide during the sales presentation."}]},{"spanish_text":"Propuesta","english_text":"Proposal","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A plan or suggestion put forward for consideration or discussion.","main_translations_es":["Propuesta","Oferta","Iniciativa"],"collocations":["proposal for","proposal to","proposal was accepted","proposal meeting"],"synonyms_en":["suggestion","offer","plan"],"example_sentence":"The committee''s proposal was approved unanimously.","example_es":"La propuesta del comité fue aprobada por unanimidad.","example_en":"The committee''s proposal was approved unanimously.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a pro chef posing a proposal on a propuesta menu.","cloze_distractors_en":["Vegetation","Hypothesis","Ingredient","Atmosphere"],"examples":[{"es":"La propuesta del comité fue aprobada por unanimidad.","en":"The committee''s proposal was approved unanimously."},{"es":"Debemos enviar la propuesta antes de que finalice el plazo de licitación.","en":"We must submit the proposal before the bidding deadline ends."},{"es":"El cliente solicitó cambios importantes en nuestra propuesta inicial.","en":"The client requested major changes to our initial proposal."}]},{"spanish_text":"Factura","english_text":"Invoice","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A document itemizing goods or services provided and requesting payment.","main_translations_es":["Factura","Recibo","Comprobante"],"collocations":["invoice number","invoice date","invoice amount","invoice processing"],"synonyms_en":["bill","billing statement","statement of charges"],"example_sentence":"I need you to send me the invoice before Friday.","example_es":"Necesito que me envíes la factura antes del viernes.","example_en":"I need you to send me the invoice before Friday.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a loud voice shouting the invoice amount, en voz, the bill appears.","cloze_distractors_en":["Inference","Incidence","Insolence"],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito que me envíes la factura antes del viernes.","en":"I need you to send me the invoice before Friday."},{"es":"El departamento de contabilidad rechazó la factura porque faltaba el número de pedido.","en":"The accounting department rejected the invoice because the purchase order number was missing."},{"es":"Por favor, adjunta la factura al correo electrónico para que podamos procesar el pago.","en":"Please attach the invoice to the email so that we can process the payment."}]},{"spanish_text":"Orden de compra","english_text":"Purchase order","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A document issued by a buyer to a seller specifying the items, quantities, and agreed prices for a purchase.","main_translations_es":["Pedido de compra","Orden de adquisición","Solicitud de compra"],"collocations":["issue a purchase order","purchase order number","receive a purchase order","purchase order form"],"synonyms_en":["order form","buying request","procurement order"],"example_sentence":"I need to send the purchase order to the supplier before Friday.","example_es":"Necesito enviar la orden de compra al proveedor antes del viernes.","example_en":"I need to send the purchase order to the supplier before Friday.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a purchase order as a clipboard with the word ''orden'' printed on a shopping list.","cloze_distractors_en":["Product vision","Market analysis","Company culture","Service feedback"],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito enviar la orden de compra al proveedor antes del viernes.","en":"I need to send the purchase order to the supplier before Friday."},{"es":"El departamento de contabilidad rechazó la orden de compra porque faltaba la firma del gerente.","en":"The accounting department rejected the purchase order because the manager''s signature was missing."},{"es":"Por favor, adjunta la orden de compra al correo electrónico para que podamos procesar el pago.","en":"Please attach the purchase order to the email so that we can process the payment."}]},{"spanish_text":"Reembolso","english_text":"Reimbursement","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A repayment of money that has been spent or lost, typically to cover incurred expenses.","main_translations_es":["devolución","reintegro","restitución"],"collocations":["reimbursement claim","reimbursement policy","reimbursement request","reimbursement form"],"synonyms_en":["refund","compensation","repayment"],"example_sentence":"I requested the reimbursement for my purchase because the product was defective.","example_es":"Solicité el reembolso de mi compra porque el producto estaba defectuoso.","example_en":"I requested the reimbursement for my purchase because the product was defective.","mnemonic_en":"When the REEMBURSING elf hands you a REEMBOLSO, you get a reimbursement.","cloze_distractors_en":["Contribution","Distribution","Substitution","Constitution"],"examples":[{"es":"Solicité el reembolso de mi compra porque el producto estaba defectuoso.","en":"I requested the reimbursement for my purchase because the product was defective."},{"es":"Por favor, adjunta todos los recibos de tus gastos de viaje para procesar tu reembolso.","en":"Please attach all your travel receipts so we can process your reimbursement."},{"es":"La empresa ofrece un reembolso completo si cancelas tu suscripción antes de fin de mes.","en":"The company offers a full reimbursement if you cancel your subscription before the end of the month."}]},{"spanish_text":"Baja médica","english_text":"Sick leave","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A period of time when an employee is permitted to be absent from work due to illness.","main_translations_es":["incapacidad laboral","permiso médico","licencia por enfermedad"],"collocations":["take sick leave","apply for sick leave","on sick leave","sick leave policy"],"synonyms_en":["medical leave","time off for illness","health leave"],"example_sentence":"Due to a scheduled surgical procedure, the employee will need to apply for long-term sick leave.","example_es":"Debido a una intervención quirúrgica programada, el empleado deberá tramitar una baja médica de larga duración.","example_en":"Due to a scheduled surgical procedure, the employee will need to apply for long-term sick leave.","mnemonic_en":"When you feel baja, the medic says take sick leave.","cloze_distractors_en":["Work permit","Team budget","Staff survey","Sales target"],"examples":[{"es":"Debido a una intervención quirúrgica programada, el empleado deberá tramitar una baja médica de larga duración.","en":"Due to a scheduled surgical procedure, the employee will need to apply for long-term sick leave."},{"es":"Debido a una gripe fuerte, he solicitado una baja médica para recuperarme en casa.","en":"Due to a bad flu, I have requested a sick leave to recover at home."},{"es":"Mi compañera no vendrá a la oficina esta semana porque está de baja médica.","en":"My colleague will not come to the office this week because she is on sick leave."}]},{"spanish_text":"Vacaciones","english_text":"Annual leave","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Paid time off from work that an employee is entitled to each year.","main_translations_es":["Descanso","Periodo vacacional","Tiempo libre"],"collocations":["take annual leave","annual leave entitlement","annual leave balance","annual leave request"],"synonyms_en":["vacation","paid time off","holiday"],"example_sentence":"I am going to take my annual leave next week.","example_es":"Voy a tomar mis vacaciones la próxima semana.","example_en":"I am going to take my annual leave next week.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a yearly vacation where a giant leaf falls, reminding you of annual leave during vacaciones.","cloze_distractors_en":["Annual bonus","Annual budget","Annual report","Annual meeting"],"examples":[{"es":"Voy a tomar mis vacaciones la próxima semana.","en":"I am going to take my annual leave next week."},{"es":"Debes enviar tu solicitud de vacaciones al departamento de recursos humanos antes de fin de mes.","en":"You must submit your annual leave request to the human resources department before the end of the month."},{"es":"El gerente aprobó mis vacaciones para el mes de agosto.","en":"The manager approved my annual leave for the month of August."}]},{"spanish_text":"Permiso de ausencia","english_text":"Leave of absence","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A period of time when someone is permitted to be away from work or school.","main_translations_es":["Licencia de ausencia","Permiso de ausencia","Licencia por ausencia"],"collocations":["take a leave of absence","apply for a leave of absence","grant a leave of absence","request a leave of absence"],"synonyms_en":["time off","sabbatical","break"],"example_sentence":"I requested a leave of absence to take care of my family.","example_es":"Solicité un permiso de ausencia para poder atender a mi familia.","example_en":"I requested a leave of absence to take care of my family.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a leaf drifting away when you get a permiso de ausencia.","cloze_distractors_en":["Conflict of interest","Point of departure","Lack of confidence","Sense of entitlement"],"examples":[{"es":"Solicité un permiso de ausencia para poder atender a mi familia.","en":"I requested a leave of absence to take care of my family."},{"es":"Debido a una condición médica, mi doctor me recomendó pedir un permiso de ausencia prolongado.","en":"Due to a medical condition, my doctor recommended that I take a leave of absence."},{"es":"El departamento de recursos humanos aprobó mi permiso de ausencia para realizar estudios de posgrado.","en":"The human resources department approved my leave of absence to pursue postgraduate studies."}]},{"spanish_text":"Período de prueba","english_text":"Probation period","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A designated span of time during which an employee''s performance is evaluated before confirming permanent employment.","main_translations_es":["Periodo de prueba","Plazo de prueba","Tiempo de prueba"],"collocations":["serve a probation period","complete a probation period","during the probation period","after the probation period"],"synonyms_en":["trial period","probationary phase","test period"],"example_sentence":"The new employee will start his probation period next week.","example_es":"El nuevo empleado comenzará su período de prueba la próxima semana.","example_en":"The new employee will start his probation period next week.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a probation officer handing a test (prueba) for the new period.","cloze_distractors_en":["Promotion cycle","Vacation balance","Resignation letter","Retirement package"],"examples":[{"es":"El nuevo empleado comenzará su período de prueba la próxima semana.","en":"The new employee will start his probation period next week."},{"es":"Durante el período de prueba, el supervisor evaluará el desempeño del candidato.","en":"During the probation period, the supervisor will evaluate the candidate''s performance."},{"es":"Si superas con éxito el período de prueba, recibirás un contrato indefinido.","en":"If you successfully complete the probation period, you will receive a permanent contract."}]},{"spanish_text":"Objetivo trimestral","english_text":"Quarterly goal","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A target or objective set to be achieved within a three-month period.","main_translations_es":["Meta trimestral","Objetivo de tres meses","Propósito trimestral"],"collocations":["set a quarterly goal","achieve the quarterly goal","review the quarterly goal","track quarterly goals"],"synonyms_en":["quarterly objective","three-month target","quarterly target"],"example_sentence":"Our quarterly goal is to increase sales by 10%.","example_es":"Nuestro objetivo trimestral es aumentar las ventas en un 10 %.","example_en":"Our quarterly goal is to increase sales by 10%.","mnemonic_en":"Visualize a goalpost with four quarters, each showing three months—your quarterly goal.","cloze_distractors_en":["Weekly vacation","Monthly headache","Annual furniture","Daily equipment"],"examples":[{"es":"Nuestro objetivo trimestral es aumentar las ventas en un 10 %.","en":"Our quarterly goal is to increase sales by 10%."},{"es":"El equipo de marketing no logró alcanzar su objetivo trimestral debido a problemas presupuestarios.","en":"The marketing team failed to reach their quarterly goal due to budget issues."},{"es":"Debemos revisar el progreso del proyecto para asegurar que cumplimos con nuestro objetivo trimestral.","en":"We must review the project progress to ensure we meet our quarterly goal."}]},{"spanish_text":"Indicador clave de rendimiento","english_text":"Key performance indicator","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A measurable value that shows how effectively an organization is achieving its key objectives.","main_translations_es":["Indicador clave de desempeño","Indicador de rendimiento clave","Indicador principal de rendimiento"],"collocations":["track key performance indicators","key performance indicator dashboard","key performance indicator metrics","key performance indicator framework"],"synonyms_en":["KPI","performance metric","business indicator"],"example_sentence":"The company''s key performance indicator shows a 15% improvement in productivity.","example_es":"El indicador clave de rendimiento de la empresa muestra una mejora del 15% en la productividad.","example_en":"The company''s key performance indicator shows a 15% improvement in productivity.","mnemonic_en":"Think of a key (clave) unlocking a performance gauge that indicates success.","cloze_distractors_en":["Personal development plan","Corporate holiday calendar","Internal office furniture","General maintenance manual"],"examples":[{"es":"El indicador clave de rendimiento de la empresa muestra una mejora del 15% en la productividad.","en":"The company''s key performance indicator shows a 15% improvement in productivity."},{"es":"Debemos revisar el indicador clave de rendimiento antes de presentar los resultados trimestrales a los inversores.","en":"We must review the key performance indicator before presenting the quarterly results to the investors."},{"es":"El equipo de marketing definió un nuevo indicador clave de rendimiento para medir el éxito de la campaña digital.","en":"The marketing team defined a new key performance indicator to measure the success of the digital campaign."}]},{"spanish_text":"Resultado medible","english_text":"Measurable outcome","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"A result that can be quantified or assessed.","main_translations_es":["Resultado cuantificable","Resultado evaluable","Resultado medible"],"collocations":["achieve a measurable outcome","track measurable outcomes","set measurable outcomes","measure the outcome"],"synonyms_en":["quantifiable result","trackable result","tangible result"],"example_sentence":"The manager requested a measurable outcome to justify the investment in this new tool.","example_es":"El gerente solicitó un resultado medible para justificar la inversión en esta nueva herramienta.","example_en":"The manager requested a measurable outcome to justify the investment in this new tool.","mnemonic_en":"Think of a measuring tape saying measurable like the Spanish medible on a result board.","cloze_distractors_en":["Subjective opinion","Invisible strategy","Unfounded intuition","Theoretical ambition"],"examples":[{"es":"El gerente solicitó un resultado medible para justificar la inversión en esta nueva herramienta.","en":"The manager requested a measurable outcome to justify the investment in this new tool."},{"es":"Debemos definir un resultado medible antes de comenzar la fase de implementación del software.","en":"We must define a measurable outcome before starting the software implementation phase."},{"es":"La falta de un resultado medible dificultó la presentación de los avances ante la junta directiva.","en":"The lack of a measurable outcome made it difficult to present the progress to the board of directors."}]},{"spanish_text":"Crecimiento profesional","english_text":"Professional growth","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The process of developing skills, knowledge, and experience in one''s career.","main_translations_es":["Desarrollo profesional","Avance profesional","Progresión profesional"],"collocations":["professional growth opportunities","continuous professional growth","personal and professional growth","professional growth plan"],"synonyms_en":["career advancement","skill development","career progression"],"example_sentence":"Professional growth depends on continuous training.","example_es":"El crecimiento profesional depende de la capacitación continua.","example_en":"Professional growth depends on continuous training.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a professional planting a crescent‑shaped seed that sprouts tall, showing professional growth.","cloze_distractors_en":["Administrative fatigue","Corporate negligence","Operational stagnation","Financial bankruptcy"],"examples":[{"es":"El crecimiento profesional depende de la capacitación continua.","en":"Professional growth depends on continuous training."},{"es":"Mi jefe me ofreció un mentor para fomentar mi crecimiento profesional.","en":"My manager offered me a mentor to foster my professional growth."},{"es":"La empresa ofrece varios talleres diseñados para impulsar el crecimiento profesional de sus empleados.","en":"The company offers several workshops designed to boost the professional growth of its employees."}]},{"spanish_text":"Toma de decisiones","english_text":"Decision-making","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The process of identifying and choosing among alternatives.","main_translations_es":["Proceso de decisión","Toma de decisiones","Decisión"],"collocations":["decision-making process","decision-making skills","decision-making authority","decision-making style"],"synonyms_en":["choice process","judgment","determination"],"example_sentence":"Decision-making is crucial in project management.","example_es":"La toma de decisiones es crucial en la gestión de proyectos.","example_en":"Decision-making is crucial in project management.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a judge pulling a huge lever labeled Decision while shouting Toma de decisiones!","cloze_distractors_en":["Fabrication","Hesitation","Contemplation","Speculation"],"examples":[{"es":"La toma de decisiones es crucial en la gestión de proyectos.","en":"Decision-making is crucial in project management."},{"es":"El equipo necesita mejorar su proceso de toma de decisiones para evitar retrasos.","en":"The team needs to improve its decision-making process to avoid delays."},{"es":"Ella tiene mucha experiencia en la toma de decisiones bajo presión durante las crisis.","en":"She has a lot of experience in decision-making under pressure during crises."}]},{"spanish_text":"Autorizar","english_text":"Authorize","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To give official permission or authority to someone to perform an action.","main_translations_es":["Permitir","Aprobar","Dar autorización"],"collocations":["authorize a transaction","authorize access","authorize a payment"],"synonyms_en":["permit","grant permission","empower"],"example_sentence":"The manager must authorize the expense before it is made.","example_es":"El gerente debe autorizar el gasto antes de que se realice.","example_en":"The manager must authorize the expense before it is made.","mnemonic_en":"Picture an author stamping his book, saying autor, and granting permission – he authorizes.","cloze_distractors_en":["Fabricate","Exaggerate","Infiltrate","Contaminate"],"examples":[{"es":"El gerente debe autorizar el gasto antes de que se realice.","en":"The manager must authorize the expense before it is made."},{"es":"Necesito que el director venga a autorizar el acceso a los archivos confidenciales.","en":"I need the director to come and authorize access to the confidential files."},{"es":"Solo el supervisor tiene el poder de autorizar las horas extra del equipo.","en":"Only the supervisor has the power to authorize the team''s overtime hours."}]},{"spanish_text":"Asignar recursos","english_text":"Allocate resources","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To distribute or assign resources to particular tasks or purposes.","main_translations_es":["Distribuir recursos","Destinar recursos","Repartir recursos"],"collocations":["allocate resources wisely","allocate resources efficiently","allocate resources to projects","allocate resources for development"],"synonyms_en":["assign resources","distribute resources","apportion resources"],"example_sentence":"The manager decided to allocate resources to the research project.","example_es":"El gerente decidió asignar recursos al proyecto de investigación.","example_en":"The manager decided to allocate resources to the research project.","mnemonic_en":"Allocate resources by assigning her a pile of tools.","cloze_distractors_en":["Fabricate evidence","Terminate attendance","Navigate turbulence","Liquidate performance"],"examples":[{"es":"El gerente decidió asignar recursos al proyecto de investigación.","en":"The manager decided to allocate resources to the research project."},{"es":"Debemos asignar recursos adicionales para cumplir con la fecha de entrega del cliente.","en":"We must allocate resources to meet the client''s deadline."},{"es":"El departamento de finanzas se encarga de asignar recursos a cada departamento según sus necesidades.","en":"The finance department is responsible to allocate resources to each department based on their needs."}]},{"spanish_text":"Mantener el rumbo","english_text":"Stay on track","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"To continue doing something in the correct direction or according to a plan.","main_translations_es":["Seguir el rumbo","Mantener la dirección","No perder el norte"],"collocations":["stay on track with your goals","stay on track during the meeting","stay on track and avoid setbacks"],"synonyms_en":["keep focused","remain on course","stay focused"],"example_sentence":"We must focus on the main objectives to stay on track during this meeting.","example_es":"Debemos enfocarnos en los objetivos principales para mantener el rumbo durante esta reunión.","example_en":"We must focus on the main objectives to stay on track during this meeting.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a train saying ''está en track'' while it keeps the rumbo.","cloze_distractors_en":["drift off course","lose all momentum","abandon the mission"],"examples":[{"es":"Debemos enfocarnos en los objetivos principales para mantener el rumbo durante esta reunión.","en":"We must focus on the main objectives to stay on track during this meeting."},{"es":"El gerente nos recordó que es vital mantener el rumbo para terminar el proyecto a tiempo.","en":"The manager reminded us that it is vital to stay on track to finish the project on time."},{"es":"Aunque surgieron nuevos problemas, logramos mantener el rumbo gracias a una buena planificación.","en":"Even though new problems arose, we managed to stay on track thanks to good planning."}]},{"spanish_text":"Desviarse del plan","english_text":"Go off track","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To deviate from the intended plan or course.","main_translations_es":["Salir del plan","Apartarse del plan","Desviarse del objetivo"],"collocations":["go off track during a meeting","go off track with the project","go off track easily"],"synonyms_en":["veer off","stray","deviate"],"example_sentence":"We must not go off track during the results presentation.","example_es":"No debemos desviarnos del plan durante la presentación de resultados.","example_en":"We must not go off track during the results presentation.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a goat (go) sprinting off the track, abandoning the plan.","cloze_distractors_en":["take over control","look into details","keep up appearances"],"examples":[{"es":"No debemos desviarnos del plan durante la presentación de resultados.","en":"We must not go off track during the results presentation."},{"es":"Si empezamos a discutir temas personales, vamos a desviarnos del plan.","en":"If we start discussing personal topics, we are going to go off track."},{"es":"El moderador intervino para que el equipo no pudiera desviarse del plan.","en":"The moderator intervened so the team would not go off track."}]},{"spanish_text":"Necesita revisión","english_text":"Needs revision","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"Requires further review or correction.","main_translations_es":["Requiere revisión","Precisa revisión","Debe revisarse"],"collocations":["This document needs revision","Your essay needs revision","The policy needs revision"],"synonyms_en":["requires editing","should be revised","needs editing"],"example_sentence":"The report needs revision before sending it.","example_es":"El informe necesita revisión antes de enviarlo.","example_en":"The report needs revision before sending it.","mnemonic_en":"He needs a re‑vision, like a doctor checking his eyes again.","cloze_distractors_en":["Avoids feedback","Denies approval","Refuses input"],"examples":[{"es":"El informe necesita revisión antes de enviarlo.","en":"The report needs revision before sending it."},{"es":"La propuesta de presupuesto necesita revisión por parte del departamento financiero.","en":"The budget proposal needs revision by the finance department."},{"es":"Su estrategia de marketing necesita revisión para alinearse con los objetivos trimestrales.","en":"Your marketing strategy needs revision to align with the quarterly goals."}]},{"spanish_text":"Urgente","english_text":"Urgent","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"requiring immediate attention or action","main_translations_es":["Apremiante","Inmediato","Prioritario"],"collocations":["urgent care","urgent matter","urgent request","urgent need"],"synonyms_en":["pressing","critical","immediate"],"example_sentence":"I need you to send me the report as soon as possible; it is urgent.","example_es":"Necesito que me envíes el informe lo antes posible, es urgente.","example_en":"I need you to send me the report as soon as possible; it is urgent.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a fire alarm shouting ''Urgente!'' demanding immediate action.","cloze_distractors_en":["Voluntary","Obsolete","Fragrant","Circular"],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito que me envíes el informe lo antes posible, es urgente.","en":"I need you to send me the report as soon as possible; it is urgent."},{"es":"Por favor, marca este correo como urgente para que el equipo lo vea de inmediato.","en":"Please mark this email as urgent so the team sees it right away."},{"es":"Tenemos una solicitud urgente del cliente y debemos resolverla antes de la reunión.","en":"We have an urgent request from the client and must resolve it before the meeting."}]},{"spanish_text":"Alta prioridad","english_text":"High priority","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Something that is considered very important and should be dealt with before other matters.","main_translations_es":["Prioridad alta","Máxima prioridad","Prioridad máxima"],"collocations":["high priority task","high priority issue","high priority item","high priority list"],"synonyms_en":["top priority","urgent","critical"],"example_sentence":"This project is of high priority for the company.","example_es":"Este proyecto es de alta prioridad para la empresa.","example_en":"This project is of high priority for the company.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a tall (alta) priority banner flying high above the crowd","cloze_distractors_en":["Low capacity","Full duration","Past schedule"],"examples":[{"es":"Este proyecto es de alta prioridad para la empresa.","en":"This project is of high priority for the company."},{"es":"Debido a la fecha límite, el informe del cliente tiene alta prioridad hoy.","en":"Due to the deadline, the client report has high priority today."},{"es":"Por favor, marca este correo electrónico como alta prioridad para que el equipo lo vea primero.","en":"Please mark this email as high priority so the team sees it first."}]},{"spanish_text":"Baja prioridad","english_text":"Low priority","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"Something that is considered less important or urgent than other items.","main_translations_es":["Prioridad baja","Prioridad reducida","Prioridad menor"],"collocations":["set to low priority","treated as low priority","low priority task","low priority issue"],"synonyms_en":["minor importance","secondary priority","less urgent"],"example_sentence":"This ticket has low priority, so we can address it later.","example_es":"Este ticket tiene baja prioridad, así que podemos atenderlo más tarde.","example_en":"This ticket has low priority, so we can address it later.","mnemonic_en":"Think of a low (baja) priority task as a tiny flag at the bottom of the list.","cloze_distractors_en":["High capacity","Full approval","Deep analysis","Fast delivery"],"examples":[{"es":"Este ticket tiene baja prioridad, así que podemos atenderlo más tarde.","en":"This ticket has low priority, so we can address it later."},{"es":"Debido a la falta de recursos, el proyecto se considera de baja prioridad por ahora.","en":"Due to the lack of resources, the project is considered low priority for now."},{"es":"Por favor, marca esta tarea como de baja prioridad en el sistema de gestión.","en":"Please mark this task as low priority in the management system."}]},{"spanish_text":"Punto de contacto","english_text":"Point of contact","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person or place that serves as the primary source of communication or information.","main_translations_es":["Persona de contacto","Contacto principal","Referente"],"collocations":["primary point of contact","main point of contact","single point of contact","designated point of contact"],"synonyms_en":["contact person","liaison","go-to person"],"example_sentence":"For any questions, please contact Maria, who will be your point of contact.","example_es":"Para cualquier duda, por favor contacte a María, quien será su punto de contacto.","example_en":"For any questions, please contact Maria, who will be your point of contact.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a dot (punto) on a map marking the point of contact.","cloze_distractors_en":["Point of departure","Point of contention","Point of reference","Point of exhaustion"],"examples":[{"es":"Para cualquier duda, por favor contacte a María, quien será su punto de contacto.","en":"For any questions, please contact Maria, who will be your point of contact."},{"es":"El gerente de ventas es el punto de contacto principal para los nuevos clientes internacionales.","en":"The sales manager is the primary point of contact for new international clients."},{"es":"Necesitamos designar a un punto de contacto en el departamento de TI para coordinar la actualización del software.","en":"We need to appoint a point of contact in the IT department to coordinate the software update."}]},{"spanish_text":"Compartir pantalla","english_text":"Share the screen","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To display one''s computer screen to others, typically during a video call or presentation.","main_translations_es":["Compartir la pantalla","Mostrar la pantalla","Proyección de pantalla"],"collocations":["share the screen with the team","share the screen during the meeting","share the screen on Zoom","share the screen for a presentation"],"synonyms_en":["display the screen","project the screen","show the screen"],"example_sentence":"I need to share the screen during the meeting.","example_es":"Necesito compartir pantalla durante la reunión.","example_en":"I need to share the screen during the meeting.","mnemonic_en":"When you COMPARTIR pizza, you SHARE the SCREEN.","cloze_distractors_en":["Delete the server","Cancel the office","Rotate the floor"],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito compartir pantalla durante la reunión.","en":"I need to share the screen during the meeting."},{"es":"Por favor, avísame cuando estés listo para compartir pantalla y mostrar los resultados.","en":"Please let me know when you are ready to share the screen and show the results."},{"es":"El presentador olvidó compartir pantalla antes de empezar su explicación.","en":"The presenter forgot to share the screen before starting his explanation."}]},{"spanish_text":"Silenciar el micrófono","english_text":"Mute the microphone","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To turn off or lower the microphone''s sound so it cannot be heard.","main_translations_es":["Desactivar el micrófono","Apagar el micrófono","Poner en silencio el micrófono"],"collocations":["Please mute the microphone","Remember to mute the microphone","He forgot to mute the microphone"],"synonyms_en":["silence the mic","turn off the mic","disable the microphone"],"example_sentence":"You can mute the microphone if you don''t want to be heard.","example_es":"Puedes silenciar el micrófono si no quieres que te escuchen.","example_en":"You can mute the microphone if you don''t want to be heard.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a mute button pressing the mic, turning the micrófono into complete silence","cloze_distractors_en":["Amplify the volume","Broadcast the feedback","Disconnect the hardware","Reconfigure the settings"],"examples":[{"es":"Puedes silenciar el micrófono si no quieres que te escuchen.","en":"You can mute the microphone if you don''t want to be heard."},{"es":"Por favor, recuerda silenciar el micrófono durante la presentación para evitar el ruido de fondo.","en":"Please remember to mute the microphone during the presentation to avoid background noise."},{"es":"El moderador tuvo que silenciar el micrófono del participante porque había mucha interferencia.","en":"The moderator had to mute the microphone of the participant because there was a lot of interference."}]},{"spanish_text":"Conectarse a la reunión","english_text":"Join the meeting","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To connect to or participate in a scheduled meeting.","main_translations_es":["Unirse a la reunión","Entrar a la reunión","Conectar a la reunión"],"collocations":["join the meeting on time","join the meeting via Zoom","join the meeting early","join the meeting tomorrow"],"synonyms_en":["attend the meeting","participate in the meeting","enter the meeting"],"example_sentence":"Please click the link to join the meeting with the team.","example_es":"Por favor, haz clic en el enlace para conectarse a la reunión de equipo.","example_en":"Please click the link to join the meeting with the team.","mnemonic_en":"Juan joins the meeting, just like connecting a plug to a socket.","cloze_distractors_en":["paint the furniture","bake the document","vacuum the hallway","repair the weather"],"examples":[{"es":"Por favor, haz clic en el enlace para conectarse a la reunión de equipo.","en":"Please click the link to join the meeting with the team."},{"es":"Si tienes problemas técnicos, intenta reiniciar tu computadora antes de conectarse a la reunión.","en":"If you have technical issues, try restarting your computer before you join the meeting."},{"es":"El gerente nos envió una invitación formal para conectarse a la reunión sobre el nuevo proyecto.","en":"The manager sent us a formal invitation to join the meeting about the new project."}]},{"spanish_text":"Abandonar la reunión","english_text":"Leave the meeting","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To exit or depart from a meeting.","main_translations_es":["Salir de la reunión","Irse de la reunión","Dejar la reunión"],"collocations":["to leave the meeting early","to leave the meeting abruptly","to leave the meeting without notice"],"synonyms_en":["exit the meeting","walk out","depart the meeting"],"example_sentence":"I''m going to leave the meeting because it''s getting late.","example_es":"Voy a abandonar la reunión porque ya es tarde.","example_en":"I''m going to leave the meeting because it''s getting late.","mnemonic_en":"A band on a reunion walks out, leaving the meeting.","cloze_distractors_en":["cancel the project","ignore the feedback","dismiss the agenda","postpone the deadline"],"examples":[{"es":"Voy a abandonar la reunión porque ya es tarde.","en":"I''m going to leave the meeting because it''s getting late."},{"es":"Si tienes una emergencia, puedes abandonar la reunión sin pedir permiso.","en":"If you have an emergency, you can leave the meeting without asking for permission."},{"es":"El director decidió abandonar la reunión antes de que terminara la presentación.","en":"The director decided to leave the meeting before the presentation ended."}]},{"spanish_text":"Tomar nota","english_text":"Take notes","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To write down information for later reference.","main_translations_es":["Anotar","Hacer anotaciones","Apuntar"],"collocations":["take notes during the lecture","take notes on the meeting","take notes for later"],"synonyms_en":["jot down","make a note","record"],"example_sentence":"During the meeting, it is important to take notes of the key points the boss mentions.","example_es":"Durante la reunión, es importante tomar nota de los puntos clave que menciona el jefe.","example_en":"During the meeting, it is important to take notes of the key points the boss mentions.","mnemonic_en":"Take notes as you tomar a note from a bright red tomato.","cloze_distractors_en":["Make claims","Give orders","Lose track","Keep secrets"],"examples":[{"es":"Durante la reunión, es importante tomar nota de los puntos clave que menciona el jefe.","en":"During the meeting, it is important to take notes of the key points the boss mentions."},{"es":"Si no puedes recordar todos los detalles de la presentación, será mejor tomar nota de lo más relevante.","en":"If you cannot remember all the details of the presentation, it would be better to take notes of the most relevant information."},{"es":"El cliente habló muy rápido, así que tuve que tomar nota de sus requisitos específicos para no olvidarlos.","en":"The client spoke very quickly, so I had to take notes of his specific requirements so I would not forget them."}]},{"spanish_text":"Hacer una demostración","english_text":"Give a demo","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To present a demonstration of something, typically showing how it works.","main_translations_es":["Realizar una demostración","Mostrar una demo","Presentar una demostración"],"collocations":["give a demo of the product","give a demo to the client","give a demo during the meeting"],"synonyms_en":["show a demo","present a demo","demonstrate"],"example_sentence":"I''m going to give a demo of the new software to the team.","example_es":"Voy a hacer una demostración del nuevo software para el equipo.","example_en":"I''m going to give a demo of the new software to the team.","mnemonic_en":"Picture yourself handing a demo DVD to a crowd, showing exactly what a demostración means.","cloze_distractors_en":["Make a receipt","Take a lecture","Form a vacuum","Keep a vacancy"],"examples":[{"es":"Voy a hacer una demostración del nuevo software para el equipo.","en":"I''m going to give a demo of the new software to the team."},{"es":"El ingeniero va a hacer una demostración de cómo funciona el prototipo durante la reunión.","en":"The engineer is going to give a demo of how the prototype works during the meeting."},{"es":"Es necesario hacer una demostración de la aplicación antes de lanzarla al mercado.","en":"It is necessary to give a demo of the application before launching it to the market."}]},{"spanish_text":"Próximos pasos","english_text":"Next steps","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A set of actions or tasks that should be taken after the current point.","main_translations_es":["Pasos siguientes","Siguientes pasos","Próximas acciones"],"collocations":["next steps in the process","next steps for implementation","next steps after the meeting","next steps to take"],"synonyms_en":["following steps","future actions","subsequent steps"],"example_sentence":"The next steps are to review the report and present the results.","example_es":"Los próximos pasos son revisar el informe y presentar los resultados.","example_en":"The next steps are to review the report and present the results.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a NEXT sign pointing to a staircase of STEPS labeled PROXIMO, showing the upcoming steps.","cloze_distractors_en":["Past habits","Brief pauses","Final wishes","Daily chores"],"examples":[{"es":"Los próximos pasos son revisar el informe y presentar los resultados.","en":"The next steps are to review the report and present the results."},{"es":"Al finalizar la reunión, definiremos los próximos pasos para el lanzamiento del proyecto.","en":"At the end of the meeting, we will define the next steps for the project launch."},{"es":"Por favor, envíame un correo electrónico detallando los próximos pasos después de nuestra llamada.","en":"Please send me an email detailing the next steps after our call."}]},{"spanish_text":"Prórroga","english_text":"Extension","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A continuation or prolongation of something, especially a period of time.","main_translations_es":["prórroga","aplazamiento","extensión"],"collocations":["extension cord","extension deadline","extension of a loan","extension service"],"synonyms_en":["prolongation","expansion","continuation"],"example_sentence":"The team requested an extension to complete the quarterly audit.","example_es":"El equipo solicitó una prórroga para completar la auditoría trimestral.","example_en":"The team requested an extension to complete the quarterly audit.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a pro rope being pulled longer, turning into an extension.","cloze_distractors_en":["Dimension","Suspension","Detention","Conversion"],"examples":[{"es":"El equipo solicitó una prórroga para completar la auditoría trimestral.","en":"The team requested an extension to complete the quarterly audit."},{"es":"Solicitamos una prórroga para entregar el informe final del proyecto.","en":"We requested an extension to submit the final project report."},{"es":"El banco aprobó una prórroga en el plazo de pago del préstamo.","en":"The bank approved an extension on the loan repayment deadline."}]},{"spanish_text":"Solución alternativa","english_text":"Workaround","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A method for overcoming a problem or limitation in a system.","main_translations_es":["Alternativa","Solución provisional","Método alternativo"],"collocations":["find a workaround","temporary workaround","implement a workaround","workaround solution"],"synonyms_en":["alternative solution","temporary fix","stopgap"],"example_sentence":"We implemented a workaround while the team fixes the bug.","example_es":"Implementamos una solución alternativa mientras el equipo corrige el error.","example_en":"We implemented a workaround while the team fixes the bug.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a worker circling a wall, using a solución alternativa to get the job done.","cloze_distractors_en":["Breakdown","Backtrack","Overhaul","Feedback"],"examples":[{"es":"Implementamos una solución alternativa mientras el equipo corrige el error.","en":"We implemented a workaround while the team fixes the bug."},{"es":"El software no permite exportar archivos, así que buscaremos una solución alternativa para terminar el reporte.","en":"The software does not allow exporting files, so we will look for a workaround to finish the report."},{"es":"Debido a las restricciones del sistema, tuvimos que crear una solución alternativa para procesar los pagos.","en":"Due to system restrictions, we had to create a workaround to process the payments."}]},{"spanish_text":"Bloqueador","english_text":"Blocker","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person or thing that prevents progress or blocks something.","main_translations_es":["Obstáculo","Inhibidor","Bloqueador"],"collocations":["ad blocker","traffic blocker","blocker issue","blocker task"],"synonyms_en":["obstacle","impediment","hindrance"],"example_sentence":"The technical team identified a blocker that is preventing the deployment of the new update.","example_es":"El equipo técnico identificó un bloqueador que impide el despliegue de la nueva actualización.","example_en":"The technical team identified a blocker that is preventing the deployment of the new update.","mnemonic_en":"A blocker stops traffic by dropping a giant block, just like a Spanish bloqueador.","cloze_distractors_en":["Catalyst","Blueprint","Feedback","Schedule"],"examples":[{"es":"El equipo técnico identificó un bloqueador que impide el despliegue de la nueva actualización.","en":"The technical team identified a blocker that is preventing the deployment of the new update."},{"es":"Durante la reunión, mencioné que la falta de presupuesto es el principal bloqueador para avanzar con el proyecto.","en":"During the meeting, I mentioned that the lack of budget is the main blocker to moving forward with the project."},{"es":"Necesitamos eliminar este bloqueador rápidamente para cumplir con la fecha de entrega establecida.","en":"We need to remove this blocker quickly to meet the established deadline."}]},{"spanish_text":"Disponibilidad inmediata","english_text":"Immediate availability","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"The state of being ready for use right away.","main_translations_es":["Disponibilidad al instante","Disponibilidad sin demora","Disponibilidad inmediata"],"collocations":["subject to immediate availability","with immediate availability","immediate availability of"],"synonyms_en":["ready now","instant access","prompt availability"],"example_sentence":"I have immediate availability to start working.","example_es":"Tengo disponibilidad inmediata para comenzar a trabajar.","example_en":"I have immediate availability to start working.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a flashing billboard shouting Immediate availability, echoing the Spanish word ''inmediata'' for instant.","cloze_distractors_en":["Constant instability","Absolute invisibility","Frequent irritability","Persistent illegibility"],"examples":[{"es":"Tengo disponibilidad inmediata para comenzar a trabajar.","en":"I have immediate availability to start working."},{"es":"El candidato confirmó su disponibilidad inmediata para incorporarse al equipo de ventas el próximo lunes.","en":"The candidate confirmed his immediate availability to join the sales team next Monday."},{"es":"Por favor, indique en su solicitud si cuenta con disponibilidad inmediata para cubrir el puesto vacante.","en":"Please indicate in your application if you have immediate availability to fill the open position."}]},{"spanish_text":"Entorno de pruebas","english_text":"Test environment","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A setting or system used to conduct testing of software or processes.","main_translations_es":["Ambiente de pruebas","Entorno de test","Ambiente de test"],"collocations":["set up a test environment","test environment configuration","test environment variables","test environment setup"],"synonyms_en":["testing environment","sandbox","staging environment"],"example_sentence":"The team set up the test environment before releasing the new version.","example_es":"El equipo configuró el entorno de pruebas antes de lanzar la nueva versión.","example_en":"The team set up the test environment before releasing the new version.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a lab where every test has its own entorno sign, a test environment.","cloze_distractors_en":["Coffee machine","Office furniture","Parking permit","Holiday schedule"],"examples":[{"es":"El equipo configuró el entorno de pruebas antes de lanzar la nueva versión.","en":"The team set up the test environment before releasing the new version."},{"es":"Debemos verificar que los datos sean correctos en el entorno de pruebas antes de pasar a producción.","en":"We must verify that the data is correct in the test environment before moving to production."},{"es":"Los desarrolladores encontraron un error crítico mientras ejecutaban el código en el entorno de pruebas.","en":"The developers found a critical bug while running the code in the test environment."}]},{"spanish_text":"Entorno de producción","english_text":"Production environment","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The setting where software or a system is operated for real users, as opposed to testing or development.","main_translations_es":["Entorno de producción","Ambiente de producción","Entorno productivo"],"collocations":["deploy to production environment","production environment setup","production environment monitoring"],"synonyms_en":["live environment","operational setting","deployment environment"],"example_sentence":"The software was deployed to the production environment after testing.","example_es":"El software se desplegó en el entorno de producción después de las pruebas.","example_en":"The software was deployed to the production environment after testing.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a factory (producción) inside a garden (entorno) to recall Production environment.","cloze_distractors_en":["Administrative cafeteria","Conceptual blueprint","Theoretical laboratory","Hypothetical workspace"],"examples":[{"es":"El software se desplegó en el entorno de producción después de las pruebas.","en":"The software was deployed to the production environment after testing."},{"es":"Debemos evitar realizar cambios directos en el entorno de producción sin una revisión previa.","en":"We must avoid making direct changes to the production environment without prior review."},{"es":"El equipo técnico detectó un error crítico justo después de actualizar el entorno de producción.","en":"The technical team detected a critical bug right after updating the production environment."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cadena de aprobación","english_text":"Approval chain","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A sequence of individuals or steps required to give approval for a decision or document.","main_translations_es":["cadena de autorización","flujo de aprobación","cadena de validación"],"collocations":["establish an approval chain","approval chain process","manage the approval chain","approval chain hierarchy"],"synonyms_en":["authorization sequence","sign‑off chain","approval workflow"],"example_sentence":"For the project, we follow an approval chain before launching the product.","example_es":"Para el proyecto, seguimos una cadena de aprobación antes de lanzar el producto.","example_en":"For the project, we follow an approval chain before launching the product.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a chain of stamps giving approval on a document.","cloze_distractors_en":["Accounting ledger","Attendance record","Assembly manual","Assignment deadline"],"examples":[{"es":"Para el proyecto, seguimos una cadena de aprobación antes de lanzar el producto.","en":"For the project, we follow an approval chain before launching the product."},{"es":"El director de finanzas debe revisar los gastos si la cadena de aprobación es demasiado larga.","en":"The finance director must review the expenses if the approval chain is too long."},{"es":"Necesitamos simplificar nuestra cadena de aprobación para que los contratos se firmen más rápido.","en":"We need to simplify our approval chain so that contracts are signed faster."}]}]'::jsonb) as x(
  spanish_text text, english_text text, section_name text, part_of_speech text, definition_en text,
  main_translations_es jsonb, collocations jsonb, synonyms_en jsonb, example_sentence text, example_es text, example_en text, mnemonic_en text, cloze_distractors_en jsonb, examples jsonb
)
where c.deck_id = dk.id
  and lower(c.spanish_text) = lower(x.spanish_text)
  and lower(c.english_text) = lower(x.english_text);

-- english-academic-english (107 cards)
update public.decks set
  title = 'Academic English', description = 'Upper-intermediate and advanced academic vocabulary for essays, reports, presentations, and formal discussion.',
  language_from = 'es', language_to = 'en'
where slug = 'english-academic-english';

update public.cards c set
  section_name = x.section_name, part_of_speech = x.part_of_speech, definition_en = x.definition_en,
  main_translations_es = coalesce(x.main_translations_es, '[]'::jsonb),
  collocations = coalesce(x.collocations, '[]'::jsonb),
  synonyms_en = coalesce(x.synonyms_en, '[]'::jsonb),
  example_sentence = x.example_sentence, example_es = x.example_es, example_en = x.example_en,
  mnemonic_en = coalesce(x.mnemonic_en, c.mnemonic_en),
  cloze_distractors_en = case when jsonb_array_length(coalesce(x.cloze_distractors_en, '[]'::jsonb)) > 0
                              then x.cloze_distractors_en else c.cloze_distractors_en end,
  examples = case when jsonb_array_length(coalesce(x.examples, '[]'::jsonb)) > 0
                  then x.examples else c.examples end
